This is the complete override text for the condition testing quest.
If I help Arlen's men thin the Werewolves roaming the Moors, they'll stand more of a chance.
I've killed many of the foul lupine beasts.  Arlen will welcome the news - I should tell him immediately.
I collected the Den Hops. All that's left is to bring them to Father Aron in the Silverspar Inn.
Gaspar asked that I slay King's Guard Zombies and collect their blades. King's Guard Zombies roam the ruins southeast of Eagle's Watch.
I've collected enough blades to satisfy Gaspar. I should return the blades to Eagle's Watch.
The bandits are slain. I should return to the Magis Order in Camlorn to report in.
I've found both Simine and Dalomar. I should return to Kallath.
I've completed my patrol of Camlorn. I should report back to Inquisitor Bieller.
I have disrupted the ritual and driven the remaining acolytes to flee, for now. Jha's shade suggested that the Bone Colossus may yet have risen, albiet weakened. I should report to the Redoubt.
I've gathered a number of werewolf ears. High Inquisitor Averos will probably want to hear of my deeds.
High Inquisitor Averos asked me to slay Shornhelm Werewolves and bring him their ears.
Watcher Emeric directed me to the crafter's circle in the southwest once I was through patrolling the temple. I should head there next.
Simine should be in the center of the city, across from the western gates, but Dalomar seems to be missing. He was supposed to be speaking near the temple in town.
One of Kallath's orators was murdered, most likely by the Magis Order. His body had a small locket with an inscription from his wife. She may want the news, however bad it might be.

I have been asked to help kill bandits and their leader by a member of the Magis Order. The bandits are all over Ykalon, but the leader has a camp just to the south of the city, where he is staging raids.

There is a priest of Arkay in Northern Ykalon, northwest of the Redoubt but surrounded by bandits, according to Commander Blarae. Alternately, I could potentially enlist the aid of Claude, the hermit, at the ruins just outside of Camlorn.

Curate Marcel was grateful for my assistance in driving off the bandits, and is more than happy to help me stem the tide of undead. He has asked me to retrieve holy water from the tomb of old Priests of Arkay.

Claude knows of a camp to the north, one he ignored previously due to his oath to stay near the spirits. He told me that the spirits spoke of dark magic in that part of the forest. The camp is likely the source.
The Curate has asked me to accompany him as he consecrates the graveyards, which should prevent more undead from being created.

I've found a map of the area that indicates that supplies are being brought from farther north, to fuel the efforts of one "Jha Gra'Muzgob", a necromancer. There is also a place on the map that would seem to be the perfect place for an ambush.
Curate Marcel has been attacked by a projection of the necromancer gra-Muzgob. I should ensure he is all right.
Jha gra-Muzgob is working on a powerful ritual. I have discovered its location and must disrupt it.
I've collected a number of soul gems with the souls of slain Shornhelm soldiers. I should return to Captain Danfor in the pass below Eagle's Watch and tell him of my deeds.

To break their spirit, Danfor asked me capture the souls of Shornhelm soldiers. To capture a soldier's soul, I must first fight them until they are considerably weakened, then use the magic of Danfor's soul gem on them to finish them off.
Warden Godwin sent me to discover the fate of the contingent of men he sent west out of Crosswych.
Captain Blayne asked me to investigate Cath Bedraud for any clue as to why the bodies might be vanishing.

I found a recently disturbed grave, as if I had just scared off a robber. Whoever it was dropped a parchment with the words -The King of Worms shall rise, and his enemy shall name him-. I should return to Captain Arin with what I've found.
The Priest of Arkay stated that his order is opposed to disciples of the King of Worms, people involved in necromancy. He told me to burn the parchment at a statue of Arkay outside the chapel.
While working at the chapel, Gui often chased off an orc witch who was trying to steal bodies - Jha gra-Muzgob. He told me her old house is south of Camp Mercy. Perhaps I'll find something there.
After hearing about the orc, Jha gra-Muzgob, buying bodies, Barnard asked me to return to the bandit leader and force him to set up a meeting with her. I should return to the bandit camp.
The bandit leader said he meets Jha gra-Muzgob behind Cath Bedraud Chapel when they have bodies to sell. He suggested I look for her there.
I confronted Jha gra-Muzgob behind the chapel. She brought allies, but Gui arrived with soldiers from both the Hands of Northmoor and the Magis Order.
I confronted Jha gra-Muzgob behind the chapel. She brought allies, but Barnard arrived with soldiers from the Hands of Northmoor.
Alongside my allies, we slew Jha gra-Muzgob and put an end to her graverobbing for good. I should return to Arin and let her know no more dead will be taken.
I must destroy Maormer Siege Engines and slay the Engineers who maintain them. They are on Sunhold Island, offshore south of the Harmonium Fortress.
I should return to Battlereeve Tariella at the Harmonium Fortress to report my success.
Some of the hags south of Crosswych are covered in scales that are of medicinal use to the doctor. I must bring him eight scales from these Scaly Hags.
I managed to find eight Hag Scales.  I should bring them to Doctor Sevarain in Crosswych.
I've slain the spectre that was haunting young Faya in the form of her friend. I should return to Aldcroft to make sure Faya is okay.

Warden Godwin needs additional hands on the City Watch.  He's had his eye on a Redguard named Saul for some time and has asked me to try and recruit him. He can usually be found in the Silverspar Inn.
I should use Thetis' potion to purify the lake water near the goblin camp.
The Oyinaam lies to the east of the Harmonium Fortress, near the Liriel River.
I have driven off the Zombie attack on the Oyinaam. I should tell Battlereeve Tariella in the Harmonium Fort of my success.
Veraul asked me to collect reports from Master of Arms Alborn, at Eagle's Watch, Captain Danfor, in the pass below Eagle's Watch, and Doctor Marris, at Camp Mercy to the south of Eagle's Watch.
I've collected the reports Veraul needs. I should return the reports to him at Eagle's Watch.
Inquisitor Roche was furious that I allowed Elsie to stay and sent me to talk to Brennoc.
Elsie told me to talk to the people of Grayborne to establish her reputation.
Roche has sent me to Elsie Dolban's house in Grayborne to tell her to leave the village or be killed.
After attacking the caravan, I've managed to take an acolyte prisoner. I should interrogate him and find out who's leading him and what their plans are.
Captain Danfor gave me a report on the Shornhelm attack. I should deliver the report to High Inquisitor Averos at Eagle's Watch.
I should return to Watchman Derran and let him know that Al'kari and Guillie should pose no further problems.

I followed Alaric to a camp filled only with children. They have all the supplies they seem to need, but not a parent in sight. The eldest girl in the camp seems to be the nominal leader. I should speak with her and ask about the camp.
Having talked to the Grayborne villagers, I should return to Elsie to tell her if she must leave town or stay.
High Inquisitor Averos told me to go offer my services to Tactician Veraul. I'll find him in the east quarter of Eagle's Watch.
I'm will present Oron with the note I found in Glenumbra.
I found Pierric's band of men in the woods west of Crosswych.  They told me Pierric disappeared in the dead of night and hasn't been heard from since.  nnI'd best return to Godwin and let him know.
Godwin fears Pierric was killed by Werewolves.  He asked me to go to the Barracks and collect Pierric's things to deliver to his wife, Guendeline.
The Cultist attack in the Barracks raised new mysteries. Was Pierric attacked by these fanatics? I need to find out.

Warden Godwin gave me two leads in my hunt - I should speak with either Guendeline, Pierric's betrothed, or Vireche, the exiled witch from the Beldama Wyrd. Either might be able to shed some light on Pierric's fate.

Guendeline is sick.  The doctor has confined her to her home, but has been less than forthcoming with information about her illness.  She's asked me to confront Doctor Severain on her behalf. He's located in the tents on the northwest side of town.
Before Vireche would say anything about Pierric, she asked me to collect ten hag's toes from the bogs south of Crosswych for some foul concoction she is brewing.
I have the hag's toes Vireche wanted. I should return them to her.
Doctor Severain is unsure what ails Guendeline. He needs reagents to discover the truth. I need to bring him five Wolf's Teeth. I can find wolves both to the northwest and southeast of Crosswych.
Pierric decided to return to town, leaving the cult behind.
I should find out more about this Vandica that Faya speaks of.
This text is step-specific; it will be replaced when the quest proceeds to a new step.
Same as for regular steps, this will appear in the journal to describe what must be done for this optional step.
I need to obtain the Cultist's Plans from Vireche's home.
Odette wonders if her parents could still be alive. I should see if she can tell me anything about Mother Murk that might help me find the bog witch's lair.
Odette and the other murklings will soon rejoin their parents at the caravan. I should speak to Warden Rielle at the caravan to ensure they need nothing else to take care of the former murklings.
Vireche suspects Pierric joined the Cult of Ulorion, who are rumored to have a cave north of town where they initiate new converts.  She suspects I will find Pierric there.
I have the Doctor's arcane reagents. I must return them to him.
The Doctor informed me that Guendeline is pregnant. I must tell her.
The single writing desk in Marshal Gerard's tent must hold whatever plans he is using to direct his invasion. I must steal those plans.
I've gathered a number of documents from Marshal Gerard's Writing Desk. I should return to Tactician Veraul before I am discovered.
Upon catching flame, the parchment expelled a spectre which attacked me. When I slew it, it screamed a name -- Jha gra-Muzgob. I should return to Gui and see if he has heard the name before.

Jha Gra Muzgob's house was in ruins, but a necromancer remained. When he attacked me, I slew him and found a note from Jha Gra Muzgob. The orc witch asked him to meet her at ?the weeping witch'. Perhaps Gui will know what it means.
The bandit leader insisted Jha gra-Muzgob must have sent the construct to silence us both. I should return to Barnard with this news.
Denise asked me to find Henri. I'll know him by his pendant - the other half of Denise's pendant.nnHenri is somewhere in the Mines of Khuras.

I found Henri, but Namira's creatures had slain and possessed him. I slew Henri's possessed body and retrieved his pendant. I should return the pendant to Denise.nnDenise Colville is waiting outside the Mines of Khuras.

I'm to invade the Mines of Khuras and find a buried Shrine to Namira taken by cultists. I must stop them before they resurrect their master, Ulorion.nnThe entrance to the Mines of Khuras is due south of Dwynnen, in the mountains.
Thomas thinks we can bust open the shrine with a battering ram the cultists left behind - but first, we must destroy webbing that disables it.
I unleashed the battering ram Thomas showed me, and it smashed open the wall of the buried shrine.n nI must enter the buried Shrine of Namira and stop the cultists from resurrecting Ulorion.

High Inquisitor Deville was thrilled with my success and lauded me as a hero of Northmoor. He told me to speak with Bruno Dabney to collect an enchanted item from the Magis Order's supplies as a reward.
Should I encounter a Daedric servant in the mines, I should slay it and bring Dabney its heart.nnThe Ulorion Cultists have summoned dark magic to do their bidding inside the Mines of Khuras.
Deep in the mines I fought one of Namira's servants, a fierce Daedra that looked half woman, half spider. After killing it, I cut out its heart. I should bring the heart to Bruno Dabney.
Alain said if I used his gem to capture the soul of a weakened kelpie, he would reward me.n nI'll find kelpies in the Bogfire Cavern deep within the Mines of Khuras.
I've captured the soul of a kelpie in Alain's gem. I should return the gem to him.n nAlain is waiting outside the Mines of Khuras.

I must get into the Shornhelm camp, locate Marshal Gerard's tent, and retrieve any documents within it. If I should acquire a Shornhelm uniform off a fallen soldier, I can use that to disguise myself - though werewolves will still detect me.
Averos asked me to journey to the pass below Eagle's Watch and help Captain Danfor repel the impending Shornhelm attack.
Now that I've survived the ambush by Frey's men, I should give Gallmau both my news and Constable Barre's tabard.
Seems some of the neighbors in Crosswych aren't exactly... neighborly.
Shornhelm werewolves attacked the soldiers guarding the pass below Eagle's Watch almost the moment I arrived. I must help the Northmoor defenders repel the attack.

Odette asked me to track down and slay the bandits who have been threatening her small camp of children. They have a camp north of the murklings. If not for the direwolves, the bandits would certainly have stolen from the children by now or worse
I've slain the bandits that were troubling the murkling camp. I should return to Odette and see what else she needs done.
Constable Barre has sent me to find Morgan Frey, somewhere in Westtry.
Warden Godwin is lacking the military support he needs to defend Crosswych.  He's asked me to help recruit citizens for the cause - starting with a villager named Julien Rissiel.
Julien is less than eager to join the City Watch. He is in love with Guendeline, and asked me to deliver a bouquet of ten Lacelillies to her on his behalf.
I've collected Jes' weapon crates from the bandits, who will no longer turn the weapons on innocent travelers. I should return the crates to Jes.
Jes asked me to venture to the bandit camp southeast of Camlorn and retrieve his stolen weapon shipment.
The lumberjack camp is a wreck. There is blood and fur everywhere. I should find Foreman Maston.
I found a surviving miner, Thomas Garnier, deep in the Mines of Khuras. I should ask him if he knows anything about the cultists.
Baron Avon will be pleased to learn that the Inquisitors were convinced that Magister Averos murdered Lord Ranser.  I must return to the Baron at once.
I am headed to Baron Avon's home, in the market district of Camlorn.
Avon suspects the Magis Order is behind Ranser's murder: at his suggestion I'm going to eavesdrop upon some Watchers at the Inn and try to overhear anything they might say about the murder.
Danain handed me a symbol to use upon the possessed citizens of Camlorn.
I expelled the specter possessing the people of Camlorn.  It desperately sought to announce that Countess Virolynn had the murder weapon and revealed a potential motive.

Upon entering the shrine, I saw the Ulorion Cultists summon a Spawn of Namira. It slaughtered them and came for me, but I slew it before it could do more harm. nnIn its death throes, the daedra revealed a secret exit leading to the Magis Order camp.

I must decide with whom to spea, Brennoc or Roche, as the Hands of Northmoor and Magis Order are at odds. I will only be able to assist one or the other. Brennoc is by the Inn in Grayborne, while Roche has a house on the East side of Grayborne.
Inquisitor Roche mentioned that the courier was last seen to the north east of Grayborne.  Hopefully the Spriggans did not harm him.
Inquisitor Roche informed me that the courier was kidnapped.
Brennoc was unable to locate the courier.  He suggested I assist the Innkeep while his spies hunt for the courier.
I've killed several wolves and smoked out their den. Paine should be told about this.
The wolves are scattered throughout southern Ykalon Forest, and they make their dens in a large rock formation in the forest north of the lumberjack camp.
I was able to free the courier from his prison cell.  We are headed south of Grayborne, where I will question him about the murder weapon.

I need to free the courier and question him once we reach a safe location.  It is possible to do this through martial force or disguised as a Watcher, wearing a Magis Order uniform.nnBrennoc said I should defeat a Watcher if I wanted their uniform.
I have decided to wear a Magis Order uniform and attempt to free the courier disguised as a Watcher.

Roche mentioned that his men prepared a ritual with the courier's body between two trees in the center of Westtry.  I am headed there now and when I make contact with the bones will begin the summoning of the courier's spirit.
Before I can speak with the Countess I must speak to her Chamberlain
The courier handed the murder weapon off to a second courier named Katarin.  She took the weapon north, to Urvaius.
The ritual was a success.  I must now speak to the spirit of the courier and find the murder weapon.
The courier handed the murder weapon off to a second courier, named Katarin.  I must travel to Aldcroft, in Urvaius, to speak with her.
I'm going to try and free Adwin the courier by dressing up in a stolen Magis Order uniform and infiltrating the storehouse where he's being held.
I am on my way to investigate the abandoned house to the east of Aldcroft.
I can find the herbs I need for the potions just outside Camlorn, to the south.
I've retrieved the herbs Alchemist Symbellene wanted, and should return to her to deliver them.
Alchemist Symbellene has asked me to deliver the next batch of potions to Inquisitor Bieller at the Magis Order headquarters in Camlorn.
I am currently fighting zombies to acquire any limbs that might be useful in treating our maimed soldiers.
I should return these limbs to Doctor Marris at Camp Mercy.
I must return to Aldcroft at once and at last speak to the Countess.
The Chamberlain attacked Countess Virolynn!  He turned into a werewolf the moment she mentioned the Shrouded Throne.  Should I chase after him or help the priestess heal the Countess?
With the beast slain, I wonder where Gargast was headed  What is this Shrouded Throne?
The priestess believes Virolynn is strong enough to speak.  I should speak to her.

I have decided to help the priestess save the Countess.  She informed me of the cure to lycanthropy.  I must collect Wolfsbane and Belladonna flowers which grow on the gnarled Spriggans to the south east.
I am joined by Guardian Caldrun on the hunt of Gargast.  This beast must be slain.
You should probably go kill something
You've killed the bad guy, now return to Bob
Guardian Caldrun believes Chamberlain Gargast was headed to the town of Crosswych, in Dwynnen.  He told me to seek out the Warden Godwin, who governs the town.
Countess Virolynn believes her Chamberlain was headed to the town of Crosswych, in Dwynnen.  She told me to check with the Warden Godwyn, who oversees the town.
Warden Godwin had not seen Chamberlain Godwyn.  He handed me a letter from Oron, urging me to return to Camlorn at once.
Oorn asked me to travel to the temple of Zenithar in northern Camlorn and use the murder weapon on Lord Ranser's corpse.
Lord Ranser's spirit arose from his corpse.  I must destroy this angry specter.
Lord Sebastien murdered Ranser!  I must inform Oron of this at once!
I must decide to help King Sebastien, by journeying to Eagle's Watch to defend Northmoor, or to assist Oron by investigating Gargast's connections in Crosswych.
King Vincintian suggested I assist Averos in the defense of Eagles Watch. I'll find him in the west tower of Eagle's Watch.
I have decided to assist Oron. I will journey to Crosswych and see if I can find any trace of Gargast or his allies.
I have the symbols for Doctor Marris, and I will give them to her so she may try to stop the dying soldiers from being raised into undeath. nI should return them to her at Camp Mercy.
I've collected a bouquet for Guendeline.  Now I just need to bring them to her.
I should let Julien know that Guendeline accepted his present.
The potion didn't have the intended effect. I should return to Julien and give him the bad news.
I need to acquire symbols of Ar'Kay from the Cath Bedraud, the large cemetery to the West of Camp Mercy.
Once I have informed Warden Godwin of Varik's behavior, he will surely see reason to replace him with Saul as Captain of the northeast watchtower.
Saul is accustomed to a command of his own.  He won't join up as a grunt in Godwin's crew.  He'll only join if he is given command of a Watchtower.  I'd best inform the Warden.

Warden Godwin is loathe to remove any of the men he has stationed at the watchtowers surrounding Crosswych - but if his hand were forced, the sword would fall on Varik of the northeast tower.  I should speak with him to judge his commitment.
Varik didn't avail himself well in the Bandit assault... I need to speak with him once more.
Varik talked a mean game, but when confronted with a bandit ambush, he ran for shelter and left me to fend for myself.  I should inform Warden Godwin of the weak link in Crosswych's defensive chain.
I have heard very little of the spirits haunting Camlorn, and the Abelard in the temple in town cannot help. I should ask the townspeople if I want more information.

The mantrap Darien prepared captured a young man, Alaric, as he was attempting to steal Darien's shipment of mushrooms. He must be almost 18. He claims he'll never steal again if I let him go, but I'm not sure if that's the case.

I found a camp filled with children and supplies, but no adults in sight. It was surrounded by fierce direwolves, however, the wolves seemed to leave the children alone. I should tell Warden Rielle all I've found.
I am currently working to try to collect Lady's Mantle leaves for Doctor Gillibert at Camp Mercy. He indicated they might be near some ruins northeast of Camp Mercy.
I've collected enough Lady's Mantle leaves to satisfy Doctor Gillibert's needs. I should return to Camp Mercy.
Darien Mene has prepared a harmless mantrap to immobilize the thief, should he appear. The trap is just to the west of the caravan. He asked me to set the trap at his camp, then watch it.
I've caught the little thief, and I should interrogate him now
I've escorted Alaric safely back to the caravan, where he will be cared for. I should speak to Warden Rielle about his missing parents.
Speak to Doctor Severain to see if he has any spare medical supplies for Arlen's men.
Doctor Severain allowed me to take a package of medical supplies. I need to bring it to Arlen at his camp west of Crosswych.
Doctor Severain told me I could take a package of medical supplies from their stores.
I was ambushed by a cultist in the Barracks!
Oron has asked that I speak with the people of Camlorn, while he collects more information.
After the bandit leader told me where to find Jha gra-Muzgob, a massive undead attacked us. I slew it.
Oron needed time to gather evidence - requesting I return to him later.

I found a recently disturbed grave, as if I had just scared off a robber. Whoever it was dropped a parchment with the words -The King of Worms shall rise, and his enemy shall name him-. I should return to Captain Arin with what I've found.
Captain Arin advised me to seek out Gui, the prior chapel keeper of Cath Bedraud. I'll find him at Camp Mercy, south of Eagle's Watch.
Captain Arin asked me to speak to Barnard with the Hands of Northmoor - he handles burials for their men. He may have some idea why bodies have been vanishing.
I found Gui. Though he cannot read the parchment, he advised me to speak with a Priest of Arkay in the chapel at Cath Bedraud.
I must follow up with Oron's request and speak to Inquisitor Danain at Magis Order Headquarters.
Vireche suspects Pierric joined the Cult of Ulorion.  They supposedly have a cave north of town where they bring new recruits for indoctrination.  She suspects I will find Pierric there.
Guendeline admitted to seeing Pierric return from the direction of the Wrothgar Mountains on several occasions.  I need to track him down there.
The Shade of Ranser must be slain for the citizens of Camlorn to be safe.
Guendeline admitted to seeing Pierric creeping around by night, coming back to Crosswych from the north, towards the Wrothgar Mountains.  She thinks I may find him there.
Gui said the weeping witch is the statue of Mara behind Cath Bedraud Chapel. He wants to stop Jha gra-Muzgob. He will meet me at the graveyard after calling in a favor.

Jha gra-Muzgob's house was in ruins, but a necromancer remained. When he attacked me, I slew him and found a note from Jha gra-Muzgob. The orc witch asked him to meet her at the weeping witch. Perhaps Gui will know what it means.
I need to look for clues in the National Cemetery
What I have found is disturbing. I should report that an agent of Shornhelm is behind the undead rising in the cemetery.
A local tradesman, Seth Grindle, asked me to collect a shipment from his contact in Wayrest, Iamel Langstrom, and bring it back to him.
I need to pick up the shipment Iamel directed me to for Seth.
I have Seth's package of silver. I should deliver it to Iamel Langstrom in Wayrest.
Danain handed me a symbol to use upon the possessed citizens of Camlorn.
Danain handed me a symbol to use upon the possessed citizens of Camlorn.
I've retrieved the holy water and should now light the brazier Curate Marcel mentioned, at the westernmost graveyard. He is supposed to meet me there.
The blacksmith's assistant, Keet, asked if I could go in search of a merchant who was set to make a delivery days ago. She said I may find him along the road north to Wayrest.
Keet's merchant seems possessed!  I must dispatch him and take the shipment of glass from his caravan.
Keet's merchant won't be making any more trips to and from Wayrest, but I did recover her shipment of glass.  I should return it to her.

Barnard has prior experience with graverobbers - he hung members of a bandit group several years back for the crime. He suggested I look for them southwest of Camp Mercy, and see if the bandits know anything about the missing bodies.
When I approached him to ask about the missing corpses, the bandit leader attacked me. I should subdue him instead of killing him so I can find out what he knows.
After I subdued the bandit leader, he admitted to robbing graves and selling the bodies to an orc named Jha gra-Muzgob. I should return to Eagle's watch and tell Barnard what I've found out.
Barnard asked me to meet him and his men behind the Cath Bedraud Chapel. There, we will put an end to Jha gra-Muzgob's necromancy.
Keet's merchant was possessed by some dark magic.  He fell upon me - I had no choice but to dispatch him.
Lord Ranser of Shornhelm was slain a few nights ago.  There is a representative from the Nine Crowns by the name of Oron who is in charge of the investigation.
I began the ritual.  It appears I have awakened the spirits of Westtry  Hopefully the courier's spirit will arrive soon.
I've helped the Magis Order patrollers, and have been asked by Patroller Jaeson to talk to Inquisitor Bieller.
I've gathered a smattering of opinions about the Hands of Northmoor from the populace of Camlorn. I should return to Baron Winoc with what I've found.

While escorting the recruits, I fought and killed a group of zombies. The recruits were shaken up. I was able to reassure Mallery, but Ames deserted. I should return to Capel with news of his recruits and the attack.
I have slain a number of the encroaching undead. The commander at the camp would probably like an update.
I've gathered a number of worn curaisses. I should return the armor to Master of Arms Alborn, at Eagle's Watch.

The blacksmith in Camlorn will be able to help, but will need some protection getting his supplies to the lumberjack camp. He's asked me to inform Lord Jes at the Hands of Northmoor holdings that an escort would be greatly appreciated.
I've been asked to deliver an order for the blacksmith in Camlorn to fill.
I should speak to <<1>> and find out how he plans to win Guendeline's affection.
I agreed to help Julien win Guendeline's heart through the use of a love potion. He wants me to talk to the alchemist Vireche will create one for me.
I need to collect a hair from both Julien and Guendeline.  Guen may be tricky...

Julien Rissiel is obsessed with winning the hand of Guendeline.nnHe asked me to collect some silver nuggets from around town. Then I can create her a necklace that might win her heart. In exchange, he'll consider joining the watch.

I convinced Julien not to abandon his idea to give Guendeline a necklace. I just not to retrieve the components he needs to craft it from the bandits that stole them. They're hiding in the ruins west of Hoarfrost Downs.
I've asked Elsie to leave, and should now return to Roche.
Guendeline was enamored of the necklace and asked Julien to call on her sometime. I should let him know. He'll be pleased to hear the news.

The alchemist Vireche Kel says she can make me a love potion, but I need to acquire the essence of a lovesick spirit for her to use. She suggested I go to the Sanguine Barrows and slay wraiths to find an essence.
Vireche Kel gave me the love potion. Now I need to get Guendeline to drink it.
Capel asked me to journey to Cath Bedraud, southwest of Eagle's Watch, and lead two of his recent recruits in a patrol around the graveyard.
I found the recruits, Ames and Mallery, at the journal, and we began our patrol. Ames seems to resent my presence here.
Recruit Mallery was too scared to fight when the zombies appeared. I should talk to him to see what happened.
Like Mallery, Recruit Ames was too scared to fight as well. I should talk to him and see what happened.

While escorting the recruits, I fought and killed a group of zombies. The recruits were shaken up. I was able to reassure both that being frightened was normal. I should return to Capel with news of his recruits and the attack.
Recruit Mallery was too scared to fight when the zombies appeared. I should talk to him to see what happened.
I have volunteered to help the soldiers in Northern Ykalon drive back the undead invaders and slayers.
I should give Capel my report on his recruits and the zombie attack.
After I told Capel what happened in the graveyard, he asked me to forward the news to Captain Arin at Eagle's Watch.
After I told Capel what happened in the graveyard, he asked me to forward the news to Captain Arin at Eagle's Watch.
I should give Capel my report on his recruits and the zombie attack.
After I told Capel what happened in the graveyard, he asked me to forward the news to Captain Arin at Eagle's Watch.

The Magis Order patrollers are hiding from an angry mob, who believe they killed a Hands of Northmoor agent. Before I could do anything, two Hands of Northmoor members burst into the building. I've been caught between the two sides.
I have helped the Hands of Northmoor agents, Marc and Ravsten. They have asked me to tell Lady Kallath what's happened while they clean things up.
At the end of our patrol, zombies attacked us.
Julien is reluctant to join the watch because he's smitten with a local girl named Guendeline. He wants me to help win her heart. I intend to speak with her and determine what sort of woman she is.
Guendeline strikes me as a practical woman who prefers a pragmatist over an idealist. I'll communicate my findings to Julien.
A Priest of Arkay at the Chapel in Cath Bedraud asked me to slay specters roaming the grounds and bring him their pendants, so he may consecrate them and lay the souls to rest.
I've gathered a number of spectre pendants. I should return the pendants to the Priest of Ar'kay at the Cath Bedraud chapel so he can put the spirits to rest.
Alborn asked me to salvage intact curaisses from fallen Shornhelm soldiers.
I must unlock the Adwyn's cell and escort him to safety.
Veraul asked me to find and dispatch Scout Charnoc, Scout Neff, and Captain Sanxay in the pass below Eagle's Watch, then look for evidence on their bodies identifying the spy.
I found and slew the soldiers Veraul named and recovered a few scraps of information. I should return the scraps to Veraul and see if he can make any sense of them.

Vireche wants me to bring her a few samples of a Void Essence so she can complete her love potion.nnShe said I can collect one by using her soulstone on a coffin containing one of the recently deceased. There should be one near the gravedigger.
I must show this missive to a guard to gain audience in Camlorn's court.
I've found Oron and I can help get to the bottom of the murder.
There are several large bags of salt on the Biren farm, with a distinct leading towards the Circe farm. I would seem someone in the Magis Order is behind salting Tarrant's land.  I should inform him.
I should speak with Aquil Gervine. If he's behind Tarrant's failing crops, he must be stopped.

Aquil is aware that Tarrant suspects him, and he seems hurt by the accusation. He thinks Tarrant's troubles come from the Biren farm to the south of him. It was abandoned after one too many poor harvests, but he swears people live there still.
I've stumbled upon a small contingent of Magis Order members living the in the abandoned Biren farm. They deny knowledge of any farmland sabotage, but I should investigate the area just in case.
Roche has sent me to kill as many of the Wyrd in their northeastern enclave as I can.nnI could do as he asks, or try and find out more from the Wyrd themselves...
I killed several of the Wyrd and should return to Roche in Grayborne.
I've killed the Wyress. I should return to Roche.
Capel asked me to slay King's Guard Zombies roaming Cath Bedraud, then examine the corpses for any trace of what's got them stirred up.
I've found a strange charm imbedded in the skull of one of the King's Guard Zombies I killed at Cath Bedraud. I should return to Capel and see what he makes of it.
The love potion worked, but not on the intended target. Instead of falling in love with Julien, Guendeline has become infatuated with me. I should let Julien know what happened.
Things are more complicated than I thought. While Julien is in love with Guendeline, Khalisah is in love with Julien. I should talk to Julien and help him figure out how to proceed.
Julien is sympathetic to Aubrey's feelings, but he feels he must go ahead with the plan to woo Guendeline. I should bring the necklace to her.
Julien was unaware of Khalisah's feelings. He reconsidered his decision to pursue Guendeline and asked me to give the necklace to <<1>>. She should be pleased.
Julien was unaware of Khalisah's feelings. He reconsidered his decision to pursue Guendeline and asked me to give the necklace to Khalisah. She should be pleased.
Kallath has sent me to check on a lumberjack camp to the south of Camlorn. It was apparently attacked.
Caretaker Villas asked that I speak to Jailor Newbury and see what I can do about the hauntings. I'll find Jailor Newbury in the east tower of Eagle's Watch.
Bhogoth gave me an ancient key and told me to investigate the old west tower, outside the walls of Eagle's Watch. He said that the 'voices' are waiting for me there.

The three spirits recited odd limericks, implying something bad once happened in the tower. I chose to help the spirit of Wembley find peace. Wembley urged me to 'find him' in an offshoot of the pass to Shornhelm, west of the Eagle's Watch lines.
When I reached the western pass, the spirit of Wembley appeared. It seems to want me to follow it.
When Wembley reached his destination, a small graveyard, ghosts of King's Guard citizens appeared and attacked me. When I stuck them, they morphed into fierce, ghostly werewolves.
After I dispatched the werewolves, Wembley urged me to collect their bones and bury them in front of the chapel at Cath Bedraud.
Wembley appeared to me and told me to prepare myself. Once I am ready, I am to bury the bones and await the result.
After I buried the bones, they seemed to coalesce into a fearsome looking undead werewolf - half wolf, half skeleton. The construct attacked me.

After I slew Morgur, Wembley's spirit reappeared. He told me he was at peace, finally. He asked me to take the Defender's Horn and blow it inside the West Tower of Eagle's Watch. That, he says, will allow the other spirits to rest.
The key allowed me to unlock the door the ancient west tower, which appears to have been sealed for years. As soon as I opened the door, I heard weeping from upstairs.
When I reached the western pass, the spirit of Wembley appeared. It seems to want me to follow it.
When Wembley reached his destination, a small graveyard, ghosts of King's Guard citizens appeared and attacked me. When I stuck them, they morphed into fierce, ghostly werewolves.
After I dispatched the werewolves, Wembley urged me to collect their bones and bury them beneath the statue of Stendarr, at Cath Bedraud.
When I blew the horn at the west tower, the spirits in the area vanished. They appear to be at rest. I should return to Caretaker Villas and tell him of my deeds.
Aubrey and Julien are both quite happy, but I must speak with Julien again to make sure he's going to sign up for the watch.
Iven sent me to Westtry to find some of the belongings of the Westtry refugees in Grayborne.
I've found the refugees' belongings and should return them to Iven in Grayborne.

Warden Godwin told me that Crosswych is besieged by werewolves.  He knows nothing of Gargast.  This trail has gone cold.nnGodwin handed me a letter from Oron, calling me back to return to Camlorn at once.

The assassin was sent by a necromancer, one Jha gra-Muzgob, who seems to be coordinating the undead in this part of Northmoor. She will ultimately have to be dealt with, but for right now Marcel and I are cutting off her supply of bodies.
The Curate and I were ambushed by an assassin wearing the same acolyte's robes we've been seeing. I must defend him!
Jha gra-Muzgob is working on a powerful ritual. I have discovered its location and must disrupt it.
I have disrupted the ritual and driven the remaining acolytes to flee, for now. Jha's shade suggested that the Bone Colossus may yet have risen, albiet weakened. I should report to the Redoubt.
I am about to speak with the Countess.
I have the herbs and must return to the priestess.
Goodwife Mallory sent me to kill wolves around the village of Grayborne.
The Doctor told me that Guendeline is pregnant. I must tell her.
I must choose between doing what Barre asked and killing Morgan Frey, or taking a chance that I can save her life with the antidote to Frey's poison.
Guendeline has seen that she is better off with her original courtier and the father of her child, Pierric. I only hope Pierric sees things the same way.
I have chosen to kill Morgan Frey, as Constable Barre asked.
We repelled the Werewolf assault. I should speak with the Warden.
Having killed Morgan Frey, I should return to Constable Barre, who is on the road between Grayborne and Westtry.
Doctor Sevarain was attacked by Werewolves  as we spoke! I need to aid him in repelling the assault!
Now that I have a key, I must free the courier.
Constable Barre asked me to take word of Morgan Frey's demise to Constable Meillor in Grayborne.nnI will also tell him she at least lived to see justice done.
I should take word of Constable Barre's death and her tabard to Sergeant Gallmau.  His men patrol the road between Grayborne and Camlorn.
I must remain as the ritual is carried out.  As Oron mentioned, I should learn who the murderer was once it is complete.
I finished killing the bears. Teddy was happy.
Teddy has asked me to kill two bears. He said they were near the building.
I spared Morgan Frey's life in exchange for an antidote to the poison he used on Constable Barre.nnHe sent me to Thetis the Poisoner, in the hills near Grayborne.
I have collected all of Ahlotica's wind-blown papers and should return them to her at the Fane of Breath.
I must ride south along the road to Grayborne, then west to Thetis' house, on a hill. There, I must ask Thetis for a cure to help Isaac, then return the cure to Isaac before he expires.
I should speak to Isaac to see if the cure has helped with his poison.
I must question Vincintian about the Shrouded Throne.
I'm going to ask <<1>> in Hoarfrost Downs if he would be willing to join the town watch.
I need to speak with Doctor Sevarain.
Isaac asked me to take his horse and use it to bring him back a cure for his poison.
Oron wishes me to help him by journeying to Crosswych to investigate rumors of the Shrouded Throne and whatever ties Gargast had to the area.
I have decided to assist Oron. I will journey to Crosswich to look into any allies Gargast may have had there.
I failed to return to Isaac in time. It would appear he expired during my absence.
Doctor Sevarain got jumped by werewolves before he could test me. I think saving his hide proved I was all right in his book.
I've hired on with Doctor Holcombe, who seems to be a monster hunter of some repute. I should speak to him about my first task as his assistant.
Holcome asked me to journey into the swamp and activate a sound box near the docks. It will attract bogrums. I am to slay all those who appear.
As the soundbox began to play a raucous noise, bogrums emerged from the swamp and attacked me.
I've slain all the Bog Lurchers who appeared when I activated the sound box. I should return to Doctor Holcombe outside Aldcroft with this news.
I've gotten the antidote from Thetis the Poisoner and must return with it to Constable Barre, hopefully in time to save her life.
While Constable Barre goes in search of Morgan Frey once again, I am to locate his gang of bandits and kill them.nnThey can be found in the forest to the west of Grayborne.
Having found Frey's gang, I kill any of them I can while Constable Barre tries to find Morgan Frey.
I should try to find Constable Barre and tell her the news.
The guard outside Camlorn Manor directed me to an official of the Nine Crowns named Oron.  Oron was sent here by King Fahara'jad, the ruler of the Nine Crowns.  nnI am on my way to speak to Oron now.

I must present this letter to King Sebastien's guard and gain an audience with the King. King Sebastien's manor is in the southeastern part of Camlorn. I am to go straight there along the main road. It will be North of Lord Drugo.
I've agreed to search the swamp for both Aurore and Isabelle Bagot, then escort them safely back to Aldcroft.
The Bagot family is safe. I should see if Aurore needs any further assistance.

I've found Isabelle and Aurore Bagot, and they have agreed to return with me to Aldcroft. I must escort Aurore and Isabelle Bagot back to Tristan. To stop the threat of the large Bog Lurker Tristan spoke of, I will need to dispatch it as well.
I will ask the guard more about this murder and where I can find the man leading the investigation.
I am headed to Baron Avon's home, in the market district of Camlorn.
I've reunited Isabelle nad Aurore. I must now convince Aurore to return with us.
I've talked to Alaric and agreed to follow him back to his camp. I just need to tell him I am ready to go.
Seems some of the neighbors in Crosswych aren't exactly... neighborly.
I spoke with Guillie.  Now I need to get Al'kari's side of the story.
I need to choose a side!
I spoke with Al'kari.  Now I need to get Guillie's side of the story.
I need to choose a side!
I've agreed to search the swamp for both Aurore and Isabelle Bagot, then escort them safely back to Aldcroft.
Aurore is ready to leave. I should let Isabelle know that it's time to go.
I am on my way to speak to Oron now.

The guard outside Camlorn Manor directed me to an official of the Adamant Crown named Oron.  Oron was sent here by King Fahara'jad, the ruler of the Adamant Crown.  nnI am on my way to speak to Oron now.
I am headed to Baron Avon's home, in the market district of Camlorn.

Baron Winoc asked me to ask people around Camlorn about the Hands of Northmoor, pretending to be an uninformed visitor. He hopes I will be able to gain honest opinions about the Hands that he could not gain himself, due to his position at their head.
I've bandaged all injured lumberjacks who need immediate medical attention. I should see if Stanwood has anything else for me to do.
Medic Standwood gave me bandages to use on injured lumberjacks. I should do what I can to make sure these unfortunate souls survive the day.
I need to kill a field rabbit to lure a kitty. I'm pretty sure I can find one roaming the farms east of Crosswych.
The cat is following me. I need to either lure it to Al'kari's house to get rid of her roosters or lure it to Guillie's house to get rid of his rats.
I've decided to take Alaric back to the caravan. The people there should be able to take good care of him.
I've decided to follow Alaric back to the camp he spoke of, where he says there are other children. He also mentioned someone called Gran Mog.
Warden Rielle asked me to go west from the caravan and try to find the camp Alaric spoke of. I should find out what I can about the camp and its inhabitants.
I led the cat to Guillie's house. It promptly chased away the rats. I should tell Al'kari about my success.
I led the cat to Al'kari's house. It promptly chased away the roosters. I should tell Guillie about my success.
As a first step in clearing the murkling camp, Warden Rielle wants me to slay the dire wolves that prevent the children from leaving.
When I slew the last of the charmed dire wolves, a grotesque hag materialized from the swamp and attacked me. She threatened me with doom should I continue to interfere with the murkling camp.
I've slain the dire wolves guarding the murkling camp, allowing the children to flee, if they wish. I should return to Rielle to plan our next move.

Warden Rielle asked me to gather Blue Fang Roots from the area west of her, then grind them up and dump them in the murkling well. It won't harm the children, but will make their water taste very sour, encouraging them to leave.
I've gathered the roots Rielle mentioned and ground them up as best I can. All that remains is to dump them into the murkling well.
I've dumped the ground Blue Fang Roots into the murkling well with none of the children the wiser. The well already smells awful, so I think the mixture worked. I should return to Rielle.

Warden Rielle asked me to burn the murkling supplies - the food and other perishables they've stolen from local merchants. Without those to keep them warm and fed, the caravan and adults may look more attractive to the children.
I slew the hags that attacked me. Both screamed that I would be punished for my actions, and that someone named 'Mother Murk' would make me pay. I should return to Rielle with what I've found out.
When I set fire to the murkling supplies, grotesque, haglike creatures emerged from the bog and attacked me.
I need to find Veris' son, Balen.
I've successfully escorted Balen out of the docks. I should tell Veris that his son is safe.

I must go to the children's camp and speak with Odette. Now that the camp can no longer sustain itself, I should be able to convince her to lead her children back to the caravan, where they will be cared for.

At Odette's feverish shouting, a gruesome apparition appeared from the swamp - it can be no other than Mother Murk herself, the abomination that has been working behind the scenes to hold the children at this camp. She must be slain.

I've slain the gruesome apparition of Mother Murk, and her hold over the children is finished. Odette is ready to leave, now, but asked me to find her parents. I should speak with Warden Rielle at the Aldcroft caravan and see if she has any leads.
I should find Sweetling and bring her back to Varle.
I've found Sweetling and should return her to Nathaniel Varle in Grayborne.
I have found enough Drythistle for Amelie, and must return to Aldcroft to bring it to her.
I've obtained the sample of lakewater Doctor Holcombe requested. I should return the sample to him and see what he makes of it.
I need to go to Aldcroft Harbor, dispatch Inquisitor Niare, kill five Magis Order Soldiers, and free the captive Hands of Northmoor.
I've put a significant dent in the Magis Order's numbers, slain Inquisitor Niare, and freed the captive Hands. I need to return to Gargast and report my success.
I've decided to help Odette throw off the tyranny of Mother Murk. I will help her and the other children escape the camp.

Once I agreed to help Odette, a gruesome apparition appeared from the swamp - it can be no other than Mother Murk herself, the abomination that has been holding the children at this camp. She must be slain.

I've slain the gruesome apparition of Mother Murk, and her hold over the children is finished. Odette is ready to leave, now, but asked me to find her parents. I should speak with Warden Rielle at the Aldcroft caravan and see if she has any leads.
If I come across a man named Arnand, I should take a moment to speak with him - it may be to my benefit.
I have the supplies from Arnand's chest. I should return them to him.

Doctor Holcombe believes the minty smell the children associate with Mother Murk may be caused by Greenfoot Roots, which grow beside the lake. He asked me to collect a sample of water from the lake near the Greenfoot Roots, then return it to him.
I've freed Grit from the bandits that had captured him. I should return to Serge with the good news.
The hostile bandits have taken Grit hostage - they have him locked in a cage at the center of their camp. One of the bandits must have the key. I should slay them and see if I can find it.
I've recovered the key to Grit's cage. I should open the cage and let Grit run free.
Serge asked me to look for Grit to the north, where the bandits have set up camp. I should look for the dire wolf, if he's still alive.
Greenfoot Root grows by the lake to the north.     Odette asked me to gather some, then dump them into the murkling well. She believes that will fix the sour taste the water has taken on.
I've gathered the Greenfoot Root as Odette requested. I should dump them into the well to freshen the soured water.
I should return to Odette and see what else she needs. The well smells much better after I dumped the fresh Greenfoot Root in the water.
Inquisitor Roche has sent me to collect spriggan's hearts and worm's cap mushrooms. The mushrooms are in the forest to the southwest.nnHe also gave me a catalyst I can use to make poison.
I should use the catalyst Roche gave me to make a poison out of mushrooms and spriggan hearts.

I should take the poison I made and find some sprouts around the Wyrd Tree, the source of their magic.nnApplying the poison to the sprouts will leech poison to the tree itself and decrease the Wyrd's power.
Now that I've diminished the Wyrd's power by poisoning their tree, I should find the sigil staff they stole from Roche.
I found Roche's staff near the Wyrd Tree.nnHe'll be glad to have it back. I should return it to him in Grayborne.

Doctor Holcombe believes the entrance to Mother Murk's lair must be submerged beneath Lake Urvaius. He asked me to dive into the lake near where I took the sample, find the lair, then search for the murkling parents.

I've found Mother Murk's lair. It's filled with disgusting pods that look to have something writhing inside them. It looks like people, suspended in some sort of stasis. If I break apart the pods, I should be able to free those inside.
Something else besides hags is in Mother Murk's lair something ancient and angry. If I don't kill it, it may start the whole cycle of disappearances and kidnappings all over again.
I've freed the parents who were trapped in stasis inside Mother Murk's lair. I should return to Odette to make sure she and the other murklings are all right.
I slew a massive bog witch named Gran Mog. It seems she kept the people she captured in pods to eventually turn them into hags
If I can get into the goblin camp and dispel their effigies, I will greatly reduce the goblin shamans' power.
I could use the magical thread the Wyress Jacinta gave me, and make a goblin disguise.nnThe goblins may leave various... goblin parts around their camp middens.
I should go and dispel the goblin effigies in their camp to the southeast of Grayborne.
I can use the parts I've collected to make a disguise.
I should return to the wyress Jacinta and let her know I was able to dispel the effigies.
I need to find and loot Arnand's chest. It's somewhere on the pirate's boat.

Faya insists that her friend, Vandica, is real. I'm concerned that Faya insists that Vandica can manipulate real objects such as coins and toys. There may be more at work here. I should follow Faya to her "friend" and see what I can discover.
Faya wandered off to a spot near the bog. I should say with her.
Faya claims she often plays with Vandica. There is a waterlogged toy on the ground choked with moss. Faya claims it belongs to Vandica...
When I picked up the toy, the spector of a young girl appeared on the lake shore. However, she quickly grew hostile, and attacked me.
Roche has sent me back to the Wyrd camp to kill one of the Wyress leaders.
I should return to Watchman Derran and let him know that Al'kari and Guillie should pose no further problems.
Inquisitor Bieller wants me to patrol Camlorn. I'm supposed to ask Watcher Emeric about the usual route, and what things to watch out for.
Watcher Emeric directed me to the south gates of the city once I had patrolled the crafter's circle, specifically the tavern nearby, as it's often rowdy.
Watcher Emeric directed me to start my patrol of Camlorn with the temple at the top of the hill. I'm supposed to head there and then speak with one of the priests, who should be outside.
Captain Arin advised me to seek out Gui, the prior chapel keeper of Cath Bedraud. I'll find him at Camp Mercy, south of Eagle's Watch.
Though Gui cannot read the parchment, he advised me to speak with a Priest of Arkay in the chapel at Cath Bedraud.
The Priest of Arkay stated that his order is opposed to disciples of the King of Worms, people involved in necromancy. He told me to burn the parchment at a statue of Arkay outside the chapel.
Upon catching flame, the parchment expelled a spectre which attacked me. When I slew it, it screamed a name  Jha gra-Muzgob. I should return to Gui and see if he has heard the name before.
While working at the chapel, Gui often chased off an orc witch who was trying to steal bodies - Jha gra-Muzgob. He told me her old house is south of Camp Mercy. Perhaps I'll find something there.

Jha gra-Muzgob's house was in ruins, but a necromancer remained. When he attacked me, I slew him and found a note from Jha gra-Muzgob. The orc witch asked him to meet her at the weeping witch. Perhaps Gui will know what it means.
Gui said the weeping witch is the statue of Mara behind Cath Bedraud Chapel. He wants to stop Jha gra-Muzgob. He will meet me at the graveyard after calling in a favor.
I confronted Jha gra-Muzgob behind the chapel. She brought allies, but Gui arrived with soldiers from both the Hands of Northmoor and the Magis Order.
Alongside my allies, we slew Jha gra-Muzgob and put an end to her graverobbing for good. I should return to Arin and let her know no more dead will be taken.

Barnard has prior experience with graverobbers - he hung members of a bandit group several years back for the crime. He suggested I look for them southeast of Camp Mercy, and see if the bandits know anything about the missing bodies.
Captain Arin asked me to speak to Barnard with the Hands of Northmoor - he handles burials for their men. He may have some idea why bodies have been vanishing.
When I approached him to ask about the missing corpses, the bandit leader attacked me. I should subdue him instead of killing him so I can find out what he knows.
After I subdued the bandit leader, he admitted to robbing graves and selling the bodies to an orc named Jha gra-Muzgob. I should return to Eagle's watch and tell Barnard what I've found out.

After hearing about the orc, Jha gra-Muzgob, buying bodies, Barnard asked me to interrogate a gravedigger at Cath Bedraud named Palo. Give Palo's history of looting graves, he suspects Palo may be involved with Jha gra-Muzgob.
Through his stuttering, Palo all but admitted to selling bodies to an orc.
I confronted Jha gra-Muzgob behind the chapel. She brought allies, but Barnard arrived with soldiers from the Hands of Northmoor.
Barnard asked me to meet him and his men behind the Cath Bedraud Chapel. There, we will put an end to Jha gra-Muzgob's necromancy.
Palo insisted Jha gra-Muzgob must have sent the construct to silence us both. I should return to Barnard with this news.
When Palo admitted to working with Jha gra-Muzgob, a massive undead attacked us. I slew it.
Alongside my allies, we slew Jha gra-Muzgob and put an end to her graverobbing for good. I should return to Arin and let her know no more dead will be taken.

Inquisitor Ephin is certain that Shornhelm spies are among the refugees sheltering in Eagle's Watch. He asked me to round up refugees from the camp outside the west walls and bring them back to him for interrogation.
I should grab another refugee from the camp outside the west wall and bring him back to Ephin for interrogation.

Inquisitor Ephin is certain that Shornhelm spies are among the refugees sheltering in Eagle's Watch. He asked me to round up refugees from the camp outside the west walls and bring them back to him for interrogation.
I've provided Ephin with several refugees to interrogate about the identify of the Shornhelm spy. I should see if he's made any progress.

A refugee I captured admitted to helping a necromancer steal bodies from Cath Bedraud. Ephin's aide, Heaton, took the refugee to Cath Bedraud, where he will reveal his master. Ephin asked that I go meet Heaton behind Cath Bedraud's chapel.
Upon reaching the refugee camp, some angry refugees attacked me.
I slew the refugees that tried to murder me. I doubt we can gain more from the refugee camp - if the spy was there, he has certainly fled by now. I should return to Ephin to plan our next move.
Despite Heaton's betrayal, I slew Jha gra-Muzgob and put an end to her graverobbing for good. I should return to Arin and let her know no more dead will be taken.

I found a recently disturbed grave, as if I had just scared off a robber. Whoever it was dropped a parchment with the words 'The King of Worms shall rise, and his enemy shall name him'. I should return to Captain Blayne with what I've found.

Captain Blayne asked me to gather the advice of Barnard Danvers, of the Hands of Northmoor, Inquisitor Ephin, of the Magis Order, and Caretaker Villas, who knows the Cath Bedraud staff. One of these three may offer a path to stop the graverobbing.
Captain Blayne told me to look for Gui at Camp Mercy, south of Eagle's Watch. I should head there when I'm ready to continue the investigation.
I've decided to work with Barnard Danvers and the Hands of Northmoor. I should speak to Barnard about our next move.
I've decided to work with Inquisitor Ephin of the Magis Order. I should speak with Ephin about our next move.
I must decide whether to work with the Hands of Northmoor, the Magis Order, or the Cath Bedraud staff to investigate the missing bodies.
Annalysse was nowhere to be found, but I was ambushed by several werewolves.
I need to find Inquisitor Lyssa to ask for her help in defending Crosswych.

Inquisitor Lyssa suspects Crosswych's greatest threat comes from within. She has asked me to bring three citizens from Crosswych or the surrounding farms to her for a failsafe test that will determine their true nature - man or beast.
I need to bring my newfound friend to the Biren barn, where Inquisitor Lyssa awaits.
The first villager was determined by the Order to be uninfected. I need to find another potential Werewolf to bring before the Order's Inquisition.
I've patrolled the temple area, and should now check in with the priest of Zenithar, who should be outside. He is a man by the name of Cael Thierry.
I've patrolled the tavern and the front gates of Camlorn. Two men appear to be fighting outside of the tavern. I should break the fight up.
I am headed to the south of Grayborne in search of the courier.
It appears the courier wandered too close to the Spriggan's territory.  I must inform Inquisitor Roche I found his corpse there.
I found another villager willing to accompany me to Inquisitor Lyssa. I should bring them to her posthaste.
I managed to convince a third villager to accompany me to the Biren farm.
The second villager was cleared of suspicion as well. I need to find a third villager to submit to Lyssa's test.
Now that I've made the disguise, I can use it to sneak into the goblin camp and dispel the shamans' effigies.
The last villager turned out to be a Werewolf in disguise! I must dispatch them!
From the marks on his body it appears the Spriggans did slay the courier.  I must inform Inquisitor Roche of the courier's fate.
I should talk to Inquisitor Roche again.
The Werewolf mentioned the name "Annalynne" before perishing. That is the name of Godwin's fiancee! I must inform him immediately.
I've chosen to side with Chamberlain Gargast and the Hands of Northmoor. I should speak to Gargast to determine our next move.

I slew the courier and retrieved the documents he was bringing to Aldcroft. As he died, he rasped something about 'The Shrouded Throne'. I should return to Inquisitor Spencer and show him the documents I collected.
I've collected the Elixir of True Nature from Doctor Holcombe. I should return to Spencer and see what he plans to do next.
I've agreed to hunt Gargast down and slay him for Warden Caldrun - however, Caldrun asked me to speak to him before I leave.
The process is complete. Auri-El is ready, waiting in Sinderon's hands.
It seems Brennoc of Grayborne would like me to handle a matter of civil import before he trusts me with information about the courier.
I should speak to the Alaygon villagers to find out more information about this "reading".
I am going to speak with Brennoc.

Inquisitor Ephin is certain that Shornhelm spies are among the refugees sheltering in Eagle's Watch. He asked me to round up refugees from the camp outside the west walls and bring them back to him for interrogation.
I met Heaton behind Cath Bedraud's chapel, but there was no refugee in sight. Instead, a strange orc woman arrived.
I freed Adwyn.  I am leading him south of Grayborne, where I will question him about Ranser's murder weapon.

Heaton was working with a necromancer, Jha gra-Muzgob, to steal bodies from Cath Bedraud and raise an army to attack Eagle's Watch. I slew both. I should return to Ephin and tell him Heaton was the spy - and tell Captain Blayne her brother's fate.
Inquisitor Ephin is continuing to interrogate the refugees I captured, and believes they will soon reveal the identity of the spy. He asked me to capture one or two more refugees - just to be sure.
I will search for the prison to the east of Grayborne.
The werewolf muttered something about "Annalynne" before he died. Annalynne is Warden Godwin's fiancee, so I'm sure he would appreciate that information delivered immediately.
Godwin fears for Annalynne's safety. He sent me up to their house on the hill to check on her.
Annalynne was nowhere to be found, but I was ambushed by three werewolves! This doesn't bode well. I should inform Godwin.
the first villager was cleared of suspicion. I need to bring another one in for testing.
Annalynne was nowhere to be found, but I was ambushed by three werewolves! This doesn't bode well. I should inform Godwin.
Godwin believes some of the villagers within Crosswych are in fact werewolves in disguise. He wants me to annoint them with an elixir that will reveal their true nature.
Annalysse was nowhere to be found, but I was ambushed by several werewolves.
The werewolf plans implied that they are taking Crosswych from "within."  What this means is beyond my ken, but I'd best report the information to Godwin immediately.
I need to find Gargast's body.  Warden Godwin mentioned it was southwest of Crosswych.
I need to examine Gargast's corpse for evidence of how he was killed.
I need to find the Werewolf Camp. I saw footprints leading off to the west, I should head in that direction.
I need to look at the Werewolves' plans to see what they have in mind for Crosswych...
I expelled the specter possessing the people of Camlorn.  It desperately sought to announce that Countess Virolynn has the murder weapon.
The Shade of Ranser must be slain for the citizens of Camlorn to be safe.
I have managed to gather many clues that may lead to Ranser's murderer. Baron Avon told me to seek his friend Hughes in Grayborne, but first I must return to Oron and tell him what I've learned.
Danain handed me a symbol to use upon the possessed citizens of Camlorn.  He mentioned the citizens would be in their homes to the west of him.
I must follow up with Oron's request and speak to Inquisitor Danain at Magis Order Headquarters.
Baron Avon will be pleased to learn that the Inquisitors were convinced that Magister Averos murdered Lord Ranser.  I must return to the Baron at once.
I found barrels broken open and pouring sludge into the lake. Since a goblin attacked me, I assume they are to blame. I should talk to Varle about this sludge and show it to him.
The courier is dead.  I should examine his body to determine how he was slain.
Varle suggested that I take the sludge to Thetis. He should be able to tell me how to stop the goblins.nnVarle said Thetis lives in a house North-Northwest of the windmill.
The infected villagers called out something about Annalynne when they died... I had better inform Godwin about this, she could be in danger.
I need to see if Annalynne is still at Godwin's house.
Annalynne was nowhere to be found, but I was ambushed by three werewolves! This doesn't bode well. I should inform Godwin.
Annalynne was nowhere to be found, but I was ambushed by several werewolves.

Tactician Veraul believes that we could halt the entire Shornhelm invasion if we still Marshal Gerard's plans, thus depriving him of the ability to lead his troops. I should talk to him about how best to accomplish this.
I must slay a Shornhelm soldier and steal his uniform. Then, I can use the uniform to sneak into the Shornhelm camp and retrieve Marshal Gerard's invasion plan.
I've collected a Shornhelm uniform. If I don't want to be attacked by Shornhelm soldiers, I should don it before entering the camp.
I should present the head of Rahoeri to Battlereeve Tariella at the Harmonium Fortress.
I am headed to Magis Order Headquarters to speak with Inquisitor Danain.
I need to talk to Baron Avon to find more evidence. He resides in the northwestern section of Camlorn.
Baron Avon was right - the Watchers boasted that Averos killed Ranser, and that the blade he used has been taken away to the village of Grayborne.nnI must inform Baron Avon.
Emeric's girlfriend, one Mage Guard Elorian, should be at the Redoubt Camp just north of Camlorn, in Ykalon Forest.
I've found Mage Guard Illain, and found out more about the Redoubt Camp. It seems that they could use some help here, and I should talk with Commander Blarae for more information.
Laeran Jes can be found at the Redoubt Camp, just north of Camlorn in Ykalon Forest.
I've found Laeran Jes, and found out more about the Redoubt Camp. It seems that they could use some help here, and I should talk with Commander Blarae for more information.
The werewolves have retreated. I should speak with Godwin.
I need to meet Godwin at the main Werewolf camp north of Crosswych.

Apparently I could get some blood nettle flowers and marrow for Thetis, if I want to poison animals. Blood Nettle are all around his house to the Sourth, and there are goblins near the lake and near the nettles at times.
I've got some poison now. I just have to poison the food the goblins eat. I think I saw them attacking rabbits...
I've collect nettles and marrow like Thetis suggested. I need to take it back to him so he can make a poison.
Ahlotica has dropped three papers, which are blowing around the Fane of Breath. I'll need to be quick to catch them.
Someone in town has to have seen Orator Dalomar. Probably someone who wouldn't draw much attention.
Jaeme the Beggar told me that he saw Magis Order soldiers putting something large and heavy-looking in the lake. It seems to be worth checking out.
Canning asked me to use his pendant to drive fiends from the possessed citizens of Camlorn. I will start looking for possessed citizens in the northern part of the lowercity.
I must destroy the demon for the citizens of Camlorn to be safe.

When I exorcised a Camlorn citizen, the demon taunted me and hinted that Ranser's Body would soon pass through something called Thrandor's Portal. I must find High Priest Canning by the footbridge of the residential section and tell him of this.
I'm caught up on current events in Eagle's Watch, thanks to Arin Blayne. I should now report to Tactician Veraul.
Captain Blayne has offered to fill me in on events at Eagle's Watch. I should ask her about what's led to the Shornhelm invasion of Northmoor.
I must journey to the ruins and fight the wraiths there. Once the wraiths are weakened, I must use the Soul Cage Danain gave me to capture their essence, ensuring they will plague Camlorn no longer.
I've weakened and captured a number of wraiths in the ruins outside Camlorn. I should return to Danain, on Camlorn's docks, and inform him of my success.

One of the merchants, recently relieved of his goods by the vengeful spirits near the ruins, mentioned that he saw bandits sneaking in shortly afterwards. There are certainly plenty of bandits in Ykalon, and they may have what I'm looking for.
I need to aid in the battle between Crosswych and the Werewolves!
I'm going to hear if the Watchers offer any clues.
I've chosen to side with Inquisitor Spencer and the Magis Order. I should speak to Spencer to determine our next move.

I should see what else I can find out about the standoff in Aldcroft. I've found the courier who delivered Ranser's weapon to Countess Virolynn in Aldcroft, but she's stuck in the city until the Magis Order blockade of the docks is lifted.

I cannot speak to Virolynn until I settle the dispute in Aldcroft. It arose between Inquisitor Spencer, of the Magis Order, and Chamberlain Gargast, Countess Virolynn's advisor. I should speak with both and see if I can convince either to give in.

I must pick a side and resolve the situation. Chamberlain Gargast insists he is no spy. The Magis Order insists he is. Until Gargast is taken by the Order or the Hands of Northmoor push the Order out of town, it will be impossible to see Virolynn.
A man by the name of Tamarus from Coldun who lives in the village now may have more information on how to help deal with the approaching army. I should speak to him, near the smithy.
Spencer told me a Shornhelm courier will be arriving in Aldcroft along the road from Crosswych. I should follow the road to Crosswych until I intercept him.
Though I discovered the courier, I did not get a chance to speak to him. He said I 'smelled like Magis Order', then revealed himself as a werewolf and attacked me.

I have been tasked with delivering a message to one of the surrounding encampments of the town. Into the mountains are the mystics of the Bloody Eye. The woods of the north hold the nomads. I must speak with one of them, and quickly.
I should extract what I can from the nearby plants. Once I have them, I should try to injure the wolves and use the extract on them to see what happens

Using the extract upon the wolves caused wondrous effects that I would of never imagined. It transformed them back to their true selves, innocent villagers picked up by the Coldun army. I should return to Drigg to inform him of this news.

We've found the cause of the pigs being let out. The wolves were setting a trap for the goblin nomads in hopes of baiting them out. The leader, Direfang, was behind it all, but slain by our combined might. I should speak to Dirk right away.
I should follow Dirk into the forest as he attempts to call the piggies out of hiding.
I was told to follow the mountain wall east until I ran across Scag.
I should speak to the Forest Spirit to ask for her blessing.

I was surprised to find myself in a world similar to the one I stand in now, but filled with that of lost and damned souls. A small whisper told me to defeat those who stood against me and now I stand back in the world of the living.
Natasha Bladespire, located on the Bloody Eye grounds, holds more information regarding what this "Veil" is and what the Coldun army would want with it. I should speak to her at once.

I've discovered that the source of the spirit realm lies inside the dark statues erected about the town, channeling the power of the Dreadlord. nnI will only have a limited time to destroy the statues; otherwise I will be damned in the spirit realm
The statues of the Dreadlord Valyn have been destroyed and I have made it back, spirit intact, to the realm of the living. I must let Sly know at once that the deed of the Bloody Eye is complete.

Located around the spirit realm are three statues that must be destroyed. One in the farm land, one in the smithy, and one located in one of the houses of Alaygon. I must be cautious, attacking the statues will signal a cry for help.

Spencer asked me to gather ingredients for a rare potion called an 'Elixir of True Nature'. I must collect bog moss, then find the oldest lurker in the bog. After I slay him and take his brain, I should visit Doctor Holcombe at the Aldcroft caravan.
I've gathered the ingredients Spencer listed. I should visit with Doctor Holcombe and ask him about the 'Elixir of True Nature'.

In exchange for the time and materials necessary to mix the Elixir of True Nature, Doctor Holcombe asked that I slay Bog Lurkers that have been threatening the caravan he is with. Once I've slain a few lurkers, I can return and pick up the elixir.
I've slain a number of Bog Lurkers around the caravan with which Doctor Holcombe is staying. I should return to him and see if he has completed the elixir.
I used Canning's pendant to force a fiend out of one of Camlorn's citizens, and slew the vile thing that emerged. I should continue to exorcise other citizens until all the fiends are gone.
I've exorcised another citizen and slain a second fiend plaguing Camlorn. I must continue to do what High Priest Canning asked and exorcise more citizens.
I need to find the werewolf camp Godwin spoke of.
I spoke to a few more of the villagers, with mixed results about whether or not Elsie is dangerous or not.
I should speak to High Kinlord Maldarawo at the Isquer Kinhouse.
I should speak to High Kinlord Maldarawo at the Isquer Kinhouse.
The tide spiders should be able to be found along the southwestern coast of Northmoor.
High Kinlord Maldarawo suggested I speak to Vartisan Urselor at the Syldarim Kinhouse in Orrery.
Countess Virolynn has emerged from her chambers to sign the fake surrender papers. I should splash Gargast with the elixir while he is standing in front of her.
When I splashed the elixir on Gargast, he turned into a werewolf! He gravely wounded Virolynn before fleeing the manor. I should speak with Virolynn's advisors to see what can be done.
I've agreed to help Eliana heal Virolynn - however, Eliana asked me to speak with Caldrun while she eases Virolynn's bleeding.
I was ambushed by an assassin! I must dispatch him.
Inquisitor Bieller is in the Magis Order Barracks in Camlorn.

Inquisitor Bieller has sent me to Daenia to deliver a box of potions for the Magis Order soldiers in town. He suggested I deliver them to Nathaniel Varle rather than bothering the Inquisitor in town, and mentioned that Varle may know of work for me.

Spencer gave me fake surrender papers to deliver to Gargast. He hopes this will draw Virolynn out of seclusion to sign them. As she does so, I am to splash Gargast with the Elixir of True Nature. This will force Gargast to reveal himself.
I need to free the captive Hands!

I've spoken to one of the villagers who assured me that nothing strange has happened to the town, and that the Prophet was beginning to lose his mind. He suggested I visit the Elder in town for any reassurance I might need.
I should head to the farm located behind the village and begin to clear out the spider infestation. Perhaps I'll find cause of what is stirring them up.

It appears a Queen spider and her children were creating the issues with the farmland. A smith from Alaygon, Tamarus, came to my aid when attacked suddenly. He spoke of the spiders not being native to this region and had some concern to his voice.
Gargast was surprised I encountered trouble at the abandoned house and said he was relieved to see me safe. Now, I must convince Gargast to let me see Virolynn.
When Virolynn spoke of The Shrouded Throne, Gargast turned into a werewolf! He gravely wounded Virolynn before fleeing the manor. I must ask Virolynn's advisors what can be done.
I've agreed to hunt Gargast down and slay him for Warden Caldrun - however, I must get Ranser's weapon from him before I leave.
I've agreed to help Eliana heal Virolynn - however, Eliana asked me to speak with Caldrun while she eases Virolynn's bleeding.
I have been charged by Warden Caldrun to hunt down and destroy Gargast.  The beast must be put down.
With the beast slain, I wonder where Gargast was headed...  What is this Shrouded Throne?
I have the herbs and must return to the priestess.
The priestess believes Virolynn is strong enough to speak.  I should speak to her.

I have decided to help the priestess save the Countess.  She informed me of the cure to lycanthropy.  I must collect Wolfsbane and Belladonna flowers which grow on the gnarled Spriggans to the south east.
Roche intends to evict Elsie by hook or by crook. I have to warn her.
Roche thinks my methods of persuasion leave something to be desired. He has bid me watch him deal with Elsie personally.
I need to see if I can get Roche to leave Elsie alone
The Forest Spirit has given me the blessing of the goblins for when the town of Alaygon needs their aid. I am to speak to Scag immediately so I can bring news to Tamarus.
I should do the tasks given to me by Drigg and Dirk in order to gain the trust of the nomads.
I've helped both Dirk and Drigg with the wolf issues the goblins were facing. Both of them thanked me and gave me proof of their trust that I am now to show Scag.
I should speak to Tamarus while we wait for the Coldun army to arrive. Perhaps he will have need of me for some particular task...
Brennoc asked me to speak to Roche about some trouble in Grayborne.

After I slew Mother Murk, she provided a chilling revelation with her dying breath - the parents of the camp children are alive, and she has secreted them away somewhere. I should speak with Odette and see what she thinks of this new revelation.
I must speak with Odette. After I slew Mother Murk, with her dying breath she provided a chilling revelation - the parents of the camp children are alive, and she has secreted them away somewhere.
