As a first step, Doctor Holcombe asked me to interview the murklings to find out anything they can tell us about Mother Murk or her lair. He hopes one of the children may provide a clue that will lead us to her lair.

Odette stated that when Mother Murk left her, she always went in the direction of the lake. Serge stated that Mother Murk usually smelled like mint. I should return to Doctor Holcombe and see what he makes of this information.
I have been charged by Warden Caldrun to hunt down and destroy Gargast.  The beast must be put down.nnI must reach the bridge just north of Aldcroft.
Inform Roche that Elsie still refuses to leave.
Oorn asked me to travel to the temple of Zenithar in northern Camlorn and use the murder weapon on Lord Ranser's corpse.
I must remain as the ritual is carried out.  As Oron mentioned, I should learn who the murderer was once it is complete.
Lord Ranser's spirit arose from his corpse.  I must destroy this angry specter.
Lord Vincintian murdered Ranser!  I must inform Oron of this at once!
The Ritual Master wouldn't let Pierric leave without a fight. We had to dispatch him.
I need to accompany Pierric back to his betrothed's house, making sure he arrives there safely.
I need to tell Pierric to follow me closely in case we encounter beasts on the way back to Crosswych.
I need to return to Guendeline to see if Pierric made it back safely.
I have exorcised the evil remnant of Ranser from Rickard, and I must now kill it.
I have exorcised another spirit of Ranser.
I must return to Oron and inform him of what I have learned.
Elsie Dolban sent me to speak to Wyress Jacinta. She's in the enclave of the Beldama Wyrd to the south.
If I can get into the goblin camp and dispel their effigies, I'll greatly reduce the goblin shamans' power.
I should get close enough to Roche to use the stun powder.  Hopefully, it will give me time to steal back the Wyress' Howling Pipe.
I dispelled the effigies. I should return to Wyress Jacinta and let her know.
I could use the magical thread the Wyress Jacinta gave me to make a goblin disguise.nnThe goblins may leave various goblin parts around their camp middens.
While Inquisitor Roche is stunned by the Wyress' powder, I should steal the Howling Pipe back and get out before his guards find me.
I can use the parts I've collected to make a disguise.
Now that I've made the disguise, I can use it to sneak into the goblin camp and dispel the shamans' effigies.
I dispel the goblin effigies in the camp southeast of Grayborne.
I can use the Howling Pipe to drive off the goblins at the camp. That might give me a chance to attack their king and his henchmen.
Now that the goblin king is dead, I should return to the Wyress Jacinta.
The cult refused to allow Pierric to leave. We must dispatch them.
Roche sent me to the Wyrd enclave to kill as many witches as I can. nnHopefully thinning the witch population will stabilize this troubled area.
I've slain a Shornhelm soldier and stolen his uniform. I can use the uniform to sneak into the Shornhelm camp, find Marshal Gerard's tent, and steal his invasion plan.
Now disguised, I must collect Marshal Gerard's invasion plans from his desk in his tent in the Shornhelm camp.
I have arrived back in Crosswych and must deliver this missive to Warden Godwin.
I must speak with the Crosswych flight master and travel to Camlorn.
I have arrived in Camlorn, and I must speak with King Sebastien. He is in the southeastern part of Camlorn.
I've gathered the advice of the people Captain Blayne recommend. I should return to speak with her.
I've told Elsie she can stay, and now should return to Roche.
Seems some of the neighbors in Crosswych aren't exactly neighborly.
Brennoc has asked me to come to my own conclusions about Elsie Dolban, but to speak with Inquisitor Roche first.
I've successfully repelled the Shornhelm attack on Northmoor's lines below Eagle Watch. I should speak with Captain Danfor to see if he needs any more assistance.
The guard outside Camlorn Manor directed me to an official of the Adamant Crown named Oron.  Oron was sent here by King Fahara'jad, the ruler of the Adamant Crown.
I have exorcised another spirit of Ranser.
I must return to Oron and inform him of what I have learned.
I need to talk to Baron Winoc to find more evidence. He resides in the northwestern section of Camlorn.
Winoc suspects the Magis Order is behind Ranser's murder: at his suggestion I'm going to eavesdrop upon some Watchers at the tavern and try to overhear anything they might say about the murder.
I'm going to hear if the Watchers offer any clues.
Baron Winoc was right - the Watchers boasted that Averos killed Ranser, and that the blade he used has been taken away to the village of Grayborne.nnI must inform Baron Winoc.
I have managed to gather many clues that may lead to Ranser's murderer. Baron Winoc told me to seek his friend Brennoc in Grayborne, but first I must return to Oron and tell him what I've learned.

High Priest Canning will exorcise any spirits that remain in Camlorn. He told me to seek out Commander Blarae, at the northern Redoubt, and enlist his help to recover Ranser's body from the hooded figure that attacked us.
Talk to QA Talker or get the QA Quest Item.
I must talk to both Inquisitor Jaques Vanne and Taverner Dilborn Farr inside the Aldcroft Inn to learn why the Magis Order and the Hands are at odds.
I administered Stanwood's poultice to the diseased lumberjacks. I should return to Medic Stanwood and inform him.
I can find the herbs I need for the potions to the North of the lumber camp.
I need to combine the two herbs to create the poultice.
I must find four diseased lumberjacks and use the Healing Poultice on them.
I need to seek out and slay 6  of the undead wolves roaming the area north of the Mill.
I killed six of the beasts plaguing the Lumber Mill. They did not die easily, and are clearly unnatural in origin.
I killed the leader of these undead wolves, Necanis. It's time to return to Foreman Maston and report my success.
I need to use the Bear Carcass on the Wolf Dens north of the camp to lure out and destroy Necanis, the leader of these loathsome creatures.
Drugo's courier has asked me to go to Camlorn and warn King Sebastien of the plot to assassinate King Ranser.
Drugo's courier tells me to go to Camlorn and warn King Sebastien of the plot to assassinate King Ranser.
I arrived too late. Judging from the chaos in King Sebastien's manse, Ranser has already been assassinated. I need speak to someone in authority regarding the note I found on the Reachmage.
Oron, an emissary of High King Fahara'jad, is trying to find King Ranser's murderer. I must speak to Oron to learn all I can about the circumstances of Ranser's death.

I've obtained both the Chalice of Gwedrun from Inquisitor Danain and the Soulstone of Brall from Jes of Wayrest. I should return them to High Priest Canning in Camlorn's temple so he can summon Ranser's spirit and reveal the murderer.

High Priest Canning needs two relics to summon Ranser's spirit, the Chalice of Gwedrun and the Soulstone of Brall. Once I acquire both relics and return those relics to him, we can complete a ceremony to summon Ranser's spirit.
While collecting Jes' weapon crates, the leader of the bandits confronted me and attacked, swearing he had a deal with Jes.
I've found a body in the sea beneath Camlorn's docks which seems to be Orator Dalomar. I should return to Jes with this news.
Jes asked me to check on his associates in Camlorn. I will find the first, Bovie, in the lower town near the tavern.
I took a Tattered Document from the body near the water. It is addressed to Claudette Franiellie, I should look for her in Camlorn.
I've completed the patrol route set for me by Inquisitor Danain. Captain Bieller said Danain would meet me on Camlorn's docks, so I should look for Danain there.
I've agreed to patrol Camlorn on behalf of the Magis Order. Inquisitor Danain has sent me to Captain Bieller to join the city patrol.

As the first step of my patrol, Captain Bieller asked me to visit Camlorn's temple. He is worried that citizens blame the Order of Arkay for the rise of undead in Northmoor, and wants me to run off any who threaten the priests.

As Captain Bieller feared, I arrived at the temple to find angry citizens accosting the priests of Arkay. They are angered by the rise of undead throughout Northmoor. I should do what I can to calm the citizens.

As the second step on my patrol, Captain Bieller asked me to enter Camlorn's tavern, in the lower city on the shore. Bieller is worried about too much drink leading to fights, and needs me to keep the peace.
No sooner had I entered Camlorn's tavern when I heard shouting among its patrons. Two men lost in their cups are yelling at each other. I must resolve the situation before it starts a brawl.
As the last step on my patrol, Captain Bieller asked me to patrol the Camlorn docks and reassure the merchants there the Magis Order still watches over them.
I arrived at the docks just in time to witness a theft from a dock merchant. A thief sprinted out of a stall, attempting to escape with stolen goods.
I retrieved Masolaude's valuables from the Bandit Camp. I should return them to him immediately.
I need to find the Bandit Camp east of the Caravan Road and retrieve Masolaude's belongings.
I must take the Chalice of Gwedrun to High Priest Canning in Camlorn's temple, in the upper city next to Sebastian's manse.
I must take the Soulstone of Brall to High Priest Canning in Camlorn's temple, next to Sebastian's manse.
I need to travel to the Lumber Camp south of Camlorn and speak to Foreman Maston to assess their situation.
I need to return to Brigitte in Camlorn to let her know I've killed the bandits.
I need to track down and kill 5 bandits.  They seem to roam the woods east of Camlorn.
High Priest Canning is going to attempt to raise Ranser's spirit using the power of the artifacts I've gathered. I must ensure he is not interrupted.
I should speak with High Priest Canning to see if he needs anything else for the ritual.
When High Priest Canning attempted to summon Ranser's spirit, a hooded figure appeared and attacked. The fiend stunned Canning and disrupted the ritual. I must make sure Canning is all right.
Jes asked me to check on some of his associates throughout Camlorn. Bovie is safe. I should look for the second, Simine, in Camlorn's northern residential district.
Orator Dalomar is missing from his stand on the docks. I should ask around on the docks to see if anyone knows where Dalomar might be.
Jes asked me to check on his associates throughout Camlorn. Simine and Bovie are safe. I should look for the last orator, Dalomar, down on Camlorn's docks.
I need to find three Defiled Burial Mounds and cleanse them by planting the Blessed Banners of the Magis Order at their summits. Hopefully I won't anger any spirits in the process.
I planted the banner, but it did not go unnoticed. I must slay the undead riled by the rite.
I need to find two Defiled Burial Mounds and cleanse them by planting the Blessed Banners of the Magis Order at their summits. Hopefully I won't anger any spirits in the process.
I need to return to Commander Blarae and give him the good news.

I should stop the thief attempting to escape from the docks with stolen goods.
After I stopped the thief, the Magis Order appeared and took him away.
I need to find three Defiled Burial Mounds and cleanse them by planting the Blessed Banners of the Magis Order at their summits. Hopefully I won't anger any spirits in the process.
I need to find two Defiled Burial Mounds and cleanse them by planting the Blessed Banners of the Magis Order at their summits. Hopefully I won't anger any spirits in the process.
I need to find one Defiled Burial Mound and cleanse it by planting a Blessed Banners of the Magis Order at its summit. Hopefully I won't anger any spirits in the process.
King Sebastian asked me to speak with Oron Nassir, emissary to the High King. I'll find Oron in Sebastian's manse.
I must go to the temple outside King Sebastien's manse and speak with High Priest Canning about raising Ranser's spirit.

High Priest Canning needs two relics to summon Ranser's spirit. Inquisitor Danain at the barracks beside Sebastien's manse has one of them. I should speak to Danain about acquiring the Chalice of Gwedrun.
High Priest Canning needs two relics to summon Ranser's spirit. Jes of Wayrest in Camlorn's tavern has one. I should speak to Jes about acquiring the Soulstone of Brall.
High Priest Canning is ready to begin the ritual. I should light the Holy Incense Burner in the Camlorn temple when I'm ready to protect him during the ritual.
I must go to the temple outside King Sebastien's manse and speak with High Priest Canning about raising Ranser's spirit.
Jes asked me to check on his associates in Camlorn. I will find the first, Bovie, in the lower town near the tavern.
Jes asked me to check on some of his associates throughout Camlorn. Bovie is safe. I should look for the second, Simine, in Camlorn's northern residential district.
Vorgo Emeric is dead at my hand. I must return to Watcher Emeric and inform him.
I need to track down and kill the bandit leader Vorgo, the Red Rook.
I have given four Dark Acolytes over to the spirits of Glaes Maar. I should inform Claude.
I need to leash four Dark Acolytes with the Crystalwan and bring them to the Altar of Glaes Maar.
The Spirits of Glaes Maar are destroying the Dark Acolyte!

High Priest Canning will exorcise any spirits that remain in Camlorn. He told me to seek out Commander Blarae at the northern Redoubt and enlist his help to find Ranser's body and recover it from the hooded figure that attacked us.

When I exorcised one citizen, the fiend taunted me and hinted that Ranser's Body would soon pass through something called Thrandor's Portal.nnPerhaps High Priest Canning knows what it meant - I must tell him of this.

I should look in the hills near the redoubt camp for Coren's spirit. Once I find her, I must slay her.
Return the Locket to Captain Geves
Coren's spirit left behind a locket Blanche gave her. I should return it, along with the news that I've sent Coren to her final rest.
I must locate four of the Third Squad's missing soldiers.
Captain Geves will be expecting my return.

Undead are attacking the Redoubt- I fear High Priest Canning's failed ritual unleashed an undead horde.  I must kill as many of the dead as I can, and rally the Magis Order troops by fighting beside them to repel the assault and save Camlorn.
The undead siege has diminished, and the Redoubt defenders fight with renewed vigor. I should return to Inquisitor Blarae at the Redoubt.
I must locate four of the Third Squad's missing soldiers.
I must locate four of the Third Squad's missing soldiers.
I must locate four of the Third Squad's missing soldiers.

Inquisitor Blarae said I would find Thrandor's Portal southeast of the Redoubt, among ancient ruins. If I hurry to the portal I can stop Morholdt from opening it and throwing Ranser's body into Oblivion.

I arrived at the ruins to find Morholdt in the midst of a dark ritual, assisted by acolytes who are magically protecting him. I should slay the acolytes to remove Morholdt's protection, then slay Morholdt.
I've slain Morholdt, but King Ranser's body is gone. I should search his body for any clues that may help me recover the slain king's corpse.
I found a note on Morholdt's body, but it's written in a language I cannot read. Oron has joined me at the ruins - I should speak to him regarding the note.
Oron asked me to journey to the town of Grayborne, east of Camlorn, and speak to a man there, Constable Brennoc, about the Bloodstone mentioned in Morholdt's note.
I've killed a number of goblins. I should return and speak to Questgiver.
I'm to kill goblins and then return to Questgiver.
Constable Brennoc told me that Wyress Jacinta, part of the Beldama Wyrd, is tending Varic, a wounded man from Shornhelm, in a house on the edge of Grayborne. I should speak to Jacinta about Varic.
Wyress Jacinta asked me to go to Thetis in her stead and ask for his help cleaning the polluted lake. I should look for Thetis at his house south of Grayborne.
There are unfinished Defensive Barricades in the river that flows out of the Fane of Breath to the southwest. I must use Vendialara's Defensive Netting on a Barricade.
There are unfinished Defensive Barricades in the river that flows out of the Fane of Breath to the southwest. I must use Vendialara's Defensive Netting on a second Barricade.
I've completed contruction of several barricades. I should return to tell High Priestess Vendialara at the Fane of Breath.
Thetis asked me to search the lake edge for traces of whatever the goblins used to move their poison to the lake.
I've found a barrel containing a trace of noxious smelling sludge - this must be what the goblins are dumping in the lake. I should return the sludge to Thetis so he can examine it.
I need to locate Michael Herbert in Westtry.
Michael Herbert was attacked by Spectres, but I was able to rescue him.
I need to return toThetis the Poisoner.
I need to scare the goblins from Thetis's garden by killing some of them.
Thetis asked that I collect Blood Nettle from around the lake, and slay goblins to collect their bone necklaces. While I complete this task, he'll mix the remedy to purify the lake.
I've collected Blood Nettle and goblin bone necklaces as Thetis asked. I should return these ingredients to Thetis.
Thetis asked that I journey to a spongy island at the center of the lake and pour his remedy into it - he believes the island will allow the remedy to seep into the lake at a safe rate.
Thetis asked that I journey to a spongy island at the center of the lake and pour his remedy into it - he believes the island will allow the remedy to seep into the lake at a safe rate.
I've slain the corrupted lake monster and started the purification of the lake as Thetis asked. I should return to Thetis and see if we must do anything else.
In an abandoned home to the north of the Wyrd tree, I must light a fire in the fireplace to drive out the goblins.
I must return to Wyress Shaelle to tell her I frightened the goblins.
In exchange for his help, Thetis asked I deliver a note to Wyress Jacinta on his behalf. I'll find Jacinta in Grayborne, tending to Varic Aston.
As the first step in purifying the Wyrd Tree, Wyress Jacinta said I must slay the maddened Spriggans around the tree, southeast of Grayborne, and gather their sap.

I've collected Spriggan sap from slain Spriggans. Jacinta told me that once I had done so, I should enter the Wyrd Tree and mix the sap in the Scrying Well inside. This should draw out the evil spirit infesting the tree.

I've collected Spriggan sap from slain Spriggans. Jacinta told me that once I had done so, I should enter the Wyrd Tree and mix the sap in the Scrying Well inside. This should draw out the evil spirit infesting the tree.

I've slain the corrupting spirit that had infested and weakened the Wyrd Tree. It seems that Wyress Jacinta and her sisters have arrived during the struggle - I should speak to Wyress Jacinta just outside the Wyrd Tree.
Wyress Jacinta wants me to charm a wolf to help find the imposter amongst the Wyrd. I can use the whistle to charm any Daenia Pack Wolf wondering out in the woods.
I found the imposter, a hag disguised as one of the Beldama Wyrd. I should return to Wyress Jacinta and tell her what I've found.
There are unfinished Defensive Barricades in the river that flows out of the Fane of Breath to the southwest. I must use Vendialara's Defensive Netting on a third Barricade.
Wyress Jacinta has used her power to draw Varic from his healing slumber, and he will live. I should speak to Varic and see if he knows anything about King Ranser's murder, or the Bloodstone.
Varic said King Ranser's most valued possession was his Bloodstone. He also implied Ranser was murdered by something called 'The Shrouded Throne'. I should see if Jacinta recognizes the name.

Wyress Jacinta asked me to journey to Westtry and seek out another witch of the Beldama Wyrd - Wyress Zoe. She believes that our mutual enemy, the One Who Hungers, serves the Shrouded Throne - and I may find out more about it in Westtry.

Wyress Jacinta asked me to exorcise Westtry's Spectres and gather Spiritual Essences. Westtry's Spectres are infused with the power of the One Who Hungers, and Zoe can use that connection to rip the One Who Hungers from the shadows.
I have collected the Spiritual Essences Zoe requested. I should return to her and see what we can do about the One Who Hungers.

Wyress Zoe said that when I'm ready, I'm to place the Spiritual Essences I gathered in the fire at the center of their witches circle. This will allow them to draw the One Who Hungers from the shadows - when they do, I must exorcise it.

After the Beldama Wyrd summoned the One Who Hungers, I vanquished it, but it offered no clues as to its master. I should speak to Zoe and see if she knows anything else about the reasons the evil spirit was here.
When I arrived at Aldcroft, I found the town in an agitated state. Wyress Adele said Oron is staying upstairs in Aldcroft's inn I should speak to him.
Wyress Zoe suggested I speak to Wyress Adele, at Aldcroft's inn, about the shadow prowling Wesstry. I should journey northwest to Aldcroft.
Mirelle's ghost has sent me to find her locket, which the goblins stole.nnI should kill as many goblins as it takes to find it.
Now that I've recovered the locket, I should take it to Mirielle's sister at the "big tree," which is probably the tree of the Beldama Wyrd.
Now that I have charmed a wolf, I should proceed back to the Wyrd Tree and investigate the Wyrd guarding the tree. The wolf will sniff them out and find the imposter.
Mari Viralaine will be glad to hear that I've returned her parents' ashes to their home.
I need to place an urn of ashes in what remains of Mari Viralaine's old home in Westtry. The house is on a hillside overlooking the town.

As the first step of my patrol, Captain Bieller asked me to visit Camlorn's temple. He is worried that citizens blame the Order of Arkay for the rise of undead in Northmoor, and wants me to run off any who threaten the priests.

Thetis asked that I look for a sample of the original poison the goblins used in the lake in a goblin camp south of the lake. I should return the sample to him.
I've collected a sample of the original goblin poison, as Thetis asked. I should return the poison to Thetis.
As I've gathered the Blood Nettle Flowers, I should give them to Thetis the Poisoner on behalf of Melusine Darte.
Thetis the Poisoner's home is evidently surrounded by these flowers. I hope I'm not allergic to them, too.
I can either kill the Chieftain with assistance, or first poison his guards via the Forest Rabbits, then slay him by myself.
Thetis will be pleased to hear of my success.
I should return to Wyress Jacinta with the news.
Shava asked me to speak with Constable Baird inside Shava's home and grant her a dying wish.
Oron asked that I speak to Brennoc Hursh, by Grayborne's inn, to find out more about Ranser's manservant and the situation in Grayborne.
I am to report the news of Orator Dalomar's death to his wife.nnTheir house is near the Camlorn docks; there are often orators speaking right outside.
I've gotten the purse, but it was empty of gold.  nnWhat I did find was dice, and a debtor's slip.  It seems as likely he was killed for his gambling debts as his political convictions.
We've released a Spirit from within the chest of drawers. I'll need to deal with it so that Michael and get whatever it is he needs from them.
Lady Dalomar seemed less than upset about her husband's demise.nnShe asked me to retrieve his coin purse from the body.
I must find four diseased lumberjacks and use the Healing Poultice on them.
The Starglass Bell should be placed on Mara's Altar to begin the ritual.
The ritual has concluded. I should speak to Vendialara.
The incense has been lit, but it won't burn for long. I must quickly light each of the Divine candles before the incense burns out.
I need to combine the Porous Cloth, the Witchroot, and the Aldwort to create the poultice.
I've destroyed the Maormer supplies. I should report to Exultant Eador at the Harmonium Fortress on the southern coast of Isque.
I need to destroy Weapon Racks near the heavily defended center of Sunhold Island, and burn Supply Crates on the southern docks. The island lies off the southern coast of Isque.
QA Quest NPC wants you to touch the nearby flag.
I should return to Ranger Lord Merin and report my culling of Silvermist Castle's undead.
I should bring the Silvermist Keepsakes to Cleric Sellan, in the Ashen Order camp near the entrance to Silvermist Castle.
No sooner had I entered Camlorn's tavern when I heard shouting among its patrons. Two men lost in their cups are yelling at each other. I must resolve the situation before it starts a brawl.

As the second step on my patrol, Captain Bieller asked me to enter Camlorn's tavern, in the lower city on the shore. Bieller is worried about too much drink leading to fights, and needs me to keep the peace.
As the last step on my patrol, Captain Bieller asked me to patrol the Camlorn docks and reassure the merchants there the Magis Order still watches over them.
I arrived at the docks just in time to witness a theft from a dock merchant. A thief sprinted out of a stall, attempting to escape with stolen goods.
I've completed the patrol route set for me by Inquisitor Danain. Captain Bieller said Danain would meet me on Camlorn's docks, so I should look for Danain there.

As the first step of my patrol, Captain Bieller asked me to visit Camlorn's temple. He is worried that citizens blame the Order of Arkay for the rise of undead in Northmoor, and wants me to run off any who threaten the priests.

As Captain Bieller feared, I arrived at the temple to find angry citizens accosting the priests of Arkay. They are angered by the rise of undead throughout Northmoor. I should do what I can to calm the citizens.
I've agreed to patrol Camlorn on behalf of the Magis Order. Inquisitor Danain has sent me to Captain Bieller to join the city patrol.

As the first step of my patrol, Captain Bieller asked me to visit Camlorn's temple. He is worried that citizens blame the Order of Arkay for the rise of undead in Northmoor, and wants me to run off any who threaten the priests.

As the first step of my patrol, Captain Bieller asked me to visit Camlorn's temple. He is worried that citizens blame the Order of Arkay for the rise of undead in Northmoor, and wants me to run off any who threaten the priests.
I have been directed to speak with the spirit of Princess Aurais, the late daughter of the Silvermist family. I am told she is just inside the castle keep.
Having obtained the blessing and returned from the spirit world, I should return to Cleric Sellan.
Now that I am in the spirit world, I will need to find my bearings. There should be a soul nearby that I can speak with.
The blessed chain was not enough to bind the vampire within the crypt. I will need to destroy it, now that it is free.
Cleric Sellan wants me to speak with Ranger Lord Merin, so that he can determine the Gravebinders' next course of action.
I should speak with Cleric Sellan. He will want to know of the vampire, and of its worrying report of more powerful evil here.
I have a note to deliver to Forester Mannis in Camlorn.
Princess Aurais is the perfect person to give me the blessing I need. I should ask her if she will grant it to me, so that I can free her spirit from this place.
The forester Selene Brehat has sent me to check the local game for poachers' arrows.nnShe thinks the poachers may be to the northeast of the foresters' camp.

The poacher admitted the arrows are his.nnNow I must decide whether to let him go with a warning or issue him a warrant.  If I give him the warrant, he will have to report to the foresters immediately or be considered a fugitive.
I spoke to the poacher, and chose to give him a warrant.  He must report to the foresters or be considered a fugitive.
I spoke to the poacher, and chose to let him go with a warning.  They should use better practices but everyone has to eat.
Vivienne asked me to find her husband, who must be a spirit as well. I should search for Tomas near Westtry's abandoned barn.

Tomas Atois was murdered by feuding soldiers who overran Westtry. His spirit will not return to his wife, Vivienne, until he finds her missing locket.nnTomas believes the locket may be lost somewhere in the abandoned town of Westtry.
I've found the missing locket belonging to Tomas' wife, Vivienne, in an abandoned house in Westtry. I should return the locket to Tomas in Westtry's old barn.
Tomas is finally ready to return to his wife. He asked me to visit their house before leaving. He and Vivienne will be waiting for me there.
I should give Lord Alain the harpy feathers I've collected.
Lord Alain wants to make fishing lures from harpy feathers. He asked me to gather some. I suspect I'll find harpies and their nests on the rocky hillside near the shore.
Squire Maddoc offered to pay me for any harpy eggs I find. The most likely place to find an egg would be in a harpy's nest, hidden in the high caves along Glenumbra's western coast.
I've collected several harpy eggs. With any luck, one of them will hatch. If I return the eggs to Squire Maddoc east of the cliffs, he'll pay me for my trouble.
The spirit of Claire Lirlane asked me to destroy the spirits of Bealton raiders and Gradwyn warriors so she may rest avenged.

I have destroyed many spectres of the soldiers who destroyed Westtry and killed Claire Lirlane. The burden on her spirit may be eased by this news.nnI will find her in the ruins of her small house in Westtry.
Vivienne's spirit asked me to take her locket to her granddaughter, Colette Atois. She lives in Aldcroft, a large coastal town east of Westtry.
I've collected tools for Alphonse. I should return them to him.
I need to collect the tools the rootlings scattered.  nnThey're in the forest northeast of Daggerfall, strewn to either side of the road.

Now that I've helped the Beldama Wyrd reclaim their tree, Wyress Zoe suggested I travel to Aldcroft and consult with Lord Magister Averos. As the leader of the Lion Guard, he might be able to help me face a larger threat: Angof, the Reachmage.
Adelle asked me to kill goblins, cut out their hearts, and bring them to her. She claims she can make the goblins hate each other as much as they hate us.
I've collected goblin hearts for Wyress Adelle. She's eager to cast her spell on the goblins. She's waiting for me in a narrow valley in central Daenia.
If I quell the Corrupted Wyrd Saplings scattered around the Wyrd Tree, then plant a seed in the earth while they are quelled, I can free the glen around the Wyrd Tree of corruption.
I purified the Corrupted Wyrd Saplings that took root in the soil beneath the Wyrd Tree. Wyress Zoe, who is waiting at the entrance to the Wyrd tree, will be glad to hear of this.

Ormax has asked me to take tools to his foremen:nnFrizkav is to the north, on the far side of large stacks of lumber.nnMichelle is in a large clearing slightly to the northwest.nnPierre is northwest of Deleyn's Mill, just across the road.
I delivered the foresters' tools as Ormax Maitrenance in Deleyn's Mill asked. He'll want to know the foresters are back at work again.

Laure gave me a charm to use on the trained wolves that goblin hunters keep as pets. She said the charm would free a trained wolf and turn it against its goblin master.nnShe wants me kill the goblin hunters and set the wolves free.

I've used Laure's charm to turn trained wolf pets against the goblin hunters who enslaved them. I've killed the goblins and set the wolves free.nnWyress Laure is waiting along the road north of the Wyrd Camp. She'll be eager for this news.
Ileana asked me to kill spriggans around the Dresan Ruins and collect their limbs. She says that by gathering the limbs, we can summon spriggan spirits.
I've collected spriggan limbs, just as Wyress Ileana requested. I'm returning the limbs to her at the entrance to the Dresan Ruins, so we can use them to summon a spriggan spirit.
Danain tells me the Chalice is in the nearby Magis Order barracks. He'll give it to me if I prove myself to him by either assisting him with his patrol or dealing with some wraiths out by the ruins.
Ask Danain about the Soul Cage
I must return the Chalice of Gwedrun to Canning. He cautions me that if I am slain while I carry it, the Magis Order will retrieve it through mystical means, and I'll be back to square one.
I must journey to the ruins and fight the wraiths there. Once the wraiths are weakened, I must use the Soul Cage Danain gave me to capture their essence, ensuring they will plague Camlorn no longer.
Tell Danain you've done his chore.
Tell Danain you've done his chore.
Wyress Paulette asked me to prune withered hawthorns throughout the forests of Daenia and collect their seeds.
With enough hawthorn seeds, Wyress Paulette can replace the plants that have withered away completely.nnShe'll be waiting for the seeds in central Daenia.
I must reduce the number of Noxious Nereids along the banks of the Liriel River, east of the Isque Kinhouse.
Melodian Liriondion can be found in the main hall of the Isque Kinhouse.nnI have reduced the number of Noxious Nereids. Liriondion should be notified.
Ashtah asked me to burn all the goblin idols I can find in the groves of Daenia.nnShe also warned me to be wary of goblins. If they see me burning their idols, they'll gather and attack.
I've burned goblin idols in the forest, discouraging the goblins from invading Daenia. Wyress Ashtah will be pleased to hear this.
The Wyress Alene has sent me with the spriggan limbs and some oil to a brush pile near the camp, somewhere along the rocks to the north.nnBurning the limbs may enrage the Great Elum, if it appears.

Ileana asked me to light an ancient brazier in the ruins. The Wyrd once used it to summon the forest spirits. I should speak to any spirits that appear.nnShe hopes this will shed some light on the reasons behind the spriggan uprising.

Bloodthorn adepts are summoning corrupting vines all over Glenumbra. They'll kill spriggan trees and drive the spriggans mad. Now I know why the spriggans are so aggressive.nnAs Ileana asked, I should speak to Wyress Jacinta at her camp to the west.

Zoe asked me to enter the great Wyrd Tree. The power of the spirits flows through me, and now I must channel it into the Sigil of the Wyrd Tree.nnThis should draw out Angof's minion. Once I slay it, the Wyrd Tree will be free of corruption.
I've slain the corrupting spirit that infested and weakened the Wyrd Tree. Wyress Zoe waits for me beside the tree. She'll be grateful to hear of my success.
Kinlord Maldarawo is in the Isquer Kinhouse, south of the Fane of Breath. I have agreed to deliver the Blessed Bell to him on behalf of High Priestess Vendialara.

Janett warned me that Rock Biter goblins poisoned the streams leading to the Wyrd Tree. Now they're poisoning the stream that leads past Westtry to Aldcroft.nnIf I want to save Aldcroft from poison, I'll have to stop the goblins.

I've destoyed the barrels of poison the Rock Biter goblins were pouring into the stream to Aldcroft. nnI should see if Wyress Janett has any other advice. She's waiting in a small rock valley west of the stream,
Sebastian the Fletcher indicated that the arrows in the deer probably belong to Felix Glenan, who is camped on the eastern shore to the north of the foresters' camp.nnHopefully Glenan can explain.
Warden Mallery asked that I go into the swamp southwest of Aldcroft and fight alongside the Aldcroft Deputy. We are to slay threats to the refugee camp - Corrupted Bog Lurchers and Will-O-the-Wisps.

I've slain a number of monsters alongside the Aldcroft Deputy, enough to give the deputy some real experience in fighting such threats. Warden Rielle, at the refugee camp south of Aldcroft, will be glad to hear of our success.

Warden Rielle asked me to speak to Warden Mallery, at the Aldcroft refugee camp, about taking a deputy under my wing. Through example, I'm to teach the deputy how to fight the monsters that threaten Aldcroft.
Wyress Jacinta asked that I go north of the Wyrd's temporary camp in the forest and look for Wyress Gwen. I'll find her at a ritual site marked by large standing stones.

Wyress Gwen wants to sacrifice a lurcher to appease the spirits of the land. She asked for my help.nnI now have a powerful charm. The wyress asked me to slay a lurcher, use her charm to reanimate it, and then bring it to her at the ritual site.

Wyress Gwen wants to show the spirits of the land that the Beldama Wyrd are fighting the forest's corruption.nnI've reanimated a lurcher with Gwen's charm. If I can bring it back to Wyress Gwen at the ritual site, she'll sacrifice it there.

When I returned to the ritual site with a lurcher, Wyress Gwen sacrificed it to appease the spirits of the land.nnThe spirits have appeared before us. If I speak to them, I may find out more about the corruption plaguing High Rock.
I spoke with the spirits of the land. I learned much of the corruption plaguing Glenumbra, but the details still elude me.nnPerhaps Wyress Gwen will understand of the words of the spirits.
I've found several arrows that do not bear the Daggerfall mark in the bodies of hunted deer in the forest.nnSebastian Nicostratus, the fletcher at the foresters' camp, may know whose these are.
Lord Magister Averos informed me that werewolves that overran Camlorn from within now threaten Aldcroft from the north. If someone does not slay them, Aldcroft may fall.
I have slain Prowling Werewolves who threatened Aldcroft from the north. Lord Magister Averos, waiting in Aldcroft's main square, will be glad to hear this news.
Maston tells me that Necanis lurks in a wolf den nearby. I must slay one of the forest bears and collect its corpse for use as bait. Once I've done that, I can use the carcass to draw Necanis out.

Chamberlain Weller ordered a shipment of silk sheets from Wayrest that have yet to arrive. He suggested I look for the Wayrest courier who was transporting the sheets along the road north of Aldcroft.

There is a band of brigands or pirates that has set up shop on the eastern Aldcroft Docks.  I may find looted goods there; hopefully the Chamberlain's sheets included.nnThe Chamberlain's servant, Beaure, may know more.
I've recovered several sets of folded silk bedsheets from crates Astrid's Lot had looted and stored.  Though a bit worse for wear, they should still suit Chamberlain Weller and his staff.

Aldridge asked me to find the bodies of the recently deceased in Glenumbra so I can focus a magical item on them: a Remembrance Crystal. The crystal records the names of the fallen and burns their bodies, so they can't be raised as undead.

I've chronicled the names of those who died in High Rock's violence and cremated them. The spirits of those I saved spoke of corruption in tarn.nnFather Aldridge is waiting at the Wayshrine west of Camlorn. Perhaps I should ask him about this.
The Alchemist Shava, Sibellec's apprentice, sent me to harvest rare ingredients from the Bog Lurchers.nnBog Lurchers can be found all around the swamp north of Sibellec's home.
Alchemist Shava is awaiting these Bog Lurcher materials at Sibellec's home in the swamp.
I must journey northwards into the swamp to find Sibellec and request aid on behalf of Aldcroft.
I've need to convince Sibellec to focus on distracting the swamp's inhabitants so that the Magis Order will be free to rescue Camlorn.
I will need to kill several Bog Lurchers and then make my way to the northern end of the swamp to meet with Sibellec's Familiar.
I've killed several Bog Lurchers. I should head to the northern part of the swamp for further information on how I can help Sibellec win back her home.
I must collect the Chalice of Gwedrun from the Magis Order. Danain may grant it to me if I assist him, or there may be another way
Sibellec claims she can use Cinnabar Yellow Caps to help us locate Raven Direnni's lost Ehlnofic Lens. Cinnabar Yellow Cap mushrooms grow in the swamp around Sibellec's hovel.
I've gathered a number of Cinnabar Yellow Caps for Sibellec. I'll find her at her hovel north of Aldcroft.
Kill Mud-cloaked Hags to obtain their Mud-encrused Amulets.
Sibellec's Familiar awaits me near the northern end of the swamp. I will take her this unusual Thorn that I found in the Mud-cloaked Hags' dens.
Tell Danain you've done his chore.
Alchemist Shava has asked me to get Mandrake Roots, which can be found in the swamps to the north and northwest of Sibillec's hut.
I've collected the Mandrake Root, and should now return to the Alchemist Shava.
I was sent from Aldcroft to find the Alchemist Thetis somewhere northeast of Aldcroft near a lake.

Coty told me to enter the hole between past and present. I must exit his tomb to do so.nnCoty will guide me with whispers. Together, we will find the thief who stole the sword Werereaver and recover it.

When I exited Coty's tomb, I stepped through a portal into a pocket realm of Oblivion. I stand now in an echo of the Battle of Glenumbra Moors.nnAiden Direnni led Coty's allies. Speaking to him may yield information about the Ehlnofic Lens.

When I exited Coty's tomb, I stepped into an epic from the First Age: the Battle of Glenumbra Moors.nnCoty asked me to aid the Direnni and kill the Alessian Order's soldiers. If they overrun the Direnni camp, we may never find the thief.
Aiden Direnni requested I speak with his cousin, Raven. He said she's been expecting me. Perhaps she can tell me more about Werereaver.

I now know where Raven Direnni went after the Battle of Glenumbra Moors - a place called the Cave of Penance. Perhaps Averos will know more about it.nnI am now fully aware this is a dream. I can wake from it by speaking to Raven Direnni.

Raven Direnni said she could feel a connection to every weapon she's ever made with her magic, including the Werereaver. She knows the thief is hiding in the Cave of Penance.nnShe said to ask Coty about it. Perhaps he'll know more.
Sibellec needs to see the Unusual Thorn with her own eyes in order to better identify it. She awaits me at her house in the southern end of the swamp.
Sibellec recognizes the Reach magic within this Unusual Thorn as coming from Angof, a powerful Reach Mage.
Sibellec's Familiar asked me to retrieve the Ehlnofic Lens from deep within the Cave of Penance on the western shore of the Corrupted Lake.
When I recovered Werereaver from Angof's assassin, the spirit of Raven Direnni appeared to me. I should speak to her about her artifact.
Eidene asked me to look in the forest to the west for a wild boar that has enthralled all of their missing sows, and kill it so the sows will return home.
I've slain the wild boar that had drawn off all of Eidene's sows. Eidene, who is waiting at the trapper's camp, will be glad to hear of this.
I must speak to Kerry Bladespire in order to find out the thing that haunts the realm of the dead, and find a way to stop it.
Benendare calls to me now that we've both entered this dark realm. I should speak to him at once and let him know I am ready.
Sly has informed me that I must  enter the spirit realm. He will send me into it and I must seek out Benendare for assistance.
The last of the statues is destroyed and we must now escape the spirit world! We will need to return to the entry point upon the hill where the Bloody Eye camp is located.
I must find a watcher in Camlorn and present them with proof of Corbeau's demise.
It's likely Corbeau was a wanted man. I should present the Watchers in Camlorn with proof of his demise.
I let Felix Glenan go with a warning, and he was grateful for the mercy.  He sent me to his wife for some hot stew before I move on.
<<1>> asked me to enter Eagle's Brook, just west of Camlorn. He wants me to kill any Red Rook Bandits I find and burn their corpse carts.
I've burned the bodies the Red Rook bandits stole, and I killed anyone who tried to stop me. <<1>>, waiting just south of Eagle's Brook, promised to reward me for my work.

After giving the ring back to Didier Panoit, he mentioned that Warden Moreau might have a 'reward' for me. I should talk to Warden Moreau to see what Panoit meant. I believe he is standing guard outside the forester camp.
<<1>> asked me to slay the undead wolves west of their camp. The wolves are plaguing the Lion Guard soldiers encamped below Camlorn, forcing them to split their forces.
I've slain many of the undead wolves harassing the Lion Guard from the west. Knight Adept Elbert is waiting for me at the Lion Guard camp below Camlorn. He'll be glad to hear of this.
Kinlord Langdruun has requested I speak with his emissary, Telenger, at the Deadsands about the recent undead activity along the shoreline.
Kinlord Langdruun has requested I speak with his emissary, Telenger, at the Deadsands about the recent undead activity along the shoreline.
If I collect 5 samples of Zombie Ichor and bring them to Telenger, he may be able to determine the source of the scourge.
Marie suggested that if I want to hurt Hircine and the werewolves in Camlorn, I must shatter every cauldron I find in the city.

The werewolves in Camlorn guard their cauldrons fiercely - and a strange voice whispers in my head after I shatter them. Hircine, Daedric Prince of the Hunt, is known to be the progenitor of lycanthropy... could he be involved?

The strange voice whispered to me again when I shattered the Temple Cauldron, warning of dire consequences if I continue. If I am to shatter the last cauldron in Camlorn, in the Royal District, I should be on my guard.

I've shattered Hircine's cauldrons throughout Camlorn, decreasing the strength of General Faolchu's werewolf army.nnMarie told me to seek out a nightblade named Ashby at the redoubt. Perhaps she can tell me more about Marie and her curse.
Thetis gave me four potions to test on undead wolves. To test each potion, I'll have to toss it at a wolf... and see what happens.

I've tested all of Thetis' potions. Only the redwort potion successfully killed an undead wolf. I should let Thetis know what I've discovered.nnThetis is waiting at his tent on the southern end of the Cambray Tarn.

Coty said I could find the Cave of Penance by exiting the ancient battle site on its west side, then following the road west. He believes the Werereaver and its thief to be inside.nnCoty wants me to recover the Werereaver and use it against Faolchu.
This ring must have an owner around here. I should look around.
I need to return the ring to its rightful owner.
I spoke to a resident at the foresters camp about the ring and they directed me to Warden Thierry, who guards the camp at the West entrance from Daggerfall.

Before he died, the Magis Order Nightblade placed beacons in the Residential District, Temple District, and Royal District of Camlorn.nnI do not know what purpose the beacons serve, but if the Magis Order uses them, activating them could be useful.
The safest place for a beacon in Camlorn's temple district might be inside the temple itself. Placing a beacon there would expand the Magis Order's view of the city.
The last beacon would work best in Camlorn's Royal District, allowing the Magis Order net to encompass the entire city. The small park in the Royal District is probably the safest spot to place it.

When I activated the last beacon, a Projection of Magus Commander Danain appeared by the beacon. It seems to be some sort of magical communication method.nnIf I wish to find our more, I should speak to Danain.
Thetis gave me a large vial of redwort potion. I'm looking for thorny vines on the borders of the tarn. If I saturate them with the potion, Thetis believes that will start the cleansing of the tarn.
I have used Thetis' redwort potion to cleanse corruption from the vines around the tarn. Thetis will be pleased to hear of my success. I'll find him at his tent on the south side of the Cambray Tarn.

Magus Commander Danain asked me to use his focusing gem on any Werewolf Behemoths I come across. The Magis Order can use the magic of the gem to drop a fireball on the Behemoth, making it easier to kill.

Many Werewolf Behemoths are dead, and Magus Commander Danain's forces should now be able to invade Camlorn with far less severe losses. Danain will be glad to hear of this - I'll find him at the Magis Order camp below Camlorn.
I'll need to investigate the debris within the Mud-cloaked Hags' Dens to see if there are any clues that would explain their sudden change.
I must quickly use a Channeling Pedestal at the forge in order to place a Shattered Crown piece and channel its magical energy.
The forging has been foiled by my performance. I should speak with Sinderon so that we may attempt the process again.
Warden Rielle has sent me into the marshes west of Aldcroft to find and kill Will-O-the-Wisps.
I've killed Will-O-the-Wisps. Warden Rielle in Aldcroft will want to know that I rid the marshes of a number of these strange and eerie threats.
I must quickly use a Channeling Pedestal at the forge in order to place a Shattered Crown piece and channel its magical energy.
I must quickly use a Channeling Pedestal at the forge in order to place a Shattered Crown piece and channel its magical energy.
The spirit of Raymond Geotene will be waiting for me near the entry to the Cave of Penance.
The spirit of Raymond Geotene asked me to take his offering to Namira's shrine deep within the Cave of Penance.
While clearing out the spiders, I should see if I can find the cause of the sudden disturbance of the farm. This might possibly help with future infestations.
The Queen spider carried a oddly marked rune that seemed to be shoved into the skin of the beast. I should return to town and see if anyone knows something of these markings.
I've handed the rune over to Belle Kayne, daughter of the Prophet of Alaygon. She needs time to research it, but believes that she has seen the markings somewhere before.

Flanked when least expecting it, I was nearly struck down by the Queen of Dusk, leader of the Duskweb spiders infesting the Camaroot farm. Luckily a smith from Alaygon, Tamarus, came to my aid. I should speak to him to give thanks.
I retrieved an undamaged Varla Lens from Landbreaker. Surely Vartisan Ameralee will be at the Imagerie awaiting my return.
Ameralee has been turned to stone! I should bring the tome to the High Kinlord as soon as possible.

Vartisan Ameralee can be found at the southern entrance of the Imagerie.nnI've recovered Chapter XLVII of the book "Varlines and Vartisans." The information within should allow Ameralee to repair the Var Lens.
Vartisan Ameralee is at the southern entrance of the Imagerie.nnI've recovered the stolen Varla Lens from Hainen. It must be brought to Ameralee for the needed repairs.
Vartisan Ameralee is at the Imagerie.
High Kinlord Langdruun can be found within the Felballin Kinhouse.nnThe Varline Focuser restored Felballin's Varla Lens. The High Kinlord will be pleased to hear the news.
I must seek out Telenger the Artificer at the Deadsands, along the southwestern coast of Varyllis.
I have reduced the number of Drowned Zombies in the area around Liralen.
I found Fulgurite. Telenger awaits it on the bluff overlooking the Deadsands.
I have slain the Sload menacing Varyllis. Telenger waits for news of my success on the bluff above the Deadsands.
I found and destroyed Larva Sacs in the shoals near the Pearls. I should report to Telenger at his camp on the shores of the Deadsands.
High Kinlord Langdruun awaits word of my success at the Felballin Kinhouse.
High Kinlord Langdruun bade me speak with Battlereeve Heldarmo at the Verdant Grove Tower. The tower stands on the verge of the Stonewake to the east.
Battlereeve Heldarmo will want to know of my success. I should return to him at the Verdant Grove Tower.
I've destroyed and buried the souls of five Earth Atronachs. Battlereeve Heldarmo waits for this welcome news at the Guard Tower.
I've collected Dawnshards and must deliver them to Sorceress Andria at the Verdant Grove Tower.
Battlereeve Heldarmo asked me to speak with Melodian Fiannalor to the east of the Stonewake, at Tersicor Collegium.
Battlereeve Nenwe asked me to talk with her once the killing was done.
I am hunting Stormwitches along the Tessellated Shores.
Vartisan Taarifil gave me Imbued Stones to place upon the Quo-Plinths on the Grid.
Taarifil will be relieved to know that the Imbued Stones are in place once again.
I was able to disable the spellfire pillars. I must inform the Thief, at his shrine, of my success.
I should return to the Mage, who waits at his shrine, with the Daedric Soul Gems he requested.
I must return the Orrery's Varla Lens to Vartisan Urselor at the Syldarim Kinhouse.
I must now speak with Kinlady Genivra, in the Syldarim Kinhouse.
I have gathered a pouch of Fire Salt and must return to The Thief in his shrine, southwest of the Syldarim Kinhouse.
I have completed the ritual and must speak to Skyharker Nureva.
I must deliver the Irradiant Jewel to Battlereeve Heldarmo at the Verdant Grove Tower.
I destroyed the Fragment of Orgnavar and collected its debris for The Mage. I should return to him.
The Atronach is repaired. I should speak with it.
I must inform Vartisan Urselor at the Syldarim Kinhouse that the Stormwitch has been slain.
I must inform Skyharker Vilmo that Suuniqwe's wraith has been slain. He waits at the Mage's Shrine.
I must take Skyharker Suuniqwe's journal to Skyharker Vilmo at the Mage's shrine.nnThe books is harming me, it might harm Vilmo.
I need to speak to Vartisan Urselor at the Syldarim Kinhouse about the strange artifact I found on the Serpent.

The General Faolchu mentioned in the note must be the same one Coty Danain fought so many years ago.nnIf I want to help reclaim Camlorn, I should seek out the commander of the Magis Order in the city. I'll find Camlorn east of the Cave of Penance.
The Thief asked me to deactivate the spellfire pillars to the southwest of his shrine.
Find Meteorites north of the Tyrsicor Collegium and collect Meteoric Glass.nnThe Tuneless Discarnates that are there may have some glass as well.
Melodian Fiannalor awaits the Meteoric Glass at the Tyrsicor Collegium.
I must kill a Giant Sea Serpent and claim its heart.
I must take the Serpent's Heart to Battlereeve Nenwe.

Magus Commander Danain asked me to kill werewolves in and around Camlorn. nnThose who did not escape Camlorn have been reduced to mindless beasts by General Faolchu, and will not hesitate to murder anyone they come across.
I've slain many among the crush of werewolves assaulting the Magis Order camp. The battle now favors the Magis Order. Magus Commander Danain will be relieved by this news.
Liralen has asked me to kill Drowned Zombies, as they distract him from his work.
I must search for Sload Larva Sacs and destroy them. These Sacs would provide Telenger with proof that a Sload is about.
I must slay Maormer on the contested beachhead along the southern shore of Dusk. Artulion's young warrior will assist me.
The young soldier has learned by my side, and the Maormer invaders have been decimated. Artulion will be glad to hear of this.
Magus Commander Danain asked me to enter Camlorn, fight my way to Duke Sebastien's manse, and kill General Faolchu.nnMeanwhile, he and the Lion Guard will distract most of Faolchu's army.

I've slain General Faolchu. With Faolchu dead, the new type of lycanthropy that nearly destroyed Camlorn has finally been stopped.nnMagus Commander Danain should hear of this. With Faolchu dead, Danian and his soldiers should be in the city soon.

Warden Mallery asked that I go into the swamp northwest of Aldcroft and fight alongside the Aldcroft Deputy. We are to slay threats to the refugee camp - Bog Lurchers, Will-O-Wisps, and Mud-cloaked Hags.

Warden Rielle asked me to speak to Warden Mallery, at the Aldcroft refugee camp, about taking a deputy under my wing. Through example, I'm to teach the deputy how to fight the monsters that threaten Aldcroft.

I've slain a number of monsters alongside the Aldcroft Deputy, enough to give the deputy some real experience in fighting such threats. Warden Rielle, at the refugee camp northeast of Aldcroft, will be glad to hear of our success.
My attempt to educate one of Artulion's young warriors has suffered a setback. It is my duty to inform the Battlereeve.
Fulgurites can be found in areas of Scorched Sand along the shore of the Deadsands. However, Mudcrabs appear to build nests in Scorched Sands.
I must slay the attacking Maormer.
I have defended the Warrior's soul gem and must return to him.
I must examine the Warrior's soul gem for damage.
Magus Commander Danain can teleport me into Duke Sebastien's manse, if I wish.
I've been teleported into Sebastien's manse. I must slay General Faolchu.
Upon my request, Sorceress Rolantae will teleport me to the Maormer Flagship. Once aboard, I can kill one of the Commanders.nnRolantae can be found on the height east of the Maormer Beachead.

I've slain one of the Maormer Commanders aboard their flagship. Now I must escape to shore and tell Battlereeve Artulion of my victory.nnArtulion may be found on a rise just north of the Maormer Beachead.
Artulion told me that Ruuva, a Priestess of Magnus, might be able to assist me in this endeavour.
I unleashed the fury of an Atronach on the Maormer, diverting them while I eliminated their Commander. Artulion needs to hear about my exploits.
I must use the Wand of Disincarnation on the corpses of Rogue Discarnates to collect Daedric Soul Gems for The Mage.
Telenger informed me there are Imago Plinths on each of the Pearl Islands. I need to use the Sload Inveigler on one to summon the Sload.
I must place the Sload Lure on the Sun Column in the ruins on the furthest island of the Pearls. The Lure will draw out the Sload that I must slay.
The Silver Wolfsbane cured the Wounded Magis Order Soldier. Muriel Eardswulf will be glad to know that her cure worked.
Apothecary Bella gave me some Silver, but suggested I obtain Foxglove Nectar instead of Wolfsbane I will do as Muriel asked and gather Wolfsbane near the Military Camp..

I've agreed to lead the disoriented traveler to Warden Rielle, a warden watching over a refugee camp in Aldcroft. He claims that the voice that lured him out into the swamp may return at any time - we should hurry.
The traveler said I should speak to Warden Rielle and let her know he is back safely.
I am on my way to find the Serpent's Soul Gem in depths of the Serpent's Burrow, east of The Warrior's Shrine.
Death to the Serpent! Once it is slain, I must retrieve the Varla Lens from its corpse.
I must bathe the Starglass in the Sky-Well to the south in the Orchestrated Gardens.
Vartisan Lalathal is waiting to receive the Starglass at the Isquer Kinhouse, northeast of the Orchestrated Gardens.
The Military Camp's Apothecary will tell me exactly where I can find Wolfsbane nearby.
Apothecary Bella gave me some Silver, but suggested I obtain Foxglove Nectar instead of Wolfsbane. I will do as she suggested and gather Foxglove Nectar near the Military Camp.
The Jewel worked as Heldarmo anticipated and the Scouts appeared. I must slay them.
I have collected enough Medallions to impress Battlereeve Artulion.nnI should deliver them to Artulion on the hill northeast of the Maormer Beachhead.
I should collect several Medallions from Maormer Marines on the southern beach of Dusk.
I need to put down five Earth Atronachs, spawned by the Landbreaker, and bury their souls in Mundus Fissures.
Sorceress Andria asked me to collect Dawnshards from within and around the Stonewake.
The Wakeshards I've collected should suffice in reinforcing the March-Ward if I deposit them in a Silovar Well.

Priestess Meloria can be found on the road north of the Orchestrated Gardens.nnI have returned many Contagious Cadavers to the earth and air from whence they came. Meloria will be glad to hear of my success.

Blanche begged me to find Coren's undead corpse in Cath Bedraud and destroy it. He roams the inner part of the graveyard. Blanche said I would recognize Coren by his size and prowess in battle. He's a champion in the ranks of Angof's undead.
I've retrieved Coren's locket from his corpse. I'll find Blanche at the military camp south of Cath Bedraud.
After I slew Coren, his spirit appeared and asked that I bring his locket to Blanche. I can collect the locket from his defeated corpse.
Apothecary Bella was very distracted. She said the plants that I need are found by the trees near the Military Camp.
The Silver Foxglove Nectar caused the Wounded Magis Order Soldier to immediately become a Werewolf. The Apothecary will want to know what happened.

The pieces of the Shattered Crown are kept in three Aldmeri crypts spread throughout Dusk.nnOne lies half sunken along the bay.nOne sits deep beneath the Maze of Obliquity.nOne stands high above the Tesselated Shores.
Master Metalwright Sinderon will be waiting for me at the Anquillius Forge, just outside the Scintilla Kinhouse.
I convinced Optimate Illira not to end her life. I should tell Exultant Elleste in the Felballin Kinhouse to the north,
If I can talk down Optimate Illiria from her rash decision, Elleste will be most pleased.
Optimate Illira was intent on taking her own life. I should tell Exultant Elleste in the Felballin Kinhouse to the north.
I must slay the Contagious Cadavers, then burn their remains with the Scorching Scepter.
Rolantae suggested speaking to Archivist Talrien at the Umbral Tower to the east should I need assistance with the Maormer crew.
Archivist Talrien gave me a strange Lockbox. He warned me not to use it until I am beset by the Maormer.
Sorceress Rolantae is atop the hill which overlooks the bay, south of Battlereeve Artulion. I should speak with her about boarding the Maormer Flagship.
Muriel Eardswulf gave me Silver Wolfsbane to use on a wounded soldier.
Apothecary Bella gave me Silver Foxglove Nectarto use on a wounded soldier.
Now that I've gathered the necessary component, I will need to have the Liquid Silver potion made. Muriel will combine Silver with Wolfsbane.
Benedict Mercier asked me to place flowers from his father's birth tree on his father's grave. I'll find the grave of Alexis Mercier in Cath Bedraud.

I've placed flowers brought by Benedict Mercier on the grave of his father, Alexis.nnBenedict is still hiding from undead in some rocks north of Cath Bedraud. He'll be pleased to know I've properly honored his father.
The Military Camp's Apothecary will tell me exactly where I can find Wolfsbane nearby.
Now that I've located Gerard's Pick-ax, I should return it to him in Crosswych.
In order to keep his job, Gerard asked me to find his Pick-ax inside the mine.
Sapiarch Lilia can be found at the Felballin Kinhouse, which lies to the south of Alinor.nnDeclaen asked me to deliver the Opalescence to Sapiarch Lilia.
The Silver Foxglove Nectar caused the Wounded Magis Order Soldier to immediately become a Werewolf. The Apothecary will want to know what happened.
Apothecary Bella gave me Silver Foxglove Nectarto use on a wounded soldier.
The Silver Wolfsbane cured the Wounded Magis Order Soldier. Muriel Eardswulf will be glad to know that her cure worked.
Muriel Eardswulf gave me Silver Wolfsbane to use on a wounded soldier.

Now that I've gathered the necessary component, I will need to have the Liquid Silver potion made. Muriel will combine Silver with Wolfsbane, but Apothecary Bella will combine the Silver with Foxglove Nectar.

High Priestess Vendialara can be found at the Fane of Breath, north of the Isquer Kinhouse.nnI must deliver the roses to her at the Fane's ritual area, which is at the highest platform of the temple complex.
The traveler I found in the swamp seems disoriented - I should let him know when I'm ready to lead him back to Aldcroft.
I let Colette go but I should report to Warden Rielle and tell her what I found out.
The Guardians have been summoned to assist me against the Serpent. I must speak with the Warrior.
Isque Roses grow north, uphill from the Isquer Kinhouse.
Villagers in Alaygon still remain! I must urge them away from the town in hopes that Coldun does not reach them. I should also destroy any soldiers who stand in the way.
I should speak to Tamarus while we wait for the Coldun army to arrive. Perhaps he will have need of me for some particular task
Villagers in Alaygon still remain! I must urge them away from the town in hopes that Coldun does not reach them. I should also destroy any soldiers who stand in the way.
Gem Spiders can be found along the road leading south from Alinor to the Felballin Kinhouse.nnDeclaen asked me to kill Gem Spiders and collect Opalescence from their corpses.
I have a requisition for the Varla Lens being used by Vartisan Taarifil at the Tessellated Shores, on the east coast. I must bring it to him.
Now that I've gathered the necessary component, I will need to have the Liquid Silver potion made. Apothecary Bella will combine the Silver with Foxglove Nectar.
I must situate myself next to an unused Channeling Pedestal, and await Sinderon's order to place the next piece of the Shattered Crown.
I must situate myself next to an unused Channeling Pedestal, and await Sinderon's order to place the next piece of the Shattered Crown.
I must situate myself next to an unused Channeling Pedestal, and await Sinderon's order to place the next piece of the Shattered Crown.
The Thief gave me a Star-Enchanted Lockpick to use on the boxes, held inside the large tents to the southwest of The Thief's Shrine. I am to plunder these boxes and take Fire Salts to The Thief.
Marcel asked me to gather bones from any undead minions of Angof that I slay, and return those bones to him to grind into bonemeal.

I have gathered a number of bones from Angof's risen undead. Marcel, who is waiting at an ancient altar south of Cath Bedraud, can create bonemeal from the bones. The Magis Order can use this bonemeal as a weapon against other undead.
I must travel east of the Imagerie to Landbreaker, at the north end of the Stonewake, to find a replacement Varla Lens.
A Lion Guard lieutenant gave me a Flash Crystal with six charges. It's a magical artifact that immolates zombies. When I burn their corpses, they'll stay dead.
I've burned many of the zombies wandering Cath Bedraud. The Lion Guard should face less resistance now. I should return the spent Flash Crystal to the Lion Guard lieutenant at the redoubt.
Battlereeve Heldarmo asked me to retrieve an Irradiant Jewel from the Spyglass on the Landbreaker.
Northeast of the Imagerie is Hainen's retreat. I should be able to find a footpath leading up through the mountains, and then retrieve the book from his library.
I've retrieved the book from Hainen's retreat. Ameralee waits for me to return with it.

The orphans won't tell me anything. They simply insist that I speak to their "mother". It doesn't sound like she'll be happy to see me.nnPerhaps there is truth to Ascience's story. I should be cautious if I approach the "mother" of these orphans.
Now that I've found and killed Mother Murk, I can let Asciene know that the tales she heard as a child were a bit more than just harmless fairy stories.
I have a requisition order for the Varla Lens being used by Vartisan Taarifil at the Tessellated Shores, on the east coast.
A Maormer Thief made away with the Varla Lens. If I can pick up the trail, I might be able to get the Lens back.
The High Kinlord suggested I speak to Vartisan Ameralee at the Imagerie east of the Kinhouse.
I must collect the Atronach Rubble.
I have collected Atronach Rubble. Now I must combine it at The Atronach's shrine by using its Soul Gem.
The High Kinlord asked me to retrieve several pages of the Tome, which lie scattered across my previous path.
I'm hunting Rogue Discarnates in the Maze of Obliquity and trying to recover Scintillated Ore for Sinderon.
I've collected the Ore Sinderon wanted. He will be waiting for it at the Forge in the Scintilla Kinhouse.
Vartisan Ameralee is still at the Imagerie - it's not as if she can go anywhere.
Sinderon is waiting for the magical reagent at the Anquillius Forge.

The Anquillius Process requires a relic from a powerful magical creature.nnThe fangs of a Giant Sea Serpent are highly magical; they swim the waters off the eastern coast.nnThe horn of a Kirin would do as well; a few are known to reside in the north.
Sinderon is waiting for the magical reagent at the Anquillius Forge.

Ahlotica can be found on the easternmost bridge in the Fane of Breath.nnAhlotica's missing book drove the priestess Nailanya mad, resulting in her death and the destruction of the book. I should deliver these tidings to Ahlotica.
I must collect 9 Welkynd Shards for Skyharker Nureva.

Nureva asked me to perform a ritual to repair Auri-El's bracket. To start the ritual I must touch the Welkynd shard inside the shrine. After this I will need to be quick and make contact which each as soon as they appear.
I have gathered the Welkynd shards for Nureva and must speak to her at the Ritual's Shrine, just northwest of the Kinhouse.
I have gathered rubbings of the various murals throughout the lower levels of the dungeon. Lith Nilian, who waits on the top level of the ruins, will be eager to receive these.
Lith asked me to make rubbings of any murals I find on the lower levels of the Dwynnarth Ruins, and return these rubbings to her.
I must make contact with the Welkynd Stone.
I must make contact with the Welkynd Stone.
I must make contact with the Welkynd Stone.
I must make contact with the Welkynd Stone.
Ahlotica believes the book fell from the bridge she was on, and may have been picked up by someone else at the Fane. I should search the areas below Ahlotica.
The power of the book has driven a young priestess mad. There is no alternative but to kill her and destroy the book.
I should retrieve a few more blessed arrows from the cold ground of Cath Bedraud. Their distinctive glow will make that a little easier. Someone at the redoubt may be interested in them.
I've retrieved blessed arrows from Cath Bedraud. The soldiers at the redoubt will be anxious to have them back.

Although Arturo Charascel is dead, he died fighting like a hero in the mine. I found his leather necklace to take to his mother.nnDarene will be grateful to know what happened to her son. She waits at the Crosswych Inn for news.
I must make contact with the Welkynd Stone.
I must make contact with the Welkynd Stone.
The smithing tools will likely be scattered throughout the Maze of Obliquity to the north of the Anquillius Forge.
Apprentice Braefurn will be eager to have the tools back at the Anquillius Forge, south of the Scintilla Kinhouse.
Magus Commander Panoit suggested that I bring the Midnight Talisman to a mage named Marcel Wirch. I'll find Marcel at an altar west of Panoit's camp.

Arnand asked me to look for Magus Commander Panoit at the Lion Guard redoubt. It's west of Crosswych and south of Cath Bedraud.nnPanoit may know a mage powerful enough to reactivate the Midnight Talisman.
I've helped the Lion Guard defend their banner against waves of Angof's undead. Now we must survive his final assault.
I've defended a Lion Guard banner against everything Angof could send at us. I should speak to a Lion Guard lieutenant at the banner to plan our next move.

Pia Mornard has a plan for freeing the mines fromf Angof's influence. Her strategy requires a substantial amount of mort flesh. She said there might be zombies in the mines. They're outside Crosswych to the northwest.
I retrieved enough mort flesh for Pia Mornard. I'll deliver it to her in Crosswych.
Vartisan Ameralee has lent me a Varline Focuser. Our combined efforts should lift the Varla Lens into place.
I must enter the Dwynnarth Ruins in northern High Rock and search for Welkynd Stones.
I should speak with Scholar Lael about his theories, he might have some insight into what is going on in High Rock.
Inside the Dwynnarth Ruins, I found the sample Welkynd Stones Scholar Lael requested. I should deliver these Stones to her. She is just south of the Ruins.
I am sent to speak with Battlereeve Artulion, who heads the Altmer defense on the southern coast of Dusk.
Priestess Nailanya is getting the book for me.
If Arturo Charascel is a miner, I might learn more about him by speaking with other miners. Of course, I could go directly to the mines instead and look for him myself.
I've retrieved the Midnight Talisman from Crosswych Mine.nnArnand Murrelll is waiting at the exit to Crosswych Mine. He'll tell me what to do next to use its power against Angof.

Arnand Murrell helped hide the Midnight Talisman in the Crosswych Mine, but it was recently found there by Jadier the Blackhand. I must get the Midnight Talisman back from Jadier, no matter what it takes.
I've discovered that Arturo Charascel's mother, Darene, is staying at Crosswych's boarding house.nnI should speak to her about Arturo's fate.
I should take this Embossed Leather Necklace into the nearby town of Crosswych to see if I can locate Arturo Charascel's family.
I should ask around town and see who may know more of the Bloody Eye as well as the Nomads.
I've talked to several of the villagers of Alaygon and have learned some information on both the Bloody Eye and Forest Nomads.
Ahlotica asked me to speak with High Priestess Vendialara, in the ritual space in the northeast of the Fane of Breath.
Marcel asked me to listen to the story of how Ulorion, founder of the Magis Order, quelled the Midnight Talisman. He says I must first understand the story of the talisman before I can reactivate it.
Marcel told me to look for an island west of Cath Bedraud. I can light a brazier to summon the spirits of air, water, and earth. The spirits can restore the power of the Midnight Talisman.
I've gained an audience with the spirits of air, water, and earth. I must speak to each of them and gain their blessings. This may be a difficult task.
I've gained the blessing of the spirits of air, water, and earth. Marcel is waiting for me at a wayshrine west of the redoubt. He can tell me if the Midnight Talisman has been reactivated.
The power of the Midnight Talisman is now in my hands. I can wield it against Angof and defeat him. Magus Commander Panoit is at the camp below Cath Bedraud. He'll want to hear of this.
I should report my success to Melodian Liriondion at the Isque Kinhouse.
The Welkynd Stone vanished after I defended it for a minute. I should report what happened in the Ruins to Scholar Lael. She is just south of the Ruins.
The Welkynd Stone I placed is under attack. I must defend the stone for at least a minute.
I must find a pedestal and place the Welkynd Stone Scholar Lael gave me. I need to protect the Stone for one minute.
I must kill Noxious Nereids, which can be found along the Liriel River to the east of Isque Kinhouse.
I am headed to the Steed's shrine, north of the Apprentice's shrine, to return its soul gem.
Skyharker Suuniqwe approached me, asking for me to give her the Steed's soul gem. I must decide whether I should trust her or Vilmo.
I decided to trust Suuniqwe, the protector of the Orrery.
I must deliver Thoe's Head to Melodian Liriondion at the Isque Kinhouse.
I must return the soul gem to the Steed's shrine.
I must find a pedestal and place the Welkynd Stone Scholar Lael gave me. I need to protect the Stone for one minute.
Averos gave me a Potion of True Nature and asked me to use it on Camlorn's refugees and guards. He believes some may be spies loyal to the enemy. This potion will reveal them.

I've revealed several werewolf spies. Aldcroft should now be free of them.nnLord Magister Averos will be eager to hear of my success. I'll find him by Duke Sebastien's house at the center of Aldcroft.
The cave containing the Bell Forge can be found behind the largest waterfall on the eastern side of the Fane of Breath.nnThe Nereids within the cave take offense at intruders in their pools.
I've forged a Starglass Bell in the Nereid cave. It should be returned to High Priestess Vendialara, at the top of the stairs leading up into the Fane of Breath.
This book... it burns. Suuniqwe wants me to deliver it to Skyharker Vilmo, back at the Apprentice's shrine.
I read a portion of Suuniqwe's book...
I read the book Suuniqwe wanted delivered to Vilmo.

In the Dwynnarth Ruins I must place the Resonance Crystals on the correct pedestals in order to amplify the power of the Welkynd Stone. Each Crystal seems to emit a different tone; perhaps that will help me find the correct pedestal.
There was much I did not understand... It appears to be about the center of the Aetherius?

The Crosswych Mine's main support beams seem to be in good shape. The miners should be able to return to work once the undead are cleared out for good. Miner Marthe Yvienne in Crosswych will be glad to hear my report.
I've agreed to check on Crosswych Mine's main support beams for Marthe Yvienne.
The mausoleum is heavily warded with magic. Even the Lion Guard can't match it. I may be able to penetrate the wards with the Midnight Talisman. If this works, I'll be able to find and defeat Angof.
When I used the Midnight Talisman in the mausoleum, it opened a portal. Angof may be hiding inside. Before I can face him, I must step into Oblivion.

I've entered a pocket realm of Oblivion, one created by Angof... or those who control him. I should search for any signs of Angof's presence. Perhaps there's a place he uses to communicate with his master.

I've slain Angof the Reachmage, but I've earned the wrath of a Daedric prince named Molag Bal.  Angof was working for Molag Bal all along. Magus Commander Panoit is at the Lion Guard camp below Cath Bedraud. He needs to know the grim truth.

I met a man named Verick in Crosswych. He's been gathering notes on Welkynd stones and the Ayleid ruins. Verick asked me to deliver his notes to Scholar Lael. She can be found near the ruins southeast of Crosswych.
I've recovered the Thornbane Cloak. I should talk to Ackers in the ruins of Dwynnarth about our next step.

Ackers asked me to search the catacombs beneath Dwynnarth ruins for the Thornbane Cloak. He also asked me to look for any survivors.nnThough he's too injured to help, he told me not to enter the ruins alone. I'll need help.
<<1>> asked me to speak to two feuding neighbors in Crosswych: Al'kari and Gulitte. If I can resolve their dispute, he can concentrate on protecting the town from greater dangers.
Both Al'kari and Gulitte suggested the same plan: I should gather catnip, then use it as a treat to lure a local cat to his neighbor's house. Then it will devour the pets. Problem solved.
I've gathered some catnip to use as a lure for a cat. I can lead it to either Al'kari's or Gulitte's house.

I've lured a stray cat. Now I have to decide if I want to help out Al'kari by leading the cat to Gulitte's rats. If I don't, I should help out Gulitte by leading the cat to Alkari's chickens.nnEither way, the cat will likely find easy prey.
I led a cat to Gulitte's house. It made short work of the rats Gulitte kept for his experiments. Al'kari will be glad to know her chickens can wander her yard unopposed, at least for the moment.

I led a cat to Al'kari's house. It made short work of the chickens Al'kari kept around her house. Gulitte will be glad to know he can experiment on his rats without chicken attacks skewing his results.
I resolved the dispute between Al'kari and Gulitte by using Gulitte's rats as cat's paws. Al'kari's chickens should be free to roam Gulitte's yard now.nnI can't wait to tell Guard Derran about this.
