I resolved the dispute between Al'kari and Gulitte. Al'kari's chickens perished beneath the paws of a Crosswych cat. Gulitte can continue to keep rats without worrying about chicken attacks. nnGuard Derran will want to know about this.
The Varla Lens has been restored. I should talk to Vartisan Ameralee to see if there is more to be done.
I killed many Gem Spiders from the Phidian Menagerie at the behest of Head Keeper Calnemin. He will wish to hear that the clean-up is complete.
Head Keeper Calnemin has asked that the Gem Spider population at his Menagerie be thinned out.
To continue the ritual I must accompany Vendialara on the Sacred Instrument.
I must use the Varla Lens on the miniature orrery to return it to the sky.
High Kinlady Genivra requested that I travel to the Scintilla Kinhouse to the east and deliver Auri-El to High Kinlady Astraela.
The Kirin is safely secured in its enclosure. Keeper Lahara will be beside herself with joy.
I am to find a Kirin and lure it back to the prepared enclosure at the Phidian Menagerie.
I found plans for an invasion on the corpse of an Altmer Commander. I should take them to someone in the Daggerfall Army, Camlorn's army, or the Lion Guard.
I need to go to the military camp outside Camlorn. Then I can deliver the invasion plans to Danain.
I am on my way to recruit the Orrery's Guardians. The Mage is to the north of the Kinhouse, the Thief to the south, and the Warrior to the southeast.
The Guardians have all agreed! When I am ready, I must inform the Warrior that it is time to assail the Serpent.

Danain asked me to journey to a set of ancient ruins and help a scout he sent out there, Nightblade Ackers, in his search for the ancient artifact. I'll find the ruins by following the  road northeast from Camlorn.
I must defend the first Barricade from Drowned Zombies.
I must defend the second Barricade from Drowned Zombies.
I must defend the third Barricade from Drowned Zombies.

Asciene asked me to find out about the orphans stealing things from Crosswych, and where they might be staying. If there's truth to the story, they may be hiding in a nearby cave.nnPerhaps I can follow one of the orphans back to their hideout...

I've discovered a cave in which a number of orphans appear to be living - some of the same children that have been causing trouble in Crosswych.nnThey don't look happy to see me, but perhaps I can convince them to return their ill-gotten goods...
Follow an orphan back to their hideout.
Follow an Orphan Back to their Hideout
I chose not to threaten Suuniqwe.
Skyharker Suuniqwe approached me, asking for me to give her the Steed's soul gem. I must decide whether I should trust her or Vilmo.
I should inform Vilmo, back at the Apprentice's Shrine, that I spoke with and defeated Suuniqwe's wraith.
I refused Suuniqwe the soul gem and she is attempting to take it by force.
I have been asked to free the trapped souls from their reliquaries in the Umbral Tower by using the Pyxides of Ashes. The Umbral Tower is located south of the Scintilla Kinhouse.
I have freed the trapped souls from their reliquaries in the tower walls. I should talk to Talrien in the base of the Umbral Tower, south of the Scintilla Kinhouse in Dusk.
Didier uses Green Stain Cup Caps in the medicines he makes to treat injured miners. He asked that I gather Green Stain Cup Caps from the area outside Crosswych where they grow near the trees.
I've gathered a number of Green Stain Cup Caps for Didier, who is waiting upstairs in the inn at his makeshift infirmary.nnHe'll be anxious to have the cups - he must be low on medicines by now.
The Mage asked me to destroy the Fragment of Orgnavar and bring him some debris to examine.

Deep within the Umbral Tower, Talrien studies the histories of Summerset. He should be able to provide guidance in forging Auri-El's new protective magics.nnThe Umbral Tower can be found on an island immediately south of the Scintilla Kinhouse.
I am to find Battlereeve Nenwe at the Tessellated Shores, on the far eastern coast of Tamvir.
I must collect the debris of Orgnavar.
I must protect the Oyinaam from the Zombies lurching out of the river.
I failed to protect the Oyinaam. I should notify Battlereeve Tariella at the Harmonium Fortress.
I go with the Atronach to slay the Stormwitch before she strikes again. She is hiding south of the Atronach's shrine, in the gap between the hills.
I have been granted an audience with High Kinlady Astraela at the Scintilla Kinhouse, and should speak with her directly.

I hope you strapped your belt on tight, young <class>, because there is work to do here in Northshire.nnAnd I don't mean farming.nnThe Stormwind guards are hard pressed to keep the peace here, with so many of us in distant lands and so many (EOT)
Arnand asked me to go south to the Dwynnarth Ruins and recover the Thornbane Cloak, an artifact said to offer protection against Reach magic.
Wyress Alene asked me to find Wyress Jacinta - if I go north from Deleyn's Mill, find a game trail, then follow it northwest, I should find Jacinta's camp.
I Destroyed the Bone Colossus which stalked Cath Bedraud. I should return to Swordsman Zacharie in Crosswych and tell him I completed this task.
I need to scout the hills surrounding Cath Bedraud for the Bone Colossus. Once found, I must slay this abomination of Angof's.
I must complete my journey to the Orrery to deliver Auri-El's Welkynd Stone to Vartisan Urselor.
The Welkynd Stone of Auri-El has been reforged with protective magics. The High Kinlady should be informed at once.
The Maormer landing boats are decimated. Perhaps Sorceress Rolantae has a reward for my services.
Auri-El orbits the Orrery again. I should report the good news to Vartisan Urselor.
Suuniqwe's wrath appeared and seeks to take the Steed's soul gem from me.
Exultant Ecclea asked me to destroy the Elementals and bury their Piths in the Fissures. They are southeast of the Felballin Kinhouse.
I should inform Exultant Ecclea of my success. She waits at the Imago Serry southeast of the Felballin Kinhouse.
Skyharker Vilmo asked me to speak with Suuniqwe. She was last seen east of the Mage's Shrine, north of the Shadow's Shrine.
Suuniqwe shed her mortal visage and became some form of ghastly wraith, threatening to destroy the Orrery. I must stop her.
Suuniqwe asked me to deliver her journal to Skyharker Vilmo.
Pia Mornard has given me potions to make the risen miners grow. nnThe good news is that they'll yield more mort flesh.nnThe bad news is that they'll make the risen miners more powerful.
I've used all the potions Pia Guillard gave me.
I've come across a tailor in the town of Aldcroft. Though lacking the proper supplies due to recent demand, he appears to be able to fashion something for me with what he has avaliable to him.
I should seek out a tailor or craftsman located in one of High Rock's towns who can make use of this Fine Harpy Feather.
Vartisan Ameralee can be found at the Imagerie, east of the Felballin Kinhouse.
I should see if a Mages Guild official is interested in the bronzed Orc skull.
Vartisan Talcantar is standing beside Velanya and Ameralee at the Imagerie.nnVelanya wonders if Talcantar knows any cure for Ameralee's condition.
Nimbleberries grow in the gardens outside the Felballin Kinhouse, and in the Imagerie to the east.
Christophe Greves is a Mages Guild official in Deleyn's Mill. He might be interested in the sword hilt.
There should be a Mages Guild Emissary in Aldcroft near the Lion Guard tents. He might be interested in this ornate harp.
There's a Mages Guild official in Aldcroft. I should see if he's interested in this odd stone.
There should be a Mages Guild official in Crosswych. I should see if he's interested in this ancient horn.
Now that I have freed Ameralee I should speak with her at once.
I am to meet the Vartisan Ameralee in the courtyard of the Felballin Kinhouse.
To draw out the Sload, I must place the Lure on one of the Sun Columns on the Pearl Islands to the southwest.
I must bury the Aquiferi Piths in the Fissures.
With the recent unnatural activity in Daenia, there should be a Mages Guild official in the Foresters Camp. I should see if he is interested in this sword hilt.
There should be a Mages Guild official in Aldcroft. I should see if he is interested in this odd stone.
There should be a Mages Guild official in Crosswych. I should see if he is interested in this ancient horn.
There should be a Mages Guild official in the Foresters Camp. I should see if he is interested in this bronzed Orc skull.
There should be a Mages Guild official in the Aldcroft. I should see if he is interested in this ornate harp.
I should ask around in Deleyn's Mill. Maybe someone is interested in an artifact like the one I found.
I'll need to ask around in hopes of finding someone who may be familiar with a tailor in the area. I should check with the nearby fishermen, or possibly at one of the neighboring towns.
Hainen's retreat is northeast of the Imagerie. I should be able to find a footpath leading up through the mountains, and then retrieve the book Varlines and Vartisans from his library.
Vartisan Ameralee will be awaiting my return at the Imagerie, east of Felballin Kinhouse.
Given Ameralee's indisposition, I should speak to one of her assistants.
I retrieved an undamaged Varla Lens from Landbreaker. Surely Vartisan Ameralee will be at the Imagerie awaiting my return.
I have recovered a Varla Lens from the Maormer ship. Vartisan Ameralee will want to examine it at once.
I am to meet the Vartisan Ameralee in the courtyard of the Felballin Kinhouse.
I should talk to Vartisan Ameralee. She is waiting for me at the Imagerie.
I have fulfilled the last wish of Rolperil. I should inform Battlereeve Tariella in the Harmonium Fort south of Isquer Kinhouse.
Rolperil asked me to slay the Maormer that have overrun Sunhold.
I've been told that the Mages Guild is always interested in artifacts found in Glenumbra. I should talk to the Mages Guild Emissary in Deleyn's Mill.
Battlereeve Heldarmo asked me to travel to the south end of the Stonewake, use the Irradiant Jewel to find stealthed Maormer Scouts, and slay them.
Heldarmo asked me to travel south, down the Stonewake, use Irradiant Jewel, and slay any Maormer Scouts I discover.
Hainen the Deranged is lurking in the Imagerie, east of the Felballin Kinhouse. He should have the Varla Lens in his possession.
I've been told that the Mages Guild will be interested in artifacts found in Glenumbra. I should seek one in Crosswych.
I should ask around Crosswych to see if anyone is interested in an artifact like the one I found.
I have killed the Maormer for Rolperil and I should report back to him on the western side of Sunhold Island.
I should ask around Crosswych to see if anyone is interested in an artifact like the one I found.
I've been told that the Mages Guild will be interested in artifacts found in Glenumbra. I should seek one in Deleyn's Mill, Aldcroft, or Crosswych.
I've been told the Mages Guild is interested in artifacts found in Glenumbra. I should talk to the Mages Guild Emissary in Deleyn's Mill.
I should ask around Deleyn's Mill. Maybe someone is is interested in artifacts like this bronzed Orc skull.
I should ask around Aldcroft or Crosswych to see if anyone might be interested in an artifact like the one I found.
I've been told that the Mages Guild will be interested in artifacts found in Glenumbra. I should seek one in Deleyn's Mill, Aldcroft, or Crosswych.
One of the miners outside the Crosswych mine may know Arturo... or know his fate. I should speak to a miner near the Crosswych Mine entrance.
I spoke with several miners in Crosswych about Arturo Charascel.
According to a miner named Merard Alouette, Arturo died a hero while defending the mine. His body is still inside.
Ameralee awaits me in front of the Kinhouse, ready to begin the ritual. I should talk with her when I am ready.
I am to meet the Vartisan Ameralee in the courtyard of the Felballin Kinhouse.
Glaewon told me to report to the Queen in Immaculate Tarbernacle in the Turquoise district
The Scouts have appeared, I must slay them quickly.
I should use the Jewel again and reveal more Maormer Scouts.
Again, I must slay the Maormer Scouts.
I should use the Irradiant Jewel one last time to reveal some Maormer Scouts.
I am to be inspected by Glaewon the Discriminant.
I have access to the Turquoise district and the Immaculate Tabernacle which is where the Queen waits.
Quest NPC is sad because his midget has dissapeared.
I found Quest NPC's midget.  He was eaten by a large undead wolf.  I should return to Quest Giver NPC at the start of RL_DungeonTest to tell him the good news.
Report to the Immaculate Tabernacle in the Turquoise district where the Queen awaits.
Queen Ayarynne wants me to unite the land under her banner and has commanded me to report to High Kinlord Langdruum in Varyllis, south of Alinor.
Vartisan Treyfellin is waiting to meet me at the wreckage of Auri-El, in the mountains southwest of the Orrery.
I must protect Treyfellin while he extracts the Greater Welkynd Stone from the wreckage of Auri-El.
Treyfellin successfully extracted the Greater Welkynd Stone. I should report back to Kinlady Genivra at the Syldarim Kinhouse.
Urselor fell attempting to recover the Welkynd Stone. I should report back to Battlereeve Tariella at the Harmonium Fortress.
When I placed the rock into the statue, I was teleported back to the entrance of the dungeon.
I am on my way with Captain Rielle to arrest Warden Moreau for aiding in the theft of the Thierry family ring.
Panoit told me to speak to Warden Moreau. I could take his advice, or I could let Ormax Matreinace know what Panoit said.
I've talked to Ormax and turned in Moreau. Warden Moreau was an accomplice in stealing the Thierry family ring. I should speak to Ormax about this.
I must decide what I want to do about Moreau. Should I turn him in, let him go if he gives me gold, or just let him go?
I've refused the money Moreau offered me. I won't turn him in. I should speak with him again to let him know I'll keep his secret.
I've accepted the bribe offered by Moreau. I'll need to speak with him again to reassure him.
After speaking with Moreau, I've made the decision to turn him in. I need to seek out Ormax Matreinace and talk to him.
Head to the east and protect the Oyinaam from the Zombies lurching out of the river.
I must protect the Oyinaam from the Zombies lurching out of the river.
I have driven off the Zombie attack on the Oyinaam. I should tell Battlereeve Tariella in the Harmonium Fort of my success.
I failed to protect the Oyinaam. I should notify Battlereeve Tariella at the Harmonium Fortress.

With the spriggan threat growing, Ormax can't spare anyone to arrest Warden Moreau. He asked me to handle Moreau's arrest.nnI'll find Warden Moreau watching the road to Daggerfall, south of Deleyn's Mill.

I have spoken with Warden Moreau, and he has agreed to turn himself in. He asked for a moment with his wife, Paulette, and Warden Thierry before he leaves. He asked me to let Ormax know of his decision.
All is prepared. It's time to light the Isque Rose Incense in the silver censer bowl to begin the ritual.
I've been tasked with finding a magical tome, somewhere in RL_DungeonTest by Discheveled NPC.
The well dressed mage told me that he would make it worth my while to give him the tome instead of the disheveled guy who origionally asked me to find it. I need to decide who to give it to...
Give the Tome to the Mage
Give the tome to Discheveled NPC
A well dressed and important looking mage suddely appeared after I picked up the Magical Tome. I should see what he has to say.
I must speak to Skyharker Nureva, who waits within the Syldarim Kinhouse, about the vision I witnessed of the Sload inside of Orgnavar.
I must protect the Oyinaam from the Zombies lurching  out of the river.
The Lover's shrine can be found to the southwest of the Syldarim Kinhouse.nnI must speak to the constellation Exemplars to enlist their aid. Their shrines can be found encircling the Kinhouse.
I must speak to the constellation Exemplars to enlist their aid. Their shrines can be found encircling the Syldarim Kinhouse.
I must speak to the constellation Exemplars to enlist their aid. Their shrines can be found encircling the Slydarim Kinhouse.
I must speak to the constellation Exemplars to enlist their aid. Their shrines can be found encircling the Syldarim Kinhouse.
The Welkynd Stone is infused with the power of the constellations. I can glimpse inside of Orgnavar.
I must protect the Oyinaam from the Zombies rising out of the river.
I must escort Vartisan Treyfellin to the Greater Welkynd Stone within the heart of fallen Auri-El.
I failed to protect Vartisan Treyfellin, and by necessity he teleported away from danger. I must find him and convince him to try again.
I must deliver the bell to Battlereeve Tariella at the Harmonium Fortress on the coast south of the Isque Kinhouse.
The journal Suuniqwe gave me burns at my touch, and seems to be whispering strange things to me. Suuniqwe wants me to deliver it to Skyharker Vilmo, back at the Apprentice's Shrine.
I am on my way to recruit the Orrery's Guardians. The Mage is to the northwest of the Syldarim Kinhouse, The Thief to the southwest, and The Warrior to the southeast.
The Guardians have all agreed! When I am ready, I must inform The Warrior that it is time to assail The Serpent.
I've destroyed the evil book Skyharker Suuniqwe gave to me, saving Skyharker Vilmo from an unknown fate.
Cannonreeve Lefalto can be found within the Felballin Kinhouse in Varyllis, I should make contact with him for more information on how to advance the Queen's goals.
Speak with High Kinlord Langdruun in the Felballin Kinhouse south of Alinor in Varyllis.
Using the Welkyn Stone, I was able to summon a vision of the orchestrator of the Orrery's problems - a Sload! I must question this creature's apparition to try and figure out its intentions.
You should return to Commander Lafavre.
You should return to Commander Lafavre.
You should return to Commander Lafavre.
I have defeated the Stormwitch with the help of the Atronach.
You should return to High Mage Dilborn.
I have failed to kill the Maormer Stormwitch.
Vartisan Taarifil has asked me to speak with his assistant Lorifaire regarding the missing Varla Lens. Lorifaire stands below the tower at the Tessellated Shores.
The Varla Lens is now in my possession. I should take it to Vartisan Guyeron at the Scintilla Kinhouse, who will be able to set it back in place and restore full power to the Anquillius Forge.

I need to follow the trail to the Maormer thief, kill him and recover the Varla Lens. Lorifaire said that the Lens fell on the Tessellated Shores, just below the tower. I should start my search there.
The Baron is slain. I should return to Merin Brushe and leave this place.
The Baron's Guard Captain is a werewolf - this I have seen with my own eyes. I will need to report this to Merin Brushe.
I have seen the nightmares the Baron keeps in his cellar. The undead walk through his keep, welcome as if honored guests. Merin Brushe will wish to know of this monstrosity.
Speak with Optimate Illira to the south in the Pearls.
I must find Illira and perhaps talk her out of suicide. She is on the Aquine Bluff west of the Kinhouse.
Vartisan Lorifaire has provided me with a Magicka Pulsator, which I must use to reveal the trail of residual magicka left by the stolen Varla Lens.
I should talk to High Kinlord Maldarawo in the Isquer Kinhouse northeast of the Orchestrated Gardens. He will want to know about the Maormer that I discovered.
I should talk to High Kinlord Maldarawo in the Isquer Kinhouse northeast of the Orchestrated Gardens. He will want the Battle Plans from the Maormer.
Either kill the Marooned Maormer Marine by rolling a boulder onto him, or lower the rope to help him up.
Talk with the Maormer Scout to get the Battle Plans.
Vartisan Guyeron is just outside the Scintilla Kinhouse. I should speak with him about traveling back to the Orrery to deliver Auri-El's reforged Welkynd Stone.
High Kinlady Astraela has asked me to meet her personal guards along the road to the Orrery. The second guard can be found on the road along the border between the Orrery and Dusk.
I failed to protect the Oyinaam. I can speak with an Oyinaam Conductor if I want to try again.
I must protect the Oyinaam from the Zombies lurching out of the river.
I must protect the Oyinaam from the Zombies lurching out of the river.
I must protect the Oyinaam from the Zombies lurching out of the river.
I am to speak with the Phidian Keeper about finding a Kirin for the Menagerie. He can be found in a nearby enclosure, east of the main Menagerie pavilion.
The two Enkindle Rods stand on opposite sides of the northern Throne platform. Using them will charge Auri-El with the magicka it needs to launch into the sky.
I must finish the ritual of raising Auri-El and use the last Enkindle Rod.
The two Enkindle Rods stand on opposite sides of the southern Throne platform. Using them will charge Auri-El with the magicka it needs to launch into the sky.
I must use the second Enkindle Rod to continue the ritual of Auri-El.
The Celestial Cradle of Auri-El sits atop the southern platform of the Throne. I must use it to begin the launching ritual.
Prodigious Mudcrabs can be found along the border between Isque and The Orrery.
Vartisan Urselor can be found in the Syldarim Kinhouse at the center of The Orrery.nnI need to deliver the Crab Carapaces to Urselor.
I must reach the next tower. I should use the Cloudwalk Staff located at the edge of the Throne's platform.
I must protect Dehilia from Discarnates as she performs her task.
Battlereeve Heldarmo can be found at the Guard Tower on the western edge of the Stonewake.nnDehilia has reached the tower safely. Heldarmo has offered to reward me, if I speak to him.
Dehilia's attempt to gather pomegranates went awry. She waits to try again at the bridge east of the Imagerie.
I have retrieved the relics for the Mages' Guild, although they seem to have been corrupted by dark magic. Nonetheless, I should bring them to Magus Garamond.

I have managed to impress the Mad Architect by prevailing in his twisted dungeon and defeating his horrific arena. While he has left me without the chance to get some revenge, he has left a projection that seems to want to talk.
Alorkhane awaits my arrival near the Lover's Shrine, southwest of the Syldarim Kinhouse.
I must speak to the Atronach, confirm I am prepared.
Collect the Varla Lens from Hainen's Corpse.
The power of the book has driven a young priestess mad. There is no alternative but to kill her and destroy the book.
I met Sir Edmund, a Knight of the Flame, outside Firebrand Keep. He claims Sir Croix, another Knight of the Flame, exiled him. Croix is allegedly plotting against Duke Nathaniel.
Lakana asked me to deliver a message to Ra'ud, her ally at the Old Goat Inn. She promised to explain more when I returned.
When I returned to Alcaire Castle, Duchess Lakana was no longer in Duke Nathaniel's throne room. Her handmaiden, Adima-Al-Toun, waved me down when I entered. Perhaps she knows Lakana's whereabouts.
Duchess Lakana is no longer in the throne room. She asked me to meet her in her quarters when I returned. She was waiting for me upstairs in the manse.
I've summoned Derelle Nin to help free Inwold Vanne from his magical bindings. The two of us should be able to discover what happened to Inwold Vanne and how the Glenmoril Coven is involved.

Dabienne begged me to work with Derelle. She asked me to find out what happened to her husband, Inwold, and she wants me to bring Inwold safely back to her. Derelle is probably drinking at the Koeglin Village Inn, just off the square.
Derelle Nin suggested that I should walk to the Vanne farm, east of Koeglin Village. Once I'm there, I might find signs of Dabienne's missing husband, Inwold.
I've sent for Derelle Nin. She can help me free Inwold Vanne from a Daedric altar. The two of us should be able to discover what happened to Inwold Vanne and how the Glenmoril Coven is involved.
Lady Eselde Tamrith believes Lord Montclair has food supplies that could be used to feed the starving peasants around Shornhelm. She's asked me to collect some.
I've obtained some rations. Now I can give them to desperate citizens outside Lady Eselde's outpost.
I've given rations to the peasants who seemed to need it most. I should let <<1>> of House Tamrith know.

Based on the descriptions in Arfinwe's journal, there should be three other journals from the party, somewhere in the Crypt of Hearts. Finding them should give me some more insight into the Mad Architect, and possibly help find his weaknesses.

The journals I've read have suggested that the Mad Architect sees this whole place as some kind of twisted game. Based on the descriptions of those lost to this place, I might be able to buy my freedom if I can impress the mad lich somehow.
I've located the missing Shornhelm soldiers, but only one was still alive: <<1>>. I should return to Finnegan with the news.
Montclair's attack scattered Finnegan's men. I should search along the sides of the road running south from Shornhelm to Oldgate.
I need to collect building materials the refugees lost in their hasty retreat. I have to bring wood, stone, and tools back to Sybille in <<1>>.
I've collected enough materials to help Sybille. She's waiting for me to return to <<1>>.

A Spirit Guard witnessed a scuffle below Pariah Abbey. A mob attacked three figures fighting at the crossroad.nnPart of the mob headed off toward Hammerdeath Arena. If I wish to find Rin, Makana, and Christophe, I must start my search there.
The best place to begin this investigation is the last place the apprentices and the Book of Circles were seen.
I should take the list of names Sosia gave me to Duke Nathaniel.
I should begin by investigating Alcaire Keep. I could search Lakana's quarters for evidence, ask if the courtiers saw anything, or speak with the Duke's head spy, James Tailas.
I've learned of House Tamrith through their leader, Eselde. She appears to be a younger noble who wants to make a name for her once lesser house. Her main priority seems to be pushing back Montclair.
I should find Lady Eselde Tamrith. She should be able to tell me what's happening in Shornhelm.
I should travel north along the road from Oldgate to Shornhelm, looking for Finnegan Polstic and Cray Jotal. <<1>> commands a column of soldiers.
Alard Dorell should explain to me why he's leaving Shornhelm.
Alard Dorell has been key in defending Shornhelm against Montclair. Polstic recommends I speak to him at his house in the western part of the city to learn more.
Under torture, a member of the Glenmoril has promised to tell me anything I need to know. If I find out the protonymic of the Daedric altar holding Inwold Vanne, Derelle and I can set him free.

If I interrogate a Glenmoril Coven Initiate with Derelle's scroll, I may get the altar's true name. We can banish it. Or, if I collect Daedra hearts, we can free Inwold with a spell. nnInitiates and Daedra walk the Vanne farm and stones to the east.

I've collected the hearts of many Daedra - enough to provide Derelle Nin with the magical energy she needs to destroy the Daedric altar holding Inwold Vanne.nnDerelle will be anxious to begin. I'll find her inside the barn at the Vanne farm.
Using her powerful magic, Derelle Nin has banished the power of the altar holding Inwold Vanne. He is now free. If I wish to know what the Glenmoril Coven is planning, I should speak to him.
Montclair appears to be feeding the citizens of Shornhelm to some kind of vampiric Orc. I should learn more about what's going on from the escaped slave.
I've brought a witness of Montclair's atrocities back to Eselde Tamrith.

Ra'ud said Lakana's letter detailed a threat to her life from Sir Hughes, the leader of Alcaire's Knights of the Flame. He said he'd act on the letter immediately. In the meantime, I should meet Duchess Lakana in Alcaire Castle.

Adima-At-Toun told me that Duchess Lakana left for a private meeting with Sir Hughes in her quarters. Lakana requested I meet her there when I return. The Duchess will certainly be interested in Ra'ud's manifest.
I should enter the Crypt of Hearts in order to find any treasure within.
I will need to find a way out of this place, starting with the vile Bone Vaults.

I have escaped from the Bone Vaults only to find that this nightmarish dungeon continues on in even more disturbing ways. Somewhere in this warren is the sanctum of the Mad Architect, which may be the key to escaping this place.

<<1>> wants me to send a message to the defectors by hunting them down and slaying them. I can find Montclair's men in the northern part of Shornhelm.nnI should also keep an eye out for anyone willing to provide me with information about his plans.
I've slain several of Montclair's troops. Now I can return to <<1>> and tell him what I've learned.
The escaped slave has asked that I bring him to one of the two noble houses. He warns that the House I do not go to may consider me a traitor so I should consider my choice wisely.
I've brought a witness of Montclair's atrocities back to Alard Dorell.

A member of the Glenmoril Coven revealed the true name of the Daedric altar binding Inwold Vanne - jakay-jhe. Derelle Nin will be anxious to hear what I've discovered. She's waiting inside the barn at the Vanne farm.
I should keep my ears peeled for any guards willing to part with information regarding Montclair's newfound power.
I've found that Montclair swore an alliance with something called "The Bloodsworn" and this is how he's taken the advantage in Shornhelm.
I killed one of the local merchants. I should go to the Mule and Bull Inn and report this to Sosia.
I should go speak the words, "sanguine my sister," to Sosia. She can be found in the Mule and Bull Inn. Sosia might have information on Lakana's murder.
Sosia has asked me to kill a local merchant in exchange for information about Lakana's murder. She warned me to watch out for guards. I should wait until the merchant is in an isolated location.

Ra'ud asked me to kill the brigand One Eyed Zach in his storehouse near Alcaire Keep. In exchange, Ra'ud will give me evidence to the identity of Lakana's killer. nThe storehouse is the southernmost building on the east side of the creek.
I should speak with Ra'ud-Abd-Mara in the market near Alcaire Keep. The letter I found in Lakana's quarters was written upon the same paper he used to stamp his seal.
I should report One Eyed Zach's death to Ra'ud-Abd-Mara.He is in the market near Alcaire Keep.
I should bring Lakana's letter to Duke Nathaniel in Alcaire Keep.
In order to free the Shornhelm slaves as Eselde asked, I will have to kill their gaolers and search them for keys.nnThe slave pits are behind and to the north of Montclair's estate.
Now that I've freed Montclair's captives, I should speak to <<1>>. She should be near the entrance of the <<2>>.
The librarian in the Mages Guild told me they've sent their mages to Crestshade, a town west of Shornhelm. He hasn't heard back from them in several days, so he's asked me to find out what happened.
I need to find the priest and mage <<1>> spoke of. They are being held in the <<2>>.nnOnce the captives are freed and cured, <<1>> will ensure their safety.
I've defeated Lord Montclair. I should speak to <<1>> to learn what he plans to do next.

<<1>> wants Lord Montclair dead. In fact, both of the noble houses in Shornhelm want him dead. Verandis told me Montclair is lurking within a cavern in the back of the <<2>>. If I can slay him, that should put an end to the strife in <<3>>.
I found a letter in Lakana's quarters. I should read it.
The Servant of Meridia has begun the ritual to request Meridia's blessing. I must drink from the two basins on either side of the shrine to show my devotion.
I defeated <<1>> in <<2>>. Now I need to let <<3>> know the necromancer will no longer plague Rivenspire.
I've found Tainted-Heart's lair deep within <<1>>. He's protected by some sort of magical barrier I can't breach. I have to find a way to lure him out from behind that barrier.
I should search for <<1>> in <<2>>, a cave south of <<3>>. I must put a stop to his evil machinations before he becomes even more powerful.
I have found the head of Meridia's statue. The Servant of Meridia awaits my return in the Veiled Grotto.
Derelle asked me to speak with Constable Sal, in the center of Koeglin Village. nnDerelle hopes I can convince Sal to free Dabienne.

Ganise Oscent gave Constable Sal a sworn statement that Dabienne Vanne bewitched her beloved. She is on the docks with her brother. If I prove Ganise's claim false, Constable Sal may release Dabienne from the stocks.

Ganise says Dabienne bewitched Inwold. This must be why she believes Dabienne is with the Glenmoril Coven.nnBrother Stental performed Inwold and Dabienne's marriage. Perhap he can shed light on Ganise's claims. I'll find him at Koeglin's Wayshrine.
Brother Stental said I would find proof of Dabienne's innocence by digging at the center of a copse of three thin trees at the Nurdin Farm, north of Koeglin Village.
Constable Sal has agreed Dabienne was falsely accused, and given me a key to release her. I'll find Dabienne in the stocks near the docks of Koeglin Village.
I've freed Dabienne from the stocks. I should speak with her and make sure she's all right.
If I follow the footprints leading from Ahtah's Study window, I will be closer to discovering what happened. The footprints lead down the hill from Pariah Abbey.

Inside a pine box I found parchment with love poems written by Inwold. They mention Dabienne by name.nnThe paper is old, and the poems were written years ago. They prove Inwold loved Dabienne before Ganise claims she bewitched him. Sal must be told.

Alard Dorell sent me to free and kill captives in Montclair's slave pit, which is behind and to the north of his estate.  nnKeys to the cells will be on Montclair's gaolers, and the cells themselves are ringed around the pit.
I need to find the priest and mage <<1>> spoke of. They are being held in the <<2>>.nnKilling the captives is the only way to be sure Lord Montclair will not use them against Shornhelm.
Now that the difficult task of freeing and slaying Montclair's unfortunate prisoners is complete, I should speak to <<1>>. He should be near the entrance of the Fevered Mews.
Jerwinna has asked me to aid her with the defense of Hallowed Refuge. I should check the status of the defenses.
I'll need to help a refuge defender hold off the attacking bloodfiends.
We've survived the attack, but Jerwinna was gravely injured. I should check on her.
We've survived the attack, but Jerwinna was gravely injured. She asked me to speak with <<1>> and let him know the attack was repelled.
Bloodfiends dragged Jordan Frost from the graveyard on the southern side of <<1>>. His body should still be somewhere within the village.
I've retrieved Jordan's remains. Now I need to bury Jordan in the graveyard on the south side of <<1>>.
Jordan Frost sacrificed his life to honor his brother, Cedric. Now he is at peace, buried beside his brother.
Jerwinna and I wait for the advancing horde of vampire that approach. If I wish to survive the battle, I should assemble the fortifications around to give us an advantage.
I told Duke Nathaniel that I killed the <<1>>. I've made my decision about Sir Hughes. I should talk to Duke Nathaniel again to hear his reaction.
I need to heal one of the bloodfiends. The false sense of life within a healed ghoul should cause the remaining ghouls to turn on him.
I need to find the Amulet of Holy Light. If I can use it on the bloodfiends, it should be able to disorient them long enough for me to sneak in and retrieve Jordan's remains.
If I'm skilled enough, I should be able to face the ghouls feasting on Jordan and kill them outright.
I need to use the Amulet of Holy Light on the bloodfiends so I can retrieve Jordan's remains.
Lord Wylon Montclair is lurking in the back of the Fevered Mews. If I can kill him in the name of House Dorell, I can put an end to this war!
I have finally defeated Lord Montclair. I should return to Shornhelm to inform House Dorell of this victory.
Duke Nathaniel asked me to travel to Firebrand Keep and speak with Sir Edmund. He believes that Edmund is still loyal, and will help us find Sir Hughes.
Sir Hughes has fallen into a deep sleep in the infirmary beneath Firebrand Keep's Great Hall. I need to go down and speak with the healer, Odette, about Sir Hughes' condition.
I should examine <<1>>. He's unconscious in Firebrand Keep's infirmary, surrounded by a magical aura.
Inside Sir Hughes' dream, I've encountered echoes of his recent memories. One of them told me I must slay the Omen of Fear to free Sir Hughes from his paranoia. The Omen is in the throne room.
I retrieved the artifact from the frozen body. I should present it to the Servant of Meridia to prove my worth.
Three braziers surround the frozen supplicant near the Shrine of Meridia. I should light each of them to thaw the body.

Andras sent me to bring word of what happened in Hallowed Refuge to the Houses of Tamrith and Dornell in Shornhelm.nnNow that I've spoken to Eselde Tamrith, I should seek out Dorell in the western part of the city.

Andras sent me to bring word of what happened in Hallowed Refuge to the Houses of Tamrith and Dornell in Shornhelm.nnNow that I've spoken to Alard Dornell, I should seek out Tamrith in the eastern part of the city.
Andras sent me to bring word of what happened in Hallowed Refuge to the Houses of Tamrith and Dornell in Shornhelm.nnHouse Tamrith is to the east, Dornell to the west of the city.
Dabienne asked me to speak to Derelle Nin, a Lion Guard investigator, about gaining her freedom. Derelle is standing on the road leading east out of Koeglin Village.

I've slain the leader of the Glenmoril Coven, Sister Nissa. Without her strong ties to Hircine, the coven's plan to raise a Daedric army cannot succeed.nnDerelle Nin will be glad to hear of my success. I'll find her in Koeglin Village.
To light the braziers around the frozen supplicant, I'll need to gather fire crystals from the corrupted fire atronachs.
I should go speak the words, "sanguine my sister," to Sosia. She can be found in the Mule and Bull Inn. Sosia might have information on Lakana's murder.
After I lit the braziers, ice thawed from the mage's frozen body. I should retrieve the artifact for the Servant of Meridia.
The mage was last seen in the caves to the south. I should seek him out for any information he's learned from the shrine of Meridia.
I acquired the price lists for Ra'ud. I should deliver them to him. He's near the Mule and Bull Inn.
Ra'ud asked me to acquire lists of prices from merchants in Alcaire. He claims these lists are evidence of price fixing.

Ra'ud told me he overheard two Knights of the Flame conspiring. They claimed that Lakana planned to raise a revolt against them, and that Sir Hughes should "take care of it".nnI should return to Duke Nathaniel with this new evidence.
I should speak with Ra'ud abd-Mara in the market near Alcaire Keep. He may have information about Lakana's murderer.
I should take the list of names Sosia gave me to Duke Nathaniel.
I killed one of the local merchants. I should go to the Mule and Bull Inn and report this to Sosia.
I should go speak the words, "sanguine my sister," to Sosia. She can be found in the Mule and Bull Inn. Sosia might have information on Lakana's murder.
Sosia has asked me to kill a local merchant in exchange for information about Lakana's murder. She warned me to watch out for guards. I should wait until the merchant is in an isolated location.
I found a letter in Lakana's quarters. I should read it.
Duke Nathaniel asked me to speak with James Tailas about Lakana's murderer.
I should go speak the words, "sanguine my sister," to Sosia. She can be found in the Mule and Bull Inn. Sosia might have information on Lakana's murder.

Makana does not remember Rin, Christophe, or Pariah Abbey. However, the Spirit Guard at Pariah Abbey did see someone else dragged off to Hammerdeath Arena.nnIf I investigate Hammerdeath Arena, I may find either Rin or Christophe there.

Though he can recall nothing of his former life, Makana suggested that I speak to Baelbrone's Constable, someone named Winchcombe, about finding Christophe. He says Winchcombe has been "hassling him" - perhaps the Constable is free of The Fervor.
The fire is warm and inviting in this barren land.
The fire is nice and toasty.  Return to the witch, when you are warm.
Andres Madiern asked me to race to Moira's Hope. I need to inform them that Captain Janeve's soldiers won't be returning as reinforcements.
Scarlette Dwynor sent me to talk to the Ravenwatch leader, Verandis Ravenfeld. He's informed me that they need my help. In return, they can offer assistance in destroying Montclair.

I have located the Mad Architect's sanctum and can see a portal stone, much like the one I saw when entering. It is possible I can use it to escape, although I will need to make it past the lich first
I've run across an agent of the resistance. He wants me to covertly approach their headquarters. I've been told to follow signs within the undercity. I should be wary the foul beasts lurking there.
I'll follow the trail to Baelbrone and speak with someone there. Perhaps I'll learn whether it was one of Ahtah's missing apprentices, or someone with his Book of Circles.
Verandis Ravenfeld asked me to take word of the Ravenwatch's allegiance to my sworn household.nnHouse Tamrith is in the west of Shornhelm, House Dorell to the east.
Verandis Ravenfeld asked me to take word of the Ravenwatch's allegiance to my sworn household.nnHouse Tamrith is in the west of Shornhelm.
Verandis Ravenfeld asked me to carry news of Ravenwatch's allegiance to Alard Dorell. House Dorell's representative is east of Shornhelm.
I should light the braziers around the ritual site.
I've killed the summoned daedra and helped <<1>> to stop the Supernal Dreamers from further desecrating the ritual site. I should return to him and tell him of my success.
If I kill the goblin warlord in Cumberland's Watch, I can get the key to the cage holding <<1>>.
Now that I've released Pierre, I should talk to him again.
I'll need to use this infusion on Makana to restore his memory. He's probably still drinking at the pub.

I've used Azura's infusion on Christophe, and he seems to be thinking much clearer now. If I wish to learn more about Rin, Christophe, and Ahtah's missing Book of Circles, I should see what he remembers.
<<1>> in <<2>> should know about Jerwinna's vampirism.
She faces a grim decision: to live as a vampire or end her unnatural life. She's asked for my help in choosing her fate.
<<1>> in <<2>> should know about Jerwinna's death.
I should investigate the town in search of any truth to the rumors of this "resistance" that seem to be circulating.
The Mages Guild has asked me to report my recent discoveries to one of the two nobles in Shornhelm. I should speak to either <<1>> or <<2>>.

Even though I have saved Inwold Vanne, it is only a matter of time before the Glenmoril Coven takes another victim. If I wish to stop them, I should track down the leader Inwold mentioned - Nissa.nnI should speak with Derelle Nin about killing Nissa.

To stop the Glenmoril Coven I must kill their leader, Nissa. She is well protected. Inwold suggested I bring friends. The coven meets at stones south of the Vanne farm, up a switchback.nnIf I decide to fight Nissa alone, Derelle Nin might offer help.
I've convinced Jerwinna that death is the answer. She's accepted her fate. I must destroy her before she becomes a danger to others.

If I gather the robe of a Glenmoril Coven Initiate, I can use it to disguise myself as a coven member. Once disguised, coven members will only attack me if I get close enough that they can see through my disguise.

If I gather the heart of a Herne, the personal warriors of Daedric Prince Hircine, Derelle believes I can sacrifice it on Hircine's altar and disrupt the Glenmoril Coven's ritual.nnI should use a Glenmoril Coven Uniform to disguise myself first.
I've disguised myself as Sister Agnes. I should be able to walk among members of the Glenmoril Coven and their Daedra - but I'd best not get too close.
I've collected an intact robe from a Glenmoril Coven member. If I return to the barn at the Vanne farm and give the robe to Derelle, she can enchant it to disguise me as Sister Agnes, a coven member.
When I smashed the heart upon the altar, an enraged Hircine sent additional Herne to slaughter the Glenmoril Coven members.
I've gathered a Herne heart. If I disguise myself as a Glenmoril Coven member and smash the heart on the altar during the ritual to Hircine, I may disrupt whatever they have planned.

I've collected a Glenmoril Coven robe. When I don it, I will appear to be a Glenmoril Coven member for a short time.nnDerelle warned me the disguise won't stand closely scrutiny. I should keep my distance.
When I smashed the heart upon the altar, an enraged Hircine sent additional Herne to slaughter the Glenmoril Coven members.
Before my battle, I should speak to Verandis and learn more about Karnoris.
I've let House Tamrith know the threat to Shornhelm will soon fall with the defeat of Montclair and his dark master. I should speak to Verandis within Lady Eselde's sanctuary.
I should investigate the town to find any truth behind the rumors of a "resistance."
While the Ravenwatch examines the essence, I should speak to Verandis and learn our next step.
I've slain the Spirit of Sirden and collected his essence. It might be useful Verandis. He's waiting for me at the hideout.
Speak with Captain Rodrick about having a guard accompaniment.
After using the infusion, Makana is coherent again. I hope he remembers what happened at Pariah Abbey.nnWe still need to find Christophe, Rin and Ahtah's Book of Circles.
Speak with Captain Rodrick about having a guard accompaniment.
Speak with Captain Rodrick about having a guard accompaniment.
Speak with Captain Rodrick about having a guard accompaniment.
Ahtah says Durak, leader of the Spirit Wardens, wishes to speak to me. If I agree, I will find Durak in the highest tower of Pariah Abbey.

Before they can become full members, Spirit Warden Initiates must go to a shrine east of Pariah Abbey and complete a rite of passage.nnFahjiri, Durak's initiate, recently left for the shrine and has not returned. Durak asked me to look for her.

I found Fahjiri. When I tried to wake her, a presence manifested at the shrine: a Glimmer of Madness.nnWhen I destroyed it, Fahjiri waked. If I speak with her, I may find out more about what happened at this shrine and the thing that attacked me.
When I found Fahjiri at the ancient shrine, she warned me that the nightmare I fought there hunts Durak. She urged me to return to Pariah Abbey and warn Durak that he is in danger.

I returned too late. Durak has fallen into a deep sleep, and no one can wake him. This may be the threat Fahjiri warned me about.nnAhtah guards Durak with his life. Perhaps he knows something about Durak's condition.
Reges Morascel sent me to silence the wailing apparitions around Hoarfrost Downs.

I managed to silence some of the apparitions haunting the moors. Reges Morascel is waiting for me in Hoarfrost Downs. He'll be pleased to hear my tale of success instead of that uncanny spectral wailing.

Makana confirmed what Rin said. Christophe stole the Book of Circles.nnThough he remembers little from his former life, he does remember being kept at shrine east of Pariah Abbey. Perhaps I'll find Christophe and the Book of Circles there.

Rin confirmed what Makana said. Christophe stole the Book of Circles.nnRin was in and out of consciousness while her captors brought her to Hammerdeath Arena. One mentioned the shrine east of Pariah Abbey. Rin suggested I might find out more there.
Verandis Ravenfeld asked me to carry news of Ravenwatch's allegiance to Eselde Tamrith. House Tamrith's representative is west of Shornhelm.
I think I've convinced Martin Dathieu to turn away from the life he led. He wants to walk the straight and narrow path. Only time will tell.

The ghost of Serine Dathieu wants me to help her son, Martin. I should find out more about him from the people of Hoarfrost Downs and see if I can convince him to change his ways before it's too late.
If I can defeat Ranser's Crownguard, I may be able to secure his crown.
Before General Dathieu vanished, he mentioned that Chancellor Karine sought the crown. She would probably be in Hoarfrost Downs.
Now that I have the Book of Circles, I should look for a Spirit Warden at the entrance to the Moonlit Maw and return the book.

Ahtah suspects Fahjiri, the Spirit Warden initiate I rescued, of having a hand in Durak's state. He has asked me to find out what Fahjiri knows about Durak's condition. Ahtah does not trust himself to question her.

Fahjiri believes that Durak has been trapped in a dream by what she calls a "dro-m'Athra". He will not wake until someone frees him from the dream.nnThe Spirit Wardens seem to be experts on dreams - perhaps Ahtah will have thoughts.

I have slain the Nightmare of Madness that trapped Durak in the dream world. I will not know if I was successful in waking Durak until I wake from the dream and speak to him in his tower, in Pariah Abbey.
When I drank the Potion of Endless Dreams, I slept and found myself in a dream world version of Pariah Abbey. Durak must be somewhere nearby. I must find him and wake him from the dream.

The Spirit Wardens have a powerful potion that can induce dreaming - the Potion of Endless Dreams. Ahtah said I'll find it in the shrine to Azura deep beneath Pariah Abbey.nnIf I wish to rescue Durak from the dream world, I must drink the potion.
By unsealing the wards, I've summoned a spirit named Sirden. He holds valuable information about the Doomcrag. I'll have to get it, one way or another.
I've convinced the Spirit of Sirden that I was on his side. I was given his essence, which holds valuable information about the Doomcrag. Verandis is waiting for me back at the hideout.
While the Ravenwatch examines the essence, I should speak to Verandis and learn what our next steps are.
Serine Dathieu's jewelry was recently stolen from her grave. She says the thief resides in the inn at Hoarfrost. nnI should retrieve the jewelry and give it to her daughter, Aubrey.
I've retrieved Serine's jewelry. I should give it to her daughter, Aubrey. She's in Hoarfrost Downs.
I've given Serine's daughter her necklace. She was elated to receive it.
Only one can be saved: the Book or Christophe. His soul is entwined with the Book, and severing the link will destroy the one I do not help.

Durak asked me to journey to Wayrest and speak with S'Rashi. He is a Khajiit who specializes in extremely valuable and exotic information. Durak feels that if anyone has heard about the Moonbird, it will be S'Rashi.
The gate guard said Count Hosni is at his manor house with <<1>>, his betrothed. I should talk to him, see if I can get close to the Dream Shard.
King Emeric gave me an invitation to Count Hosni's betrothal celebration. I should take it to a guard to gain entry to the at-Tura estate.

Hosni-Abd-Tura's guards accepted S'Rashi's letter and allowed me entry to his estate. A guard said that Hosni is busy at the moment, but suggested I speak with his wife, Tahra. I'll find her in Hosni's manse at the center of the estate.

Hosni's wife, Tahra, demanded a favor before I could speak to Hosni. She asked I retrieve a rare Altmer statue of Auri-El from ruins to the northwest of her estate. The team that excavated it apparently fled when attacked by something in the ruins.
I retrieved the statue of Auri-El from the ruins as Tahra requested. If I wish to speak with Hosni-Abd-Tura about the Moonbird, I should return it to her at the Abd-Tura estate.
I have paid S'Rashi's steep fee, and he has promised to tell me what he knows about the fate of the missing Moonbird. If I wish to know more, I should speak to him.
I have retrieved the Moonbird from Hosni-Abd-Tura. It now rides in my pack in the form of an egg. If I wish to stop The Fervor, I must return the egg to Durak at Pariah Abbey.
Hosni-Abd-Tura has agreed to haggle with me over the price of the Moonbird. If I wish to retrieve the Moonbird from Hosni, I will have to deal with him.

Hosni-Abd-Tura has offered to trade me the Moonbird if I collect a wyvern egg and bring it to him. Wyverns nest on the cliffs north of his estate.nnAlternately, I can find out where Hosni is keeping the Moonbird and steal it.
I've collected an intact wyvern egg. If I return it to Hosni-Abd-Tura at his retreat in western Menevia, he will trade me the egg for the Moonbird.

Hosni-Abd-Tura has traded me the wyvern egg I collected for the Moonbird. He told me his men brought the Moonbird's cage to the pool behind his estate. If I wish to collect the Moonbird, I should look for it there.
I have retrieved the Moonbird from Hosni-Abd-Tura. It now rides in my pack in the form of an egg. If I wish to stop The Fervor, I must return the egg to Durak at Pariah Abbey.
I've cast the insignia into the fire, destroying them completely. I should tell King Ranser the dying soldier's last words.
A dying soldier wants me to gather insignia of service from the bodies of his fallen comrades on the tor.
I've collected the soldiers' insignia. I should defiantly cast them into the fire near King Ranser.
When I touched General Dathieu's remains, a magical explosion blinded me. Dathieu said I would see their fate with my own eyes. I should explore the tor to see what he described.
Chancellor Karine, a noble from Wayrest, seeks any information that may help her find the Crown of Ranser. I should tell her of General Datheiu's ghost.
Chancellor Karine has asked me to deliver the newly recovered Crown of Ranser directly to Wayrest. She said to give it to Chancellor Regina, who will be expecting me.
I need to save the Book of Circles and Christophe from the Supernal Dreamers. Christophe may know how I can release him from their sorcery.
A ghost appeared to me after I had banished several wraiths and seemed to ask for my help. I should ask Reges if he knows who this General is.
A peasant told me a rumor about a place called the "Slave Pits," north of Shornhelm. I should search the area for any surviving witnesses.
I've brought a witness of Montclair's atrocities back to Eselde Tamrith.
The survivor I found was badly injured, and is dying slowly. I need to take him back to one of the noble houses quickly, before he expires, so he can tell them his story.
I've brought a witness of Montclair's atrocities back to Alard Dorell.
Now that I've saved Christophe, I should meet him at the entrance to the Moonlit Maw.
By helping Christophe escape, I will prevent the Supernal Dreamers from using Ahtah's Book of Circles as a weapon. Unfortunately, doing so means I cannot recover the Book.
I will retrieve Ahtah's Book of Circles. While Christophe will perish, the Book will be returned to its rightful owner and used as an instrument of learning rather than death.
Duke Nathanial has asked me to decide whether Sir Hughes should be set free or executed for the murder of Lakana.
Sir Hughes has asked me to report to Duke Nathaniel in Alcaire Keep.
The survivor I found was badly injured, and is dying slowly. I need to take him back to one of the noble houses quickly, before he expires, so he can tell them his story.
A peasant told me a rumor about a place called the "Slave Pits," north of Shornhelm. I should search the area for any surviving witnesses.
I've brought a witness of Montclair's atrocities back to Eselde Tamrith.
I've brought a witness of Montclair's atrocities back to Alard Dorell.
I must burn Ranser's skeleton. That will awaken his spectre. If I can defeat him, I can finally put the ghosts of this war to rest.
I've destroyed King Ranser's wraith. Now I should return to General Dathieu at the tower in the center of the tor.

I've found the missing excavators, and they've repaired the damaged sections of the lift. Unfortunately, a massive construct is blocking the way forward. If it can be defeated, Tahra may be able to reactivate the lift.
I've filled Tahra's memory stone by examining machinery within Volenfell. I should return to her with the stone.
I have retrieved the Resplendent Pearl of Zeht and should return to Arzedram.
I have delivered the gyroscopes to Artificer J'neth. I should collect my reward from him.
Derrick has given me the teleportation rune. He's asked me to find Verandis. nnVendaris desperately needs this artifact. I'll search the Doomcrag and hope he's still alive.
A Ravenwatch Guard said Verandis pushed through towards the Doomcrag with a small scounting party. I should journey to the top and make sure he made it safely.
I should report back to Mul near Camp Gavaudon.
I have burned tents and killed centaurs at the camp near Bjoulsae Dam. I should return to Ghara and report what I have done.
<<1>>'s home is near the Bjoulsae River, southeast of Wind Keep. According to Jacques, Velain is a Daedra worshipper.
I need to find Master Noleon's tools at the Ogre Camp and take them back for him. The tools may be scattered throughout the camp.
I should locate Noleon Velain and return these tools to him.
<<1>> is defeated, and the Lightless Remnants are no more. In the end, <<2>> sacrificed his life to destroy them. I should return to the base of the <<3>> and let <<4>> know what happened.
Now that I've entered the pinnacle of the <<1>>, I must find a way to destroy the Lightless Remnants that fuel Karnosis Xane's power.
The ogres can be found to the north of the dam in Gavaudon.nnMul told me that if I kill the Ogre Patriarchs the other ogres will become demoralized and run away.
I managed to talk Lierre out of taking action against <<1>>. I should tell the doctor of his unsatisfied customer.
Lierre has asked me to pick up a cure for his wife from <<1>> in Hallowed Refuge.
I've picked up the cure from <<1>>. I should administer it to Charlotte as soon as possible.
Lierre is consumed by grief. I think he might do something reckless if I don't stop him.
Lierre ran off after his wife died. I think he's going to confront the merchant who sold him that false cure.
Jacel Thorin in Wayrest should be quite excited to see the Dwemer Map Fragment.
I destroyed the bodies around <<1>>, ensuring that the victims would not rise again as undead.
I need to search <<1>> and burn any corpses I find.

General Dathieu ordered me to go to the central tower and "get ready for a retreat." He's reliving the battle where he betrayed and killed King Ranser.nnI should see if the ghost of General Dathieu is in the tower. He'll know what to do next.
Azura's Winged Twilight gave me a Duskstone I can use to enter King Emeric's dream. I must return to Wayrest and check in with Abbot Durak.
After drinking Master Noleon's potion, I entered a vision of Moonshadow. Now I must find the Winged Twilight, who can tell me how to summon Azura.
Once I've gathered sufficient Glow Dust from the Will-O-the_Wisps, I must place it on the altar at Azura's Shrine to begin the summoning.
I gathered the Glow Dust and used the altar at Azura's Shrine.
Ahtah asked me to look into the theft of his Book of Circles and the disappearance of his apprentices.nnHe suggested I begin my search in his study, which is below Durak's tower in Pariah Abbey.

Apprentice Lachay believes Christophe and Makana fought in Ahtah's study, and Rin tried to stop them. Lachay also believes one of the three stole Ahtah's Book of Circles.nnA Spirit Guard patrolling Pariah Abbey's walls may know more.

A Spirit Guard witnessed a scuffle below Pariah Abbey. A mob attacked three figures fighting at the crossroad.nnPart of the mob headed off toward Baelbrone. If I wish to find Rin, Makana, and Christophe, I must start my search there.

With the help of some strong, determined spirits, Reezal-Jul's abomination was destroyed. Sadly, Crestshade is now a ruin as well. I should tale to the mayor one last time before she departs this world.

The mayor's spirit wants to rally the dead of Crestshade to destroy the abomination stalking the streets. She also wants to pass on the tale of what happened here. I must find the accounts written by the town's healer and mage.
I've located several documents that detail Montclair forging a new alliance with an unknown ally. I should return to Scarlette and show her the orders.
Scarlette believes Montclair's men might be carrying their orders. I need to find a complete set of his orders.

I should search the northern district of <<1>> for any sign of citizens being held by Montclair. Zeli mentioned a jailer held their keys, and she saw walls of stone. I'll concentrate my search on stone buildings.
I've freed all but one of the prisoners in Montclair's holding cells. I should search the basement for the last prisoner.

I should tell <<1>> that I've freed captured peasants from Montclair's jail, but I haven't discovered why he was holding them captive. She'll be near the broken wall separating the northern district from the rest of the <<2>>.

Lob gro-Bug offered me a chance to become a Hammerdeath gladiator. If I do, I'll be paid well, I'll have free run of the arena. He gave me a token to take to his brother, Mar gro-Bug, in the stands of Hammerdeath.

I've defeated three gladiators. I should bring news of my triumph to Log gro-Bug. He's enjoying the spectacle and basking in glory next to the gladiator arena. He's promised to initiate me as one of the Champions of Hammerdeath.
Ghara asked me to travel to the camp in northeast of the dam. She wants me to burn their tents and kill a number of the centaurs there.
I've destroyed the <<1>>, and should inform <<2>>. He told me to meet him in a rowboat northwest of the Imperial Landing beach.
Rin told me that if I can free her son Tahn from Moric Nirin, she'll leave Hammerdeath Arena. If I want to help her and her son, I must deal with Moric Nirine.

Moric Nirine will trade me Rin and her son, Tahn, if I collect the souls of five Daedra in a soulstone he gave me. To do this, I must weaken Daedra and focus the stone's power on them.nnOr, I can simply buy Rin and Tahn's freedom by bribing him.
I have collected five Daedric souls in Moric's soulstone. If I return the soulstone to him, he will trade it for Rin and her son, Tahn.
As a result of my efforts, Moric Nirine has freed Rin and her son, Tahn. I'll find them at the gate to Hammerdeath Arena.
I should check the road to make sure the Swamp Cypress moved.
I need to deliver the Moondrop Mold to Aenlin at the Sunlight Stair to the northeast of Man-Grove Swamp.
I must slay Slouchbears and collect their Flanks for Cinas.
Cinas asked me to "commune" with the Swamp Cypress and ask it to move...
I need to speak with the Forest Spirit to the north of Cinas' outpost.
Now that I have the Seedling, I must place it near the Large Cypress tree to the east of the Forest Spirit.
Saproot Seedlings grow all along Haven Trace trail, northeast of Southpoint.
<<1>> is in Haven Trace East, just off the main road.

Battlereeve Alengwe says that Maormer Incendiaries carry Kindlepitch Sacks that can be used to destroy the docks and ship hulls.nnA Maormer Incendiary can be found in the Maormer Palisade and patrolling along the bay to the west.
<<1>> gave me a sack of Kindlepitch, which I can use to set crates of <<2>> on fire.nnThe supplies can be found along the western shore of the Imperial Landing beach.
The Swamp Cypress would not move because it was protecting a Seedling that fell in the road. I need to pick the Seedling out of the road.
I need to talk to the Forest Spirit.
I'm supposed to collect samples of tainted flesh from creatures in the area north of Oldgate. Harpies are an obvious source.
I've collected samples of what might be "tainted flesh" for <<1>>. He's at a small camp west of Oldgate, waiting to analyze what I've found.

Captain Gagnon sent me to find survivors of the massacre on the Wracked Plain.nnBy finding and helping those who are left, I can hopefully help the captain discover the truth about what happened there.
Lieutenant Fairfax wants me to take word of Montclair's treachery to Captain Gagnon at Oldgate.
Now I have proof that Montclair was behind the massacre on the Wracked Plain. I can let Lieutenant Fairfax know his suspicions were correct.
He's offered his "pension," the contents of a chest under his bed, in exchange for the deaths of Montclair's men.
As Linbright requested, I've slain a number of Montclair's men. His "pension" can be found in the militia barracks in Shornhelm.
I've found Tharlas Beaulade's ring. I must return it to his ghost and let him know the deed has been done.
I must destroy the bloodfiends stalking nearby to find Tharlas' ring
The Stormwitches are north of the ship Battlereeve Faerwael and his Altmer are unloading from.nnFaerwal wants me to attack the Maormer Stormwitches when I reach the shore.
Narela is in the village of Southpoint, north of the Altmer landing beach.nnI've killed several Stormwitches, and should report in to Narela.
Imperial camps can be found along Haven Trace, a trail northeast of Southpoint. I should place the traps outside the camps.
Imperial camps can be found along Haven Trace, a trail northeast of Southpoint. I should place the traps outside the camps.
Lolbor Sapfingers is on the east end of Haven Trace, northwest of Haven
The abomination has been destroyed. I should talk to the mayor to verify that this will enable the spirits' safe passage into the afterlife.
Tahra may know of a place to take the Dwemer Map Fragment.
Tahra has suggested that I deliver the Dwemer Map Fragment to Jacel Thorin in Wayrest, Ilian Elante in Elden Root, or Ulare Telvanni in Mournhold.

Hosni said Durak is waiting for me at the east gate of his estate, by the stables. Now that I have the Dream Shard, I should return it to Durak. Together, we must find a way to stop Vaermina and the Fervor.
I've entered Hosni abd-Tura's dream, where I can destroy the Omen of Blood. Durak will guide me as best he can.
I've awakened from the dream. The Omen of Blood has been destroyed. Now I can return the Dream Shard to Durak.
Tahra may know of a place to take the Dwemer Map Fragment.
Ilian Alanwe in Elden Root should be quite excited to see the Dwemer Map Fragment.
Tahra has suggested that I deliver the Dwemer Map Fragment to Ilian Alanwe in Elden Root.
Tahra may know of a place to take the Dwemer Map Fragment.
UIare Telvanni in Mournhold should be quite excited to see the Dwemer Map Fragment.
Tahra has suggested that I deliver the Dwemer Map Fragment to Ulare Telvanni in Mournhold.

I should find the wagons Calden spoke of in the northern district of Shornhelm. I'll see if they contain bodies. Even if they don't, burning them would send a message to Lord Montclair that House Dorell will not stand for his treason.
I've burned several of Montclair's wagons, which were indeed full of corpses. I should return to <<1>> at the western entrance of the Northern District and let him know the rumors were true.
The guardian of the Bonebarrow, <<1>>, has appeared at last! I should talk to him.
When I touched Sir Hughes the world around me shifted and changed. I found myself back at Alcaire Keep. I feel as though I am inside a dream. I should look around for a familiar face.

Rin does not know if Makana or Christophe are still alive, but the Spirit Guard at Pariah Abbey did see someone else dragged off to Baelbrone.nnIf I investigate Baelbrone, I may find either Makana or Christophe there.
The Lungfungus Golion needs can be found in the upper tunnels of Netherhaven.
Golion can be found beneath the village of Haven, overlooking the Pit of Stars.nnI should bring him the reagents I've gathered.
Imperial camps can be found along Haven Trace, a trail northeast of Southpoint. I should place the traps outside the camps.
I should speak to the boatman at the docks west of Northpoint, so I can travel to the Doomcrag.

Lieutenant Fairfax knows the troops that ambushed his regiment can only be Montclair's, but Gagnon will want proof. I might be able to find evidence among the bodies. I may even find a live soldier to question somewhere on the Wracked Plain.

Tahra in Volenfell has asked me to help in finding her lost team of excavators. Three of them should be in the upper level of Volenfell, and rescuing them may be the key to reaching the depths of the ruin.
Master Noleon seems to know how I can go to Moonshadow, Azura's realm, and speak with her messenger, Winged Twilight.
Fairfax asked me to find the rogue Magis Order soldier, Heloise Menoit and kill her.  She was last seen east of the Wracked Plain.
Lieutenant Fairfax will want to know of Heloise Menoit's death, and that the rest of his troops are safe from her.
Lieutenant Fairfax will want to know of Heloise Menoit's death, and of the staff she left for her squire.
I need to get a wounded Magis Order soldier to Captain Gagnon in Oldgate, south of the Wracked Plain.
Captain Gagnon can now treat the injured soldier at Oldgate,
I must collect Moondrop Mold in the Man-Grove Swamp.
I destroyed the Fatesinger and should return to King Faume Toad-Eye.
I have been given an exilir to use on Montclair's direwolves after I've wounded them. They should be in Shornhelm's northern district.
I've used the potions on the wolves and gotten some interesting effects. I should return to Perrine at House Dorell's headquarters and report my results.

Makana confirmed what Rin said. Christophe stole the Book of Circles.nnMakana remembers being kept at shrine east of Pariah Abbey before he came to Baelbrone. He asked me to look for Christophe and the Book of Circles there.

Rin confirmed what Makana said. Christophe stole the Book of Circles.nnRin was in and out of consciousness while her captors brought her to Hammerdeath Arena. One mentioned the shrine east of Pariah Abbey. Rin suggested I might find out more there.

While chasing Christophe, Rin and her brother, Makana, were attacked by a mob. The mob dragged Rin to Hammerdeath Arena, and she is now certain they dragged her brother, Makana, to Baelbrone.nnShe asked me to go to Baelbrone and look for Makana.

While chasing Christophe, Rin and her brother, Makana, were attacked by a mob. The mob dragged Makana to Baelbrone, and he is now certain they dragged his sister, Rin, to Hammerdeath Arena. nnHe asked me to go to Hammerdeath Arena and look for Rin.
I need to destroy the Fatesinger.
I should find someone from the Stenric family and return the shield to them.
The Imperials and cultists entered the house on the northeastern end of Haventown with the design sheet of the Infernal Device. I should find the design to learn what the device is designed to do.
I should take the design sheet to Conul. He is on the northern edge of Haventown.
I've collected the heirloom Manard requested. I should deliver it to him.
He wants me to collect one of the heirlooms from the underground barrows. I suppose it couldn't hurt to do as he asks.
The graverobbers are gone, the remains have been returned, and Marienne has been sent away. Now I should talk to Gerard and make sure he thinks we're done here.
Zeli asked me to speak to villagers residing inside House Tamrith. She believes that by talking to them, I may relieve them of their nightmares.

One of the infected had already turned on the other, killing him at the inn. The other waited at the top of the watchtower. Both had been turned. It was too late for them. I should return to Zeli with this news.
Tahra has requested that I take her memory stone into the lower ruins of Volenfell and examine machinery within.
I've killed the wolf that attacked Edren. Hopefully, Edren will believe that killing the wolf released his soul from the beast's curse.
The wolf tore off Edren's sleeve during the fight. If I can track and kill the wolf carrying that sleeve, perhaps Edren will be put at ease.
A villager turned by the disease attacked House Tamrith, but was quickly stopped. I should speak to Zeli to find out if she knows what's going on.
I must use the Chokeweed on the valves above each doorway in the center of the room. To reach the valve, I must propel myself above the door using the steam in the center of the room.
I was able to destroy the Infernal Device! Golion will want to hear of my success.

I've managed to convince Del that his son was already transformed before we got to him. This seems to have calmed him down. He's promised to stop speaking out against House Dorell. nnI should return to Alard.
Del Vinyar is at the inn. I've been asked to take care of him with my "usual methods." I could try to speak to him to calm him down. Then again, I could just poison his drink while he's away from it.
Del is dead, his words of hatred against House Dorell silenced forever. I should return to Alard.
Anglir Ancientwood can be found wandering the boughs of the graht oak of Elden Bole.nnI need to persuade Anglir to support Prince Aeradan against the invading Tharns.
Anglir should be able to tell me where to find the next Treethane I need to speak to.
<<1>> gave me several Welkynd stones to place on the Ayleid columns scattered north of Oldgate.
I've placed Audry's <<1>>s  in the <<2>>s around Oldgate. I should let her know Oldgate's defenses has been strengthened.
The Winged Twilight asked me to meet her atop the westernmost tower in Aphren's Hold, west of the Weeping Giant. Once there, she will tell me how to end the obsession and madness in Stormhaven.
I've entered Chieftain Godrun's dreams. Now I must find and defeat the Omen of Counting Stars.
I poisoned Del's drink while he was away. After taking a swig of it, he went to his room... and died shortly thereafter. nnI should return to Perrine.
Roublerub can be found at one of the bars in Jolly Squallor, on the east side of Elden Root.nnI should speak to the Treethane Roublerub to determine where his loyalties lie.
Roublerub can be found at the Mossy Hole tavern in Jolly Squalor.nnI've released Shadowhiskers as Roublerub asked. I should return to secure his pledge of loyalty to Aerdan.
I should tell the Cinderfen wolfmother spirit that corpses no longer pose a threat to the barrow wolves.
In telling me to get "a flame" from the "great fire of the town," I can assume the mother-wolf meant the forge at Hoarfrost Downs, where I can get a burning tinder.

Shadowhiskers is being held at the Thorns' headquarters on the east side of the Jolly Sqalor.nnTreethane Roublerub has agreed to pledge his people's loyalty to Aeradan if I can rescue his associate Shadowhiskers from the Thorn Gang.
I've located an old, faded note with a few legible words. I should find someone who knows more about this note.
Shadowhiskers is standing nearby while I sit helpless in his trap. I should talk to him in order to connive a way out.
Queen Ayarynne will be waiting in the Thalmor building of Elden Root. I should inform her of Sorcassil's treachery at once.
The secret contact will be waiting in Jolly Squalor, the most dangerous section of Elden Root.
I've put the sickened cows out of their misery. This should make the herds much safer from the Carrion Harpies.
I should cull any sickened or weak cows on the Ruined Steppe.
Treethane Orthendor asked me to destroy the Support Pillars in the Fire Veins.
I must report to Cannonreeve Sorcassil in Thalmore.
I should go to the throne room to speak with High King Emeric.

There's a chance the villagers freed from the slave pits are infected with this spreading disease. Two of the villagers left the protection of House Tamrith when they got back. I should check at the inn and watchtower for any signs of them.
It won't be long before Irne or Ghak gro-Urish does something drastic. Normar wants to evict one of them, but he can't decide. This can't go on. I should give the eviction letter to one of them.
I've given Irne his notice of eviction from Fell's Run. I should tell Normar that I've solved his Breton problem.
I've given Ghak gro-Urish his notice of eviction from Fell's Run. I should tell Normar that I've solved his Orc problem.
Irne has asked me to speak with Normar on his behalf. His farmland was given to an Orc, and he wants it back.
I've defeated <<1>> and <<2>> and dissipated their souls. That should disrupt Karnosis' plans long enough for me to confront him. I should continue my trek up the <<3>> and find Verandis.
I've found <<1>> and <<2>> on the second level of the <<3>>. I must defeat them before I can get to <<4>> on the spire's top level.
I've collected enough planar essence. Now I can use the ward to summon Verandis inside the Merging Planes.
I've destroyed several of the cult's altars. I should report back to one of the scouts outside the steppe.
I've been asked to defile altars consecrated for necromancy. I'll find the stone slabs scattered across the Ruined Steppe.
I have found the missing excavators, but it seems their repairs have activated a Dwemer machine, the Guardian of Volenfell. To go any deeper, I'll need to defeat the Guardian.
Take the gylph to  Battlereeve Sorcassil at the Thalmor in Elden Root.
I have defeated Shadwhiskers in battle. He now appears willing to give up the information I need, so I should speak with him immediately.
Queen Ayarynne will be waiting in the Thalmor building of Elden Root. I should inform her of Sorcassil's treachery at once.
I have the Duskstone, so I can enter Emeric's Dream.
I've been transported to a shrine of the Daedric Prince Vaermina. Though she isn't visible, her voice whispers in my ear.

If I retrieve the skull of Galthis from the dream world, Vaermina has promised to trouble Stormhaven no more.nnGalthis is the traitor who brought the Omens to Stormhaven, and who seeks to destroy the Daggerfall Covenant.
I must enter the palace and kill the Night Terror so I can rescue High King Emeric from this dream.
Fairfax asked me to find the rogue Magis Order soldier Heloise Menoit and somehow ensure she does not continue attacking her own troops.nnShe was last seen east of the Wracked Plain.

Heloise was obviously turning into a bloodfiend. Though she wanted to flee to a place where she couldn't hurt anyone, I convinced her that the only safe choice was death. She drank a poison that ended her life, swiftly and painlessly.
I've spoken to Leah. She's obsessed with her research on vampirism. I should let Tristan know. Maybe he'll use this to his advantage.
Tristan has asked me to speak to Leah Ohms and find out more about her. He wants to find out what interests her so he can win her heart.
I should take the unsigned covenant to <<1>> in <<2>> and see if he's willing to accept it.
I've gathered enough wickwheat. I need to deliver it to <<1>> in the Horsemen's village.
He said I can find grain for Sagert the Elder along the valley southwest of Oldgate.
I've collected all the ingredients for the potion. I should return to Tristan back at the Ravenwatch hideout.

I've been asked to collect spirit breath from lost souls, skeleton dust from the rotting skeletons, and a vial of blood from the blood guardians. All of them wander the tunnels of Shornhelm's undercity.

Durak asked me to journey to Wind Keep in Gavaudon and speak with Lord Mathias Raiment, a former Spirit Warden. Lord Raiment may know more about the situation in Gavaudon, and the affliction caused by its Omen.
When I entered Wind Keep, I came across a young girl of obvious nobility. Perhaps she knows where I can find Lord Mathias Raiment.
