Now that I've gotten pure grain I can take it to Sagert the Elder at the Horsemen's clan settlement to the southwest of Oldgate.nnSagert will be near the caves in the hills.
Lieutenant Fairfax asked me to convey the order to retreat to the Magis Order Sergeants left in the field.  nnI'll probably find them somewhere in the Wracked Plain to the north of Oldgate.
I found several Magis Order regiments on the Wracked plain and gave them Lieutenant Fairfax' orders to retreat to Oldgate.

Tristan has run off towards Montclair's castle using the tunnels of Shornhelm. He hopes that if Montclair infects him, he'll turn into a vampire and return to Leah as her lover. I should go after him to make sure he's ok.
Tristan has run off towards Montclair's castle. He's running through Shornhelm's tunnels. I should go after him. If I can't remember the way to the manor, I'll speak to Leah.

I've found Tristan.nnHe's been infected, but it's the wrong type of disease. One of the bloodfiends wounded him. His life is in danger. He has no chance of turning into a vampire. nnI've sent him back to the Ravenwatch, so I can search for a cure.

I've found Tristan and he's been infected. The problem is it's the wrong type of disease. One of the Bloodfiends wounded him and his life is in danger with no hopes of turning into a vampire. I've sent him back to the Ravenwatch to search for a cure.
Sagert the Elder blessed the grain I brought. He wants me to feed it to helhests on the Wracked Plain, north of Oldgate. I may have to beat them into submission before they accept it from me.

Thanks to the blessed grain, helhests are transforming back into horses. Sagert the Elder was right. Once I subdued them, they accepted the grain from my hand.nnI should let Sagert know of my success.
I have freed Mul. Now he has asked me to meet him at Camp Gavaudon to help him deal with the ogres there.
Mul is awaiting execution at the Bjoulse Dam. Ghara has asked me to go east to the Bjoulse Dam and rescue him.
Sagert the Elder asked me to escort some horses to Oldgate. Hotspur should still be there. He can see that they're properly tended.
We need to stop <<1>> and the soldiers in his patrol.
I killed Lieutenant Thierry and his patrol. They were stronger and faster than any normal creatures should be. Whatever is corrupting the creatures of Rivenspire must have corrupted them.
Elden Bole is the largest graht-oak of Elden Root, found on the southern edge of the mesa.nnTreethane Orthendor has taken his Senche-Tiger, Helethrun, for a walk among the roots of Elden Bole.
I've found Treethane Orthendor in the depths of the Fire-Veins beneath Elden Root.
The Winged Twilight gave me a sleeping scroll to read when I reach <<1>> within Aphren's tomb. Then I'll enter Godrun's dreams and confront the Omen of Counting Stars.
Sorcassil is believed to be hiding out in the haunted town of Gil-Var-Delle, in the north east corner of Valenwood.nnI must confront him there and mete out justice for his wrongdoings.
I pardoned Sorcassil in exchange for information about the Eye of Molag Bal. Queen Ayarynne will be awaiting my return at the Thalmor building, in Elden Root.
I should check with one of the families in Fell's Run to make sure everyone made it home safely.
I should search around the Fellwatch camp for kidnapped peasants and convince them to escape.
Tristan has run off into Shornhelm's tunnels to find Montclair. I should talk to Leah. Maybe I can learn how he plans to getting inside the castle. Maybe she knows where I might find him.

Leah gave me some directions to Montclair's castle. If I head right from the entrance of the Ravenwatch hideout and continue north, I can skulk under the walls of his castle. I should be able to enter from there.
I recovered and returned the valuables stolen from the people of Fell's Run.
I need to return the stolen valuables to peasants around Fell's Run before they turn on each other.
Treethane Orthendor's lodgings are southeast of The Soak.nnRoublerub directed me to speak with Orthendor, a Treethane of great nobility.
I have taken Sorcassil's money and let him go free. Queen Ayarynne will be awaiting my return at the Thalmor building, in Elden Root.
I have slain Sorcassil. Queen Ayarynne will be awaiting my return at the Thalmor building, in Elden Root.
<<1>> commands the Eledrim Camp at the southern base of Leaftower.nnI should give him the names of the loyalists within Leaftower.
Catian Teideius lives in the upper branches of Leaftower.nnElladrel said there's more than one way into his home, but I should be wary of his bodyguard.
Elladrel can be found at the base of Leaftower.nnCatian Teideius has been killed. I must inform Elladrel.
<<1>>, leader of the loyalists in Leaftower, lives at the base of the giant tree.nnI should talk to her, so that she can help me locate other supporters of Prince Aeradan.
Leah has asked me to speak to Verandis. Maybe I can find a way to help Tristan awaken from his torporous state.
Tristan's spirit has returned to his body. He appears to be recovering. Leah is still worried. I should speak to her.
I've slain some of the bandits around Fell's Run. Hopefully, this will send a clear message that this behavior will not be tolerated.
I should search Northpoint's southern coast for any sign of Elise. If I run into any Nords on the way, Thomas will be glad if I slay them as well.
I've found Elise, though she didn't want to return to the safety of Northpoint. I should let Thomas know.
The Northpoint guard sent me to tell the Duchess about the Nords' plan for a direct attack on NorthpointnnThe Duchess is in Northpoint, making plans in the Great Keep.
I've come across an old amulet with the initials "S.D." on it. It came from a pile of jewelry in the tunnels of Shornhelm. I should find out who has those initials.
Verandis told me to investigate the mansion on Lord Montclair's estate. I should look for anything unusual within it.
I've found the golden locket Verandis spoke of, after slaying the wraith of <<1>>. I should speak to him and have him explain his role in the death of this woman.
I've spoken to gra-Orgak. He's adamant that Sidrey is stealing her grazing lands.
The Duchess has asked me to raise Northpoint's standard on Pilot Island. The Nords camped there on the northeastern island may object, but their occupation is over.
The duchess asked me to find Adienne and let her know she's safe. She has probably arrived at the manor by now.
I should talk to gra-Orgak to see what this feud is all about. She's over in the Smallholds, just south of Fell's Run.
I should let Arniel know his cows have returned to their corral.
If I ring Arniel's cowbell near the highland cows, the ones that belong to him should go running home.

Verandis told me that Tristan's spirit has left his body. Now it wanders the tunnels of Shornhelm. What it seeks, we do not know. Verandis asked me to find Tristan's lost soul. Maybe we'll find a way to make Tristan's body and spirit whole again.
I've branded some of the cattle on the Ruined Steppe. That should be a clear indicator of which cattle belong to <<1>> and which belong to <<2>>.
I'm going to brand some of the Highland cattle grazing on the farmlands near Fell's Run. The branding iron must be heated in a campfire before I can use it. A cold branding iron won't work.
I should find and stop the Fellwatch Inductees harassing the people of Fell's Run however I can.
I need to stop Fellwatch recruits from harassing the people of Fell's Run.
I should find and stop the Fellwatch Inductees harassing the people of Fell's Run however I can.
I've ended Jolie's suffering and ended her life. I should return to Tildus to give him the news.

Scarlette belongs to the resistance group known as the Ravenwatch. She supplied me with a healing tonic to bring back to Jolie. She insisted that I hurry, however, as the infected woman could turn at anytime.

I was not in time to save Tildus. It looks as Jolie was turned by the Blood Fever and killed her husband. There are no signs of her near the site. I should return to their home and inform the Ravenwatch scout.
Tildus, Jolie's husband, has asked me to attempt to convince her there may be a cure for Blood Fever. He's heard rumors that a "resistance" in the tunnels of Shornhelm may hold that knowledge.

I've convinced Jolie that there might be a cure for Blood Fever. Tildus believes the Resistance in the tunnels of Shornhelm may hold the remedy. I should seek them out to find if there is truth to this rumor.
I managed to give Jolie the healing tonic in time, hopefully curing the blood fever. She seems to already be regaining her strength from the looks of things. I should speak to Tildus nearby.
Scarlette of the resistance group known as the Ravenwatch supplied me with a healing tonic to bring back to Jolie. She insisted that I hurry however, as the infected woman could turn at anytime.
I've agreed to end Jolie's suffering before she could possibly turn into a bloodfiend and injures her husband. She's asked me to meet her at the eastern watchtower and end her life.
I should search the fields south of Northpoint for farmers or farmhands who are willing to defend their homes from the invading Gripdjur corsairs.
I was successful in recruiting farmers for Northpoint. I should let Gregoire know. He's at the gates of Northpoint.

Thomas Edrald's son Andrew was captured by the Nords.  His father thinks he might still be alive, and wants me to go and free him.  nnAndrew is most likely in one of the camps along the coast where the Nords moor their longboats.
I've rescued Andrew Robic. Thomas Robic will want to hear about the safe recovery of his son. His farmhouse is southeast of Northpoint.
According to Lord Henri, I cannot pay the one gold tax for these people; they must pay themselves. The penalty for non-payment is death.
I've collected tax tokens from several of Wind Keep's citizens. Once I give these to Lord Henri Manteau, the citizens will no longer be under a death threat.
I've collected tax tokens from several of Wind Keep's citizens. Once I give these to Lord Henri Manteau, the citizens will no longer be under a death threat.
I should take a closer look at Countess Ilise's mirror.
I rescued <<1>> from her mirror. Now that her mind is clear, I should speak to her about what happened.
The Ironhand Shaman at the ogre encampment to the west of Camp Gavaudon can be drawn out by defacing a totem there.
I have killed the Ironhand Ogre Shaman. I should report back to Mul.
Imperials can be found in camps spread across Haven Trace Trail, northeast of Southpoint.
<<1>> is in Haven Trace West, just off the road.
I should let gro-Thorkan know I've announced the new town charter to the people of Fell's Run.
I can help bring peace to Fell's Run by putting up copies of the new town charter on empty placards around town.
Elladrel Stillwaters is at her house, on the southern side of Leaftower's foot.nnI've delivered the Digging Tools to the Camoran loyalists. Elladrel should be told.
There are three loyalists within Leaftower; Tivel, Chirrup, and Prattle. I should deliver Digging Tools to each of them.
<<1>> bloom within the Grove of the Living Dead, which lies southwest across the river from Residue.
<<1>> is in the refugee camp of Residue.nnI've collected the Asphodel Seeds, and should return them to her.
Derick of the Ravenwatch asked me to keep an eye out for a mysterious "woman in white" wandering through Shornhelm's tunnels. If I see her, I should let them know.
I attempted to contact the lost spirit of a woman wandering the halls of the undercity. I should report back to Derick at the Ravenwatch outpost.
Duchess Elviane asked me to burn the Nord's supplies all along Northpoint's coast. She hopes it will interfere wtih any plans they have to lay siege to Northpoint.
I've set fire to many of the Nord's supplies along the coast. I should let Adienne know the duchess has put the first part of her plan in motion.
I must plant the Seedling in the Mound of Dirt beneath the White Swamp Cypress in the Mangrove Swamp.

An Imperial Dispatch would be carried by Imperial Messengers, who travel between the Imperial camps along Haven Trace trail.nnThe Messengers employ stealth as they travel the trails, so locating one may prove difficult.
<<1>>s can be found at any Aldmeri Dominion outpost in Valenwood.
I should travel back to the Bjoulse Dam, in the eastern part of Stormhaven, and search Godrun's tent for anything which might overshadow his obsession with the dam.
In Godrun's tent I found letters from his wife. Perhaps speaking of her will make Godrun want to see her again.
Godrun decided to return to Orsinium after I spoke with him about his wife. He asked me to inform Borkul that he may take over command of the Blackmauls.

She believes the talisman she found on one of Montclair's soldiers may hold the key to their power. She's asked me to collect more of their dark magic with the talisman, so I can find out how to use it.
When I brought the talisman to her, Scarlette attacked me. After I defeated her, <<1>> arrived. I should talk to him.
To meet the spirit, we'll need to head up the stairs and out to the east. Scarlette said she'd be right behind us.
We've stopped the spirit of Jon Murloe for now, but he vowed we would see him again at the Doomcrag. Scarlette asked me to meet her back at the Raven's Den inside the tunnels of Shornhelm.
Tor was sent to the northwest near the Imperial Palisade.
Gammer Robins in Northpoint says her granddaughter has gone missing in the giants' home, Breagha-Fin.
I rescued Sanda from the clutches of a vampiric necromancer named Veraya. I should leave Breagha-Fin. Then I can make sure Sanda escaped safely.
I should destroy the Spectral Overseers and see if I can find a key to disable the necromantic focus in the cave. It seems to be the cause of the giants going mad.
After freeing several giants from the enslaving powers of the strange crystals, one of them decided not to flee immediately.nnI should listen what the giant has to say.
After freeing several giants from the enslaving powers of the strange crystals, one of them decided not to flee immediately.nnI should listen what the giant has to say.
Caius Fullo asked me to retrieve his troops' standard. He's alluded to a grisly scene of carnage surrounding it in a small town east of Oldgate.
I found Thierry Gagnon's standard in the middle of the Moira's Hope massacre. I should bring this back to <<1>>.
The Ravenwatch scout said I should walk up to the <<1>>, so I can see for myself what's happening up above.

The second glyph of the Doomcrag is also in the upper corridors of the spiraling tower. Once I activate it, I can enter the Dark Council's plane of existence. Then I can confront another vampire councilor.
The spirit I spoke to on the ascent to the <<1>> said I should speak to <<2>>. The spirit also warned me to be wary, though I've yet to find out what it meant by that.
Now that I've entered the mirror, I should begin my search for <<1>>.
I should enter Volenfell and find the location of the Pearl of Zeht.
I must return this Statue to its base.
I've collected the harpy trophies Jonne needed for his harpy scarecrow.
Jonne needs harpy talons and feathers to create a gruesome scarecrow to ward the harpies away from the horsemen's village.
Light the Candle at Illira's son's grave. It is outside and down the path.
I've assembled a few harpy scarecrows around the village. I should let <<1>> know.
I've got a selection of "crafting materials." Now I can assemble harpy scarecrows around the horsemen's village.
<<1>> wasn't particular - he said killing any creature in the <<2>> would aid his soldiers. I should encounter more than enough to fill his needs during my ascent towards the <<3>>.
I've killed a large number of creatures in the <<1>>. I should proceed to the camp <<2>> said his forces were going to establish just outside the <<3>> proper.

I've killed the harpy matriach and the next generation of eggs. This will certainly reduce the harpy population in the months to come. I should let the leader of the horsemen know their troubles with the harpies will be less frequent.
If I can find more harpy eggs nearby, I can destroy them.
The <<z:1>> is in the Shrouded Pass to the southwest of the Ravenwatch camp. <<2>> noted the creature is further up the stairs, beyond the spider nests.
The cloak is displayed as a trophy at House Tamrith's base camp.
I've freed the souls <<1>> planned to use in his ritual to awaken whatever evil lies atop the <<2>>. I must speak to <<3>> atop the altar.
Scarlette asked me to enter the <<1>>, find the bodies of her soldiers, and discover what happened to their scout.
I've returned to the ritual site with a lurcher.
I must return this Statue to its base.
I must return this Statue to its base.
I should tell the scout leader what happened to his regiment. He'll probably be with Verandis.
Celeste begged me to hunt down the Ravenwatch Vampires. She doubts any of them can be saved, but there's still a chance.
Some of the Injured Ravenwatch may be able to be saved.
Warden Moreau admitted he stole Warden Thierry's ring, but told me he did it to buy a cure for his wife. She's very sick.nnHe pleaded for me to speak with Warden Thierry instead of arresting him.

Though Warden Thierry treasures his family's ring, he worried for his friend, Warden Moreau, and Moreau's wife, Paulette. She's very sick.nnThierry has asked  me to spare Moreau. It is up to me whether I'll arrest Moreau or not.
I have spoken with Warden Moreau and Warden Thierry. Thierry has asked that I spare Moreau so he may take care of his sick wife, Paulette, and I have agreed. I should let Ormax know of my decision.
I spoke with Warden Moreau, and he agreed to turn himself in. He asked for a moment with Warden Thierry and his wife before he leaves. He also asked me to let Ormax know of his decision.
I spoke with Warden Moreau and Warden Thierry. Thierry asked that I spare Moreau so he could take care of his sick wife. I agreed. I should let Ormax know of my decision.
I refused to give the ring to Didier Panoit, and I was attacked. I still need to find the rightful owner.
I should find the Base upon which this Statue belongs and place it there.
I must return the Statue to its Base in the Imago Serry.
I must return the Statue to its Base in the Imago Serry.
I've lit the torches in the Shrouded Pass, creating a path of light to the top.
I should light any torches I come across while travelling through the Doomcrag.

The Baron has asked me to assassinate the city's master at arms, Adienne Balmont.  I can land this blow against Northpoint, or I can strike against the Baron by killing his servant instead.  nnNow is the time to decide where my true allegiance lies.
The duchess will want to know what happened with the baron. I should return to her and let her know he got her message.
I've helped Baron Chirane assist the Nords in their takeover of Northpoint. Only time will tell the effect this event will have on Northpoint. In the meantime, I need to talk to Baron Chirane.
Seleine asked me to kill Felix Glenan. If I do, she will split the bounty with me.nnSeleine has already located Felix. He's in a camp north of the Forester's Camp.
I killed Felix Glenan. Seleine Brehat is waiting at the Forester's Camp. She will want to hear this news.
If I steal a Red Rook uniform off a Red Rook Poacher, it should allow me to move freely among them as long as I don't get close enough for them to recognize me as an enemy.
The city's garrison key is now in the hands of the Nords. The baron will want the reward I'm carrying for him. He'll be at his home on the northern corner of Northpoint's city square.
I've found a Red Rook Poacher uniform. If I don it, I can blend into the Red Rooks.

The Baron's contact will meet me at the top of Northpoint's lighthouse.  nnThey will exchange the city's garrison key - which would give them a quick and easy way to control all of Northpoint's armaments - for a reward for the Baron.

The Pride of Northpoint sit at four compass points along the city walls of Northpoint. The Minister of Legacy has asked me to retrieve the artifacts and bring them to him. He's assured me he can keep them safe.
I found the four lions of the Pride of Northpoint, despite the ghostly apparitions that attacked me. I should return them to the Minister of Legacy.

I found Tristan lurking in the Doomcrag. He appears to have finally gotten his wish. He's been turned into a vampire, allthough he's struggling to control his powers. I've convinced him to come back with me to Verandis. Maybe we can help him.
I've been asked to enter the Merging Plane to find the survivors of the Ravenwatch scouting party.

I found Tristan lurking in the Doomcrag. He appears to have finally gotten his wish. Someone turned him into a vampire, although he was struggling to control his powers. I offered to end his life, and he accepted. I should go back now.
To win Gaffer Robins's wager, I have to kill sandy mudcrabs before the rest of the sand runs out of his hourglass.
I killed plenty of mudcrabs in the allotted time. I hope Gaffer Robins didn't have plans for that gold.
As soon as I'm ready, I'll tell Gaffer Robins to turn over his hourglass. It doesn't have much sand in it, but there's plenty of mudcrabs.
The entrance to Hainen's Sanctum is at the north end of the Imagerie.nnI should be able to retrieve the book "Varlines and Vartisans" from his library.
The entrance to Hainen's Sanctum is at the north end of the Imagerie.nnThe book "Varlines and Vartisans" should be somewhere in his his library. I need to obtain one specific chapter.
It is written on the sheets that someone by the name of Melodian Liriondion is the owner of this music. I should return this to him if I meet him.
I should gather Oratorio Sheets from the Warbling Zombies that wonder around the bridge northwest of the Isquer Kinhouse.

Wyress Zoe asked me to search the Wyrd Tree's glen for three signs: water, earth, and air.nnAs I touch each sign, I'll summon a spirit of the land. Before I can restore purity to the Wyrd's glen, I have to defend the spirits from Angof's corrruption.

I've summoned the spirits of Water, Earth, and Air, and I've defended them from Angof's corruption. They've purified the Wyrd's glen.nnWyress Zoe is waiting for me at the base of the Wyrd Tree. She'll be eager for this news.
Captain Gagnon has asked me to check on Audry's plan to bolster Oldgate's defenses.
I used Handre's gem to secure the freedom of the packhorse Fadeel. Once Fadeel is set free, Handre's last wish will be fulfilled.
I may be able to convince the Captain of Montclair's Guard to hand over the key without any need of violence. I may wish to speak with them in the Northern District.
Hainen's Sanctum lies at the northern end of The Imagerie.nnI need to recover the stolen Varla lens from Hainen the Deranged.
Talk to Optimate Ianlin in the library south of the Verdant Grove Tower.
Collect Altmer Books from the Animated Books around the library.
Put the Altmer Books away in the Bookshelves in the library.
I've collected enough spider ichor for the blood fever remedy. I should take the ichor to <<1>> at the wayshrine near the Shadowfate Camp.
If I can harvest enough ichor from the spiders around the Shadowfate Camp, <<1>> will be able to create poultices from them for his homemade blood fever cure.
I should speak to the Hosoth, the daedra who stole Isrisa's voice. The daedra awaits on the plateau, across the bridge to the west of Priestess Cerine.
I will confront Hosoth and retrieve Isrisa's voice. The Daedra waits on the plateau, across the bridge to the west of Priestess Cerine.
I have died and must now return to Hosoth to prove death holds no power over me.
I decided Priestess Isrisa would value the divine voice more than her mortal visage. I should inform Priestess Cerine of Hosoth's bargain.
I decided Priestess Isrisa would value her mortality more than her voice. I should inform Priestess Cerine of Hosoth's bargain.

I have agreed to demonstrate my Numinous ability to return from death. Hosoth teleported me to the tallest bridge above the Fane of Breath. If the fall does not end my life, I must die another way to appease Hosoth.
I must kill Mara's Singing Cats and take their tongues to Hosoth.
I must answer Hosoth's riddles correctly.
The mudcrabs are on the shore near the docks of Deleyn's Mill.
Now that I've got enough mudcrab legs for a hearty meal, I should get them to Tanet Kerglen at the docks of Deleyn's Mill.
I need to find the entrance to the undercity. A resistance informant told me it's located on the westernmost side of Shornhelm in one of the buildings.
I've collected the "symbols of service" from the undead roaming Crestshade.
I should kill Bloodfiends in Crestshade to find the "symbols of service" Mathias spoke of. It is difficult to tell the creatures apart; any of the Bloodfiends may carry them.

Hosoth has agreed to return the divine voice - but I must choose who receives the gift. If Isrisa receives the voice, she will become a cat. If I give the voice to one of the stray cats of the Fane, Isrisa remains mute.

High Kinlord Maldarawo has asked me to acquire a Blessed Bell. One of these Bells was lost in the Liriel River, east of the Isquer Kinhouse. Another Bell is being created by Priestess Vendialara, in the Fane of Breath.
Kinlord Maldarawo is in the Isquer Kinhouse, at the center of Isque. I should deliver the Bell I recovered to him.
Kinlord Maldarawo is in the Isquer Kinhouse, at the center of Isque. I should speak with him once more.
Hosoth will now present a second riddle - I should answer it correctly.
Hosoth will now present a third riddle - I should answer it correctly.
I need to either answer Hosoth's first riddle correctly or deal with the consequences of an incorrect answer.
I need to either answer Hosoth's second riddle correctly or deal with the consequences of an incorrect answer.
I need to either answer Hosoth's first riddle correctly or deal with the consequences of an incorrect answer.
I need to either answer Hosoth's second riddle correctly or deal with the consequences of an incorrect answer.
I need to either answer Hosoth's third riddle correctly or deal with the consequences of an incorrect answer.
I have a chance to speak to the Ravenwatch's leader, Verandis. Hopefully, I can learn more about the truth behind Rivenspire.

Hosoth has agreed to return the divine voice - but I must choose who receives the gift. If Isrisa receives the voice, she will become a cat. If I give the voice to one of the stray cats of the Fane, Isrisa remains mute.
I decided Priestess Isrisa would value the divine voice more than her mortality. I should inform Priestess Cerine of Hosoth's bargain.
I decided Priestess Isrisa would value her mortality more than her voice. I should inform Priestess Cerine of Hosoth's bargain.

Hosoth has agreed to return the divine voice - but I must choose who receives the gift. If Isrisa receives the voice, she will become a cat. If I give the voice to one of the stray cats of the Fane, Isrisa remains mute.
I decided Priestess Isrisa would value her mortality more than her voice. I should inform Priestess Cerine of Hosoth's bargain.
I decided Priestess Isrisa would value the divine voice more than her mortality. I should inform Priestess Cerine of Hosoth's bargain.
I have obtained the tongues of Mara's Singing Cats and am on my way to deliver them to Hosoth.
I decided Priestess Isrisa would value her mortality more than her voice. I should inform Priestess Cerine of Hosoth's bargain.
I decided Priestess Isrisa would value the divine voice more than her mortality. I should inform Priestess Cerine of Hosoth's bargain.
The Varla Lens of Isque is atop a tower on Sunhold Isle, south of the Isquer Kinhouse. It is being held there by the Maormer invaders.
High Kinlord Maldarawo is in the Isquer Kinhouse, north of Sunhold Isle. I should return to him with the Varla Lens.
Warden Tilmo thinks that the spider-creature Selene is somewhere to the northeast of their camp. I should kill her if I can.

I have destroyed the spider creature, Selene. I should return to Warden Tilmo and let her know that whatever influence she has exerted on the Thornvenom tribe and the other creatures of this area is over.
Several Bosmer scouts are missing. Many of them may be caught in the webs throughout the valley. I should release any I find and burn as many webs as possible.
I've freed Bosmer soldiers and burned many webs. I should report back to Tilmo.
Nathalie asked me to recover some of her stolen goods. I should be able to find them while killing bandits in their camps or searching for caches in nearby ruins.
Now that I have Nathalie's stolen goods in hand, I can return them to her camp at Trader's Meet.
I have the body of Treethane Loiran. Protector Tilmo will want to know of this.
I've been asked to reclaim the body of the Thornvenom Tribe treethane, a Bosmer named Loiran.
Suuniqwe shed her mortal visage and became some form of ghastly wraith, threatening to destroy the Orrery. I must stop her.
<<1>> gave me a carved totem he says will help return the dead to rest. I should defeat the barrow wraiths and dispel their fractured spirits.
Now that I've convinced <<1>> to leave the Sanguine Barrows, I should speak to Gerard.
I should search the barrows for any remains and burn them.
I should search the tower for General Dathieu's remains. General Dathieu's spirit told me that his bones would show me why the dead here are so tormented.
I'll find <<1>> in Fell's Run, north of Hoarfrost Downs. He needs to know Hoarfrost is having problems. He might be willing to help them.

Wyress Gwen asked me to meet <<1>> at the base of their great Wyrd Tree, north of the ritual site.nnTo stop the spread of Angof's corruption, I'll need to work with her to reclaim the Wyrd Tree, the ancestral home of the Beldama Wyrd.
Get the shady chest from the shady shop keeper.
I should seek out a tailor or craftsman located in one of High Rock's towns who can make use of this Fine Harpy Feather.
It seems Adradan and Jillae have found their way back to the camp.
Lefalto told me that I would need to get a Baton of Fidelity from High Kinlord Langdruun in order to prove his loyalty to the Queen.nnLangdruun doubtless has tasks I could perform to earn his trust.
Canonreeve Lefalto can be found within the Felballin Kinhouse.
I need to kill Red Rook bandits north of Deleyn's Mill. Then I can retrieve a sample of the poison they used in a recent attack.
I have the poison the bandits used when they attacked the foresters. I should return to Warden Broles.
Sagert the Elder asked me to escort some horses to Oldgate. Hotspur should still be there. He can see that they're properly tended.

Lord Magister Averos has asked me to work with his aide, Magus Commander Madier, to ferret out the spies in Aldcroft.nnIf I wish to help the Magis Order, I must speak to Madier. He's standing beside Averos in Aldcroft.
Averos asked me to go to Aldcroft's lighthouse and search for Magus Commander Madier, then give him any help I can.

I found Madier murdered, a note in his hand. It says the Red Rooks, led by Astrid the White, are working with Angof. They have taken over Aldcroft's lighthouse.nnAstrid the White or someone near here must have murdered Madier. She must be stopped.

Astrid the White is dead, and Magus Commander Madier is avenged. Lord Magister Averos will certainly want to know that Madier confirmed the Red Rooks are working for Angof.nnI'll find him by this tent at the north gate of Aldcroft.
Astrid the White is dead, but I have learned nothing more of what she planned. If I search her body, I may find a clue as to why she has pitted the Red Rooks against the Magis Order.
I should speak with Sibellec about Alice's cat, Jenkles.
I should look in the swamp for Alice's cat, Jenkles.
I found a Reach Vine Thorn upon a Bog Lurcher corpse. I should return to Sibellec and give it to her.
The Bog Lurchers can be found in the swamp along the Eastern Coast of High Rock.
The Bog Hags, and their dens, are found in the swamp north of Sibellec's hut.
I have collected the Hag Hearts and Reach Vine Thorns Sibellec requested. I should return to her and deliver them.
I need to get a Baton of Fidelity from High Kinlord Maldarawo in order to prove his loyalty to the Queen.
Canonreeve Lefalto can be found within the Isque Kinhouse.
I need to get a Baton of Fidelity from High Kinlady Genivra in order to prove her loyalty to the Queen.
Canonreeve Lefalto can be found within the Syldarim Kinhouse.
I've destroyed the altars on the Ruined Steppe. I should let Normar know that his town is free of the necromancers.
I should inform <<1>>, the treasurer of Fell's Run, of Leon Gavendien's death, so I collect a bounty.
Warden Broles asked me to sneak into the Red Rook bandits' camp. I'll use one of their uniforms to disguise myself. I'm heading north of Deleyn's Mill to poison their food.
I've poisoned the Red Rook bandits' food. I need to report back to Warden Broles south of the Red Rook Camp.
Canonreeve Lefalto can be found within the Syldarim Kinhouse.
I need to get a Baton of Fidelity from High Kinlady Astraela in order to prove her loyalty to the Queen.

I aided Raven and Aiden Direnni as they led the Direnni army against the Alessian Order. I've fought beside Altmer, Nord, and Bretons.nnCoty asked me to speak with his past self at the Direnni camp. I guess it will be the first time we ever meet.
Queen Ayrenn can be found at her palace in Alinor.nnI should deliver the Coffer to her.
Sibellec asked me to plant her concoction in the earth near her hut.
I planted Sibellec's concoction in the earth near her hut and a giant Lurcher sprang forth from the ground. I should return to her and report that the deed is done.
I've found a writ of employ. Now I need to speak with Warden Broles.
Normand, the Sea Wolf's boatswain, inadvertantly told me where he hid the ship's treasure. It's near a stone arch under the Northpoint lighthouse. I should see if the chest is hidden there.
I should show this writ to a Warden in Deleyn's Mill.
I've talked to a neatby Warden and they suggested I speak to <<1>>.
I should bring this letter to the Duchess immediately. She must be informed there is a traitor in her midst.
I returned to the duchess, only to find that Skorsgaard has already made the first move. I must save Northpoint by defeating Skorsgaard and his troops.
Gammer Robins gave me this basket of turnips to take to her granddaughter, Sanda.  She's with the giants of Breagha-fin, east of the Watchers.
I need to "talk some sense into" Irne Oscent. Hopefully, he'll drop his accusations against Govran Cerone.
If Govran Cerone buys Irne a new boat, Irne will drop the charges against him. I need to ask the guard at the warehouse to let me in so I can negotiate with Govran.

I now know the that dock around the damaged boat was covered with smelly slime. Also, the hole in the boat appears to have been made by a claw.nnWater Dreugh have claws that could cause such damage. If I collect one, it may prove my theory.
Govran Cerone is one of the villagers locked up in the warehouse. The guard said I can use a calming charm on the villagers, but I can't attack anyone.

I've struck a deal with Irne Oscent. Govran will pay Irne for the damage caused to his boat. Irne will get Govran released from the warehouse. I need to let Valentin Cerone know about our arrangement.
I couldn't convince Irne Oscent. Govran Cerone offered to pay him for the damage caused to his boat, but he remains locked up while awaiting trial. I need to let Valentin Cerone know what's happened.
I have killed the River Dreugh for Miller Jodoin. I should return to him at the mill in the Alcaire region of Stormhaven.
The River Dreugh can be found in the rivers throughout the Alcaire region of Stormhaven.
I should search the creek near Stonebridge Mill, in the Alcaire Region of Stormhaven, for the three missing cogs.
I have recovered the three missing cogs from Stonebridge Mill. I should return them to Miller Jodoin. He can be found at the mill which is in the Alcaire region of Stormhaven.

Captain Leon offered me a reward to find the missing magical items and clear his name. nnHis ship ran aground in the cove below Koeglin Village. The items may have either have sunk in the cove near Leon's ship or been washed up on the beach.
I've found the missing items Constable Sal has accused Captain Leon of stealing. If I return the items to Captain Leon, in the stocks in Koeglin Village, I can prove his innocence.

Captain Leon was thrilled to see that I had recovered the missing magical items from his hold. He said that if I presented the items to Constable Sal and freed him from the stocks, he would reward me.

Though Constable Sal did not agree Captain Leon was innocent, he did agree to free Leon now that I've returned the magical items, and gave me a key to do so.nnLeon is in the stocks near the docks of Koeglin Village. He will reward me for freeing him.
I have freed Captain Leon from the stocks. I should speak to him again if I wish to obtain my reward.
I've found a journal page detailing the grisly events that transformed a person into a tree near the <<1>>. I should speak to the sapling to see if that satisfies its curiousity.
Queen Ayrenn can be found at her palace in Alinor.nnI should deliver the Coffer to her.
Queen Ayrenn can be found at her palace in Alinor.nnI should deliver the Coffer to her.
Queen Ayrenn can be found at her palace in Alinor.nnI should deliver the Coffer to her.
I have taken out Sir Croix. I should return to Sir Edmund and report the deed is done. Sir Edmund can be found outside Firebrand Keep.

Sir Croix can be found inside Firebrand Keep which lies in the Alcaire region of Stormhaven. It may be difficult getting inside as the knights may be expecting agents of Duke Nathaniel. Perhaps I can acquire a disguise.
Arcady offered me a modest payment if I collect pearls for him. I can find pearls both inside oysters in the cove below Koeglin Village and on Water Dreugh, who prize them.
I've collected a number of pearls from the cove. If I return them to Arcady Farnele, on a small island south of Koeglin Village, he will pay me for them.
Jillae told me that her love, Adradan, was taken by the Thornvenom tribe. They should be somewhere in the canopy. I promised I'd do what I could to find him.
I must kill Imperials west of Southpoint and collect their thumbs for Narela.
The villager asked me to lead him back to Koeglin Village, away from the pirates.
I've led the captured slave back to Koeglin Village. He asked me to speak with Brother Stental at the local wayshrine.
The Imperials keep their slouchbears in and around the Imperial palisade, northwest of Southpoint.
<<1>> is waiting for me back in Southpoint. I'll talk to him after I've poisoned the slouchbears with mind-altering fungi.
The villager asked me to lead him back to Koeglin Village, away from the pirates.
Now that the beacon has been lit, I should return to Sir Edmund outside Firebrand Keep.
The eternal flame burns to the south of Firebrand Keep. I should go there and ignite the torch Sir Edmund gave me.
Firebrand Tower is within Firebrand Keep. I should take my lit torch and reignite the beacon at the top.
<<1>> is still recovering from her last skirmish. If I kill enough pirates, they may decide to leave this area.
I've been busy slaying pirates near Koeglin Lighthouse. <<1>> is recovering from her wounds near a bridge leading to the lighthouse. She'll appreciate an update on my progress.
The Ooze-Eel traps can be found along the coast, southeast of the village of Southpoint.
I've collected a quantity of Ooze-Eels for the residents of Southpoint. I should deliver them to Southpoint's Treethane, Narela.

Ra'Dara plans to ransom the lighthouse and raid Koeglin Village, enslaving all he can.nnHe may succeed unless I kill him. Ra'Dara's ship is docked at the island south of the lighthouse. Ra'Dara must be on board - but I may need help to kill him.
I've slain Pirate Captain Ra'Dara and thwarted his plans to invade and enslave Koeglin Village. I have his head as proof of the deed. If I bring it to the authorities, they may reward me.
I've slain Pirate Captain Ra'Dara and thwarted his plans to invade and enslave Koeglin Village. I should take his head as proof of the deed.
I have disabled the Firetraps. I should report back to Tiradil, who's waiting on one of the islets on the Imperial side of the bay.
Disable the Imperial Firetraps on the western side of the bay.
Captain Lash gra-Agdur is looking for salvage like this amulet. If I speak to her, she may give me a fair price.
Captain Lash gra-Agdur is looking for salvage like this shield. If I speak to her, she may give me a fair price.
Captain Lash gra-Agdur is looking for salvage like this coin. If I speak to her, she may give me a fair price.
Captain Lash gra-Agdur is looking for salvage like this tankard. If I speak to her, she may give me a fair price.
Captain Lash gra-Agdur is looking for salvage like this gem. If I speak to her, she may give me a fair price.
The Blacksap Lurcher's heart appears to be drawn to an area east of Southpoint village.
<<1>> can be found in the town of Southpoint.nnHe would certainly want to know about the hostile Bosmer village I discovered hidden to the east of town.
Someone from the Aldmeri Dominion would be very interested in this letter. I should take it to an <<1>>; they can be found at any Dominion outpost in Valenwood.
I should search the pile of logs and bodies for anything of value that might be salvaged.
I've slain many Water Dreugh encroaching on Koeglin Village. If I bring this news to Arneil, perhaps it will ease his fears.
Arneil asked me to kill Water Dreugh to ease his fears of invasion.
I'll need to swim out to the sunken ship to recover Captain Catae's lockbox. It's most likely found in his cabin.
J'Hriss is standing on the docks of Southpoint village.nnI should return Captain Catae's lockbox to him at the earliest opportunity.
Looters can be found roaming the beach directly south of Southpoint.
Battlereeve Alengwe is in the town of Southpoint, north of the landing beach.
Mainard has asked that I use the Commanding Whistle near the Wandering Cattle to bring them back with me. He warned me that if I took too long however, they may wander away.
I've returned several of the lost cattle back to Nurdin Farms. I should speak to Mainard.
I agreed to deliver Per's rent payment to Melanie Oscent in Koeglin Village. According to Per, Melanie is by the docks.
Until some climbs to the top of the lighthouse and re-lights the lighthouse, ship captains will have difficulty knowing how close they are to the shore in bad weather.
I've relit the signal fire in the lighthouse. I should speak with the lighthouse keeper one more time to say goodbye.
House Dres dismissed my aid and sent me to speak to a representative of House Redoran in Davon's Watch.
I was able to get a confession from the Ashlander, after a few choice words.
I discovered that Fort Arand has succumbed completely to the Blight, with no survivors.  The Davon's Watch Quarantine Master will want to know.
I should talk to Mainard Nurdin, William's son. He probably knows more about his mother's disappearance.
I've come across a scarf tattered and torn in an apperant struggle. Footsteps nearby lead east towards several buildings near the mill. I should follow them to see where they go.
Mainard said William headed northwest, toward the older farmhouses. I should show him Rosalie's broken necklace. Then maybe he'll remember more about what happened to her.
I found Rosalie Nurdin and set her free. I should talk to her about what happened.
I should take the Glowing Toad to King Faume Toad-Eye and see if it belongs to him.
Take the King's eye to the Treethane Vault in the Bonebarrow.
I found an ailing Ashlander Farseer in their camp, ravaged by the Blight. It seems that whatever is spreading the Blight is infecting them as well.

Giras of House Redoran has asked me to find proof of the Ashlander's involvement in the Blight.nnTheir camp is to the west of Senie. I should look for their Farseer, and demand they cease attacking the town.
I've saved the Hortator's spirit from Marea's plot. I should talk to it and find out what's going on.
I should tell Marea Hloriss about the priestess' decision. She's still waiting outside Othrenis.

The priestess granted me entry and gave me incense to awaken the Hortator's spirit. nnI must make my way into Othrenis and light the incense upon his grave marker to summon his spirit. The priest warned me that he may react violently.
Fort Arand is to the southwest of Davon's Watch.  I should go there and find proof of what occurred there.
I promised to look for Ama Loche's father amongst The Old Goat's mead crates.
Didier Loche was poisoning the mead to silence his enemies when I found him. The poisoned mead bottles must be destroyed.
Now that the poisoned mead bottles are no longer a threat to its patrons, I should check that Didier Loche returned to work with his daughter Ama.
<<1>> asked me to find  knights in Firebrand Keep still loyal to the duke and send them to Edmund. I won't know which knights are loyal to <<1>> until I talk to them.
I've found several knights in the keep who agreed to join us in deposing Sir Croix. I'll check in with Sir Edmund now to see where we stand.
Sir Edmund asked me to enter the tower in Firebrand Keep's Great Hall and blow the horn there. The sound of the horn will signal the knights to begin the attack.
I sounded the horn in Firebrand Keep's Great Hall. Sir Edmund has begun the assault. I must leave the hall and find him.

Sir Edmund was wounded and lacks the strength to engage Sir Croix. He entrusted that task to me. Sir Croix is in the garrison on Firebrand Keep's west side. I must blow the siege horn in the garrison to stop the battle  after I kill Sir Croix.
I have killed Sir Croix, but the Knights of the Flame continue to face each other in civil war. Only Sir Edmund can stop the carnage now. He waits at the entrance of Firebrand Keep's great hall.
Sir Croix has fallen, but battle still rages in Firebrand Keep. I must blow the horn in the garrison. That will signal to Sir Edmund that Sir Croix is dead, and his knights may stand down.

I've sounded the garrison horn, claiming Firebrand Keep for Sir Edmund and his knights. The battle is over, but Sir Edmund received dire wounds in the assault. I should seek him at the entrance to the Great Hall to learn his fate.

I managed to get the machine to start, and was immediately ambushed by a Dunmer assassin. Far from a Dwemer threat, the Hortator's killer was most likely this same assassin.nnI should return to the Hortator to let him know what transpired.
I've replaced the gear for the strange machinery. Now the only thing apparently left to fix is adding some oil.nnI can probably find some usable oil on the Dwemer Spiders around the ruins.
Canonreeves can usually be found at Aldmeri Dominion outposts such as Southpoint or Razorvine Refuge.
I have the Muckspunge Elixir and should return to Tsajivi.
I should collect Muckspunge Elixir from the boat, docked in the east of Haventown.
Kill 3 of the goblins that are west of the blacksmith building.
Return to the QAT Kill Quest NPC for your reward.
Imperials can be found in camps spread across Haven Trace Trail, west of Haven.
Hadellor is waiting on the eastern end of Haven Trace trail, northwest of Haven.
The Wise Woman has sent me to pray at an altar of Meridia, which I can find around the Conclave.  It's there I will endure my trial.
Now that my prayer has summoned the blighted shalk swarm, I should kill them.
I should return to the Wise Woman now that I've endured Meridia's trial.  The Wise Woman is in the Conclave, near the compound's center.
I was unable to get a confession from the Ashlander, who continued to profess his tribe's innocence.
Bravosi Dres has asked me to try and get a confession of guilt from a captured Ashlander who claims he is immune to the Blight.
Sir Edmund asked me to take Sir Croix's sword to something called the Flaming Fissure in Windridge Cave. I will find Windridge Cave northwest of Firebrand Keep.
Orvona's Retainer informed me that Ravnos will now speak with me.
To speak to Ravnos, I have to do some dirty work for him.nnHis retainer's asked me to retrieve some of  Ravnos' property from his old business partners that are  trying to leave Sugar Cove.
I've obtained the items Ravnos "lost." I should speak to his retainer, and see if I can now talk to Ravnos.
I should head into the Balareal Ruins nearby and retrieve any of Valentin's Goods that I can find.
I've found all the goods I can carry. I should return to Valentin on the road to the south of the ruins.
The slavers are no longer in Omaynia. Ahjiivi will be relieved to hear it.
Ahjiivi refuses to speak to me while slavers remain amidst their number. I should search the town and take care of them.
Valenwood itself could have revenge on the Imperials if I pushed the piles of logs onto the unsuspecting victims.

Hoarvor can be found wandering through the Thrambles, the maze of trees north of Razorwine Refuge.nnThistlewhip noted that the "big, slow ones" always have good meat, but the "small, fast ones" only do sometimes.
Thistlewhip's camp of hunters is at the southern entrance to the Thrambles, which lies to the north of Razorvine Refuge.nnNow that I've collected the meat, I should deliver it to Thistlewhip.
Saproot Seedlings grow all along Haven Trace trail, west of Haven.
Sticky Agachon is on the western end of Haven Trace Trail, northeast of Southpoint.
I should speak to the Alcaire Guard who has taken the blade away from me.
House Dres dismissed my aid and sent me to speak to a representative of House Redoran in Davon's Watch.
I should seek out someone in Alcaire Keep who may find value in this broken, but magical dagger.
Mazhe asked me to speak to Dominique about the return of his pants. She's lounging in a pool on the west side of the Reywell Hot Springs.

Dominique agreed to return Mazhe's pants, provided I ... entertain ... her friends. She asked me to seek out Lord Giles, Lady Idah, Lord Luc, and Lady Diane. They're all near the Reywell Hot Springs. I think she wants me to dance for them.
I entertained all four of Dominique's noble friends. When I return to her, she'll return the pants to me.
I've entertained Dominique, as well as her noble friends. Perhaps now she'll tell me where to find Mazhe's missing pants.
Dominique told me that Mazhe's pants are hidden in a chest beside the pool.
I retrieved Mazhe's pants. He waits pantless beside the hot spring east of Reywell. He will be relieved to have his pants back.
Imperial Rangers and their Guard Bears protect the Cyro-Valen Trading Compound, to the east of Haven Town.
I must return to the Meddling Inveigler, who sits on a raft floating in the docks of the Cyro-Valen Trading Company.
I found the Caravanmaster, but he was raving mad, both from his injuries and the beginning of Corprus.nnHe mentioned an Ahjiivi at Omaynia. Perhaps she knows what happened to the caravan.
Ravnos Orvona has sent me to a foundered ship just off the coast of Sugar's Cove.nnHe has asked me to retrieve his cargo from the wreckage.
Orvona's Bodyguard awaits my arrival. I should give her the packages I've salvaged.
<<1>>s grow wild to the northeast of Razorvine Refuge.
I've recovered the <<1>>s and should deliver them to <<2>>.
A strange structure towers above Haven. I entered the massive chasm it ripped in the center of the town, intent on exploring the tunnels.
Golleon is not long for this world. He gave me an Amber Bracelet to deliver to Priestess Fleile in Razorvine Refuge and asked me to tell her of my success.
Golleon was mortally wounded trying to destroy the Infernal Device in Netherhaven. He pointed me to the three tunnels, stating if I destroyed the Cores of the device it would shut down permanently.
Golion pointed out a valve I should use to escape Netherhaven and asked me to speak with Priestess Flelie.
Sugar sent a caravan to Omaynia, but believes they never made it. His retained suggested I search Marshmine for any survivors.
I need to find and kill the bandit leaders in Windridge Cave.

The knight's spirit asked me to slay spectral cutthroats from the Band of the Fallen. His sword will consume their souls. Once the sword's hunger has been sated, he wants me to cast it into the Flaming Fissure.
I have done as the Knight of the Flame asked. I should return to him so his spirit may be at peace.
Brigands are harassing travellers on the northern road. Emarie is busy guarding a merchant caravan the brigands attacked, so he's asked me to hunt down Riverside's brigands.

I've killed brigands on Alcaire's roads. I've dispatched enough of them to discourage the rest from preying on travellers. Watch Captain Emarie asked me to report to Duke Nathaniel when I was done. He holds court in Alcaire Castle's manse.
I have sated the sword's hunger. Now I must throw it into the Flaming Fissure in Windridge Cave. This punishment will doom the Fallen, but their sacrifice will free the soul of a Knight of the Flame.
Thistlewhip's camp can be found just outside the southern entrance of The Thrambles.nnThistlewhip and his Bosmer hunters will be glad to hear that Dro'tahn no longer prowls through the Thrambles.
The Infernal Device threatens Grahtwood no more. I should return to Golleon with the good news.
I have found the headquarters of the mercenary leader Nevillius Kine, in a guarded area at the northern end of the Imperial Palisade.nnNow I can kill him.
I should search the Imperial Palisade for areas of interest.

I found a shipping manifest originating from Kragenmoor in Noosehole Cavern.nnI should let the Argonian slaves know their slaver has been killed - perhaps they will have more information on how to find the origin of the manifest.
Talk to the QAT Talker NPC
You have completed all of the quest conditions.  Return to the QAT Working Quest NPC.
The origin of the monstrous Lurchers must be somewhere within this village.
<<1>>, a skilled Bosmer scout, is hidden just north of Belkali Village. She'll want to see the <<2>> I found.
The Imperial Chest is sitting at the center of the camp. It is probably locked, but perhaps a key can be found.
Vivienne asked me to drop vials of poison into lamia dens. She believes killing the lamia is necessary to prevent them from preying on those in Reywell afflicted with The Fervor.
I have poisoned many dens through the lamia nests, and dealt the lamia a serious blow. Countess Muric will be eager to hear of my success. She guards the path to Reywell southeast of the lamia dens.
Ravnos sent a caravan to Omaynia, but believes they never made it. His bodyguard suggested I search Marshmine for any survivors.
Escort Tiny to the pot of stew.
Return to the QAT Cat Lady
I found a survivor, but he was raving mad, both from his injuries and the beginning of Corprus.nnHe mentioned an Ahjiivi at Omaynia. Perhaps she knows what happened to the caravan.
I should release the necromancer's captives.
Hieronian Verus is leading the Imperials camped on Haven Trace trail and should be killed.
Thunderbug nests can be found throughout the Thrambles. <<1>> asked me to collect eggs from them.
Thistlewhip can be found at the Bosmer hunting camp at the southern entrance to the Thrambles.nnI've collected the Thunderbug eggs <<1>> requested. He'll be pleased to see them.
I have the key to Glonagaum's shackles. I should bring it to him.
The Deathscale Lamia have thrown a Wayrest Noble into a cauldron. If no one intervenes, the woman will be boiled alive.
I've found the machine the Hortator spoke about, but it is not operational. There's some notes on its workings nearby.nnI should try and start the machine and see what befell the Hortator.
I've found the items needed to repair the Dwemer machinery.

The Hortator asked me to travel to the Dwemer Ruins to examine some strange machinery. The entrance is to the west, and then south up the mountains.nnHe believes the machine he was examining may have been the reason for his murder.

To retrieve Belene's ring, I need to find the hen who swallowed it. Of course, Belene doesn't want me to kill her chickens. I can lure the hen to me with feed and then whack it on the back of the neck to get the ring.
I found Belene Ancois's runaway hen on the outskirts of the farm, and I retrieved Belene's wedding ring. I can return the ring to her in Koeglin Village.
These Imperial Supply Carts should be taken out of commission.
I've found the owner of the locket, now I need only to return it to her.
I've found the owner of the locket, now I need only to return it to her.
I can ask Mainard, the farmer's son, if he is familar with this necklace. He might bring some insight into the situation at hand.
Mainard asks me to find his father and tell him of my recent discovery. He last saw him heading to the northern ranches hauling a load of some type.
Tirren, Yargo and Jory will be found somewhere within the town of Haven, southeast of Razorvine Refuge.
Bron's comrades are dead... again. I should talk to him now that the deed is done.
Gar asked me to slaughter dreugh near Reywell Hot Springs.
I've slain many dreugh. Gar will be pleased. He's still guarding Lady Idah in Reywell's eastern spring.
Imports Overseer Llameni asked me to report my findings to her and the fort commander. I should go to the main hall in Heimlyn Keep.
Now that I've been allowed to see Llameni, I should talk to her about what she has found out about House Dres.
Llameni told me she saw a hidden tunnel deep within the Heimlyn Keep dungeon.nnI should explore the tunnel and find out what secrets House Dres keeps hidden away there.

Ahjiivi directed me to Noosehole Cavern, where she says the smugglers relay the blighted cargo.nnI found vials of the "cure" sold around Stonefalls carrying the very Blight itself! I should destroy what cargo I can find.

I've killed the overseer of the slave shipping operation, but the trail ends here, in the Noosehole Cavern.nnI should search through the Overseer's desk to find some clue for the true source of these shipments.
Ahjiivi directed me to Noosehole Cavern, where she says the smugglers relay the blighted cargo.nnI should go into Noosehole Cavern and stop whoever is running this operation.

Ahjiivi directed me to Noosehole Cavern, where she says the smugglers relay the blighted cargo.nnI killed the ringleader of the shipping operation, but I've yet to find conclusive evidence in the cavern. I should search any open cargo I find.

Ahjiivi directed me to Noosehole Cavern, where she says the smugglers relay the blighted cargo.nnI found vials of the "cure" sold around Stonefalls carrying the very Blight itself! I should destroy what cargo I can find.
Ra'ud asked me to pick some blossoms, make a bouquet, and deliver it to <<1>> in his name.
I've created a bouquet of flowers for <<1>>. Ra'ud asked that I deliver the bouquet to her near him at Reywell.
<<1>> hated the bouquet of flowers I gave to her on Lord Ra'ud's behalf. I need to let him know the bad news: she will never speak with him again.
Daja asked me to light the fuses on his fireworks launcher, then kill the grumpy Daedra when it appears once again to smash the launcher.
I have killed the Grumpy Daedra, an Ogrim, who smashed Daja's fireworks launcher each time he attempted to use it. Daja should be pleased. He's waiting on the crest of Overtop Hill.
Daja asked me to light the fuses on his fireworks launcher, then kill the grumpy Daedra when it appears once again to smash the launcher.
I should try to locate the owner of the hairpin somewhere in Alcaire Keep.
I've found the owner of the hairpin, and I need only speak with him at this point.
I've found the owner of the hairpin, and I need only speak with him at this point.
Gaston swears that I need to watch out for him! He promised I would be thrown in the dungeons for defying him. I should report this incident to the Baron at Alcaire Keep.
I should use the Spriggarum on the Imperial Cargo along the docks of the Cyro-Valen Trading Compound. Inveigler warned me to quickly back away once I used the Spriggarum -- the snakes are aggressive.
The Meddling Inveigler will be waiting on the raft in the docks of the compound. I must speak to him.

There were tracks leading away southeast from the hoarvor nest. I should keep watch for any other signs of Claire's flight through the woods.nnIt's likely that she's still lost in the Thrambles somewhere.
I need to escort Claire out of The Thrambles, to Thistlewhip's camp.
<<1>> has made it safely into the care of the Bosmer hunters south of The Thrambles. I should speak to her by the fire.
Claire must have run back to the cave where I found her, in the southwest portion of The Thrambles.
I need to bring Gaston to the entrance of the Balareal Ruins to get him to safety.
I must find the items that Elder Knonk requested before my competitors Hoom and Wud. The Elder wanted something shiny, pointy, clangy, and round.
I collected the items Knonk requested. I should decide if I'm going to give the items to Knonk. I could give them to Hoom or Wud so one of them could defeat the other.
I've stopped the necromancy of House Dres and killed Teranos Dres, the Dunmer behind it. I should return to Llameni and tell her what occurred.
I've entered caverns swarming with guards and necromancers. I should traverse them and stop to the necromantic rituals within them.
I need to look in Firebrand keep for the owner of the sword.
I've returned the sword to <<1>> and I should speak with her again.
I've returned the sword to <<1>> and I should speak with her again.

I promised to deliver this coffer containing the ransom to the slave traders holding Serinna's son. The slave traders' white parlance flag will indicate to them that I have their permission to enter the camp.
Now that the ransom is paid, Solon will be able to rejoin his mother Serinna.
I was able to endure Meridia's trial, and kill the blighted shalk.  I should talk to the initiate that accompanied me before returning to the Wise Woman.
Gaston has gotten some idea in his mind and demands that I assist him. I should speak to him and quickly to give him my answer.
Gaston crossed the line. For my own safety I had to kill him off and make it seem like an accident. I need to report his untimely death to the Baron at Alcaire Keep.
I've dealt with the penitents. I should speak with <<1>> at the conclave to let her know.
I should try to find the axe's owner in Alcaire Keep and return it to them.
I've given <<1>> the sword, and now I just need to speak with him again.
I've given <<1>> the sword, and now I just need to speak with him again.
An-Gei, an Argonian slave in Noosehole Cavern, suggests I find someone in charge of the shipping records for Kragenmoor. They may be able to help me track down the shipper.
Moric asked me to collect the heads of High Priestess lamia from the Bloodscale, Doomcoil, and Deathslither tribes. I'll find the lamia dens west of Hammerdeath Arena.

I have killed the High Priestesses of the Bloodscale, Doomcoil, and Deathslither lamia tribes, and retrieved the head of each. Lord Moric Nirine, who waits just east of Hammerdeath Arena, will be eager for his prizes.
I've slain dreugh at the beach houses near Sand Cove. I should return to Lord Edgard and give him the news.
I've been asked to slay the dreugh at Sand Cove, south of Wayrest.

Lob gro-Bug challenged me to defeat three gladiators in duels. He's promised me a place in their ranks if I succeed.nnI can approach any champion and challenge him to a duel. He also said I can decide whether I want to kill any opponent I defeat.
I've defeated a gladiator. I have to defeat two more before I can take my place among them.
I've defeated two gladiators. I must defeat one more before I can take my place among them.

I've defeated three gladiators. When my foes tried to surrender, I killed them. I should tell Log gro-Bug my tales of triumph. He's grandstanding at the entrance to the arena. He's promised to initiate me as one of the Champions of Hammerdeath.
I've defeated a gladiator. He tried to surrender, but I killed him. I must defeat two more champions to take my place among them.
I've defeated two gladiators. I must defeat one more before I can take my place among them.
I should return to the elder's hut and speak to Hoom.
I should return to the elder's hut and speak to Elder Knonk.
I should return to the elder's hut and speak to Wud.
If I'm going to take part in the imga scavenger hunt, I should tak to Elder Knonk.
I need to look for cutlery south of the sand cove. Its probably strewn across the beach.
I agreed to investigate the ruins.
I should relate what I saw in the ruins to Foosh in Ookvoot.
I've defeated my final gladiator. I can return to Lob gro-Bug now... or I can slaughter my helpless foe.
I've defeated my final gladiator. I can return to Lob gro-Bug now... or I can slaughter my helpless foe.
I've killed the second gladiator I defeated. I must defeat a third gladiator before I can be counted as one of the champions.
I must find the items that Elder Knonk requested before my competitors Hoom and Wud. The elder wanted something shiny, something pointy, something clangy, and something round.
Lob gro-Bug wishes to award me a Helm of Valor. I should speak to Mar gro-Bug at the forge behind him.
Lob gro-Bug wishes to award me a Helm of Bloodlust. I should speak to Mar gro-Bug at the forge behind him.
I've agreed to take part in the Grand Melee. I must slay five challengers in the arena and survive. If I die or leave the arena before slaying five opponents, I lose.
I have emerged victorious from the Grand Melee. Tar gro-Bug waits for me at the edge of the Grand Melee arena. Now I can claim my winnings.
I need to light a signal fire when it's all clear for the privateers to make their way to their ship.
The signal fire's been lit and the privateers will soon be reunited with their ship.
Penitents linger outside the conclave's gates. The false talismans <<1>> gave me might appease them. A more honest approach could also work.
I've sabotaged the Wood Orcs. <<1>> will want to hear of my exploits.
<<1>> wants me to smoke the Wood Orcs out of their cave by lighting the firestones they've stacked.
I placed the House Father's remains on the altar, which summoned his spirit. He did not disguise his plans.nnI should speak with the diviner and see if this is sufficient proof for her.
Llameni tells me I must seek out the Tribunal in Iliath Temple and tell them what we've discovered about House Dres.

I've informed the diviner at Iliath Temple of the crimes of House Dres, but she did not believe my accusations. nnShe said placing the remains of the House Father on the Sacred Altar would clear any doubt.
Lug ran off to reunite with his friend. I should return to Roop.
I should approach one of the guards on Hoarfrost Downs so I can offer my aid.
What could have caused this endless war between armies of spirits? Perhaps I can find some clues by searching the houses in town.
Deputy Ovis told me to follow the other Deputy Harbormaster, Felisa.  She may be down on the docks to the north of town. nnI should be careful to keep my distance so she doesn't notice me.
It seems that both the Harbormaster's deputies aren't involved in any wrongdoing.  I should let him know he can trust them.
It seems that someone has information on who is receiving the kickbacks.  I should let the Harbormaster know about this also.
I should approach one of the guards on Hoarfrost Downs so I can offer my aid.
The source of the weeping may be behind the waterfall. Mournful cries are muted by the susurrus of the stream.
I have been told that the Mages Guild will be interested in artifacts found in Glenumbra. I should talk to the Mages Guild Emissary in Deleyn's Mill or Aldcroft.
I should ask around Deleyn's Mill or Aldcroft to see if anyone might be interested in an artifact like the one I found.
There's a Mages Guild official in Deleyn's Mill. I should see if he's interested in this ancient helm.
If I follow the treasure map and climb the cliffs directly east of the island, I may find something of value.
In searching out the corrupt dock officer, I should speak first to Deputy Ovis.  He can be found in the Harbormaster's office.
I should search the Dwemer ruins for any clue as to where the spiders are coming from.
I've found a strange piece of machinery deep in the ruins that seems to be the source of the spiders.nnThe only way to put an end to them is to destroy the machinery.
I've freed several of the Senie workers from the Ashlanders. I need to return to Norus and speak to him.
Norus asks that I slay any of the Orlishkaarn invaders nearby that are holding Senie Workers captive.
Jodie asked me to kill the harpies plaguing Glenumbra's western cliffs. She begged me in the name of King Casimir of Daggerfall.

I've killed many harpies along the cliffs of western Glenumbra. If Jodie hasn't left for Daggerfall yet, she'll be pleased by this news.nnLast time I saw her, she was nursing her wounds in a small valley near Daggerfall's western cliffs.
I should explore the mines and see why it was abandoned.
I found a nest of kwama eggs tended by a blighted kwama queen. I should destroy her to stop the influx of blighted kwama in the mine.
I've collected some netchlings from the netch plantation. I should return to Lluthyne.

I should gather netchlings from the netch plantation in eastern Stonefalls. To catch them, I'll have to "pop" their gaseous pouches with a highly specialized farm implement... or the stick Lluthyne gave me.
I have obtained a pelt from one of the more corrupted creatures and should take it to Ninumion in Elden Root.
An Imperial and a Wood Orc are fighting to the death. Choose a side and slay their enemy!
According to the note on the body, if I find and kill Foulwing the Younger, I can harvest her claws and sell them for a reward.
I've slain Foulwing the Younger and harvested her claws. The traveller's note said I could sell them at a Daggerfall camp north of the cliffs and claim a reward.
Now that I've convinced the cloaked stranger I'm no one to be trifled with, I should get whatever information I can from her.
The cloaked stranger sent me to talk to "Sugar" Orvona in Sugar Cove.  nnSugar cove is  up the coast from Ebonheart, to the North.

From all indications, I'm walking straight into a trap.  On the other hand, it's the only way to find out who on the Harbormaster's crew is recieving kickbacks.nnI'm to meet the stranger in the alley behind the tavern.
If I'm going to help Adrone find Lea's missing body, I should find out more about the circumstances of her death. Adrone may know more details.

Adrone said fishermen saw Lea falling from the cliffs. Her body was gone when they came ashore. Her remains were never recovered. Perhaps a search of the cliffs above the beach could yield some clues to Lea's fate.

When I reached the cliffs where Lea Rolaine threw herself to her death, her spirit appeared on the edge of the cliff. If I communicate with her spirit, perhaps I can discover the location of her body.

When I spoke to Lea's spirit, she said Lord Gette, a necromancer, resurrected her after death.nnWhat happened after that remains a mystery, but Lea's last memory was waking on the small island just west of High Rock. Perhaps I'll find more there.

When I spoke to Lea's spirit, she said a necromancer named Lord Gette resurrected her body after her death. Lea begged me to go to the small island east of the cliffs and look for a pile of dirt. If I dig there, I may find Lord Gette's secret.
I found a tattered journal buried in a small chest. It's on the island near the cliffs where Lea's spirit appeared. It may reveal what happened to her.
After I delivered the remains, the spirit appeared near the cart. I should speak to him, now that he's regained his memories of who he was.
I've collected remains from urns around Othrenis. The spirit asked me to place the remains in a merchant's cart near the entrance to Othrenis, so he can escape with his comrades-in-arms.
I should search the grounds of Othrenis for urns containing the remains of guardian spirits.

While standing on the island's beach, I must speak four words from Lord Gette's journal: "Come hither, fair maiden."nnBy speaking the words, I can summon Lea's body. If I can destroy it, I'll free her spirit from Lord Gette's horrible curse.
After I summoned and defeated the reanimated body of Lea Rolaine, her spirit appeared again on the island. She doesn't seem hostile. If I speak to her, I might learn more.
Lea's spirit is finally at peace. She asked that I bring news of her fate to Adrone Murric. I'll find him on the beach below the cliffs, not far from the precipice where Lea fell to her death.
I'll need to keep my eye out for a chest or lock in the Dwemer Ruins to see if this key will work.
I'll need to keep my eye out for a chest or lock in the Dwemer Ruins to see if this key will work.
I should find a way to put the ghost within to rest.
I must deliver these supplies to Sticky Agachon. Henidur said I would find Sticky by following the road behind the Inn to the east.
Seach the trackless paths of the Thrambles to find the way into Thrambleheart.
If I investigate at the base of the tree, perhaps I can find out more about it.
I wonder what will happen if I eat one of these mushrooms?
A promissory note I found on the cloaked stranger's body points to a "Sugar" Orvona in Sugar Cove.  nnSugar cove is  up the coast from Ebonheart, to the North.

I should get the supplies from the Orlishkaarn that have stolen them. They have either stored it away or carry it on their person.nnSome of the supplies are doubtlessly contaminated with the Blight, but leaving it in their hands helps no one.
I should let House Cousin Giras know the supplies have been returned to their rightful owners.
I've collected the supplies stolen from Senie. I should return them to House Cousin Giras.
Talk to Nedre in Deleyn's Mill
Nedre said that Galas was trapped on an island off the docks to the east.
The stranger doesn't seem inclined to conversation.  I'm forced to kill her.

I've spoken with Galas. I should go back to Deleyn's Mill and let Nedre know. nnI could tell her that Galas doesn't love her, or I could lie to her and tell her that he's dead. Either way, her heart will break.
Talk to Nedre in Deleyn's Mill
I should investigate around the monument.
I found two Dunmer in the cave, both gravely injured. I should find out what happened here from one or both of them.
I should look around the cave to see if there's anyone who witnessed what happened here.
Collect three bundles of Catnip for QAT Cat Lady or provide her with three QA Test Trophy items (Item 4824).
Now that you have the QAT Catnip, you should deliver it to the QAT Cat Lady.
If I wish to find out who would be living out here alone, I should enter the house and look for its owner.
I've collected a number of Dreugh chitin and should now return back to Faydlile on the coast of Emberquay.
I've been asked to collect several chitins from the Dreugh to the west.
I should talk to Wyress Jacinta in the Beldama Wyrd Camp.
The Redoran shippingmaster suggested I talk to the House Dres Foreman, Norus.  He can be found by the blightfence to the northeast of Kragenmore.
The Foreman Norus sent me to speak to his cousin, the Lawman Adrusu, at House Dres.
In addition to talking to the House Dres Foreman, I can also speak to the town tailor, Sulen.  He can be found in his shop in the east quarter of Kragenmoor.
The Foreman Norus sent me to speak to his cousin, the Lawman Adrusu, at House Dres.
To demonstrate my aptitude for forestry, I need to get some raw corn rose oil from plants near Daggerfall.

Now that I've successfully identified and gathered raw corn rose oil, I should report to the trainer in Daggerfall. If I'm not going to apply for an apprenticeship as a forester, I'll consider other tradeskills.
There are pockets of raw ore along the riverbanks below the Smith Guild. After I've found them, I can extract dioptase nuggets from it.
I've extracted several dioptase nuggets from the raw ore I found nearby. Smith Trainer Zhosh gro-Izburg will need to take a look at them at the Daggerfall Smith Guild.
Janan wants to test my interest in becoming an outfitter. She asked me to help the guild by collecting thin hides from woodland wolves. Apparently, the hunting is good near Daggerfall's eastern gate.
Now that I've skinned enough thin fresh hides from the lowland wolves I killed, I should take them to Janand Wickton, the trainer in Daggerfall.
I informed Nivele of Rajho's escape plans. I should let Rajho know he isn't going to be escaping anytime soon.

Before Camille Ashton can train me as a runecrafter, I'll need to bring her raw garnets from nodes at the base of Mount Dague. Then she'll know I can do the work.

I need to find a way to heal the injured man.

Now that I have the heroic remains, I can return to Lawman Adrusu, who can be found in the northeast quarter of Kragenmoor.
Reme asked me to collect cores from lurchers in the forests and groves around her home. I'll return any I find to her.

When I returned to Reme's house, she no longer looked human. Now she appears as a supernatural being. Clearly, she has a magical connection with those she tends. She doesn't appear hostile. I should talk to her and find out more.
I've collected lurcher cores that Reme can use to heal her injured guests. I better get them back to her house in the woods.

Reme's healing power relies on consuming a small portion of the life force of those she heals. The fact that she saves those who would otherwise die is a fair trade.nnI've decided to keep her secret. I should say goobye.

Though Reme's healing power may save those she feeds upon, the fact that she secretly takes their life force makes her more of a bane than a boon.nnWhen I said I would expose her, she vanished. I should explain this to her patients.
House Cousin Giras has asked me to burn the Contaminated Supplies and give the Stolen Supplies back to residents of Senie.

Now that I have the remains, I can return to Lawman Adrusu, who can be found in the northeast quarter of Kragenmoor.
Slouchbears can be found throughout the Scarlet Summit.
I have slain the Slouchbears as Mother Ana wished. I should inform her of my deeds.
Talk to Prince Gideon in the tower of Baelborne ruins.
After I fell Baelborne spirits in the ruins, I can use the soul cage to trap them forever.
I've collected remains from the grounds of Vivec's Antlers. I should bring them to Brela Garnes at the Argonian camp north of the coral growths.

You have discovered a set of ruins north of Daggerfall. Look around for evidence as to their origin.
<<1>> asked me to visit the homes of the fallen Wyrd Tree keepers. She wants me to retrieve their root charms, so she can return a small part of them to the Wyrd Tree.

Foreman Norus is pleased with my work, and wants to introduce me to Teranos, the House Father of House Dres.
