I've brewed the "curative" for Dalayn. I should give it to him to help him recover.
Dalayn has asked me to gather "ingredients" for a curative to help him recover from his last experiment.
I've gathered the ingredients Dalayn needs for his curative. Now they must be prepared with his Alchemist Tools.
I found the trapped wyress and set her free. I should return to Wyress Therese and let her know her sister is safe.
Rather than meet House Father Teranos, I should go talk to Lameni.  She's in eastern Kragenmoor.
To find out where Llameni was taken, I can try and get the information out of Lawman Adrusu, or I can see if I can get a look at the Kragenmoor Gatekeeper's log.
Now that I've found out that the Ordinator went to Heimlyn Keep, I should go there and see if I can find Llameni.
Now that I've found out that the Ordinator went to Heimlyn Keep, I should go there and see if I can find Llameni.
Now that I've found out that the Ordinator went to Heimlyn Keep, I should go there and see if I can find Llameni.

Maleron's Hoarvor Circus displays the acrobatic skill of giant, blood-sucking insects. I wonder what he feeds them?
I should escort Thellon safely out of the circus. If I do, the guards and hoarvor will certainly try to stop me.
I rescued Thellon from an Altmer's fiendish circus. He wants to rest. He asked me to report what happened to the guards along the road.
<<1>> was recaptured by <<2>> and his Wood Orc guards. They've probably taken him back to the hoarvor feeding tent.
Search the area for the source of the whisper - a Bosmer named Inveigler.
I found two lovers, one dead and one living. Perhaps I can do something to help them.
I'll find the Ashlanders to the south that I need to slay.

I've been sent to talk to Bravosi Dres, a Councilman of House Dres.
Jacinta has been enchanting charms against fever for her sisters and given out many of them, but three sisters still don't have them. She marked their last known locations on my map.

Wyress Jacinta asked me to meet with Wyress Gwen after bringing charms to her sisters.nnI should also speak to her about her sisters' suspicions. They believe that Blood Thorn adepts are working with Rock Biter goblins.
I've told the guard at Fort Thendr about the Argonian's claims that the blight storm is unnatural. I should speak to Ravus again to see about a reward.

Vivienne asked me to find her husband, who's probably also a spirit. I should search for Tomas near Westtry's abandoned barn.

I've been approached by a cloaked stranger.  I should probably find out what they want.
I should talk to Orthendor again now that his pet is healed.
Queen Ayarynne asked me to confront the suspicious members of her court. They are in the Thalmor.
I have confronted the rebellious Bosmer as Queen Ayarynne requested. I should return to her at the Thalmor building.
I must deliver the meat to Wort. He is along the road to the west of Razorvine Refuge, along the Haven Trace.
I discovered Methredhel performing a necromantic ritual in the city. She attacked me, and I defended myself - lethally.
I found Treethane Dangor, who had been transformed into a zombie. Perhaps he fell from favor with his new masters. In any event, It seems that problem took care of itself.
I confronted Ervas and convinced him to use his Imperial connections for the good of the Aldmeri Dominion.

I should find the cause of the Disturbed Spirits in Necris.

I should burn any cargo that has not yet been destroyed around Emberquay.

I have found the entrance into the heart of Black Log. The only way down is to jump.
Nix-hounds lair in the rocky outcropping around the Conclave. They occasionally raid the guar herds to pick off the slow and the weak.

I've found a scribbled note detailing the guard patrols and outline of Fort Virak. It is signed by a mysterious "S". I should return and inform Sathura of this.
I will need to investigate the camp to the south for any clues on what might bring the Ashlanders an advantage in this fight.

I've freed slaves around Omaynia and collected supplies from their masters. I should return to gra-Grensk.
I've destroyed Sera Alvar's remains, allowing Faynis to claim his fortune.

I agreed to use the Mudgum Vine on the saws in Stumptown.

The lumbercamp will fall into disrepair without leadership.

Queen Ayarynne has asked me to go to Cannonreeve Sorcassil's home and deliver him back to the Thalmor.

I should search the houses around town to find any slaves or supplies.

I should let the miners who were forced to abadon the mine that the Kwama Queen is dead and many of the blighted nests destroyed.

I ran across two duelists locked in battle. They seem to be intent of murdering each other. I should find a way to stop them.
The Imperial Scout Post is across the river to the west of Residue.nnI'll need to penetrate the camp to recover the Nirnroot <<1>> needs.

While wearing Coty's Necklace, the spirits of his brothers will recognize me as a friend. He asked that I helped these spirits pass on.nnThough Direnni wraiths should not attack me, Alessian wraiths will attack me on sight.

In order to help the Nord ghost, I can try and find an Argonian among the bodies buried here, and take his tongue.  Failing that, I could kill a few Alit and try to make a passable tongue out of their tongues.

The bottle of wine was obviously important to Chamberlain Weller. He is unlikely to return for it any time soon.nnDuke Sebastien and his entourage are waiting in Aldcroft. If I returned the bottle to Chamberlain Weller, he would be quite grateful.

Talk to Warden Rielle in Aldcroft.
I'm escorting a traveler to Warden Rielle in Aldcroft. He's been enthralled by will-o-the-wisps before, and I don't want it to happen again.
I should take this insignia and inform the someone at the gates of Davon's Watch that Fort Arand has fallen to the Blight.
I should talk to the traveler to see if I can help.
I'm escorting a traveler to Aldcroft. Protecting him from attacks will take some work.
At the Duke of Camlorn's request, I rescued a second prisoner from the Bloodthorn cult, Gloria Fausta. I should make sure that <<1>> made it back to Aldcroft.

Harim and those he works for have Duke Sebastien hostage.nnHarim refused to honor his deal with Weller. He asked for double the original price, and Weller's package, but I refused.nnWeller is at his house in Aldcroft. He should hear of this.

I should try and solve the merchant's issue, if only to keep him from doing something drastic.
I've stolen the key for Wort. I should bring it to him in Heimlyn Keep.
I should find the gaoler of Heimlyn Keep and steal the key from him. Wort gave me a sap to incapacitate him. I'll find him just outside the walls, patrolling the road.
I must survive the gauntlet and reach Goreclaw's Pit.
Danain gave me a sighting gem. I can focus it on any enemy who gives me trouble, and the Lion Guard will respond by focusing their magic on it. The gem has five charges.
I've used all five charges of the Lion Guard Sighting Gem to destroy my enemies in Camlorn.
Adept Sommers gave me a teleportation gem. He asked me to use it to rescue Lady Elise and any other survivors I find in Camlorn.nnAfter I teleport them back, the Lion Guard will protect them.
I have located all survivors in Camlorn. I should return to Adept Sommers, in Camlorn's courtyard, to report my success.
The temple may house survivors. If I find any, I should teleport them back to Sommers.
I see human footprings leading behind a house. I should teleport any survivors I find to safety.
If I find any survivors inside the inn, I should teleport them to Sommers.
I've poisoned Galva's food as hinted by Ervasa. I should return to him and let him know of my actions.
To heal the spring, I need to collect enchanted seeds from the lurchers in Glenumbra Bog.
If there are any survivors inside, I should teleport them to Sommers.
I should teleport any survivors I find in the courtyard back to Sommers.
Phrastus is in league with the Huntress. He sent me to a crocodile pit. I must escape!
I must inform Redthicket of Phrastus' treachery.
I must talk to Phrastus, the Silvenar. If he agrees with Redthicket, he will step aside as Silvenar and bestow the title upon me.
Phrastus blocks the hallway, taunting me. He will pay for his betrayal.
Destroying the laboratory will stop Blackhand necromancers from animating more corpses.

<<1>> can be found in the city of Silvenar, which lies along the road northeast from Vulkwasten.nn<<2>> asked me to carry word of Vulkwasten's plight to <<1>> in the Camoran Bosmer capital. He warned that skinchangers may guard the road.
I am to demand Prince Aeradran take up arms and resume the attack on the Feladrim to the north.
I spoke with Prince Aeradran, demanding he attack Prince Gelthior. This was a command he was eager to recieve.
I should speak to the Gulakhan so she does not leave without Ohitinti.
I've retrieved the stolen supplies. I should return them to the Gulakhan.
I should search the area nearby the Ashlander Caravan for the Stolen Supplies.
It appears that <<1>> is drawing close to a resolution. I could ask him what he's decided.
<<1>> wishes to discuss the situation at the Shrine, but can't voice his doubts to his men without losing their confidence. As an outsider, I could listen without prejudice.
I've warned the Ashlanders though they seem ready for a fight. I should continue to speak to Farseer Galesa.
I need to find a way to safely pass through the Bloodlusters. It would be simple to fight my way through, but there may be other possibilities.
I have taken Hircine's Third Stone from the Huntress, and she has fled to the ancient site of Moonhenge, west of the Valley of the Hunt.
I have found the ancient site of Moonhenge, where the Huntress is going to summon the Wild Hunt. I must stop her any way I can.
After slying the Huntress a trio of spirits has appeared in Moonhenge. I should commune with the Spirit of the Wild to see what I may learn.
I see a glowing portal in the next room. This may return me to the surface.
I've collected the two kinds of cuttle Dutabael wanted. I should bring them to him before he leaves Stonefalls.
I should search under Spongy Mushrooms and Shale Fragments for kwama. They each have a particular type of cuttle that Dutabael wants.
The slaughterfish extract needed for the Ordinator's plan will be found in the small river between the camp and shrine.
I've gathered enough slaughterfish extract to be useful. I need to return to Ordinator Ulden who waits at his camp to the west.
Urili wants me to collect the baggage she dropped while escaping the Solir Nath Ancestral Tomb.  The tomb is to the southeast of Urili's retreat.
Now that I've collected a number of Urili's things, I should return them to her.  She retreated to an Ashlander camp to the northwest of the tombs.
The braziers are located in the Shrine of Meridia, scattered through out the area. I should avoid mixing the extract while the Ashlanders are in the area.
I've finished dumping the extract and creating a horrible stench causing many to flee to the river. I should return to the Ordinator to report my success.
I should use Dyns' flute to soothe the agitated Solir Nath ancestors back to their eternal slumber.  The ancestors can be found all around the Solir Nath Ancestral Tomb.
I've played Dyns' flute for several of the Solir Nath ancestors, putting them back to rest.  I should return to Dyns with the news.
Before I enter the Danain Family Tomb, Ahji asked me to kill wraiths at the ancient battlesite. She wants revenge for their attack on her.
Ahji has her vengeance. The wraiths at the battle site speak of werebeasts and an undead king. I should explore the Danain Family Tomb for any trace of this Werereaver.

When I entered the Danain family tomb, a ghost appeared and whispered to me. It claims it was "expecting me".nnIf I want to learn more of the Werereaver, the ancient battlesite, and the wraith uprising, I should speak to it.
I'm going to help train a Lion Guard recruit. Together, we're going to kill ancient bog lurchers and will-o-the-wisps along the road to the siege camp.
Go to the main path between Aldcroft and the Siege Camp. The Magis Order Recruit said they would meet you there to continue the training.

Coty said I should leave the ancient battle site on its west side, then follow the road west to the Cave of Penance. He believes the thief and the sword Werereaver is inside.nnHe wants me to recover Werereaver and use it against Faolchu.
We've completed our training. I should talk to the Lion Guard's recruit.
I've burned the census records. Now I'm carrying false Redoran documents that accuse House Dres of selling Kragenmoor's poor into slavery. I should return to <<1>> with the forged census records.

There's a record cabinet in the southernmost building of Kragenmoor. It contains documents critical to House Dres. I could retrieve them, but I'll have to stay alert. The city has become rather dangerous of late.
Scout Mithiel wants revenge against Selene. She wants me to weaken her by killing her three champions.
I killed three of Selene's champions. I should see if Mithiel found her way back to Tilmo's camp.

Danea believes that since the nearby creatures showed up right as the brothers began to bicker that they may somehow be connected. I should begin to thin their number to see if the apparent curse seems to weaken.
I've slain several creatures within the ruin area. I'll need to return to Danea to see if the curse has weakend.
I need to find a way to safely pass through the Bloodlusters. It would be simple to fight my way through, but there may be other possibilities.
Lord Diel asked me to check on Maddoc and make sure he's all right. I'll find him along the road heading east from the beach.
Maddoc asked me to check on Lord Alain, who is west down the road to the beach, if I happen to be heading that way.
Jodie asked me to journey east down the road and make sure the squire she saw is all right.
Alain gave me a lure and invited me to use any of his extra poles to fish. He would appreciate the conversation and companionship.
I have caught a large mackerel on my first attempt at fishing. I should compare notes with Alain.
I'm still looking for the owner of Alma's locket near the farms.
I have been given a large golden key and told that it opens one of the main vaults, from which I can select one of Gemin's treasures.
I have been given a silver key that unlocks matching treasure within the Vaults of Gemin.
I have been given a silver key that unlocks matching treasure within the Vaults of Gemin.
I have been given a silver key that unlocks matching treasure within the Vaults of Gemin.
I have been given an iron key that opens a wooden box, bound in bronze.
I have helped the <<1>> escape the Imperial Palisade. I should meet him at our planned spot, by the creek crossing outside the Palisade.
Panoit asked me to travel northeast of the redoubt to Crosswych. Arnand can tell me more about a weapon that can defeat Angof.
Danain asked me to travel to Crosswych by following the road from Camlorn to the north. nnI'll discuss the contents of his urgent letter with his old teacher, Armand.

Since the warship is too large to attack directly, <<1>> asked me to burn the boats used to ferry supplies ashore.nnThe boats to be burned are moored alongside the large warship west of the Imperial Landing beach.
When I set alight several of the boats alongside the Imperial warship, the larger vessel caught fire. <<1>> will be glad to hear of this unexpected coup.
Arnand asked me to take the Midnight Talisman to Magus Commander Panoit at the redoubt.nnPanoit may know a mage powerful enough to reactivate the Midnight Talisman.
Magus Commander Panoit said I should bring the Midnight Talisman to a mage named Marcel Wirch. I'll find Marcel at an altar west of Panoit's camp.
I've recovered the Reach Cloak. Ackers asked that I speak to Arnand Murrell in Crosswych.nnCrosswych is on the road north from the Dwynnarth Ruins.
Ackers asked me to return to Arnand Murrell in Crosswych. I'll let him know we recovered the Thornbane Cloak.nnI can reach Crosswych by following the road north from the Dwynnarth Ruins.
If I want to use the crab meat as a lure, I should return to Lord Alain Diel on the beach north of Daggerfall and use his Spare Fishing Pole to fish.
I've used Alain's fishing pole to catch a small tuna. I should see if he will trade it for something valuable.
I've used Alain's fishing pole to catch a rainbow carp. I should see if he will trade it for something valuable.
If I want to use the harpy gizzard as a lure, I should return to Lord Alain Diel on the beach north of Daggerfall and use his Spare Fishing Pole to fish.
With Lord Alan Diehl's spare fishing pole and a brilliant harpy feather to use as a lure, I should be able to catch a fish.
I've used Alain's fishing pole to catch a giant catfish. I should see if he will trade it for something valuable.
Perhaps this zombie remembers something of its life. It looks to be no threat. I should see if it can speak.
Perhaps this zombie remembers something of its life. It looks to be no threat. I should see if it can speak.

Blain tracked Blanche to Soldier's Hill, just north of Cath Bedraud. He asked me to check on her.nnHe cannot involve Magus Commander Panoit because Panoit would have no choice but to bring Blanche, a deserter, home in chains.
I've returned the deed to Depaul Gaudet. I should talk to him about what happened.

Reskard's men managed to close one of the portals from which the invaders are attacking. However, they were left weak and spread out and enemies overwhelmed them and cut them off from the main force. He wants me to clear out intruders in the garden.
Commander Viskel has enlisted my aid in driving back the invaders pouring from the portals and report back to Gemin if successful.
I have helped turn away the invaders and should speak with Gemin.
After clearing out the invaders in the garden, Captain Reskard asked me to report to Commander Viskel, who is holding off invaders by the main portal just beyond the gardens.
I should inform Josaja of the Spirit's death.
Traitorous <<1>>s can be found scattered throughout the Imperial Landing beaches.
I've slain a number of the traitorious <<1>>s on the Imperial Landing beaches. <<2>> will be pleased to hear this. He awaits my return in a boat northwest of the Imperial Landing.
I should investigate the source of the acrid odor, the small house nearby.

Harpies have completely overrun the ramparts of Oldgate, but if I can manage to fire off a few ballistae, perhaps the hags will dissipate. The ballistae are on the east and west sections of the Oldgate ramparts.
I blasted some of the flying harpies over Oldgate. One can only hope the others got the message. I should let Captain Gagnon know of my success.
The poisoned spices that are to be delivered to the Lion Guard are sitting on the docks near the Aldcroft Lighthouse. I should use the Kindlepitch Josia gave me to destroy the spices.
I have been given a silver key that unlocks matching treasure within the Vaults of Gemin.
Gemin has asked me to speak to Captain Reskard and offer my help in turning away the so-called party crashers.
I should deliver this root charm to Wyress Jacinta in the Beldama Wyrd Camp.

I need to speak to the leaders of the other noble houses in Shornhelm. <<1>> of House Tamrith is on the west side of the city, and <<2>> of House Dorell is in the east. They'll have answers about the civil war within Shornhelm.
I need to choose a side. I might speak to <<1>> of House Tamrith on the west side of the city about the civil war within Shornhelm, or I may pledge my aid to <<2>> of House Dorell.
I've decided to side with House Tamrith. I need to speak with <<1>> to inform her of my choice.
I've decided to side with House Dorell. I need to speak with <<1>> to inform him of my choice.
Alain gave me a lure and invited me to use any of his extra poles to fish. He would appreciate the conversation and companionship.
If I want to use the crab meat as a lure, I should return to Lord Alain Diel on the beach north of Daggerfall and use his Spare Fishing Pole to fish.
If I want to use the harpy gizzard as a lure, I should return to Lord Alain Diel on the beach north of Daggerfall and use his Spare Fishing Pole to fish.
If I want to use the brilliant feather as a lure, I should return to Lord Alain Diel on the beach north of Daggerfall and use his Spare Fishing Pole to fish.
It is possible there could be a fisherman along the beach of Daggerfall Cove. That would be a good place to look for guidance on how to fish.
I've agreed to gather Amberberries from the ledges and bring them back to Tung. I'll have to be careful when I'm leaping between these ledges.
Tung has made some Amberberry wine. I should speak to him again.
I found all the belongings of Farmer Gaudet's family, and I killed the trackers who were looking for them. Now I'm on my way to Depaul Gaudet. He's southeast of the farm.
I should fight my way past Montclair soldiers and get to Lieutenant Fairfax. He's on the northern edge of the Wracked Plain.
To put the sentinel's spirit at ease, I should light the signal fire atop the watchtower.
The leader of this village is no friend to the Dominion. If left alive, he'll surely attack Southpoint.
<<1>> will want to hear about the death of Treethane Blackroot.
A journal in the tower revealed that this ghost has been here since the defeat of the Alessian Order in High Rock. I should tell the King's Watch Ghost.
A journal in the tower revealed that the King's Watch Ghost has been here since the defeat of the Alessian Order. I should tell the ghost how much time has passed.
I've collected Amberberries. I must return to Tung.
I've taken the head of a Hieronian scout. I should show it to a Jaqspur Bosmer at the eastern end of Haven Trace.
I should find a way to put the ghostly soldier to rest. Perhaps I should speak to him, or maybe I should search the inn for clues.
I should find a way  to put the ghostly soldier to rest. Perhaps I should speak to him, or search the inn for clues.
Dalen asked me to poison Belkali Village's water source, to avenge his death.nnThe spring is located just south of the village proper.
I've poisoned the waters at the spring. I should return to tell Dalen.nn<<1>> can be found caged at the north end of Belkali Village.
When I led the reanimated lurcher to the ritual site, the powerful magic of the Wyrd consumed it.nn I should speak to Wyress Gwen to see if her sisters have learned anything new from its destruction.

Wyress Gwen believes that her sisters are corrupted. The spirits are afraid of them.nnShe's asked me to summon the spirits. I need to present a Wyrd offering between the five standing stones at the center of the ritual site.
I've given tools to Pierre. Now I need to deliver the remaining tools to Frizkav Aurilie and Pierre Moniel.
I've given tools to Michelle, I need to deliver the remaining tools to Frizkav Aurilie and Pierre Moniel.
I've given tools to Frizkav. Now I need to deliver the remaining tools to Michelle Madach and Pierre Moniel.
Ormax asked me to take tools to his foremen:nnFrizkav is to the northeast, near the Shrine.nnMichelle is in a large clearing slightly to the northwest.nnPierre is northeast of Michelle.
As Ormax asked, I've delivered tools to Frizkav and Michelle. Now I need to find Pierre and give him the remaining tools.
As Ormax asked, I've delivered tools to Pierre and Michelle. Now I need to find Frizkav and give him the remaining tools.
As Ormax asked, I've delivered tools to Pierre and Frizkav. Now I need to find Michelle and give her rest of the tools.
<<1>> asked me to take the tools I recovered to a man named <<2>> in Deleyn's Mill, down the eastern road.nnHe said Ormax will pay me for delivery.
I've completed the sentry initiation rites. I should return to Elder Brump.
I must invoke the night stone to begin the Rite of Initiation. The night stone is outside the cave to the east.
The first apparition has appeared. I must slay it.
I defeated the first apparition. I should use the night stone to summon the last one.
Another apparition appeared. I must slay this threat to Valenwood!
I must use the Night Stone one last time.

I'm looking for the Gaudet family's belongings in the soil of the Gaudet farm. The bandits brought wolves to look for the farmer's belongings. I'll have to kill all the bandit trackers, just to make sure they never try this again.
<<1>>s hang from trees near Wood Orc camps in Haven Trace. I can use them to reach the scouts in the treetops and warn them about the orcs' fire salts.
I have warned the scouts in Haven Trace and should report what <<1>> and I discovered to <<2>> at the eastern end of the Trace.
I should speak to Shoom about the sentry initiation rites.
Whoever owned this locket must have lived near the farms.
<<1>> asked me to search the Wracked Plain for any Lion Guard survivors who might have been taken prisoner.
I should return to Alisane and let her know I helped several survivors escape the battlefield. She's with <<1>> on the Wracked Plain between Oldgate and Shornhelm.
Baf asked me to enter the Tiger Tunnels, so I could fetch a satchel from his wagon.
I retrieved Baf's satchel. I should return it to him.
If I want to help the Lion Guard, I should report to <<1>> at the front gates of Camlorn. The city lies the west.
Based on her own symptoms, <<1>> believes that Lion Guard soldiers are being turned into bloodfiends. If I can find a bloodfiend carrying Lion Guard equipment, it would prove her correct.
Naveed cannot look for Blade-Turner without leaving his Mages Guild escorts unguarded. He asked me to look for Blade-Turner deeper in the Dwynnarth Ruins.
I have agreed to help <<1>>, who is troubled by a <<2>> horde in Root-Sunder Ruins.
I have destroyed another <<1>> haunting Root-Sunder Ruins, one of many. I should return to <<2>> and inform him that the ruins are now safe for study.
Though Blade-Turner advised me to turn back, he warned me to be wary of the Shadow of Dwynnarth should I venture deeper into the ruins.nnHe said I should not face it without a friend or two.
I have defeated the Shadow of Dwynnarth. Blade-Turner has likely returned to Naveed at the top of the ruins. He will be relieved to hear the shadow is no longer a threat.
I've recharged the  <<z:1>>. I should bring it to the <<z:2>>.
I should search <<1>> for the bodies of uncorrupted nereids and recharge the <<z:2>>.
Lael asked me to destroy the corrupted forms of spectres who were once her friends. She asked me to use a magical gem on the spectres' ectoplasmic remains to free their souls from Angof's torment.
I've freed the souls of Lael's fallen friends. This news may bring her comfort. I'll find her at the center of the Dwynnarth Ruins, tending to a nightblade named Ackers.
I've been tasked to find Elder Brump in Stumptown.
According to the journal, the author was searching for a powerful Daedric artifact with her friend. The journal ends abruptly after the author mentioned making a camp at the top of the hill.
I should collect the missing journal pages scattered along the path northeast of Hoarfrost Downs.
Now that the journal is reassembled, I can find out what happened to its owner.
The lights appear to have their origin in the southern reaches of Lushwallow.
I have the totem, and I should return it to the Lushwallow sage in Mireblossom village.
I allowed the circle to collpase around the Dark Seducer, sending her soul back to Oblivion. She left behind a strange weapon.
I've released the Dark Seducer from her bindings. She vanished and left behind a strange weapon.
With the crystals taken, the circle of magic containing the <<1>> seems to be collapsing. If the Daedra is left in there, she may not survive the collapse. I should either free her or let her perish.
I should gather focus crystals from around the cave.
<<1>>, a ghostly apparition in Root-Sunder Ruins, has challenged me to a duel. I can attack him if I wish to fight.
If the survivor is still alive, maybe I can save him.
One of the bloodfiends in Moira's Hope has Edmonde's shovel. I doubt a polite request will help me get it back.
I've put out the fires in Moria's Hope.nnI should tell Edmonde the good news. He's hiding in his house at the east end of the village.
<<1>> asked me to search the Root-Sunder Ruins for his apprentice, <<2>>.
The Bosmer of Lushwallow are forbidden to harm spriggans, so Anucia asked me to use a magical stone to calm them. Using the stone on a spriggan will soothe it back into the earth.
I have calmed some spriggans. I should return to Anucia.
I should read the Rune-Etched Stones scattered around the ruins.
I have learned the history of the mages from Summerset. I should return to Anirnwe.
After touching the <<1>> I can suddenly see a ghostly figure. I should speak to it, "learn its history" as it requested.
I've slain Orcs and placed their heads on pikes in Ranser's camp. I should return to Corporal Taern and see if that's appeased her bloodlust.
I need to slay Wrothgar commanders and take their heads. Then I can put those heads on empty pikes about the tor.
I am looking for the first Hidden Tome, somewhere in Root-Sunder Ruins.nn"Tome the first, hidden underground. A tomb for a tome, a home among bones."
I've spoke with King Ranser. He believes his army will hold the tor long after death. This must be what triggered the curse.
General Dathieu cannot spare a soldier to fulfill Ranser's request, so I volunteered. I must bury the contents of the bag at four points around the tor.
I should inform Ranser that I've fulfilled his request.
A Magis Order Soldier asked me to find his leader, Magus Commander Bieller, and help him with the situation in Eagle's Brook.nnBieller should be somewhere on the south side of Eagle's Brook.
I should speak with a <<1>> and ask about the other tomes.
I am looking for the second Hidden Tome, somewhere in Root-Sunder Ruins.nn"Tome the second, not hidden, but lost. Salty leather jaws made knowledge a meal."
Jayne asked me to explore more of the caves. I need to locate and kill the creature called "Mother."
I've slain Mother Murk and her minions. I should go to Crosswych. Jayne and Margett should know the nightmare is over.
I should speak with a <<1>> and ask about the other tomes.
I am looking for the third Hidden Tome, somewhere in Root-Sunder Ruins.nn"Tome the third, once hidden, now exposed. Taken to the heights, to a tower, in the light."

Lord Montclair is holding captives in the <<1>>. I can get there through a tunnel behind his manse in the northern district. I might warn House Dorell of Lady Eselde's plans for Lord Montclair's captives, but if I do, <<2>> will surely find out.
I've informed Lord Alard of House Tamrith's plans. I should speak to him about continuing to work with his house.
In the time it took me to follow her outside, <<1>> disappeared. I'll have to track her down.
I have found the Hidden Tomes, and should now take them to <<1>>.
I have found a curious vault that seems to be pulsing with spiritual energy. I could open it, unleashing whatever is being held inside.

Lord Montclair uses the <<1>> to hold his captives. It's through the tunnel behind the manse in the northern district. If I wish I can warn House Tamrith of Lord Alard's brutal plans for Lord Montclair's captives, though <<2>> will surely find out.
I've informed House Tamrith of House Dorell's plans. I should speak to Lady Eselde about continuing to work with her house.
I tried to warn <<1>> of Lord Alard's plans, but since I had already betrayed her house, she wouldn't listen. I should go to the <<2>>  through the tunnel behind the manse, in the Northern District.

I tried to warn <<1>> of <<2>>'s plans, but since I was not aligned with his House, he wouldn't listen.nnI should travel north within <<3>>, past Lord Montclair's manse to the <<4>>, where he takes his captives.

I have spoken with the tribal sage. He's quite willing to follow me to Mireblossom village. The Peatwalkers didn't attack me when I entered the village, but the sage reminded me that if they see me abducting him, they will not hesitate to attack.
I made it back to Mireblossom village safely with the tribal sage. I should speak to him.

Grim wants me to help him find Liea, who was taken by the local Bitterkite bandits. He's suggested that I should kill the bandits around Trader's Meet until I find her. Seems like a rather straightforward strategy.
I've found Leia, who turned out to be a small ginger kitten. I should take her to Grim at Trader's Meet.

The Mireblossom tribalists can't abduct a new sage because they're too frightened of the spriggans. They asked me instead. I can find the Peatwalker's tribal sage in a village on the western side of Lushwallow.
I should find out what the Orcs are mining. I should be able to find samples in the mines or the nearby camps.
The Orcs are mining and stockpiling pyroil stone. <<1>> will want to know about this.
I have found all the survivors in Camlorn. Anyone else is either a werewolf, or has already escaped.nnOnly Lady Elise remains inside the city.
The Spider Daedra's children are crawling around the Spider Tower south of Trader's Meet. If I kill them, I should consider finding her and graciously accepting the reward she's promised me.
I've killed the Spider Daedra's children. If I return to her at Spider Tower, I should let her know I've exacted her revenge.
I told <<1>> to let her husband think he was the one to get the pelts. That would spare his wounded pride. I should still check on her, though, just in case.
<<1>> has asked me to kill lowland wolves and skin them for their pelts.
Jayne Durhnim is missing. Her sister Margett thinks she might be near a coastal cave west of the Dwynnarth Ruins.
I've located Jayne and freed her from her cage. I don't know how she got there.
I've hunted wolves, skinned them, and bundled their pelts for <<1>> and her husband. I should return to the ruined tower east of Camlorn and talk to her again.
I told <<1>> she shouldn't lie to her drunken husband. She should tell him I was the one to get the pelts, or he'll just do this again. I should check on her.
Raymond asked me to collect the vase to his left and take it to a grave in Camlorn. It holds his ashes.
Elisa Helane is buried in Camlorn's graveyard by the Temple of Julianos. Raymond asked me to go there and scatter his ashes on her grave.
I found a young woman named Jayne. She's locked in a cage deep inside a cave, and she's asked me to free her.
I released a young woman from a cage deep inside a cave on the coast. Her name is Jayne Durnhill. I should find out how she got there.
If I can calm the horses with apples, Ronal's sons should be able to reassert control of the horses and find their way home. I should find them.
Now that I've defeated the lost souls and returned from the dream realm, I should speak to <<1>>.
Jayne asked me to explore more of the caves. I need to find and kill the creature called "Mother."
I've killed Mother Murk and her minions. I should go to Crosswych. Jayne and Margett should know the nightmare is over.
Gerard and Ferdie can't leave the mine. Risen miners and spectres lie in wait between the miners and the entryway.  nnIf I can clear a path, they'll make their escape.

The path to the mine entrance has been cleared. Gerard and Ferdie lost no time in making their escape.nnGerard offered me a pint as a reward for saving them. I'll collect it later at the Crosswych Pub.
Blink asked me to board the ship and drop a Jar of Sleeping Tunnelmites in the ship's hold -- the lowest deck. The Tunnelmites will wake up angry and hungry.
The Tunnelmites burst from the jar and began devouring the ship. Soon the ship will sink.
I've found the painting of Sir Sofia. I should bring it back to the art collector. He's in the cave north of Merovec's Folly.
I should look in the ruins north of Camlorn for a painting of Sir Sofia.
A weary sailor told me about a shipwreck he survived. He lost his cargo, and he claims that mudcrabs took his ale.nnMaybe I should kill <<1>> and see if they have any Crosswych Ale.
I actually found some Crosswych Ale. I should give it to <<1>> on the northern beach.nnHe seems to need it.
I'm hunting harpies in Merovec's Folly northeast of Camlorn. A Bosmer hunter needs their sinew for bowstrings.
I should give <<1>> the harpy sinew I harvested so she can fix her bow. She should still be in a tower in Merovec's Folly.
The Herdmother bade me to defeat the wind spirits of the plains. When I'm ready, she'll summon them for me.
I defeated a wind spirit summoned by the Herdmother. I should speak to her and see if this satisfies her.
Draining the Giant Welkynd Stone may hinder the efforts of the cultists.
I should help Arlois Leyron and the other refugees establish a new home by slaying some of the spiders in Spindleclutch.
I've slain several of the spiders in the ruins. I should report back to Arlois Leyron and let him know.
Draining the Giant Welkynd Stone may hinder the efforts of the cultists.
Draining the Giant Welkynd Stone may hinder the efforts of the cultists.
Draining the Giant Welkynd Stone may hinder the efforts of the cultists.
The survivor told me at least two other mages were still alive in the ruins. He asked me to look for them and free them, if I could.
I've rescued the survivors of the Mages Guild expedition from Blackhand cultists. Lael Corgine is at the entrance to the ruins, and he'll want to hear this news.
I need to locate these three miners in Crosswych Mines and heal their injuries so that they can escape.
I've located Piers Renoit. nnIsaura and Raoul must be deeper in the mine. I must find them and heal their injuries so that they can escape.
I've located Raoul Jolvanne. Now I must find Isaura and Piers and heal their injuries so that they can escape.
I've located Isaura Belette.nnI must find Piers and Raoul, then heal their injuries so that they can escape.
I should speak with Isaura Belette.
I should speak with Piers Renoit.
I should talk to Raoul Jolvanne.
I must retrieve the cage key.
I have the cage key. Now I can unlock Elder Brump's cage.
Elder Brump ran off and is on his way to his home in Cliffvoot.nnHe asked me to talk to an Imga named Yoon, in the treetops of Calypsi's Foothold.
Augur Strenra has asked me to enter her augurium. I should be able to see and speak to her future self.
I should speak to the prophet in her human form.

I have filled Lael's gem with the corrupted essence of Angof's wraiths. Lael asked me to return the gem to her at the sealed entrance to the Dwynnarth Ruins.nnShe hopes to use it to break the ward the Blackhand Cultists have placed on the door.
I should tell Augur Strenra what I saw in the augurium.
I need to enter the cave and free any townsfolk I find.
I should let Jean know the captives have been freed.
I need to locate and heal Isaura Belette.
I need to locate and heal Piers Renoit.
I need to locate and heal Raoul Jolvanne.
I recovered the stolen stolen travelling supplies from highwaymen in Cambray Pass. <<1>> should know she can set up her business again.
I should gather stolen travelling supplies from the highwaymen in Cambray Pass.
Gustave gave me some seed to put in the empty bird baskets. That should lure the birds back inside them.
I lured several birds back into their baskets. I should return to Gustave and let him know they're safe.

The mage hoped to use an oppositely charged Welkynd shard to disrupt the flow of power to the Welkynd stones. He was killed in the attempt.nnA Welkynd shard was hidden in his journal. I can use it to prevent the cultists from harming anyone else.

I've interrupted the flow of power to the giant Welkynd stones in the ruins. The Blackhand cultists can no longer use them to harness magicka. I should speak with Lael Corgine just outside the entrance to see if anything else is required.
I need to harvest harpy talons and feathers to create a realistic harpy scarecrow.
I have the bonesnatcher heads and should place them upon King Faume Toad-Eye's grave, located behind Golleon.
Lith asked me to look for signs of the Mages Guild expedition in the Dwynnarth Ruins.
The Bitterkite's main camp is northwest of the place where the Calvez caravan was attacked. I should search the camp for Chaliene.
I've rescued Chaliene, and she immediately back to the caravan. I should follow her and make sure she made it back safely. The Calvez caravan is southeast of the Bitterkite camp.
Gustave wants me to find Therese. If she's not at the main Bitterkite camp to the northwest, she might be at the camp to the northeast.
Therese wasn't inclined to return to Gustave. She'd rather be a bandit. nnShe asked me to return his ring to him. She threw in the river to the north.
I found Gustave's ring in the belly of an extremely vicious fish. I should return it to him at the Calvez caravan.
When I replaced the last remnant of Franck's treasure, a hooded man hailed me from the first floor of the tomb. Perhaps he knows about Franck's curse.
Mudwin asked me to find and kill a bone colossus, the massive pet of Serge the Unclean. It now wanders High Rock, roaming the area around Cath Bedraud and the tombs below.
I've destroyed the bone colossus. Mudwin, the ghostly hooded figure waiting in the tombs below Cath Bedraud, will be eager for this news.
Once I find Jean Dupaul, I can offer my help. According to the flyer, I should be able to find him somewhere near the coast.
I've located Jean. I should speak to him and see how I can help.
Trinkets are hidden in a cave in Spindleclutch.
I've found the sack of trinkets. I should take them to Kayha.
Arlios wants me to rescue cocooned refugees in Spindleclutch.
I've rescued several refugees. I should let Arlios Leyron know they're safe.
I should talk to <<1>> in the Crosswych Inn.
I should go to Crosswych and confront <<1>>.
I should talk to <<1>> in the Crosswych Inn.
A villager offered me money to kill lurchers surrounding a house outside Crosswych.
I should return to <<1>> in the Crosswych Inn.

Panoit asked me to look for his lieutenants surrounding Cath Bedraud. If I can't help his soldiers defend their banner, I can at least help a lieutenant raise a new one. Together, we'll rally the Lion Guard against Angof's waves of undead.
I must defend the Lion Guard banner. I'll proudly fight beside the lieutenants and soldiers of the Lion Guard. Together, we defy the relentless undead.
The <<1>> is shaking, as if about to burst open.
The Imperials have encamped in force just south of Razorvine Refuge.
<<1>> can be found inside the south entrance of Razorvine Refuge. She will be expecting delivery of the <<2>>'s head.

The librarian in the Mages Guild is worried about his colleagues that went to aid the small town of Crestshade. He has not heard back from them in several days, and wishes me to find out what has become of them.
I should find a representative of the Mages Guild in Shornhelm. I need to ask if they have anyone they can spare to help defend against Montclair's forces.
I need to find a representative of the Mages Guild in Shornhelm. I should ask i f they have anyone they can spare to help Alard Dorell defeat Montclair's forces.

The librarian in the Mages Guild told me their forces have been sent to Crestshade, a town west of Shornhelm. He hasn't heard back from them in several days. He's asked me to find out what became of them.
The village of Razorvine Refuge is besieged by Imperials advancing from Haven. It will be difficult to reach the town.
He asked me to investigate the tower overlooking <<1>>. He believes the necromancer who created the bloodfiends roaming <<2>> hides within it.

The necromancer used bodies of fallen mages to create a powerful undead construct. I should meet spirits of the defenders of Crestshade at the graveyard ruins, light the brazier to summon the abomination, and end this nightmare by destroying it.
I defeated Tainted-Heart's undead creation, but not before he teleported away. I should inform Tharlas that the necromancer is no longer in Crestshade.
A villager pleaded with me to kill Bloodthorn lurchers surrounding a house outside Crosswych.
I should return to <<1>> in the southern tower near Crosswych.
I'll need to help a refuge defender hold off the attacking bloodfiends.
I've found the sigil shard that is luring the Daedra into the estate. Baroness Dorrell entered behind me. I should see what she has to say.
Now that I've successfully destroyed the anchors, I should return to <<1>>. She's in the fields north of her manor.
I have found the head of Meridia's statue. The Servant of Meridia awaits my return in the Veiled Grotto.
The Servant of Meridia has begun the ritual to request Meridia's blessing. I must drink from the two basins on either side of the shrine to show my devotion.
I released the Timber Mammoth and should inform Kiama, hiding outside the entrance of Barkbite.
I've spoken with the shade of the last wielder of the sword I found buried in Cath Bedraud. In life, she was known as Sir Sofia. I should return to Marcel with this new information.
I should speak to the spirit of the Herdmother and ask what I must do to prove myself.
The Lion Guard has many mages, and their redoubt is just south of Cath Bedraud. Perhaps someone there can tell me more about the ancient weapon I've found.

Marcel told me how to unlock the enchantment on the ancient weapon. We need the name of its last wielder.nnMarcel thinks the weapon's last wielder is buried in Merovec's Folly, west of the redoubt. He asked me to look for a grave marker in the area.
I've retrieved the Midnight Talisman from Jadier the Blackhand.nnArnand Murrelll in Crosswych knows what to do with it. I'll find him at the exit to Crosswych Mine.
I should speak to the sapling. I have throughly searched the cave and found items that may help ease its suffering.
I've found a potion purported to induce forgetfulness, which I used on the sapling. I should speak to it to see if it worked.
I've destroyed the strange sapling near the <<1>>. I should make sure it is truly dead.
I should follow and assist the beckoning spirit.
The spirit disappeared and a skeleton formed out of the bones I collected. I should speak to this skeleton.
Leon asked me to find his undead body and destroy it. I'll know the body is Leon's when I find a necklace with a wolf tooth on the corpse.
I killed Leon's resurrected body and recovered his necklace. Leon's spirit wanders the tombs east of Cath Bedraud. I should find it and give him this news.
The cries of the  <<1>> are maddening. Ellaria Belloc might know of a way to silence it.
I've silenced the spirit. I should speak with Ellaria Belloc again.
I need to locate trapped miners. Then I can let them know I've cleared a way for their escape.
I located several surviving trapped miners within the Crosswych Mine and cleared the way for their escape.nnThey asked that I stop to let Marthe Yvienne outside the mine know how many I've rescued.
Didier Panoit has put a contract on my head. I should find Panoit and show him exactly what I think about this.
I've killed Didier Panoit. According to the contract he placed on my head, someone has also put a bounty on Panoit. I should visit his brother to collect it.
I am searching for the daughter of <<1>>, a woman by the name of <<2>>. She should be somewhere within Branglebracken, east of Moss Lord.
It appears that <<1>> is not dead after all. I should speak to her about the body I found in Branglebracken.
I have tried to tell <<1>> that her real daughter is dead, but she refuses to believe me. I should speak with her one last time before I leave.
I have found the body of <<1>>. I should return to Moss Lord and inform her mother.
<<1>> will never know the truth about her daughter - at least not from me. I should speak with her one last time before I leave.
I need to locate Trapped Miners and let them know I've cleared a way for their escape.
I need to locate Trapped Miners and let them know I've cleared a way for their escape.
<<1>> is dead, and a Changeling has taken her place. I can choose to tell <<2>> the truth about her supposed daughter, or let her go on living in ignorance.
I should talk to <<1>> in Koeglin Village. It's in Stormhaven.
I should inform Arturo's family of his death.nnThough the news may grieve his family, it may help them to know his fate.
Someone in Crosswych may know if Arturo Charascel has any family in town. I should ask around to see if anyone knows more.
A citizen of Crosswych informed me that Arturo Charascel's mother, Darene, recently arrived in Crosswych. She's staying at a boarding house in town.
Krisandra wants me to kill the Daedric invaders in Edrald Manor. They're gathering around the manor house and in the fields.
Now that I've rid the Edrald estate of its uninvited guests, I should return to Krisandra and let her know of my success.
I need to find the Daedric portal and close it.
Now that the portal to the Daedric planes is closed, I should return to the baroness. She's encamped on the Edrald estate.
I've killed the Fellwatch Knaves. I should return to Corrie to let her know I'm finished.
I need to go to the Fellwatch Camp and kill the Fellwatch Knaves to help Corrie test her quest.
I've destroyed the befouled ectoplasm, releasing the spirit within it. Perhaps Elder Rebia can shed more light on what exactly that was.
I need to pet one of the Boralis Sows to boost its self esteem.
I couldn't close the portal, but I might be able to convince Arlie to do it. I should speak to her at her cave in the Smallhold southern mountains.
Thorkan asked me to destroy necromantic altars on the Ruined Steppe.
Normar wasn't convinced by my work on the Ruined Steppe. He's given me some allegedly necromantic fetishes to show to Thorkan.
