I should deliver this parchment to someone interested in recent events on the Ruined Steppe.
Treethane wants me to find the Tharn Leaders somewhere deep inside the temple and kill them.
I have tracked down and killed the Tharn leaders. I should return to Treethane Bathi at once.
Rumors tell of a manor hidden in the Ruined Steppe. With any luck, I'll find reasons behind the cult's furtive activities within it.
I've found he ruined manor in the mountainside. There's a woman inside it, bound by a magical barrier. I should speak to her and find out what's going on.
I've dealt with some of the bandits around Fell's Run. Hopefully this will send a message that this behavior will not be tolerated.
I've bested some of the bandits around Fell's Run. Hopefully this will send a message that this behavior will not be tolerated.
I should speak to Teresa and learn what she has to tell me.
I should speak to Teresa and learn how to free her.
I've destroyed the last of the soul gem anchors. Teresa should have escaped by now. She's asked me to meet her at Fell's Run.
I need to collect pure soul gems from the Clan of Shadows cultists in the area. Once I have enough gems, I can purify the three soul gem anchors holding Teresa in place. Then she'll be free!

I need to find valuables taken from the people of Fell's Run. I'll find the Fellwatch camp and retrieve whatever I can find. The thieves might be carrying their ill-gotten gains, or the valuables might be stashed around their camp.
<<1>> told me his brother took the book east into a small courtyard to read.
I spoke the correct incantation to release the apprentice from the book's enchantment. I should talk to him.
I found the apprentice! Unfortunately, I used the wrong incantation to end the ward, and the man was transformed into a chicken. I should pick up the spellbook.
On investigation of a mysterious coffin, an Ayleid Ghost has appeared - I should talk to it.

The ghost in the catacombs warned me of the Attelus Tharn's plans and directed me to find the Library of Elden Grove.  Once I find the library, the ghost said I would find something that would help me defeat the resurrected Tharn.
Attelus Tharn has been defeated and the Elden Seed is safe once again.  I should return to Treethane Bathi.

After proving my worth, the ghost of the library warned me of Attelus Tharn's powers. He gave me a charm that will help protect me from Attelus' darkest magicksnnOnce Attelus Tharn has been defeated, I'm to return to Treethane Bathi.
I fed an offering to a mammoth. I should return to <<1>> and let him know.
I should look for the Boralis mammoths over the ridge behind Nevin's house. Then I can feed one the cake that he's made. Aodred also mentioned they're north of his home.
I've collected the holy water and garlic Deniel needs to protect his home.

Deniel Robic wants me to collect holy water and garlic to ward off the undead. A path behind his house leads to a Priest of Arkay who can bless the water. Garlic grows along the coast to the east, where Nords land their longboats.
I should let Deniel know that Aodred is taking care of the cat.
I need to lure a black cat away from Deniel Robic's farm. He's very insistent about this.
I've lured Nocturna back to her proper home. I should speak to Aodred Nevin about his cat.

I've placed the four offerings at the shrines of the Watchers and prayed at the central keystone. The spirits seem pleased with the offerings. I should let <<1>> know his family is blessed for another year.
<<1>> waits near the Watchers. He asked me to place his family's offerings at the nearby shrines.
I've spoken to the <<1>>, a spirit anchored to the giant monuments near Northpoint. I convinced it that the Bretons are not to blame for the mammoth's death. I should inform <<2>> of my success.
I should tell someone about the slaughtered mammoth I found. The farmers around Northpoint may know who I should approach.

I've informed Elder Rebia about the slain mammoth. She told me about a monument called the Watchers dedicated to protecting the mammoths. It's now filled with hostile spirits. She fears these two events are linked, and she's asked me to investigate.
I should take the befouled ectoplasm to a Breton elder near Northpoint.
Elder Rebia asked me to cast the ectoplasm into the fire before her.
I've discovered a collar on the black cat that says Nivern. I should find a way to lure the cat back to the Nivern farm.
Using a few handfuls of chicken feed, I've brought Anne-Marie's chickens back to her. I should see if she caught them all.
I've been asked to gather chickens around Northpoint. I'll lure them back using the chicken feed Anne-Marie gave me. When I throw chicken feed, they'll run where I throw it.
I need to destroy lost souls near the spirit wards hidden throughout the undercity.
I've freed the souls of lost spirits and confirmed that the wards were effective. I'll need find Derick in the Undercity tunnels so I can inform him of the effects.
I've found a collar on the black cat that says her name is Nocturna Nevin. I should use the fish Deniel gave me to lure her back to her home at the Nevin farm.
I've completed my task and feed several of the lost souls. I should return to the Ravenwatch hide out to report my success.
I should look around Altmertown for a suitable gift, then take it to <<1>> in the Royal Palace.
<<1>> has rejected the gift, and wants <<2>> to stop bothering him. I should return to <<1>> at the east end of Altmertown and tell her what happened.
Sanda has asked me to find a way to summon a necromancer. She wants to me to summon a death cultist named Veraya, so I can slay her. She might know a method, or I might be able to find on my own.
I can choose to do as <<1>> asked and use the anti-love potion on <<2>>, or inform <<3>> of <<1>>'s evil intentions.
I have used the potion on <<1>> as <<2>> asked. I should return to her and describe what happened.
I have informed <<1>> of <<2>>'s evil plot. I should speak with him again to find out what will become of her.
I can probably find Renee's sextant on one of the ghostly crewmen near the Sea Wolf's wreckage.
Now that I have Renee's sextant, I should take it to her father in the small fishing town of Farmost Reach. It's on the northern coast of Northpoint.
The trial is over. The spirits have passed on. I should return to the Trial Master and tell him of my triumph.
Now that I've lit the fire, I'll need a way to carry the fire to each of the candles. That should summon the spirits.
I must find a way to start the fire in the middle of the room. I should be able to find the tools I need to start the fire.
The candles have been lit, and the lost souls have appeared. I should speak to them all and find a way to release them from their eternal slumber.
I spoke to a concerned citizen named Melita Bannon in Northpoint. She believes a war with the Nords would be a grave mistake. She asked me to speak to her master, Baron Chirane.

The baron's contact will meet me at the top of Northpoint's lighthouse. They'll exchange the city's garrison key for the traitorous baron's reward. If I want to stop him, I should bring the key to the duchess.
I've informed the duchess about Chirane's plot against Northpoint. The duchess has asked me to tell the baron she will not tolerate his treason. No doubt the baron in his manor.
I need to let the duchess know the Nords are beginning their attack. I have to make sure she is protected.
Hopefully this is the last Saproot Snare needed to snag the Thunderbug!
I've completed all the Trials of the Body. I should speak to the Trial Master and report my success.
My first challenge in the trial is defeating the first guardian. When I'm ready, I'll speak to the Trial Master.
I've defeated the first guardian. I need to speak to the Trial Master to start the next part of the test.
Now that I have the Captain's key, I should search other chests in the Sea Wolf's wreckage for treasure.
Now that I have the Captain's key, I should search other chests in the Sea Wolf's wreckage for treasure.
Now that I have the Captain's key, I should search other chests in the Sea Wolf's wreckage for treasure.
Disturbing the chests has summoned the ghost of the Sea Wolf's boatswain, Normand. I should converse with him.
I've defeated the second guardian. I need to speak to the Trial Master to start the last part of the test.
I've killed Kaoxia, the Dark Seducer who enthralled Nierre.nnI should return to him and make sure he's all right.
I should search Breagha-Fin for the object of Nierre's desire. Then I can find out more about his obsession.

I found Kaoxia. She's a Daedra: a Dark Seducer. She's cast a seductive spell on Nierre. I might listen to what she has to say, or I might decide to release her hold on Nierre by destroying her. I'm not sure yet.
I took a locket from Kaoxia. I can give to Nierre in exchange for a kiss.

The librarian in the Mages Guild told me the rest of their forces were sent to Crestshade, a town west of Shornhelm.nnHe hasn't heard back from them in several days. He wants me to find out what's become of them.
I've been asked to search to the west for any survivors of the exodus from Crestshade.
I should gather pumpkins and corn in the crocodile-infested flooded fields to the southwest.
I've collected the items <<1>> needed. I'll take them to <<2>> and see if they've got a plan.
A fight has broken out! I should use the thunderbug horn to break up any fights that look potentially fatal.
The fight has broken up. Keeper Ra'Faril's floor is free of any unsightly corpses. I should return to him and see if he's willing to pay me for my help.
I was unable to prevent any of the bar fighters from dying. If I want to keep helping inside the Cat Box, I should probably talk to Keeper Ra'Faril about this.
Keeper Ra'Faril seem certain that a fight will break out any minute now. I should squat in the Cat Box for a while until problems start.
The fight is on! I can use my whistle to cheer on <<1>> or distract <<2>>. Of course, other spectators can do the same.
The fight's over <<1>> has won. I should talk to <<2>> and collect my winnings.
The senche fights should be starting soon. I'll have to wait until the next one begins.
I left the bottom of Gamblers' Cave before the fight ended. I should return to <<1>> to see if I can still bet on <<2>>.
The fight is on! I can use my whistle to cheer on <<1>>... or distract <<2>>. Of course, other spectators can do the same.
The fight's over, and <<1>> has won. I should talk to <<2>> and collect my winnings.
The pit fights start every fifteen minutes. I'll have to wait until the next one begins.
I left the bottom of Gamblers' Cave before the fight ended. I should return to <<1>> to see if I can still bet on <<2>>.
I healed <<1>>.  I should make sure she's all right.
I need to find a way to heal the injured orc. Perhaps if I find the missing scout I can obtain a healing poultice.
I have agreed to slay <<1>> and secure any strategic maps he may have created. He hides inside the command tent at the northern end of the Imperial palisade.
<<1>> has marched troops to the river's edge to the east. I should present her Cruor's Map.
There are witchlights by the water near Noleon's home. When I kill the witchlights, I'll be able to gather glow dust.
I've gathered enough glow dust for Noleon. I should return to him at his house beside the river.
I gave the mercenary's note to a sergeant on the battlefield. He'll want to discuss it with me.
I should deliver the mercenary's note to a sergeant on the battlefield.
I need to burn <<1>>s in and around the Imperial Palisade. If I don't hurry, the <<2>> will not be able to escape in the confusion.
I failed to burn the <<1>>s fast enough for the <<2>> to escape. I should talk to him and try the ruse again.
I'm still alive! nnI've located the glyph. Derick used its power to teleport me back to camp just before I was devoured by floodfiends. nnI should return it to him.
The glyph was last seen on the western end of the beach. I'll need to travel there to see if I can find it.
I should tell the squire that I'm ready to talk to his commander.
The brazier that will signal the ships is enchanted to burn only one thing: bloodfiend hearts. I'll need to collect the hearts of  bloodfiends or monstrosities in the <<1>>.
I've entered the ruins on the far side of the <<1>>. <<2>> is waiting for me at the Ravenwatch camp further ahead.

I need to find the magical brazier where I can burn bloodfiend hearts. It should be on the western side of the <<1>> across a bridge. Lighting the brazier will attract the attention of nearby bloodthralls. I must be prepared to defend the signal.
Return to QA QI Grant and inform him of quest completion.
Use the QA Trinket and make sure it is removed from the player quest inventory.
I should speak to an Aldmeri scout named <<1>>. He's west of the Imperial palisade at a small encampment. I should follow the beach south to get there.

Baron Chirane took me into his confidence. He has doubts about Northpoint's ability to win a war against the Nords. He would rather be on "the winning side." I can offer my help with his plan, or I can inform the duchess of a traitor in her midst.
I've informed the Duchess of the Baron's treasonous words. She has asked me to return to the Baron with a warning. I should return to his manor in Northpoint.
I've informed the baron that the duchess is aware of his schemes. I should speak to him and find out what he plans to do next.
I must speak with <<1>>. He is observing the Imperial Landing beaches from a boat in the harbor west of Southpoint.
I should search the fallen soldiers near Southpoint for salvageable weapons and armor.
I've collected salvaged equipment, which I can take to <<1>> in Southpoint.
Noleon Velain asked me to place the Offering on the altar at Azura's Shrine.
Placing the Offering completed the ritual of summoning Azura. A Winged Twilight appeared in answer to my summons.
The Winged Twilight will know how to aid Gavaudon.
Use the teleporter next to the quest giver to go to the practice area.
The Altmer soldier <<1>> is observing the activity at the Imperial Palisade northwest of Southpoint.nnWith the Imperials' supplies cut off at the landing beach, <<2>> suggested he could use my help.
I must deliver the map to Queen Ayarynne. She is in Elden Root to the north, in the center of Valenwood. I can find her in the Thalmor.
I've informed the duchess of the baron's schemes. I should return with the duchess' warning.

With the Whalebone Talisman protecting me, I should find Ithguleoir and slay him. He's probably in the waters north of the fishing village.nnWhen I'm ready to attack him, I can use the talisman to protect myself.
I've killed Ithguleoir. I should return to Therese Marron in the village of Farmost Reach.nnI can finally tell her that her son has been avenged.
If I'm going to slay the dreaded sea monster Ithguleoir, I'll have to talk to the families of those he's killed. Leon Pelaire, Jean Praul and Therese Marron are in the fishing village.

With the Whalebone Talisman protecting me, I should be able to find Ithguleoir and slay him. He's in the waters north of the fishing village. When I'm ready to attack him, I can use the talisman to protect myself.
With the Whalebone Talisman protecting me, I can find Ithguleoir and slay him. He's in the waters north of the fishing village. When I'm ready to attack him, I can use the talisman to protect myself.
I've killed Ithguleoir. I should return to Jean Praul in the village of Farmost Reach. I can finally tell him his wife has been avenged.
I've killed Ithguleoir. I should return to Leon Pelaire in the village of Farmost Reach. I can tell him his love has been avenged.
<<1>> is on the rocks south of the Imperial palisade. I should present the severed head to him for a reward.
I should inform the squire that I'm ready to speak to his commander.
I need to accompany the squire to his commander.
The squire ran off to his commander. I need speak to the commander to find out more about the invasion.
First, I need to kill some crocodiles and gather their scent glands.
I have the heart of <<1>>. I should take it to <<2>>.
<<1>> wants me to travel to the south, off the road to meet up with her.
I should give Skull-Cracker's head to the Orcs at the entrance to Shinji's Scarp.
I should offer the fallen ogre's head to <<1>>. He's at a ruined tower in Shinji's Scarp.
I should collect the teeth of dead ogres in Shinji's Scarp.
I've collected more than enough ogre teeth for Captain Dugakh to make a necklace. I should go and speak with him.
I have gathered the items that An-Zaw requested. I should take them to him and see if has additional tasks.
Murk-Watcher has given me a charm. If I place it near the large nest in the rocks, it will draw out <<1>>. Then I'll kill it and take its heart.
Go back to the Interrupt Quest Giver to give him the glasses.
Get the glasses from a treasure chest in the mountain cliff area past the forest.
I found <<1>> at Dro'Dara Plantation. I should speak to her again.

<<1>> wants me to collect Imperial weapons with Blacksap hilts. That should prove the conspiracy between them. He also wants me to destroy lurchers in the village. That should help drive out the influence of black magic in the area.

I've retrieved several sets of Imperial weapons from the Bosmer in Blacksap Village. I've also destroyed several lurchers for <<1>>. I should return to <<2>> with my proof. Vexa is hiding north of Blacksap Village.
I agreed to slay the Swamp Spirit before it attacked again.

The cavern's been collapsed and the Ironhand Ogres are no longer a threat. Perhaps now I can find out more about these plans General Godrum has made cryptic references to. I should report back to the Command Center in Shinji's Scarp.
Destroy the weak support column holding up the entrance to the cave at the top of Shinji's Scarp.
After I kill the ancient crocodile, I'll harvest its heart.
When I burned spriggan limbs in the brazier, the spirit of a spriggan appeared. If I speak to it, it may reveal the reason the spriggans have risen up against Glenumbra.

The spriggan spirit refused to reveal anything until I killed a Bloodthorn initiate and brought back its heart. I know initiates roam the Dresan Ruins.nnIt seems the spriggan spirit hates the Bloodthorn adepts more than it hates me.
I've collected the heart of a Bloodthorn initiate. If I return it to the spriggan spirit atop the Dresan ruins, it should reveal the reason it rose up against Glenumbra.
I need to speak to An-Zaw again. I'll let him know when he should use the potion.
The Widow Granger asked if I could gather wildflowers for her, as her dead husband did.
The Widow Granger asked me to retrieve her husband's wedding ring. It's on his body somewhere in the waters north of their cottage. She mentioned it may be near the rock formations.
Widow Granger was a nereid who undoutably led Matthias to his death. I should search the cottage to see if there's anything left of the creature.
<<1>> wants to know what's in the heavily guarded house within Belkali.nnBelkali village lies hidden in the woods east of Southpoint.
I found a worked metal statue of the Daedric Prince Molag Bal hidden within Blacksap village and was attacked by some of the Blacksap Spinners. <<1^F>> will want to hear of this.
I've given blood to Marcel. It seems to have brought him out of his delirium. I should speak to him about his condition.
To obtain enough blood, I can use empty vials on the corpses of bloodthrall servants, darkspire bloodfiends, and darkspire monstrosities in the <<1>>. Then I can slake Marcel's thirst for blood.
I've collected enough blood to satiate Marcel. I should return to where he and Crelie are hidden, so I can give it to him.
I have released the trapped souls of the soldiers inside the Ayleid ruin. I should meet <<1>> near the entrance to Lorkrata Nagasel within the ruins.
I should search the Ayleid ruins southeast of Marcel for <<1>>. He believes they imprison the souls of soldiers who have been turned into fiends. I must shatter them to release the souls within them.
<<1>> said that while I destroyed the gems, he would seek a way into <<2>>, the ruined Ayleid temple. If I can find the entrance, I'll probably find him there.
As Verin's request, I've slain the injured scout I found in the Ayleid ruin. I should let Verin know that the deed is done.
<<1>> is dead, but <<2>> sacrificed himself to destroy the Ayleid Soul Gem within <<3>>. <<4>> will want to know Marcel's fate. She's probably still waiting outside for his return.
I need to search for whatever might have drawn Marcel to the <<1>>.
When I investigated the Ayleid Soul Gem within the ruins, Balcone betrayed me. I must stop him before he causes any more deaths.
Now that I've collected a bouquet of flowers, I should give them to the Widow Granger. Her cottage is west of the fishing village, on the coast.
I must journey to Montclair's mansion on the northern part of Shornhelm. Once inside, I'll have to bide my time until Karnosis tires out, and then strike the killing blow.
It seems the person responsible for Matthais' death was the widow herself. I should kill her, before she kills me.
Warden Yvaine wants me to kill everything I find in the water north of their camp. I'll see what I can do.
I've killed several slaughterfish and nereids. I should return to Warden Yvaine and let her know.
Weerhat says his research pages are scattered in the waters north of Farpoint Landing. I should search around the rocks and ruins for them.
I've collected several pages of Weerhat's research. I should return with them to where he's camped on the beach of Farpoint Landing.
I should take rubbings of any interesting stones or markers I happen across inside the ruins.
Now that I've taken several rubbings of these stones, I should show them to Adele at the base of the ruins.
There may be other survivors in Camlorn. I'll search in and around the estate. If I find any, I'll teleport them to safety using the gem.
I've found survivors in Camlorn and teleported them safely home.
The Khajiit J'Hriss is a skilled locksmith. Perhaps he could open Catae's Lockbox for me.
The lockbox I found on the sunken ship is sealed tight. Perhaps someone in Southpoint could help me open it.
I need to search the <<1>> for Katesborn.
I found the scout and heard his side of the story. He claimed Balcone coerced the scouting party into visiting the Ayleid ruins, then abandoned them to an ambush.
I should deliver the Letter to <<1>>, head of the Thalmor in Elden Root.
I should take the stone I found to the archaeologist on the Farpoint Landing beach, south of the ruins.
I agreed to kill Gulpyougone to stop him from eating more imga.
I need to find the husband of a dying peasant in Aldcroft and tell him his wife's fate.
I have failed to stop the sickness from being spread, but perhaps I can do something.
I must decide whether I should heal <<1>> myself or find the ogre who took her pack.
I need to to heal the injured orc or find his missing pack. His fellow trooper told me the ogres stole the pack.
I've helped the injured scout. I should talk to him and make sure he's all right.
Cedric would like me to lay his brother's remains to rest. How I'm supposed to do that isn't quite clear. I should speak with him again to find out more.
I should find and speak one of the Orcs Gaspard spoke of.
I  need to find the black cat on Deniel Robic's farm.
I've discovered a collar on the black cat that says her name is Nocturna Nevin. I should use the fish Deniel gave me to lure her back to the Nevin farm.
I've returned Nocturna to her proper home. I should speak to Aodred Nevin about his cat.
Now that I've saved <<1>> from the ogres, I can tell <<2>> his bear mount won't get eaten.
Destroying the weak support column would collapse the tunnel. Then the ogres would be cut off from their reinforcements.nnThe entrance to the cave is near the tower on top of Shinji's Scar.
Success! I should report to Captain gro-Ghash.
A weak support column is holding up the tunnel at <<1>>. That seems like the perfect place to strike. I need to find a blocked stairwell near the bottom of the cave.
Balcone agreed to unseal the door into the <<1>>, but he needs a few moments to prepare. I should return to the door and wait for him with <<2>> and <<3>>.
The enchantment that prevented anyone from entering <<1>> has been broken. I should follow Balcone inside.
Ilise Manteau, the Countess of Wind Keep, refuses to send a constable to investigate a murder on her own doorstep. Elin Raiment asked me to speak to Countess Ilise and ask for her assistance.
As she must remain with her father's body, Elin asked me to delivery paymet to Jacques at the cemetery east of Wind Keep.
According to Jacques, his apprentice is on his way to retrieve the body of Elin Raiment's father. He said I should locate him to find out why it is taking so long to do.
The thugs who attacked Jacques are gone. I should speak to Jacques to make sure he's all right. Then I'll ask him to bury Elin's father.
An-Zaw has transformed into a werecrocodile. We should hunt down the mercenary captain before the effects of his potion subside. The captain was last seen near the Blackmaul tents north of the farms.
Setting the ogre totems on fire will bring ogre guards to investigate, one at a time. That should make them easier to kill. When they're gone, I can head into the cave to free <<1>>.
The incense has failed to summon the barrow guardian. Perhaps the Bosmer <<1>>, standing next to the grave, will know something more.
<<1>> has asked me to make an offering on the grave of <<2>>, inside the Bonebarrows east of Razorvine Refuge.
I am headed to Haventown to stop the daedric cultists.
Priestess Fleile asked me to speak with <<1>> in Southpoint. I can reach the town by following the road west.
I should return the pack to <<1>> so she can use the bandages in it to bind her own wounds.
I should return the pack to the injured scout.
I am headed to Razorvine Refuge to the east. Alengwe told me to follow Haven Trace and speak to Priestess Fleile, once I arrive.
A spirit appeared and spoke to me while I was examining Countess Ilise's mirror. I should speak to it.
<<1>> has suggested I collect the heads of <<2>>s, and make an offering of them on <<3>>.
I must lay the Bone Snatcher heads on the grave of the Bonebarrows' guardian spirit - the grave is within the Bonebarrows.
The guardian of the Bonebarrows, <<1>>, has appeared at last! I should talk to him now.
<<1>> has suggested I collect the heads of <<2>>s, and make an offering of them on <<3>>.
I must lay the Bone Snatcher heads on the grave of the Bonebarrow's guardian spirit - the grave is within the Bonebarrow.
The guardian of the Bonebarrow, <<1>>, has appeared at last! I should talk to him now.

<<1>> asked me to question the newcomers about Mathias Raiment's murder. She's given me a charm to discern the truth. Those who are honest will display a golden aura, while the liar's red aura will reveal falsehood.
<<1>> has asked me to deliver the news of Mathias Raiment's murderer to her niece, <<2>>. I can find her just outside of the countess' home.

I should throw the <<1>> at the Blackmaul. This will create an explosion that should summon crocodiles to attack.nnThe lure only works near natural riverbanks, like near the corn field. I should not use it except on Blackmaul in that area.

Fighting alongside <<1>>, I killed the leader of the Blackmauls and many of his mercenaries. After the last mercenary fell, <<1>> fled. He's fully a crocodile now. Dro'dara will want to know his friend's fate. He's at the ransacked house.
I must go to Daggerfall and find the hero Seagrave Titanborn. He's in hiding at an old manor near the docks. He'll tell me what to do next.
Elin Raiment's footman is obsessed. He asked me to speak with Elin at the center of Wind Keep.
I must retrieve a Maruhkite artifact from the Canulus Refuge.
I should give the Maruhkati Codex to <<1>>.
I should find the barn and free the farmers.
<<1>> asked me to meet him in a ransacked storehouse, so we could speak in relative safety.
I found the barn. I should tell them the way is clear.
I've collected the items needed for Breloth's perfect burial. I should deliver them to her husband, Michel.
I should look around Wind Keep for the items <<1>> has requested for his wife's burial.
I should return to <<1>> in the campsite and give him the mushrooms I've found.
I should return to <<1>> in the Lurk campsite. I should make sure <<2>> has returned.
<<1>> wants me to help him find his wife. He believes those falsely accused of having the disease have forced her into the mountains to the east of the Stranded Lurk.
I've found Nadene's husband, Sadave. I should speak to him about the wedding ring.
This report I have should go to <<1>> in the Quarantine Serk, just south of the Stranded Lurk.
Glonagaum is being held in some locked shackles. The key should be on an Wood Orc nearby.
<<1>> wants me to kill Wood Orcs in Haven Trace.
I've been busy killing Wood Orcs. I should meet <<1>> at the eastern end of Haven Trace.
The farmers told me that Dro'dara, the plantation owner, refuses to leave. nnI should speak to him and see if there's anything I can do to get him to evacuate.
I have spoken with Dro'dara, I should locate the other farmers and speak to them as well.
I have spoken with An-Zaw, I should find the others I freed and check with them.
I have recovered <<1>> and slain the murderous <<2>>. I should return to <<3>> by the river to the southeast of the Imperial Palisade.
<<1>> can be found along the road just east of the Ayleid ruin where I fought the <<2>>.  I should speak to him.

I've coated many of the betty shalk with repellant musk. Hopefully this will stop the Ashlanders from poaching them. The offensive smell the musk creates should help.nnGilvon is waiting to hear that his shalk have been coated in musk.
I should fill the Shalk Feeders about Saginate Grange to attract Betty Shalk, and use the Shalk Musk on them. The Bull Shalk may not take kindly to this.
I've found some prayer books that should suit Ravela's purposes. She's in the farmhouse at Saginate Grange, praying for my safe return.
By searching the victims of the Tribunal temple massacre near Saginate Grange, I can find prayer books for a wounded acolyte.
I've found the dead body of Diviner Vadesu. She died of her wounds while waiting for me.

There's a sacred brazier near the entrance to the Tribunal temple in Narsis. I've been asked to cast the Diviner Insignia into its flames, but I'm not sure I should. I might find someone from the temple to counsel Vadesu instead.
I've destroyed the insignia of Diviner Vadesu. I should return to the Diviner and let her know she's free of the Tribunal Temple.

I've informed an acolyte of the temple named Ravela Salmesa of Diviner Vadesu's plans. The diviner sill wants to renounce the Tribunal. I should return to the Diviner and let her know help is on the way.
I have found a wedding ring off of the corpse of a <<1>>. I should examine it for any clues.
I've retrieved the scuttle from poachers about Saginate Grange. I should bring it to someone in charge of the farm.
I should slay the scuttle poachers around the Saginate Grange and retrieve the scuttle they've stolen.
Blackmaul assassins are attacking Jacques. I need to protect him.
Helene asked me to kill spriggans around the Dresan Ruins and harvest their limbs. If I gather enough of their limbs, her sister Ileana can use them to summon a spriggan spirit.
I have collected spriggan limbs, as Wyress Helene requested. She asked me to take the limbs to Wyress Ileana at the Dresan Ruins, northwest of Deleyn's Mill.
I should inform Diviner Nevyn. The statues are once again properly displayed on their pedastals within the temple.
By slaying the Vereansu Ashlanders about the temple, I could find the statues and return them to their rightful place. I could restore them to their pedestals in the temple.
I freed the Temple Master, but she didn't want to leave the temple. She asked me to follow her to the center of the compound.
A Vereansu Gulakhan has Temple Master Nothsalea's shackle key. If I can kill the Gulakhan, I can free the temple master.
A temple ordinator has asked me to find Temple Master Nothsalea. Inside the temple compound, I might find signs of the Temple Master's fate.
I've slain the Vereansu Champion, a twisted and abominable corprus-ridden creature. Ordinator Redramea awaits my news.
I've arrived at the waterfall with Nothsalea. She stands by the temple's secret entrance. nnWithin the temple's sanctum, I can slay the abominable Vereansu Champion.
I should descend into the sanctum of the Tribunal temple. Nothsalea spoke of.a secret passage. The path begins behind a secret waterfall....
I stand in the heart of the Tribunal Temple, where I can slay the Vereansu Champion and stop any further attacks on the temple.
I saw disturbing visions while reading the prophecies of the Vereansu. I read of a "lost house" and the rise of "Lorkhan's vessel."nnPerhaps someone nearby knows something about this legend.
After reading the first line of the legend, I was overwhelmed by strange feelings of foreboding. Perhaps I should seek out other parts of the legend and learn more of their prophetic revelations.
I should speak to <<1>>. <<2>> told me I can find him in the cemetery across the eastern bridge of Wind Keep.
The tincture only seemed to offer a temporary reprieve from the visions and madness plaguing the Matuul village. I should inform Disciple Farathan of this.

Disciple Farathan believes the ravings are a sign from the Tribunal. He told me some villager suffer the same fate, and they need not bear that burden.nnHe says if I anoint them with this blessed tincture, they will be cured of their madness.
Taron Hlaalu wants me to look into House Indoril's sudden and suspicious prosperity. I should find a member of the household, possibly at the Darkshade Mine itself.
I've slain a Vereansu channeling a vile spell. I should check on Farseer Yamsi and see if her body has recovered.
I should search for Farseer Yamsi. Then I can discover if the Vereansu are holding her captive.nnThe Matuul Ashlanders may know her whereabouts.

The Farseer's spirit told me I must break the spell holding her body in an endless sleep.nnI should search the Matuul camp by the Oortrel Fort. Someone is casting this evil spell. I know I can stop him.
Brerama Indoril wants me to stop her brother Beltis before he shames the Indoril name. He is somewhere inside the Darkshade Mine.
I've killed Beltis Indoril. That may not have been the solution his sister wanted, but I had no choice. I should return to the miner's camp and let Brerama know what happened.

I experienced the vision Farseer Yamsi glimpsed. High Ordinator was murdered by the Ashkhan of the Matuul.nnSome evil force controlled him, but I managed to drive it out of his dream. Farseer Yamsi should know what I've done.
Farseer Yamsi has cast some kind of dreamwalking spell on me, so I can find out what happened in her visionary dream. In the Oortrel Fort, my vision of High Ordinator Breysun can reveal more answers.
I discovered Breysun's murdered body in the Oortrel Fort. I should slay the villain responsible for this murder. I can examine the body for clues.

I've slain many ash servants, hopefully disrupting whatever nefarious plan they had. Perhaps they wanted to control the dreams and actions of dreamers near the Tribunal Outpost. I should inform Ulimu-Samsa, the Ashlander mentioned in the note.
I should slay the ash servants near Oortrel Fort. They're channeling a spell that allows them to control the dreams of people within their influence.
I need to collect reports from the major stations of the Quarantine Serk: the tower, the southern gate, the northern gate, and the inspection station.
I have collected all of the reports around the Quarantine Serk. I need to return to Dirdren Marvo in the central tent and hand them in.
<<1>> has asked me to deliver her valuables to her husband and daughter. They're waiting for news nearby, north of the Quaratine Serk in the Stranded Lurk.
I need to return to <<1>> in the Quarantine Serk to inform him of the Vereansu's activities.

<<1>> has sent me to find any clues that may help explain what has become of the missing scout and diseased. I should search the area between the Quarantine Serk and the Stranded Lurk for any sign of him.
Narsis is south of the Quarantine Serk. Soldiers there should know of the recent activities of the Vereansu Ashlanders and House Dunmer agents spotted at Scabrous Pass.
I've freed the captured elders in the Matuul camp near the Oortrel Fort. Now I can tell Guard Mansilnat that the elders are safe.
I should search the Matuul camp by Oortrel Fort, so I can find the captured elders and free them.
Gravik asked me to recover any chains of loyalty I find on fallen Clan Murtag conscripts on the battlefield near Shinji's Scarp.
Now that I've collected enough chains of loyalty, I should return them to Gravik gro-Murtag at the healing tent in the camp next to Shinji's Scarp.
I've slain the Gulakhan in the Ashkhan's yurt. I should tell Guard Mansilnat his people have nothing more to fear from the Vereansu.
Once I enter the Ashkhan's yurt by the Oortrel Fort, I'll have to be ready for a fight inside it. I'll be confronting the Vereansu's leader, the Gulakhan.
I've entered the Ashkhan's yurt. He's negotiating with the Gulakhan of the Vereansu, but it's a waste of time. When I kill the Gulakhan, I'll end this standoff.
The servant of a Hlaalu councilor has asked me to assist his mistress. In the Council Chambers of northern Narsis, Nerena has deigned to profer an audience with me. I should talk to her.

Nerena, a newly appointed Nord on the Hlaalu Council, asked me to recover an ebony shipment she commisioned. The ebony mines are northeast of Narsis.nnThe Council expects her to defend the city with no resources - she must act covertly.
To reduce suspicion, I should bring the ebony shipments directly to the blacksmith in Narsis.
I've recovered and delivered ebony to the blacksmith in Narsis. I should tell Nerena that she'll have her weapons.
I've informed many of the unarmed guards in Narsis that their new weaponry is ready. I should let Nerena know Narsis is well-protected again.
I should inform the unarmed guards stationed in Narsis that new weapons are waiting for them.
I found the missing scout, <<1>>, and need to recover the message he was carrying. I should head further west into their camp to see if I can find it.
I've found Falena's body, slain by Vereansu looters. I recovered the gold ring I gave to Falena. I should tell Savard the bad news.
I have a gold ring to present to Falena in Narsis. Someone must tell her Savard wants to end their engagement.

The blacksmith easily recognized the weapons. He crafted them. There's no question someone within Narsis has been supplying the Vereansu with weapons from House Hlaalu's caches.nnDirani should hear the bad news.
I should search supply crates within the Vereansu camp north of Narsis, so I can collect weapons from the Vereansu.
Now I've collected some weapons from the Vereansu north of Narsis. I should bring them to the blacksmith in town and see if he can identify them.
Ogres are preventing Orcs from holding off the enemy's advance. If I can manage to hit a few ogres with a catapult, I should be able to scatter them.
I took down some ogres and defended the catapult. Hopefully, that will scatter their forces. Then the Orcs can regroup. I should report back to Captain gro-Aruk.
I've spared Hlerva, but taken his finger. I'll give it to Dirani as proof of my deed.
Hlerva is responsible for this treason. He must lose his right hand for his treasonous acts. The merchant said he fled to a dock near the Tribunal Temple south of Narsis.
I've killed Hlerva and taken his hand. I should give it to Dirani as proof of my deed.
Corrupted eggs are hidden throughout the Darkshade Caverns. I should smash any I find.
I've destroyed several of the kwama eggs I found throughout the mine. I should tell Breama Indoril about this.
The Lion Guard and I have held the banner against Angof's first waves of attack. Now we must survive his final wave.
I must defend the Lion Guard Banner beside the Lieutenant and other soldiers of the Lion Guard.

Panoit asked me to look for his Lieutenants around Cath Bedraud's exterior. He asked me to help the soldiers defend an existing banner or help the Lieutenant plant a new one.nnHe hopes to rally the Lion Guard against Angof's endless waves of undead.
I've successfully caused a rockslide that should be large enough to block the Scabrous Pass. I need to return to <<1>>, north of the Vereansu camp, and let him know of my success.
I need to go to the Quarantine Serk and inform <<1>> of what has happened at the Scabrous Pass.
I need to return to <<1>> and let him know I've freed the other diseased prisoners. He is waiting for me near the northern end of the Vereansu camp in the Scabrous Pass.
I'v killed an Ashlander assassin, named <<1>> and recovered his chitin ring. <<2>> at the Quarantine Serk has a reward for me.
Mubdinab Hansar is a wanted man. If I can kill him and collect his ring, I can collect a bounty. He's probably likely hiding somewhere in the Scabrous Pass.
<<1>> wants me to kill Wood Orcs invading the Overrun Trading Post. The post is just outside Elden Root.
I've halted the Wood Orc invasion. I should report back to <<1>>.
I need to free <<1>> by untying his restraints. He is in the Vereansu camp in the Scabrous Pass.
I should retrieve trade goods for the merchant refugees I've met. Their belongings are stashed inside the Trading Post.
I've retrieved a large supply of trade goods. I should return to <<1>>.
I should find some of the Wood Orc's incendiary bundles. Then I should take them to the Bosmer scouts guarding the trading post. They could probably tell me more about them.
I've recovered several of the Wood Orc bundles. I should bring them to one of the Bosmer scouts near the Overrun Trading Post for closer examination.
I need to speak to <<1>> at the Vereansu camp in the Scabrous Pass.
I need to free the other diseased prisoners at the Vereansu camp in the Scabrous Pass.
I've informed Nethryn's wife of the plot against her. I should let Nethryn know his affair is at an end.
I should search for Ranae and rescue her from those who hold her hostage.nnTo find her, I should question the interested parties and search for clues of her whereabouts.

Ranae wishes for me to poison Nethryn's wife so they can be together.nnI can obtain poison from the cabinet in their house if I wish to do this, but I also should consider either informing Nethryn or his wife about the plot against her.
I've informed Nethryn of Ranae's pregnancy, and her plot against his wife. I should speak to him and see what he is going to do about it.
I've rescued Ranae from her kidnappers. I should speak to her and find out who is responsible for this.
I've poisoned Mehna's tea at the behest of Ranae. I should tell Nethryn what his mistress has wrought.

Mira's shade asked me to kill the "Imperials" occupying Aphren's Keep. She must be referring to the Blackmaul mercenaries camped in the ruins of the keep. If I do as she bids, perhaps that will help her spirit rest.
I've slain many Blackmaul mercenaries camped in Aphren's Ruins. If I bring this news to Princess Mira's shade, it might appease her bloodlust and finally return her to rest.

The shade of a fallen Redguard warrior asked me to pray at the cairns which honor those who died in battle here. The shades of fallen warriors will aid me against the invaders. This time, they'll fight Blackmaul mercenaries.
I've prayed at the cairns of fallen Redguard warriors throughout the ruins, unleashing them on Blackmaul mercenaries. Perhaps the shade who sent me will take some comfort from this.
If I can locate any survivors from Brukbrook, they may be able to tell me more about what happened to the town.
Now that I've found Captain gro-Ghash, I should speak to him again.
I should report to Captain gro-Ghash at the house next to the battlefield.

I now hold Crown Prince Amal's sword. Amal asked me to take his sword to each of the three remaining towers in the Aphren Hold. He believes that by going to each tower, he can fight by his sister in death as he should have in life.

I have taken Crown Prince Amal's sword to each of the three remaining towers in the Aphren's Hold. The shade of Crown Prince Amal asked me to meet him when I was done. He waits for me by Aphren's Tomb on the west side of the ruins.
I've revealed Mathias Raiment's murderer, and was attacked. I should defend myself.

To put his soul to rest, I must take his Prince Amal's sword to each of the towers in Aphren's Hold. The sword is atop his tower, on the southeastern end of the keep.nnAmal claims it contains his spirit. I should take up his sword.
Now that I've stopped the ogre advance, I should report to General Godrun at the base of the tower.
I've been given a set of crystals to place on the peaks inside Moontooth Canyon. Spreading them about on the higher ledges of the area will help relight the Obelus.
I've placed the crystals in their proper locations. When I finished, I heard a large explosion near the camp. Maybe I should head back and find out what happened.
Mhaltu thinks there's more survivors in the area, but she's busy tending to the injured. I've been asked to round up any survivors and return them to the camp.
I've returned all the scouts I could find back to the camp. Mhaltu should be willing to tell me what her next course of action is.
If I sneak down into the canyon, I can collect Vials of Fire from the fallen. I'll need to be cautious. Stirring up the ogrim may lead to a quick death.
I've dropped a fair number of rocks down on the heads of the Ogrim. Danmus will want to talk about this again.
I need to get to the higher ground overlooking the Vereansu camp and find a boulder large enough to push and cause a rockslide to block the Scabrous Pass.
I've collected a sizeable amount of scamp skin. I should return to Drunar. He should still be in the same small clearing in the canyon.
Drunar wants me to collect scamp skins in Moontooth Canyon. He says he'll reward me.
I need to take this heart to someone who may be interested in Narsis.
The <<1>> can't be controlled, but someone well-versed in Dwemer history may find the journal valuable.
I've found the pack <<1>> left behind, and and I should return it to him at the entrance to the Irrithial Dwemer Ruins.
Balyn's pack is somewhere inside the Irrithial Dwemer Ruins.
I found Ryna surrounded by several cultist bodies. Maybe I should ask her what's going on.
<<1>> asked me to meet her at the Sia Ebony Mines. They're in the eastern part of Moontooth Canyon.

The shade of King Aphren, languishes in the catacombs below Aphren's Hold. The king is disturbed by his daughter Mira's hatred and will not rest. I should reconcile them.nnFirst, I must speak to the shade of King Aphren.

King Aphren said his sword was buried with him in his tomb on the lowest level of the catacombs. If I retrieve it and present it to the shade of Princess Mira, Aphren hopes his daughter will finally understand how proud he is of her.
I have retrieved King Aphren's sword from his grave at the bottom of the catacombs. If I present it to the shade of Princess Mira, perhaps she will finally forgive her father.
I need to search the Irrthial Dwemer Ruins for the remaining pages of the plans I found on the Vereansu Ashlander.
I need to assemble the pieces of the plans together to discover what they are for.
I need to read the plans.

Some of the remaining parts of the <<1>> lie scattered about Irrithial Dwemer Ruins. I might be able to salvage some more from destroyed Dwemer devices, or maybe I should take them from Dwemer spiders and Dwemer spheres.
Now that I have all the pieces, I need to attach them to the main body.
I should take the core to someone in Narsis who may be interested.
I need to kill the Steam Centurion.
I should examine the body to see if there is anything to salvage.
My shot killed several ogres, but a group of them are headed to destroy the catapult. I need to defend it.
<<1>> directed me to an eastern cave that's the source of the monsters in Moontooth Canyon. His cousin, <<2>>, has a plan to solve the problem.

<<1>> is in the local tavern on the southwest side of Aldsotha. I should ask her about the rumors she's been spreading. <<2>> also mentioned that I should think about my approach. I need to decide I've I'll be direct or nonchalant.

I've been asked to speak with the monastery's healer, Frizwyr. I should help him rouse the abbot of the Spirit Wardens from his endless sleep. Only their leader, Abbot Durak, knows how to retrieve the Dream Shard.

Frizwyr told me Durak is locked in a dream from which he cannot awaken. None of the Spirit Wardens can dream, so they cannot rescue him, but I can. Frizwyr gave me a Dreamstride Potion. Drinking it will place me in Durak's nightmare.

After I imbibed a Sleeping Potion, I found myself in Pariah Abbey again, but this version was strangely different. Within the dream, I heard a voice asking me for help. It must be somewhere in the temple.
I've entered Durak's dream. If I can find him, I can ask what I must do to set him free.
I've recovered the key to Durak's prison. I should return to Durak inside Pariah Abbey.
When Durak awakened from his dream, I awoke as well. Durak asked me to speak to him when we were both awake. He wants to tell me more about what happened.
When I went upstairs, there were several spirits surrounding the chest. I should find out why they are there.
The spirit of Cyri Savol asked me to bury the necklace made of their bones in the mass grave where Marnon Sebat disposed of them.
The nightmare that imprisoned Durak has ended. When I speak to Durak again, I'll awaken him from his dream.
The Daedric portal is open. I can close the portal by removing its blackened soul gems.
I've decided not to turn over the land deeds to Broker Tonasa. Instead, I'll take them to the relatives of the husks I killed on Huskhill. The Mabrigash may know where to find the widows.
Melesi of the Mages Camp has asked that I look for their scrolls that were lost as the group fled from the undead. I should find them in the swamps to the east of the camp.

I should search about Huskhill for Food Supplies the Mabrigash may have brought for the husks, and keep an eye out for the Mabrigash Charms Madris spoke of.
I've collected food supplies and a charm for Madris. By using the charm on a Bereft Husk, it should follow me. Then I can lead it to Madris' hovel to give him a companion, albeit not a talkative one.
Marnon Sebat appeared as I buried the necklace of his victim's bones! I should destroy his spectre once and for all!
I have collected all of the ingredients <<1>> asked me to find. She's waiting for them in her home in the Illsam Farmlands.
<<1>> is in the Illsam Farmlands, east of Urvali's house. I should see if she can create a remedy for Altis.

I should use one of the cleansing wards on the poison's source within the water. <<1>> told me the wards would give me a sign when I'm close to the right area.

<<1>> said she just needed a moment to create the remedy. She'll want to talk to me when it's finished.

Melesi claims that the scrolls are encrypted with an illusion spell, only visible to the enchanter. She asks that I speak to Floran who has a favor to ask of me.

I've found the scroll case Melesi mentioned, but it was empty. After opening the case, an undead creature ambushed me and spoke of "betrayal." If I can incapacitate the creature, perhaps it will speak to me.
I used the blade on a mage, and it cast a mysterious enchantment on them. The lost spirit has arrived. It seems pleased that its spell was a success.
I should talk to the maiden I set free.
Now that I've escorted the maiden off Vanne's farm, I should talk to <<1>>.
I defeated Shivina and should speak with her.

<<1>> has sent me in search of a book called the <<2>>.nnHe believes it is somewhere inside a ruined monastary in Cyrodiil, a place called the Canulus Refuge. I can use Seagrave's portal stone to travel there instantly.

The Prophet holds the Balac, but something is not right. I should speak with him again to find out what is wrong.

A door within the Archives is blocked off by a magical ward. If the Balac is behind that door, then I must find a way to bring the barrier down.

I have solved the Maruhkite's riddle, and the barrier is down. <<1>> must be located somewhere beyond it.

I used the black soul gem on Ervyna, but her spirit was too great for the vessel. Her body was killed, however, but she has gravely injured Andalas. I should speak to him and see if his quest for vengeance is complete.

I found a body on the altar with the empty scroll case. Then an angry spirit ambushed me. After its defeat, it became quiescent, and now it wants to speak to me. Perhaps it can explain the three mages' deception.
I should search around Huskhill for old campsites where Andalas may have left his missing items.

The spirit claims that the mages at the camp used him as a sacrifice to raise the dead in the area as an experiment. He's given me a dagger to use on one of them and claims it'll avenge his death.nnI'll need to think upon what actions I should take.

I'm bringing a remedy to <<1>>. He's east of the Illsam Farmlands, and his camp is near the coast of the Loqueach River.

The last of the cleansing wards can purify the water in the Illsam Farmlands Delta. <<1>> told me it should give me sign when I'm close to the right area.

I am to spread <<1>>s on the top of Altmer buildings and pillars in Altmertown. I can reach the top of the buildings by using the Vaulting Vines.nnBalen warned that Altmer Wardens will attack me if they see me with the flowers.

I need to make sure the leader of the mines is safe. If he falls, the miles fall.

I should light the lighthouse lamp with the torch.
Parveneh finds me trustworthy. She asked me to deliver her offering while wearing special robes, and she said that I would be rewarded.

Sibellec promised that if I saved her and her sisters, they would help me against Angof, who is attacking their swamp.nnSibellec said her sisters are "lost in the swamp". She feels Eilwen to the north, and Aderyn to the northwest.

I found Eilwen in the swamp. Though weak from her separation, Eilwen retains enough of her magic to recreate the spell that joined her sisters.nnBefore this spell can be finished, I must find Aderyn. Eilwen said she is to the southwest.

I found Aderyn in the swamp. Though weak from her separation, Aderyn retains enough of her magic to recreate the spell that joined her sisters.nnBefore this spell can be finished, I must find Eilwen. Aderyn said she is to the northeast.
Sadir has the key to Nevena's prison cage. nnTo free her, I need to find Sadir, kill him, and recover the key.

I fed one of the miners in the area. That should do. I should return to the supplier in the cave and let him know.
The meat from the Scuttle Beetles in the area will be an acceptable source of nutrition.

I should bring Shaleen's tail to Ah-Nakul and tell him his brother is dead. Hopefully, he will believe my lie.

It turns out Shaleen is trying to escape from Ah-Nakul, who was sent by the Dark Brotherhood to assassinate him.nnShaleen has given me the few belongings he owns. If I drop them close to the Marsh Crocodiles, that will suggest he's been eaten.

Sibellic needs power to rejoin her with her sisters. She asked me to use her Soul Gem on Blood Thorn adepts to collect their souls. She also asked me to find her sisters. Aderyn is northwest of her home, and Eilwen is to the north.

To gather power to rejoin her with her sisters, Aderyn asked me to use her lure to draw crocodiles from the swamp. When I kill them, the lure will collect their essence.
Aderyn's lure has collected the essence of many crocodiles. If I return the lure to her in the western swamp, she can absorb its power. Then she can recast the spell that joined her with her sisters.
<<1>> told me the Midnight Phantom ordered the theft of a goblin totem. I should release him from his cage.
I should report to Captain Ernard.
I must retrieve the Stonechewers' tribal totem, and take it back to Commander Kurt.
To gather power to rejoin her with her sisters, Eilwen asked me to drop a Capture Gem on the ground and lure a will-o-the-wisp into it. The gem will trap the wisp and gather its power.
If I return the Capture Gem to Eilwen in the northern swamp, she can use its power to recast the spell of fusion that joined her with her sisters.
If there are no will-o-the-wisps in the area, I should pick up the Capture Gem and take it elsewhere.
Eilwen's Capture Gem has collected enough will-o-the-wisps to restore her power. I should pick the gem up and return it to her.
I need to make sure the leader of the mines is safe. If he falls, the mines fall.
I've managed to help fend off the attack on the Sylvan Mines. I should report to the mine's leader. I should make sure he's okay.

I've found Sibellec's cauldron in the center of Glenumbra Bog. She asked me to touch the cauldron and summon her sisters. Then they'll begin the spell to fuse themselves once more.nnI must protect the cauldron while they complete the spell.
I have defended Sibellec, Aderyn, and Eilwen as they completed the spell to fuse them together. They are now one entity. I should speak to Sibellec and find out if more needs to be done.
I gave the fish crate to Master Vinden, who promply died of an unknown cause. If I return to Five-Tongue, he should have an explanation.
I should find Five-Tongue Helei and give him his letter.
Five-Tongue Helei gave me a crate of fish he needs delivered to Master Vinden. He seemed pretty agitated about it arriving on time. Apparently, he's a little late.
I am going to remove the <<1>>s. Quelline warned me to watch out for bugs.
I have removed <<1>>s from Altmertown and should return to Quellaine.
I've defeated the undead leader and his minions. The miners are going back to work. I should speak with their leader and learn more about what happened.
I've been asked to venture into the mines and defeat the undead inside them. Once I do that, the miners can return to the tunnels.
Speaking through her familiar, Sibellec asked me to find her cauldron in the center of Glenumbra Bog. She said it would be in a circle of torches west of her home.
I have killed <<1>>. His ghost confronted me. He wants to know what really happened here.
Dulnia said I would find her husband in the lighthous to the east. If I don't stop him, he'll kill more innocent travellers.
I should deliver the <<1>> to the Flint Tooth tribe's cave. The entrance is north east of Cumberland's Watch in the mountains.
I should deliver the <<1>> to the Stone Chewer tribe's cave. The entrance just to north of Cumberland's Watch.
The tortured spirit is one of the maidens killed by Mother Murk. She asked me to destroy any bog hags I find in Glenumbra Bog. Each hag destroyed will free the spirit of a sacrificed maiden.

I have destroyed many bog hags throughout Glenumbra Bog. I should find the spirit of the maiden who asked me to destroy them.nnIf her body is among those I destroyed, I may be able to help her spirit move on at last.
Several of the guar are free. I can return them to the camp. Gindralyn can tell me if the nobles got their belongings back.
With enough samples of nix-hound flesh, House Indoril can figure out how the beasts to traverse the tar.
<<1>> lost the fight against <<2>>. If I'm going to bet on the next fight, I should speak to <<3>>.
<<1>> lost the fight against <<2>>. If I'm going to bet on the next fight, I should talk to <<3>>.
To open the Portal to the Heart, I must get the four keys.
Open and Enter Portal to the Heart
I've defeated <<1>>. This will allow Jacques to fulfill his duty. I should speak with Jacques.
I have burned the bodies of the <<1>>s and re-lit the lighthouse lamp with the lasting ember so it will never be dark. I should return to <<2>> at the west side of Trident Watch and let him know.
Nardan Vanthi gave me an elixir made from hound blood. He believes drinking the potion will allow me to enter the tar pits and free the guar. Hopefully, I can then bring them back to the camp safely.
The House Indori camp waits for me to deliver samples of nix-hound flesh. One of the researchers may have an idea on how to use these remains.
<<1>> can be found wandering the poverty-ridden Jolly Squalor, south of the main tree of Elden Root.

I'm sabotaging the smuggling operation in the Olain Fir Kwama mine. Many of Othrina's workers are abandoning her after seeing her letter of pardon.nnI should find the contact waiting for the weapons shipment and confront them.
I should speak to the leader of the smuggling operation in the Olain Fir Kwama Mine. Then I can discover what they're smuggling and to whom.

I've obtained the letter of pardon from Captain Othrina. I could pursue quite a bit of subterfuge with it.nnIf I can convince her workers that she's turned on them, they would mutiny, leaving her without anyone to fulfill the weapons deal.
Incanabulist Ilerian has provided me with a magic amulet with which to blind the Blacksap spies.
I have blinded a number of Blacksap Spies. Incanabulist Ilerian will be interested in my progress.
Incanabulist Ilerian wants me to kill several Blacksap Leafstalkers.
I have slain several Blacksap Leafstalkers and should return to Incanabulist Ilerian.
I've been given a pair of nix-hound boots, crafted with their very skin. Dalynea Finyon asks that I use the boots to enter the tar and attempt to bring the guar back to the safety of the camp.

Captain Othrina, the smuggling ringleader, has told me she received a letter of pardon as payment for a large weapons shipment. If I could get that letter from her, that would seriously disrupt her plans.
I've collected three gifts for Hosni. I'll trade them to him for the Dream Shard.
I've disarmed the chest. Now I need to collect the winding key and take it to <<1>>.
I should return to <<1>> to let him know I've retrieved the music box.nnI can find him in the courtyard near the fountain.

To get the lockbox, I should go down to the southern shore of the Abd-Tura estate and find it amongst the Supernal Dreamers. I could fight through them, or I may be able to find a way to slip by them unnoticed.
I retrieved the lockbox from the Supernal Dreamers. I should return to <<1>> near the back gate entrance so she can unlock it and give me the tiara.

<<1>> and <<2>> were both dead upon my return. It appears they fought each other to the death. nnWith the guards disposed of, I can collect the necklace and return it to <<3>> just outside of the treasury.

I've offered to assist House Indoril in getting a sample of the Musk Screal flower. I should speak to the members of the camp to find out any useful information they may have.

I have a tool I can use to gather samples of the elusive musk screal flower.
<<1>>, the commander of the Camoran city guards, can be found in the Altmertown quarter to the west of Elden Root.
Incanabulist Ilerian would be very interested in seeing the note that I found.

I should speak with <<1>> and <<2>> to acquire the items Hosni is looking for. nnAccording to Hosni, they are both attending the party. If I have problems finding them, Hosni may have an idea of where they are.

I've collected three gifts for Hosni. I'll trade them to him for the Dream Shard.

I've talked to several Uplanders and heard their stories. I should return to Valeor and speak to him. Maybe I should join the Sylvan Guard....
A scout told me his troops are fighting against "evil witches" known as the Mabrigash. I should speak to the leader of the Sylvan Guard to learn more.
I've been asked to speak to several Uplanders in the area to learn more about their story and how the Mabrigash have affected their lives.
I've been asked to speak to several of the Uplanders in the area, so I can learn more of their story and how the Mabrigash have affected their lives.
Falice asked me to use her poultices on other injured Spirit Wardens. They're probably still in Pariah Abbey's fields.
I've used up all the poultices Falice gave me. I should return to her and see if she still needs my help.
I should check on the drunk to make sure he'll be all right.
I've killed the goblin warlord and collected his key. Now I can free <<1>>.
I should deliver the <<1>> to the Stone Chewer tribe's cave. The entrance is just to north of Cumberland's Watch.
The Beckoning Ghost disappeared when I ran too far away from it. I should go back and speak to it.

I've returned to Valeor who has no memory of ever assigning me the task of speaking to Gharvin.nnHe fears that I may have fallen under the curse of the Mabrigash because I do not wear an amulet that would protect me from their magics.
Valeor told me that Gharvin is usually stationed at the Overlook of the Uplands, watching over the Mabrigash's Glen. I can speak to him there.
Gharvin worries that the amulet the Sylvan Guards are wearing might be the cause of all of this. He's asked me to take a note to his wife and then leave the Uplands, if only for my own safety.

To retrieve the winding key, I'll need to find the locked chest on the second floor of Hosni's manor house. Once there, I'll have to play the harps in the correct order to disarm the trap and unlock the chest.
Sister Safia asked me to go to the Cave of Dreams on the rise northeast of here. I should look Brother Hakam.
When I confronted the guards, they attacked me. Some even muttered very strange things . I fear there may be more to the problem than Valeor realizes. I should let him know immediately.
I should look for any guard who stand out as being overly anxious or aggressive. Confronting them might calm their nerves and put a stop to this mess.
I've collected the sapphire from <<1>>.nnI still need to get the tiara from <<2>>. If I need help finding her, I could ask Hosni if he knows where she is.

I've collected two of the gifts. I still need to collect the last one.
I've collect three gifts for Hosni. I'll trade them to him for the Dream Shard.
I've spoken to Nythis. She's confirmed that Gharvin is worried about this, and she begged me for help. If I lie to Valeor, she and her husband might escape.
I should enter Hosni's treasury near <<1>> and find <<2>>. nnOnce I find him, I should say he's being investigated for the murder of Rahar, Guard Barnabe's brother.
<<1>> wants me to retrieve some items from the west barracks in case <<2>> has it searched. Although he's not really under investigation, I should find the items to see if they may be useful to me.
<<1>> gave me his badge to give to <<2>> and tell him that he no longer works for the estate. He said I could find him in the tower, southwest of the manor.
I found the items <<1>> was concerned about. I should return to him at the treasury, north of the courtyard, and tell him he's safe.

To find out more about the murders (and possibly collect the bounty), I must speak to High King Cumberland. His Highness will accept an audience with "qualified parties" in his throne room in the center of Wayrest.
Anahsu can give me amulet that will protect me from the Mabrigash. I should also check to see if Nythis and Gharvin escaped from here instead. Perhaps I can ensure their protection.

Something seems out of place here. Everyone seems to have memory loss, and they claim I've spoken with men who don't actually exist. For now, all I can do is follow along and relax. Getting a bite to eat might help pass the time.
Someone planted something in the food I ate. I lost consciousness for a while. I should speak to someone and find out what happened.

I've killed Nythis, but the damage is done. Except for Valeor, all of the Sylvan Guards have vanished, captured by the Mabrigash. Valeor swears to find them and save them, but does not want my help. It would seem I've done enough here.

Durak asked me to speak with S'Rashi, a Khajiit at the Cloudy Dregs Inn in Wayrest. Alhough S'Rashi may know about the Dream Shard, there's no guarantee he will help. A Spirit Warden named Sharag is already in Wayrest. I should find her.

S'Rashi asked me to collect debts from three men in Wayrest who owe him money. He gave me their names and locations.nnLouis is in the town square. Padier is at the Mages Guild. Islah is at Wayrest's temple.

I have collected coins from the three men who owe S'Rashi money. When I return these payments to him, he's promised to reveal what he knows about the Dream Shard stolen from Pariah Abbey.nnS'Rashi schemes in the back room of the Cloudy Dregs tavern.

The caretaker told me that I passed out for several hours. Oddly enough, I feel as though it just happened.nnNythis visited me while I slept. She felt horrible for what happened, and she left a note by my side. I read it when I awoke.
Nielle asked me to look for Rama at Cumberland's Watch, north of here. Maybe I'll convince him to have a drink with the other guards in Wayrest.
Padier asked me to look for his man, Devis, at Farangel's Landing. It's southeast of Wayrest.
Rerielle asked me to find Arcady or Adiel Charnis in the slums east of Wayrest. If I collect the taxes they owe, she'll reward me.

Nythis has been playing along all this time. She wasn't under the control of the amulet's magic. She's given me a bag of sleeping powder to use in Anahsu's food. I hope she'll pass out long enough for her spell to wane.
S'Rashi told me to look for his bookkeeper at Hammerdeath Arena, a Khajiit named Hilani. She might be able to tell me how to find the Midnight Phantom.

This entire time, I've been under a spell without knowing it. Nythis has revealed herself as a Mabrigash, and she's been using me. I can't allow this to continue. Nythis disappeared, but she's probably heading towards the camp. I must stop her.
<<1>> told me to go to Wayrest's docks on the southeast side of the city. Jonne is there. He's a witness who saw the last murder take place.
Jonne said a cloaked spirit strangled his wife. No one believes him. If this spirit has been seen before, <<1>> may know about it.

All the murders took place late at night, near the waterways of Wayrest. One victim's armor was still damp when found. I may find a clue along Wayrest's waterways.nnThe murders must be by the same person. Each victim was missing a pinky finger.

I have recovered an unnatural goo from near the site of one of the murders in Wayrest. It may offer some clue to the identity of the murder.nnJonne is an alchemist. Perhaps he can identify the goo. He works upstairs in High King Cumberland's masne.

According to legend, if you stand in the pool below Market Square and drink enough, the Strangler will appear and kill you. I'm going to stand in that pool and drink wine until the Wayrest Strangler appears.
<<1>> was very impressed with my success. He asked me to speak with High King Emeric personally. The king wants to congratulate me on my success.
The powder is in Anahsu's food. No one seems to have noticed. Nythis asked me to meet her at the overlook. We should discuss our next plan of action.

I've been under a spell this entire time without knowing it. Nythis has revealed herself as a Mabrigash. She's been using me.nnI agreed to leave the camp. She promised not to put any of the others in danger. That's our compromise.
According to Tirdad, the spirit wardens need help east of the abbey at the Moonlit Maw.
I must venture out to the west of this port to find the Filthy Cliff Racers, and put an end to two of them. I have other tasks ahead of me when that is complete.
I have killed the filthy Cliff Racers and Shalks as requested by Tester Questor and took the stomachs to Receiver Deceiver.
I have destroyed the filthy Cliff Racers, and now I must either harvest Shalk Stomachs or Open some box.
The potion in the box is labeled "Drink me." I guess it couldn't hurt...
I drank the potion and now feel ill. Maybe I shouldn't do everything someone tells me to do.
I should travel to the Bonebarrow, east of Razorvine Refuge, and speak to Golleon -- offer him my assistance.
The Supernal Dreamers are somehow destroying the souls of the captured Spirit Wardens. I need to rescue them, as well as locate the monk who led them into this place.
Now that I've released several Spirit Wardens and found their leader, I can learn more about what the Supernal Dreamers intended to do with their souls.
I need to clear a path for the Spirit Wardens by killing Supernal Dreamers.
I've cleared a path for <<1>>, <<2>>, and <<3>>. I should meet them at the cave entry of the Moonlit Maw.
I should find the cage this key unlocks.

I need to look for the key to open Ograk's cage. He said a Supernal Dreamer would likely have the key.
I have opened the cage, and now I need to speak with Ograk.
I have found the key, and now I need to unlock Ograk's cage.

Durak is trapped in a dream. Within it, betrayers lurk in the abbey. Durak needs a key to unlock his chains. One of the dream outlaws in Pariah Abbey carries it. If I kill enough of them, I'll eventually find the key.
According to the letter, Mashana was in Wind Keep. I should head there to see if she is still in the village.
I should travel to the vault, west of King Faume's grave, and look for the invisible fiend.

I should go to the Quarantine Serk and let <<1>> know about the Scabrous Pass and <<2>>'s plans to repurpose it as another camp for the diseased.

I've questioned various people around Narsis and deduced that Ranae has been kidnapped by several men, and possibly taken to a house on the outskirts of the Saginate Grange. I should go there and find her.
The Imperial official dropped a contract. I should read it.
I must confront Mender Sarvyl. He broke a promise to me to leave Deshaan. I cannot trust him again.
Mender Sarvyl is beyond help. I need to inform Belamaus Daryon of the danger he poses to all of Deshaan.
I've successfully caused a rockslide that should be large enough to strike a crippling blow to the Vereansu's numbers. I need to return to <<1>>, in the Scabrous Pass, and let him know of my success.
Soren Lilymoth wants me to search the body of the Imperial commander for his orders and take them to <<1>> in Razorvine Refuge.

Fura Lilymoth has sent me to speak to her brother, who can sneak me past the Imperial barricade between Woodberth and Razorvine Refuge.
I am inside the Infernal Device. Golleon lies on the ground before me, he appears injured. I should speak with him -- he may know how to destroy the Infernal Device.

As I walked way from Jonne, a cloaked spirit manifested nearby. The apparition murdered a Wayrest noble before soaring off to the north, toward the gate into town. I must stop it before it kills again.

Boars are known to forage for mushrooms in the glen south of the Hoarvor Circus.
<<1>> is waiting for me to deliver the hides at the concession stand of Maleron's Hoarvor Circus.

Dirani asked me to hunt down the merchant who's selling Hlaalu's weapons to the Vereansu. She says I should speak to the merchants about town to figure out the culprit's identity. Then I can mete justice.
For this challenge, I must defeat the <<1>> in the center ring.
For this challenge, I must defeat the <<1>> in the center ring.
For this challenge, I must defeat <<1>> in the center ring.

I need to find Mubdinab Hansar to kill him and collect his ring. He is most likely hiding somewhere in the Scabrous Pass.

I'm looking for Maelys Nin on the road near the farms. She can convince Koeglin Village's constable to release Dabienne from the stocks.
