According to William Nurdin, his wife Rosalie knows what's going on and can prove Dabienne's innocence. I need to find and talk with Rosalie Nurdin.
William Nurdin suggested I speak with his daughter, Ganise. She's been to the Vanne's farm many times. She may know a way to prove Dabienne's innocence.
Vinen Treewalker wants me to collect<<1>> for him.nnThey can be obtained from nests, filled with eggs.
I have collected several melon-lizards and should return to Vinen Treewalker.
I need to get to higher ground. I might go to the Scabrous Pass, since it overlooks the Vereansu forces. If I can find a boulder there large enough to penetrate the Farseer's shield, I can crush her.

I've successfully toppled a boulder large enough to break through the Farseer's shield. It crushed her, leaving the Vereansu more vulnerable. <<1>> is in the Scabrous Pass, waiting to hear of my success.
<<1>> is in Quarantine Serk. I should tell him about what happened in Scabrous Pass.

Ganise Nurdin saw her uncle's abduction. She escaped after recoving a note dropped by one of the abductors. This may be the proof we need to clear Dabienne Vanne's name. The note is still hidden in Ganise's diary. I must get it.
I'll need more lenses before I can restore the Koeglin Lighthouse. The pirates and their storage crates along the shore are the starting point for my search.
Now that most of the prisoners are free, I should return to <<1>>.
Diseased prisoners are being held captive in the Scabrous Pass. I should free them.
Durak asked me to drink a Sleeping Potion. Once I'm asleep, he'll place me in Hosni abd-Tura's dream.
I've destroyed the Omen of Blood. I must enter the portal in Hosni abd-Tura's manse to wake.
Now that I've replaced the lenses, I should be able to light the fire and finish restoring the lighthouse.
Now that I've freed his crew, I should find <<1>> and rescue him from captivity.
We must set those captive sailors free. They're tied up all around the lighthouse.
I found a bloodstained bag containing a man's clothing and a woman's necklace. I don't know if the necklace belongs to Rosalie. I'll ask Mainard if he recognizes it.
According to Mainard, Rosalie travelled the same route each night, walking down the road to the river and back. Maybe I can find more evidence by retracing that path.
The spectators around the center ring will stand up and wave when they want food. To keep them fed, I'll need to hand them fried boar skins before they sit down again.
I've passed out all of my fresh fried boar skins. I should return to <<1>>.
Conul saw a strange mechanism rise from the ground and believes it may lead into the device. I should use it and find out.
Durak asked me to personally return the Dream Shard to the Statue of Azura.
I've returned the Dream Shard to the chapel at Pariah Abbey. Durak is inside the chapel. I should speak to him about our ongoing battle against Vaermina.
Ryna asked me to find <<1>>, one of the cult's leaders. I should perform any tasks he requires of me. Then hopefully, I can retrieve his shard.
Kwama from the nearby mines have been causing disturbances among the cultists. Dalomer suggest I should break rocks that have kwama under them and then kill them as they scurry out.
I've slain a number of kwama. I should return to Dalomer and see if there are more tasks he needs completed.
I have agreed to meet <<1>> in the capital city of Wayrest. She is likely in hiding, and I will have to search the city to find her.
I should go to the Mabrigash camp in Huskhill, so I can talk Ervyna into leaving her camp. Then Andalas can confront her.
<<1>> and his pet, <<2>>, might be found near the entrance of the mines.
I've located <<1>>, the pet scamp, but no signs of its master. I should see if it understands anything I can say. If it can, then I can ask it about its master.
I ran out of time to sell my fresh fried boar skins. I should talk to <<1>> and get some more.
Soren Lilymoth wants me make my way to Razorvine Refuge. nnHe has suggested that I could search the body of the Imperial commander for his orders and take them to <<1>> as well.
I have found Imperial Orders and should bring them to <<1>> in Razorvine Refuge.
I should look for <<1>> east of Koeglin Lighthouse at Steelheart Moorings.
Shadowhiskers trapped me, called on a mercenary to kill me, and ran off. I must kill this mercenary that Sorcassil hired.
I've been asked to speak to the estate guard captain about a shipment sitting at the docks. He's usually near the western entrance.
I've collected the shipment of meat for Chef Ginie. When I get the chance, I should return it to her.
<<1>> asked me to kill some of the Supernal Dreamers down by the docks. That's on the southwest shore of At-Tura Estate.
I've killed several of the Supernal Dreamers. I should return to <<1>>.
I've spoken to the guard, and he's given me permission to collect the shipment of smoked meat. It's somewhere near the dock, down the road from the west entrance.
<<1>> is waiting for me to talk to her.
<<1>> is leading me to see the Prophet. I need to follow her upstairs.
I should collect a torch from the box in front of Helene.
I burned the slavers' tents, freed the captured sailors, and rescued Elvira from the slavers' leader. I should speak to Elvira to say goodbye.
Now that I've got the burning the log, I can set fire to the slavers' tents and burn the stolen goods at the very end of the dock.
I should assist <<1>> and <<2>> in order to prove myself to House Indoril and earn an audience with Councilman Orival.
The first mate suggested I create a diversion before releasing the captive sailors. I should pull a burning log from one of the slavers' campfires and use it to set their tents on fire.
I should assist <<1>> and <<2>> to prove myself to House Indoril. I may even earn an audience with Councilman Orival.
I found a grave marker, but could not read it. When I cleaned the grave, the spirit of the person buried there appeared.nnIf I find out their name, I can return to Marcel.
I've released <<1>>, the lighthouse keeper, from his bonds. I should speak to him again.
<<1>>, the lighthouse keeper, told me that pirates are responsible for destroying Koeglin Lighthouse and taking him captive. I should release <<1>>.
Captain Leon is convinced that someone from Koeglin Village turned the lighthouse off intentionally. He has asked me to investigate Koeglin Lighthouse and prove his innocence.
Andalas has confronted the Mabrigash, the mer who stole his soul, and he wants to do the same to her. I can use the black soul gem against Ervyna while she's distracted.
I must first speak to High King Emeric at the palace in Wayrest.
I need to meet Grandmaster Durak at Shinji's Scarp. I have no definite signs of the Omen at work in Gavaudon, but I heard that General Godrun has been acting suspicious.
I should speak with <<1>>. I can find him in the temple.
I've closed a Daedric portal! <<1>> in Aldsotha will want to know about this.
I've found proof of Captain Leon's innocence... and Ra'Dara's head. I should return to Captain Leon.
I should speak to Constable Sal.
I should free Captain Leon from the stocks.
I should go to the Koeglin lighthouse, south of the village, and find the signal fire. Once I find it, I can examine it and see if it reveals the truth of who doused the flames.
I spoke to the spirit of Master Wizard Vonuvan Retharys and learned about Kellisa's Charm. I should see what he wants me to do with it.
The vision showed me more splintered glass shards in the main hall of Shad Astula. The shard is gently pulling me in that direction. I'll need to decide if I'll answer that call.
I collected the shattered pieces of a humming, magical device. If I can find the fire I saw in my vision, I can place these shards within it.

I placed the pieces of the artifact into a magical forge. The spirit of a dead Shad Astula Master Wizard appeared before my eyes. I assume this spirit is connected to the artifact, so I should speak to him.
If what the Wayfarer said about the Crypt of Hearts is true, I should find riches in the halls at every turn.
The Wayfarer lies.nnI have explored the Crypt of Hearts to its bleak extent. nnIt was not entirely as advertised.
Something's happened to <<1>>. She's not at the well. There's an injured sailor there who might know where the first mate has gone.
Now that I've got the key, I can free the captives in the caves.

I have recovered the Balac, and should now use <<1>> to teleport out of this ruin.
I've freed all of the other captives. I should free <<1>>.
Conele offered me "good money" to fight several of the sellswords standing around Ra'ud's tavern. He wants someone to beat them in a duel and show them that they're "not so tough."

I've defeated several of Ra'ud's sellswords in duels. This should be sufficient to satisfy Guard Conele. He's waiting for me across the way from Ra'ud's tavern. He promised me "good money" for my demonstration.
I may be able to find more of the lovers' notes scattered around the crypt's halls and chambers.
I may be able to find more of the lovers' notes scattered around the crypt's halls and chambers.

I rescued several Shad Astula students at the request of their classmate, <<1>>. I should check on her and make sure her friends made it out safely. She teleported to the dormitories on the south end of Shad Astula.
I've killed the Ebonheart Slavers' leader, <<1>>. Now it's safe to free <<2>>.

Now that I've killed him, I should collect <<1>>.
Once I collect all the pieces, I should place them in the fire like I saw in my vision.

Mainard said that William headed northwest, toward the older farmhouses. I need to show him Rosalie's broken necklace. Perhaps he'll remember more about what happened to her.
<<1>> left classmates behind in Shad Astula. I should find them. With the <<2>>, I should be able to teleport them to safety.

I've found Hairan's uncle, and I stopped a cabal of enthralled Tribunal servants trafficking in sick mer. I didn't find out why they were doing this or what possessed them. For now, I should return to Hairan and let her know her uncle is safe.
I should go to the graveyard northwest of the Matuul village and look for Danabi Ashbael's grave.
Danabi Ashbael told me he was exhumed by servants of the Tribunal temple, who were transporting coffins by wagon somewhere to the east. I should look for these wagons and put a stop to this.

Danabi Ashbael told me he was exhumed by servants of the Tribunal temple, who were transporting coffins by wagon somewhere to the east. I should slay them and rescue the others trapped within the coffins.
I've found Danabi Ashbael. He seems very much alive. nnI should speak to him to find out what happened... and how he escaped from his grave.
I should find Farathan and ask him about the raving curate I encountered in the woods. He would probably be at the Matuul village.
I've slain Diviner Vemar, though I can't fully fathom the depths of his treachery. I should speak to Disciple Farathan and make sure she's all right.
I've found Farathan's acolyte, but he's entranced by a strange artifact. Several others are also under its spell. I should rouse the acolyte from his reverie.
I've found a group acolytes entranced by a strange artifact.nnPerhaps if I take away the artifact, that may rouse them from their reverie.

I've found an artifact entrancing Farathan's acolyte. When I seized it, I saw a strange vision of a patriarch, who then commanded one of the acolytes to attack me.nnPerhaps Disciple Farathan knows a way to destroy this insidious artifact.
Diviner Vemar proved to be in league with the same forces that controlled the artifact. I must slay him before he does any more harm.
I've brought the artifact to Disciple Farathan. I should accompany her to a meeting with the Diviner, who should be powerful enough to destroy it.
I have a fragment of a note. I should look for more notes.

After I spoke with Moric, a slim Khajiit hailed me. She said she wanted to congratulate me, but she might intend more than that. I should speak to this Khajiit and see what she knows about Moric's games.

Hilani revealed that Moric is fixing fights. If I fight Grul before I discover how, I'll lose. Hilani's friend, Rin, claimed to know how Moric was cheating. Moric has her captive in caves beneath Hammerdeath Arena. I should find her.
When I exited the cave beneath Hammerdeath Arena, a Bosmer hailed me, saying it was finally time for me to fight Grul the Destroyer. I should drink my potion before I face Grul.
The Midnight Phantom held a sword at Moric Nirine's throat. The Phantom has revealed himself at last. If I speak to him, I may discover what he did with the Dream Shard stolen from Pariah Abbey.
Hilani knows more about Hammerdeath Arena than I do. If I ask, perhaps she'll have some ideas about how to reach Rin.
Hilani said that only Hammerdeath gladiators are allowed to enter the area beneath the arena. I should speak to Lob about becoming one, so I can reach Rin.

Mar gro-Bug is at the center of the arena. I can trade him a Hammerdeath Victory Token for an Amulet of Hammerdeath. When I wear it, I can enter the caves beneath Hammerdeath Arena without being attacked.
I defeated Grul in Hammerdeath Arena. Moric Nirine's ploy to fix our fight failed. Now I can confront Moric at his seat above Hammerdeath Arena and claim the title of Grand Gladiator.
I placed the trinkets as <<1>> requested. I should inform her of my success.
I found a journal in Master Wizard Kellisa's room. It implicates her in the previous master's disappearance, and it seems to exonerate <<1>>. I should inform <<2>>.

I need to find villagers willing to write letters to Colane Oscent vouching for the Midnight Swell's crew. There may be tasks to complete before the villagers trust me enough to hand me a letter.
I've given Colane Oscent letters vouching for Captain Veronika and the crew of the Midnight Swell. Now I can give the captain the good news.
I should check the room of <<1>> and see if she has anything suspicious.
I found a strange totem in the room of <<1>>. This may be what <<2>> wanted me to find.
Kellisa's journal is locked by three magical sealing stones. I will have to disable them in order to examine the journal.
<<1>> said I should investigate the Master Wizard Kellisa's tower and find evidence that implicates <<2>> in Shad Astula's madness.
I found my way to Shad Astula's Master Wizard tower. I need to find evidence that implicates <<1>> in Shad Astula's madness.nnI've unlocked the book. I should search it for evidence.
I should look at Kellisa's Journal to see if it contain's any information on Shad Astula's madness.
Oscent asked me to tell the ship's captain, Veronika, that she cannot unload her cargo at Koeglin Village.
I destroyed the contaminated food before it reached the Matuul village. I should inform the village leader about what has transpired.
I should look for the wellspring mentioned in the defaced prayer book. Then I can see what kind of "blessings" are contained within it.
I found the wellspring mentioned in the prayer book. The water was contaminated, making the nearby guar sick.nnFor pity's sake, I need to find the owner of these guar and let him know.

The herder informed me that someone has infected the guar with a disease. The scoundrel's intention was to infect the whole village.nnThe herder asked me to destroy all food shipments destined for the village before they infected anyone else.
I must seek the Faded Spirit deeper in the Crypt of Hearts.nnThe spirit spoke to me briefly, then disappeared.
Alanwe told me that she and Nerien had built a place called Heartland to guide others to peace and prosperity. When Alanwe died, Nerien went mad, and the dream turned into to a nightmare.
I've completed the Trials of the Four Troubles. The next portal leads to the temple's inner sanctum, where I can speak to Vivec.
Curate Salver opened a portal to begin my Trial of the Four Troubles. When I enter, it begins.
I've entered the first shrine of the trial. I should search the room for clues on how to proceed.
I've solved the second shrine in the trial of the House of Troubles. I should enter the portal to proceed to the next shrine, and pass its test.
I've resolved the third shrine's ordeal in the House of Troubles. After I enter the next portal, I can proceed to the next shrine and continue my ordeals.
I've resolved the first shrine's ordeal in the House of Troubles. After I enter the next portal, I can proceed to the next shrine and continue my ordeals.

The Supernal Dreamers are holding Ingride Vanne at Stonebridge Mill. I'll need to find her and use the ritual items to break the spell they've placed on her.
Govran Cerone is willing to sacrifice his own savings to pay for repairs to Irne's boat, but only if Irne can get him released from the warehouse. We're close to brokering a deal between them.

Melesi Irayth asked me to look for a scroll. It's at the southern end of the Velothi Rivergraves, near an altar of some sort. He was loathe to talk about what they were doing there. Perhaps the others will be less evasive.
<<1>> may be lost or injured. I should find her.
I've slain the Omen of Fear. I should find Sir Hughes so we can leave the dream.

Perhaps talking to Sir Hughes will allow me to awaken from his dream.
When I talk to Sir Hughes, I'll awaken from his dream.
I should help J'raka by killing Imperials and burning their bodies with the torch he gave me.

<<1>> asked me to take a plant sample to <<2>> in Aldsotha.
I'll talk to <<1>> about the events in Sir Hughes' dream.

I can find <<1>> in the Deshaan swampland to the east.
I need to search for the four artifacts in the Balarel ruins.

I've taken care of all three mages at the camp. I should speak to the murdered soul and see if it's been appeased.
I need to find <<1>>'s guar and release him. She said he'd be in the Ashlander camp to the northwest. He's somewhere inside the ligorcap fields.
I'll need to find a way onto the sinking Imperial ship, so I can search for what the soldiers are protecting.
J'Hriss is standing on the docks of Southpoint village. I should return the lockbox to him.
Now that the Dremora boss is dead, the miners should eventually be able to retake the mines. I should talk to Brek.
The dead adventurer's jounral says to kill goblins and discover the fate of miners. I should be able to find the miners inside or what's left of them.
I've offered to assist House Indoril in gathering samples of musk screal flowers.nnThe researchers at the camp may have some useful advice for methods of harvesting the flower.

If I search the area around the Matuul village, I might find Farathan's lost acolyte.

I should fight my way to the villagers hiding in their homes throughout town, thus clearing a path so they can run to safety.

I've found a warehouse in town that looks like its seen a lot of recent traffic.nnThis could be the meeting place the cryptic message message. Perhaps if I search around the warehouse, I'll find clues.

I should find the conspirators listed on the paper, find out what kind of treasonous plan they're concocting, and stop them.
I should slay the daedroth while Rahira recaptures the town.

I've defeated the Mabrigash Champion and earned the right to speak to their prisoner.
I should speak to Farah inside her home. According to rumor, she knows why the Imperials have targeted Southpoint in their attacks.
I've come across a bloodied Bosmer corpse. The victim looks as if he was trying to protect something. After closer inspection, I've come to realize that this is the body of the Treethane.
The man I was escorting just ... vanished. A nearby sergeant may have witnessed this. I should speak to him.
I'll speak with the sergeant and ask him to let Arnoit Sidrey pass.
I must travel to the three great towers of Tamriel and charge the Balac upon their foundation stones.
While searching Blacksap Village, I found an Altmer prisoner. I should question him.
The goblin numbers have been reduced and all the miners inside were slain. The mining company isn't going to be happy about this, especially with with the presence of Daedra.
I am to summon and kill the Dremora that slayed the miners, then report to Brek after the deed is done. The summon stone is at the front of the tower, near the exit of the mine's upper level.
I must find a means of travel to the Adamantine Tower. Perhaps the Mages Guild can help again.
The goblin numbers have been reduced and all the miners inside were slain. The mining company isn't going to be happy about this, especially with with the presence of Daedra.
Find the Daedric artifact, summon the Dremora, and kill it.
Now that the Dremora boss is dead, the miners' deaths are avenged. I should talk to Brek.
I am inside the Adamantine Tower. Now I must find a way to the Zero Stone and imbue the Balac with its power.
Farah mentioned that her father has been hiding on the cliffs to the west for some time. Someone needs to bring him home. I should check around the western cliffs for clues.
I might be able to speak to Gladimel outside of Farah's home to see if he has heard anything about Farah's missing father.
I learned that Farah's father was the Treethane of Southpoint. If for some reason Southpoint had something to protect, he would've been the one who had the information on it.
<<1>> wishes to explain how the Balac can be restored. I should listen to what he says.
<<1>> asked me to investigate houses on the northern end of Blacksap Village.
I should find <<1>>, a student trapped in Shad Astula.
I have tapped the Balac into the power of Crystal-like-Law. I should return to the Prophet and show him the renewed staff.
I've delivered water to the watchtower. I should speak to the guard again.
I've filled the leaky bucket. I should deliver it before all of the water leaks out.
<<1>> may have more information for me on how to complete her task.
I should either fill the leaky bucket at the well next to the tower or borrow a bucket from the forester's camp up the road to the south.
I should go to the well and fill the <<1>>

I should use the kindlepitch <<1>> gave me to set crates of supplies on fire. Their supplies are on the western shore, near the beach where they landed.
I've destroyed plenty of supplies. I should inform one of the Dominion soldiers in the hidden camp to the north. I should be able to find it by following the shore line.
I have agreed to enter the Palisades and seek out any signs of plans or orders that might be imperative to the Imperial invasion.
I've recovered a set of orders addressed to General Cruor. I should return to the base camp in Southpoint and show <<1>> what I've found.

I must find a means of travel to the Crystal Tower on Summerset Isle. Perhaps the Mages Guild can help again.

A freed citizen told me he saw dreugh dragging Arcady to the spawning pools "near the statue of King Joile." I may find Arcady there, if he's still alive.

I need to find a way through the propylon and kill the magi maintaining the connection
When I'm ready to escort Arnoit Sidrey to Eagle's Gate, I'll let him know.
The captured Bosmer is free and on his way home. When I arrive in Southpoint, I should seek him out.
If I can find the key to the Bosmer's bindings, I can set him free. One of the guards in the area may be carrying it.

If I can find Vonov, I can kill him!

A Khajiit named Qi'Ravin may be able to help me. He's hiding in a tent north of here, away from the Imperials.

The Altmer asked me to help fight off spriggans and wisps throughout Spritedancer Marsh.

I need to find carcasses around the farms and burn them.

I should look around Razorvine for the remains of Fhalin's father. Fhalin said his father was an acrobat, so the remains might be in hard-to-reach areas.
I've located what I believe to be Fhalin's father. I should return to him with the remains.
I should ask Fhalin if he has any clues on where his father's remains might be.

Fhalin suggested that I should to look upwards in hard-to-reach areas for his father's remains. He said I should also check around storage areas within the camp, as his father often liked to hide behind things.

I should check on the caretaker of the burial site, a Bosmer named Golleon. He's somewhere northwest of the town.

I've activated the crystals in the Ruins of Cormeiir. A previously hidden stone has appeared inscribed with magical writing. I should investigate further.

I should search for Jaqspur Ina in Thrambles. Then I should hurry back to Thistlewhip with the food she found.
I've reached the Thrambleheart. I should talk to the Grahtlord.
I should find the Thrambleheart. It's hidden in the center of the Thrambles.
Terein gave me a bone cup and a silver cup and asked me to fill them in the nearby fountain.

I filled the cups. I should speak to Terein.
There was no taste to the water held in the cup. Terein mentioned that one cup would be invigorating. The other would be ordinary water. I guess I drank the water. I feel no different.
If I leave with the hunters, all the meat we gather in the Thrambles will become poisonous. If I leave alone, the Grahtlord will supply an ample amount of food to Thistlewhip's camp. I must decide.
I decided to leave alone. The Grahtlord pointed to a secret passage behind a hedge south of him. I should follow the path and speak to Jaqspur Thistlewhip.
I decided to leave with the hunters. The Grahtlord pointed to a secret passage behind a hedge south of him. I should follow the path and speak to Jaqspur Thistlewhip.

I should talk to Ra'Vashi and guide him along his path of training.
I need to collect Imperial weapons for a young Khajiit. The Imperials in Haven, east of here, should have plenty of them.
I need to find three books that belong to a seer in Haven. I should probably start searching in the town to the east and the surrounding areas.
I need to find a proper cowl for the young Khajiit's training. I should travel to the east and search in Haven.
I've collected the three books Ra'Vashi needed. I should return to him back at Razorvine Refuge.
I've found a cowl for Ra'Vashi. I should return to him back at Razorvine Refuge.
I gave Terein the silver cup. I'll drink from the bone cup.
I gave Terein the bone cup. I'll drink from the silver cup.
I should investigate crypts under the base of the Wrothgar Mountains. Then I can see what's become of those corpses.
I've explored the Crypt of Hearts and freed the spirit of Alanwe Melanon. I should find the gravedigger and tell her what I've learned.
According to Parvaneh, Gerarde is a spirit warden that I might encounter near the Moonlit Maw.
I'll need to find the two Bosmer from Southpoint to the north, towards the Spritedancer Marsh.
Perhaps someone in the Perroult family still lives in Hoarfrost Downs. I should bring the letter to them and see if they can make sense of it.
I've destroyed the wards. Now I can go to the cathedral to meet with Warmaster Rahira.
I should destroy the wards around the town. When I'm done, I can meet with Warmaster Rahira in the cathedral.
I've slain the Daedroth. I should return to Golleon.
Golleon asked me to check a snare trap in the vault directly south of him.
A Daedroth freed itself from the trap, but I didn't see it until it attacked me. I've got to kill it!

Farmhand Jerrick has given me one of the farm dogs to help herd the cattle into the proper pen. I should search the farm area for missing cows and have the dog lead them to the holding pen north of the farm's windmill.
I have herded the cows back into their pen. I should speak with <<1>> now, who is waiting at the pen.
I must talk to each of Evermore's Ministers on behalf of Queen Arzhela.

Now that she's had a moment to reflect on my advice, Queen Arzhela should be able to select a Regent for Evermore.
Lady Ginie, the Minister of War, is being held in the castle's dungeon. The guard at its entry behind the castle should allow me to free Lady Ginie after receiving this Letter of Release.
I'll let Lady Isabelle Errard know that the Minister of War is now free.
Both Evermore's tax enforcers and the Bjoulsae Queen's Captain asked me to be their champion in this matter. I'll go below the ship's deck and consider which cause to uphold.
After siding with the crew of the Bjoulsae Queen, I defeated Evermore's tax enforcer. Now I can tell Lord Alfred Stental that this ship will not pay the new taxes.
After siding with the city of Evermore, I defeated the Bjoulsae Queen's champion. I'll tell Lord Alfred Stental to expect his new tariff to be paid.
I'll talk with <<1>>Evermore's Minister of Health, to see if he'll tell me what's happened.
