Gerarde asked me to enter the cave on the north side of the Moonlit Maw and look for Muzgu. If possible, I must save Muzgu and stop the Supernal Dreamers from completing their ritual.

The Supernal Dreamers succeeded in their ritual. They summoned the Omen, though Muzgu has managed to resist it thus far.nnThe respite is temporary. Muzgu asked me to kill him to prevent the Omen from possessing him.

I have refused to kill Muzgu. Instead, we agreed to capture a Supernal Dreamer and trick the Omen into possessing them instead. This will save Muzgu, but doom the cultist to eternal nightmare.nnI should ask Muzgu about our next step.
I found Muzgu deep in the Supernal Dreamer's cave. I do not know if the Supernal Dreamers completed their ritual or not. I must talk to Muzgu and find out what he knows.
I should find <<1>> and let her know that I learned more about the Fighters Guild.
I should gather Moonshone Flowers from Moonlit Maw.
I've collected the Moonshone Flowers. I must crush them over the altar in the cave where Muzgu died.nnWhen the Daedra manifests, I must then kill it.
I destroyed the Daedra. It no longer threatens Stormhaven. Muzgu is avenged. nnI talk to Gerarde.
To pull the Daedra out of Muzgu, force it to manifest, I must crush the Moonshone Flowers over the altar, deep within the cave of the Moonlit Maw.
When I examined the grave, Faynis' father appeared to me. His name is <<1>>, and I should speak to him.
Muzgu asked me to use a scroll of teleportation on a sleeping cultist to teleport them to the cave.

Muzgu and I decided not to sacrifice anyone to a realm of eternal nightmare, even a daedric cultist. Muzgu has taken a vial of poison and is now dead.nnI must summon and destroy the Daedra to ensure his death means something.
I must manifest and kill the Daedra that fights to control Muzgu. To do this, we will trick it into possessing a Supernal Dreamer cultist, freeing and saving Muzgu.

I destroyed the Daedra. It no longer threatens Stormhaven. Muzgu is avenged. nnI talk to Gerarde.

Now that I've collected enough knives, I need to return to the peasant and let him know I've avenged his mistreatment.
I need to kill Reachmen around the Pens and collect their belt knives.
<<1>> suggest I speak to <<2>> for some advice about dealing with the Orlishkaarn Ashlanders. He's somewhere within the Senie camp.

<<1>> suggest that I kill an Ashlander and steal some Orlishkaarn garb. Then I could use it to disguise myself and remain undetected among them. If I do this, I'll need to look out for their nix-hounds and not linger for too long.
Ala is going to scout the aeries and find out how the Imperials are training gargoyles. In the meantime, he asked me to kill a number of gargoyles to thin their numbers.

As the explorer tried to flee the ruin, the pages of the journal were scattered in his wake. I should be able to follow the trail of shredded paper back to its source.
I've assembled most of the journal. Only the first few pages are missing now. They must be hidden in the heart of Danarkus.
I should speak to <<1>> and find out what Vonov's Imperial soldiers have stolen. Hanging vines will help me travel through the treetops.
<<1>> has given me incense to burn in the sconces surrounding Iliath Temple.
I've burned the incense <<1>> gave me. I should go meet her in the lower chambers so she can start the ceremony.

I need to use the <<1>> to test water in three pools in the ruin. The stone changes color to reflect the purity of the water. The purest water changes it blue. The most contaminated water changes it red.
The <<1>> showed pure blue everywhere I tested it. The corruption of the affliction is not in Danarkus. I should return to <<2>> with the news.
The original resting places for these bones are somewhere within the open tombs of the necropolis. If I find any other piles of bones, I'll return them to a tomb.
When I replaced the last set of bones, a spirit appeared before me. It wants to speak with me.
When I replaced the last set of bones, a spirit appeared before me. Perhaps it knows more about what happened here.
When I replaced the last set of bones, a spirit appeared before me. I should speak to it about the bones.
I have the stolen artifacts and should inform the spirit of <<1>>.
The sage asked me to find the scamp and retrieve the totem.
Marea Hloriss has asked me to reason with the priestess of Othrenis. Without her permission, any who enter will be attacked by the guardians, and Marea must get to the Hortator's grave.

Mazira believes that to stop Verro, we must assemble our own army of risen spirits. I must enter the tombs of Redguard leaders and summon the spirits. Then I must convince them to join us in defeating Legatus Verro.
I've raised many Redguard spirits and rallied them to the cause Mazira and I share. Mazira asked me to gather her army and meet her by the cave atop the necropolis.
Mazira told me to sprinkle her ashes in the tombs of ancient Redguard leaders to summon their spirits.
I should travel to Fort Virak and speak to the captain there. The nobility of Omaynia want military reinforcements to bring peace to their town.
I should journey southwest of Omaynia and seek out the alchemist Erja mentioned.
I've found a ritual book with a marked page. I should find someone with a good knowledge of the forest to interpret its writing and diagrams.
<<1>> and her son have both been poisoned. I need to find the antidote before time runs out.
I found the antidote to the poison. I can administer it to <<1>>.
I've administered the antidote to <<1>>. I have to return to <<2>> before it's too late.
<<1>> has died. I should tell one of the freed captives.
Both <<1>> and her son have died. I should inform one of the freed captives.
I should go to Kragenmoor. Once there, I could help Sting-Lash by finding the former slave owner from Omaynia.
I should travel north of Kragenmoor and give the present to the wife of <<1>>.
I should journey to Iliath Temple and speak to the Diviner there. It lies east of Kragenmoor atop the highest mountain in Stonefalls.
I should travel north of Kragenmoor to Heimlyn Keep. Then I can extend Odren's offer to the captain there.
I should look for the raving Altmer. The Bosmer said he was possibly headed east, toward Elden Root, and I could probably find him, or his corpse, on the road leading there.
<<1>> gave me a letter to take to <<2>> in Narsis. She said I need to travel to Deshaan, south of the Iliath Temple. Once there, I can follow the main road to Narsis.
I've got to return the bejeweled beetle to its rightful owner.
<<1>> has been slain. I should return <<2>> to the Fighters Guild to complete the contract.
I should retrieve <<1>> to prove that I've killed him.
<<1>> has been slain. I should return her head to the Fighters Guild and collect my bounty.
I should retrieve the head of <<1>> to prove that I've killed her.
<<1>> has been slain. I should return his club to the Fighters Guild to complete the contract.
I should retrieve the club of <<1>> to prove that I've killed him.
When I'm ready to begin my Rite of Initiation, I'll start by "invoking" the Night Stone. It's outside the cave to the east.
The first apparition has appeared. I must defeat it.
I defeated the first apparition. I should use the Night Stone to summon the second one.
I've chosen to represent Lord Olivier Belves, the Minister of Health. The other candidates' champions will face me singly in the castle's lower chamber.
I need to find out more about the choices for Evermore's Regent before I can decide whose champion I will be.
I defeated the champions of the Ministers of the Treasury and War. I should talk to Queen Arzhela in the castle's main audience chamber.
I defeated the champions of the Ministers of War and Health. I should talk to Queen Arzhela in the castle's main audience chamber.
I defeated the champions of the Ministers of the Treasury and Health. I should talk to Queen Arzhela in the castle's main audience chamber.
I've chosen to represent Lady Ginie Errard, the Minister of War. The other candidates' champions will face me singly in the castle's lower chamber.
I've chosen to represent Lord Alfred Stental, the Minister of the Treasury. The other candidates' champions will face me singly in the castle's lower chamber.
The Master of Combat is in the castle's lower chamber. He can summon any champion I need to defeat.
Michelle asked me for a birthday present. If I don't want to upset her, I should find one and give it to her.
I've given Michelle her birthday gift. I should excuse myself and walk away slowly.
I might find more pages of the book deeper in the cave. Perhaps I can put the book together and return it to its owner.
I've reassembled the torn book with all its pages and restored the entire devotion. It was lost recently enough that its owner could still be in the cave. I should find him.
I've collected the missing pages of the book. Now I can put it back together.

Mazira told me Legatus Verro is located deep in the necropolis cave in a room called the "Ra Gada Wellspring." I must reach that room. Mazira also told me the army of souls we've gathered will aid me in the cave.
I've reached the Ra Gada Wellspring, but Legatus Verro has locked himself away behind a magical shield. Its power is drawn from the souls he's enslaved. I must defeat him to free those souls.
I've killed Legatus Verro and freed the Redguard souls he enslaved. Mazira can tell me if anything else must be done to restore peace to the necropolis.
The spirit of Mazira is nearby. Perhaps she'll have advice on how I can defeat Legatus Verro.
Verro's shield has been shattered. His army of souls is busy fighting the army Mazira gathered. I must defeat Legatus Verro while Mazira and other friendly souls keep his army of the dead busy.
I've given Michelle her birthday gift. I should conclude our conversation now.
I should travel to Omaynia and speak to whoever is in charge of the freed slaves there. They may know of Half-Tail's fate.
I've given Michelle her birthday gift. I should excuse myself and walk away slowly.
I told Michelle I would never give her a present. She's taking it very hard. Maybe I should have just given her something.
If I run into any healing Redguard spirits while fighting Legatus Verro, they'll use their energy to heal me.
I've gotten answers from the two remaining farmhands on the netch plantation. I also discovered the fate of the third. I should return to Lluthyne Merns and let her know the news.
I have unlocked Elder Brump's cage and set him free. I should speak to him.
Queen Arzhela has requested I meet her at her manse at the highest point in Evermore.
I should speak to Farah before I confront Vonov. She might have some insight on how we can defeat him in this coming battle.
Farah told me to keep Vonov's minions away from him during the fight. She'll try to infuse her magic within them. When I slay them, they'll heal me.
I've been asked to infiltrate a skooma den so I can kill <<1>>. His lair is hidden in a cave behind some buildings in the Gutter of Kragenmoor.
I need to gather raw garnet from the hills to the south, directly outside of Davon's Watch.
I have the raw garnet Runemaster Tels requested and should return to him, in Davon's Watch.
I should draw raw corn rose oil from the corn rose blossoms found about the city of Davon's Watch.
I have collected the corn rose oil and should return to Galia the Stout, the Forestry trainer in Davon's Watch.
I should slay the stonescar kagouti and skin them for their thin hides.
I have enough thin hides and should present them to Seamstress Eiruki in Davon's Watch.
I should extract dioptase nuggets from the hills to the west, immediately outside Davon's Watch.
I should present the dioptase nuggets I extracted to Master Dranolos. He waits in the Smithy, inside Davon's Watch.
Farseer Arafal has sent me to the daedric temple, where I can find the daedric Baron and Baroness and hopefully bring their incursion to an end.
I have killed the Baron Xivlen and the Baroness Zeyrun. Farseer Arafal is dead, but at least her charge to me is complete. I should let Farseer Leamu know what transpired.
In order to stop the attacks from the Crucible, I must find the Lost Farseer.
Now that the rift is closed, I should return to Farseer Leamu at the Ashlander War Camp and tell her what happened.
I should destroy any magma crystals I find in the caldera before they spawn more elementals.
I was able to destroy magma crystals in the Crucible that have been spawning elementals. I should let Champion Varesa know of my success.
<<1>> wants to discuss the situation at the shrine, but he can't voice his doubts to his men without losing their confidence. As an outsider, I could listen to them without prejudice.
The Lost Farseer, Arafal, either can't or won't close the rift that she opened for the daedra.nnShe has asked me to go up into the temple and do it for her.
I should find the Tribune that helped the peasant escape. She'll probaby be on the northwestern outskirts of the Pens.
I should find Calypsi's tent and look for the cage key.
I have the cage key. I should unlock Yoon's cage.
Yoon is free! I should talk to him.
If I can find keys to prison shackles, I can free some prisoners. I should check the southern parts of the camp for Imperial commanders.

I've found the keys to prisoners' shackles. Now I should find a Bosmer scout in Calypsi's Foothold who can tell me where the prisoners are held. If I use the vines around the camp, I should be able to climb on top of giant mushroom caps and find him.

<<1>> has asked me to free prisoners in the northeastern part of <<2>>. He's told me I can use walkways to traverse the area, but only if I keep an eye out for Imperials. When I'm finished, I should look for <<3>> in the prisoner area.
I should be able to find the storage house in one of the many buildings in the Gutter slum of Kragenmoor. The writer of the note should be waiting at that location.
I found the storage house mentioned in the note. I should reenter the building and search for clues.
I've freed several of the prisoners. I should check in the northern part of the camp to see if I can find the scout that attempted the prisoner's rescue earlier.
I'll need to check the Imperial Commanders on the southern part of the camp for the keys I need to free the prisoners.
I'll need to check around the camp and free any bosmers that I can find.
The medicine that <<1>> asked me to retrieve appears to be skooma. I should question her about it before returning it to her.
Wild saltrice grows along the shores of the river that flows north past the Shrine to Boethiah.
I've collected saltrice. I should deliver it to someone at the heart of the shrine.
I've given <<1>> the saltrice, but she'd still like to speak with me.
The ordinators have taken the shrine. I can't give saltrice to the Ashlanders. I turned it over to <<1>>, but he would still like to speak with me.
I should look for support near the Reach camp southeast of Dunkarn Haven.
I've given the saltrice to <<1>>, who was left in charge of the Shrine by<<2>>. It appears he'd like to speak with me further
If I need any clarification, I can speak to Ula-Tei.
I should find the cave <<1>> mentioned. She said I can find it to the east.
I have found the key <<1>> mentioned. I should return to <<2>> outside Necris and give it to him.
I decided I didn't trust the plan <<1>> made. I decided to deliver the key to his daughter, Llira. Faynis mentioned she's at the Iliath Temple. I should try to find her.
Now that I've found the key, I should look for the jewelry box within the main building of the Thovasi Sanatorium to retrieve the ring.

I must find the jewelry box key to obtain Savila's ring. The key is either with her sister or among her belongings. There's no telling which patient it is or which room is hers Both are in the main building of <<1>>, south of Savila.
The note I found detailing the use of the corpses to "rebuild" mentioned a trapped spirit, Alanwe. I should see if I can find her.

I found corpse carts in the underground crypts; clearly someone is collecting remains here for some dark purpose. The carts were marked with the name Renwen - maybe whoever that is will have some answers.
After drinking the poison, the Nest-Mother appeared for a moment. I should journey to the top of the enclave and speak to her, now that I have passed her test.
I should search the Shadowscale Enclave for the poisons the Leaf-Sentry spoke of, and collect samples from all three.
Bahir asked me to speak to three captains and convince them to end the riots. They're aboard their ships in Sentinel's docks.
I should search the buildings for a fake royal seal. Then I should look around for a guard's uniform. If I kill some minions of the Withered Hand, I can search their bodies for clues.
I can now present the fake seal to Captain Maujad, the suspicious note to Captain Pierjean, and the guard uniform to Captain Emadal. They promised to calm the riots once they had their proof.

I should present the forged documents and fake seal to Captain Maujad, the suspicious note to Captain Pierjean, and the guard uniform to Captain Emadal. They promised to calm the riot once this proof was presented.
I should ask Captain Maujad to end the riots.
I should ask Captain Pierjean to end the riots.
I should ask Captain Emadal to end the riots.
Yisra asked me to look for Tribune Kabra at-Shadr or those she freed. They're near a Reach prison encampment. I'll find it by following the road west from Bangkorai Garrison.
Yisra asked me to look for Tribune Kabra at-Shadr or those she has freed near a Reach prison encampment. I'll find it by following the road west from Bangkorai Garrison.
Yisra asked me to look for Tribune Kabra at-Shadr or those she freed near a Reach prison encampment. I'll find it by following the road west from Bangkorai Garrison.

I believe I've found the assassin who returned from Alten Corimont. He spoke of hearing the voice of Sithis and killing his own brothers before he attacked me. I should speak to the Nest-Mother and tell her what occurred.
I should speak to the assassins in the enclave and find the one who returned from Alten Corimont without executing his target.

Telenger the Artificer asked me to recover precious Altmer relics from the ruins of Salas En. The relics can be found lying on the ground. They might also be carried by the goblins inhabiting the site.
I've collected the relics as Telenger requested. I should return to his camp and deliver them.
I've thinned the local beetle population and collected several desert grubs.  I should return them to the water gatherers.
One of the water gatherers asked me to kill beetles and collect desert grubs around Rain Catcher Fields. He gave me a whistle to call a trained <<1>> to find the grubs.
I need to find Altmer remains in the dungeon below Salas En. Then I can use the censer Rinlan gave me to sanctify the bones.
I've completed Rinlan's task. I should return and appraise him of my progress.
I've collected the three types of poison from around the enclave. According to the Leaf-Sentry, I must drink the poison to prove my faith and trustworthiness.
I should slay the Sand-born and collect their blades.
I collected Sand-born blades and should return to Guard Captain Zafira.
The rain catchers have been extinguished.  I should let Jahi know the water supply is safe.
I've found some notes that were dropped by some suspicious Argonians. They all seem to be written in the same strange code. I should take them to the Listener and see if he can decipher them.

I need to search the Shadowscale enclave for any sign of correspondence from this "Prophet of Sithis."nnI should be on the lookout for any Argonians that are acting suspiciously to find where the messages may be hidden.
I agreed to rescue Dock Master Bahir. He's being held in a warehouse on the northeastern side of the docks. First, I should kill Withered Hand minions until I find a key to the warehouse.
I found a key on the corpse of a Withered Hand minion. I should use it to enter the warehouse and free Dock Master Bahir.
The warehouse is probably locked. One of the Sand-born might have a key.

I summoned "Sithis" but saw nothing but a vision of a cloaked figure. When it realized I was no Shadowscale, it called upon the Children of Sithis to attack me.nnI must tell the Nest-Mother someone masquerades as the voice of Sithis.
I should speak to the prisoner who attacked the Nest-Mother in the enclave to discover his motives.
A vision appeared after offering up some of my blood to the shrine atop the Shadowscale Enclave. I must find out what it has to say.

The prisoner said he had spoken to Sithis directly. Whatever voice spoke to him came from the shrine atop the enclave.nnThe prisoner mentioned "an offering of blood" to speak to the voice. I need to offer up some of my own to see if he speaks true.
The Children of Sithis have taken up arms against the Shadowscales. I should ask the Nest-Mother how she will recover from this blow.

Since only the Nest-Mother and the Speakers are normally allowed into the shrine, the Nest-Mother believes the Prophet is among their numbers. She has taken drastic measures, and asked me to "bless" the Speakers with an airborne poison.
I've discovered the identity of the Prophet, though he did not live long afterwards. I should go to the Nest-Mother and let her know.
Telenger asked me to meet him at Ancestor's Landing. It lies along the coast, northwest of Salas En.

King Fahara'jad says the undead attack at the docks was the work of the Withered Hand, a group of dangerous and vengeful necromancers. He's asked me to consult with his trusted advisor, General Thoda, about how to proceed.

The undead attack at the docks was the work of the Withered Hand, a group of dangerous necromancers. Prince Azah may have clues as to what the Hand's next move will be. The Prince is not here though. I should talk to Ilmaha.

The undead attack at the docks was the work of the Withered Hand, a group of dangerous necromancers. They kidnapped Prince Azah as well, and apparently took down into an old shipping tunnel. I should investigate.
The undead attack at the docks was the work of the Withered Hand, a group of dangerous necromancers. They kidnapped Prince Azah as well, but I have found him. I should free the prince immediately.
I promised to free an Orc from his prison. I'll have to find some way to dispel the enchantment within the dungeon.
I have destroyed the prison. The Orc is free. I should speak with him now.
I should bring this note to Guard Captain Zafira. It mentions her by name.
The contents of <<1>>'s cart are scattered all over the canyon. Heavier items are more likely to have come to rest at the top, and lighter ones rolled to the bottom.
I've recovered a number of items that were scattered in the wreck of Devad's cart. I should distribute them to the residents of the village.
I've distributed <<1>>'s various foodstuffs to the villagers, to general acclaim. He'll be pleased to hear of the reaction.
The undead attack at the docks was the work of the Withered Hand, a group of dangerous necromancers. General Thoda says Prince Azah said he had heard rumors about them. I should look for the prince.
I should talk to <<1>> in front of the Town Hall of Stormhold.
I should find <<1>> and find out why she is not allowing any action to be taken against the Shadowscales. The guard said I could find her in front of the Town Hall of southern Stormhold.
<<1>> has asked me to examine the bodies of the victims. She said I can find them in the Medicinal Ward, just west of the Town Hall.
A <<1>> appeared in the morgue of the Medicinal Ward and spoke of the Shadowscales' innocence. I should speak to him to find out what he wants.
I should obtain these sabotage plans before the courier does. Shipwright Ramal said the plans will be on the small dock northwest of where I found him.
I have secured the sabotage plans and should return to Shipwright Ramal at the dockhouse, near the entrance to the docks.
Shipwright Ramal informed me that some Redguard ships mysteriously sunk. nnRamal plans to inspect every ship in the port and asked me to tell Dock Master Bahir to block all ships leaving.
I should search for Shipwright Ramal. Dock Master Bahir suggested I look among the Sand-born.

I found Shipwright Ramal. He says Sand-born sabotaged Redguard ships and left detailed sabotage information for a Withered Hand courier to pick up.nnI must get the plans first. They should be on the small dock northwest of where I found Ramal.
I have secured the sabotage plans and should return to Shipwright Ramal at the dockhouse, near the entrance to the docks.
Shipwright Ramal informed me that some Redguard ships mysteriously sunk. nnRamal plans to inspect every ship in the port and asked me to tell Dock Master Bahir to block all ships leaving.
I should enter the palace and warn the king about the Withered Hand's plans.
King Faraha'jad is taking guards to the Impervious Vault, but he doesn't know how to get in. He's asked me to speak with Gabrielle at the Mages Guild to ask for assistance.
Gabrielle at the Mages Guild agreed to help us open the vault. She has asked me to collect reagents to help her break through the seal. She requires <<1>> and <<2>>.
I've collected the reagents <<1>> needs to break the seals on the Impervious Vault. Then we can go inside and see if the Withered Hand managed to tunnel in.
I defeated the Withered Hand in the vault, but it seems some of them escaped with the Ansei Wards. I should inform the king.
I've killed a <<1>>.  I should tell <<2>>.
I should go talk to <<1>>, he's over there.
I should get an <<1>> for <<2>>.  He said it's over there.
I should take the suspicious note I found to King Fahara'jad. He's waiting at his manse in the center of Sentinel.
If I am to aid in exterminating the muckskulker shalk, I'll first need to find their mounds to unearth them.nn<<1>> said they are all around the Hist Tree in the center of Stormhold.
I should return to <<1>> and let him know I've killed many of the shalk infesting the Hist Tree.
The bandit <<1>> could be hiding somewhere in the sewers beneath Wayrest city. If I deliver her head to <<2>>, I'll collect a sizeable reward.
I killed <<1>> in the Wayrest Sewers. I should find <<2>> and collect my reward.
Now that the mercenaries are gone, I should return to <<1>> in front of the Town Hall of southern Stormhold and let her know I was successful.
<<1>> has asked me to get the mercenaries to leave. She said they are along the outskirts of northeastern Stormhold.
I should travel to Tu'whacca's Throne, northeast of Salas En. There, I could speak with a Throne Keeper about shambling skeletons.
I have the <<1>>, I should bring it to <<2>>.
The thief claimed he only stole because someone from the Withered Hand threatened to break his fingers if he didn't. I can free him, or take him to the guards.
I agreed to set the Redguard thief free, on the condition that he does not steal again.
Once a thief, always a thief. I threatened the thief with harm unless he followed me. I should turn him in to one of the city guards in Sentinel.
I should find and speak to <<1>>, an Archein noble, on the lower floor of the Town Hall.
<<1>> wants me to deliver the message to the Archeins. <<2>> said they are waiting in a house on the north side of Stormhold.
I should return to <<1>> and tell him what I've learned. He said I should meet him at <<2>>'s home on the west side of Stormhold.
The thief is fleeing the market. It is up to me to catch him.
I should descend into the sewers and try and find the evidence Chaupelle insists is there.  Waybills, incriminating letters or even stolen goods themselves will help prove his innocence.
I should go to the Marshlight Inn, just east of the Foresters Guild, and deal with the deserters there. <<1>> mentioned, I will have to use force.
<<1>> wants me to deliver news of the returning deserters to <<2>>. nnI should be able to find her in front of the Town Hall on the southern side of Stormhold.
I caught the thief who stole from a Sentinel merchant. He claims he didn't have a choice. He begged me to listen to his story.
<<1>> believes that the recent arrival of the merchant <<2>> was a portent of his village's doom. Perhaps if I can find out the real reason Devad arrived, I can calm <<1>>'s fears.
<<1>> cited three signs as proof that the Gods disapprove of the presence of <<2>> in Burrower's Chasm. Perhaps there are other explanations for these events.

<<1>> admitted he created the "portents." He claims that while he can see the future, the people would not believe him without some sign from the Gods.nnHe believes opening the village to the outside will lead to the enslavement of his people.
I've denounced <<1>> to several of his followers, and they abandoned him, telling me I should speak to <<2>> when I was done.
I've decided that even if <<1>>'s methods are suspect, he's right to want to protect his village from the corruptions of the outside world.nnI should speak to him again before I leave this place.

I've investigated the "signs" mentioned by <<1>> - the fouled water, the failing crops, and the refused shrine offerings. In each case, I found a prosaic explanation. I should return to him to discuss the matter.
I need to destroy the Restless Spirits which haunt Ancestor's Landing, and listen to their memories as they fade away.
I should conclude my conversation with Telenger.
The decision has been made. Artirinwe is dead, consumed by the hostile spirits. I should speak with Telenger to conclude this awful debacle.
I should go to <<1>>'s home in northeastern Stormhold to ask him to come speak with the other Wardens at the Town Hall.
I should bring the news of <<1>>'s fate to <<2>> in front of the Town Hall on the south side of Stormhold.
I should speak to <<1>> at the Mages Guild, just east of the Town Hall.
I should return to <<1>> and inform her about the necromantic scroll describing the ritual.
I should examine the body in <<1>>'s home for any clues and to verify if it is indeed him.
I need to search for <<1>> inside of Sanguine's Demesne.
Return to <<1>> to let him know the <<2>> is dead.
Reports are of many dangerous beasts under Wayrest. I should look there and kill whatever creatures I find.
I've killed many of the creatures threatening to take over the Wayrest sewers. I should return to Constable Lienne and let her know the population's been thinned.
I should search the Argonian homes on the outskirts of northwest Stormhold for evidence of necromancy.
I should speak to the <<1>> here with me.
I wasn't able to find any reasonable evidence. The search seemed futile. I should talk to <<1>> at the Town Hall in southern Stormhold to let her know what <<2>> is doing.
I wasn't able to find any evidence. The search seemed futile. I should talk to <<1>> to let her know what <<2>> is doing.
I've destroyed many spirits and heard the voice of their memories. I should speak with Telenger the Artificer, near the center of Ancestor's Landing, and tell him what I heard.
After I spoke with the guard, a nearby merchant whispered to me, asking him to speak to him.nnI should see what he has to say.
The merchant, Neeneban, gave me a monkey net and offered me a fee to collect monkeys for him, instead of killing them. nnTo capture a monkey, I must use the monkey net near the monkey.
A City Guard told me I'd be doing Sentinel a service by killing the monkeys that plague the city. Monkeys gather on rooftops and in the alleys of the city.
I have captured or killed monkeys across Sentinel. The monkey population has been culled. I should report my success to the city guard at the bazaar.
I should speak to <<1>> at his home in western Stormhold.
I should examine the decayed body and the journal to see if I can discover any clues as to what happened.
I should speak to <<1>>, the Archein noble, to see what he may know about Walks-in-Shade and <<2>>. nnHe is in the bottom floor of the town hall in southern Stormhold.
I should kill the Warden Hjarand imposter here, in the town hall cellar, before he brings any more harm to Stormhold.
I should tell <<1>> what has happened. She is now the only warden left in Stormhold.
Telenger will be waiting for us on the southeast road leading out of Ancestor's Landing.
Restless spirits appear to block our way out of the ruins. I should try to communicate with them, and find out what they want.
The spirits are angered by the presence of Altmer in their home, and demand one of them be sacrificed for the trespass. I must decide how to resolve the situation.
I should seek out <<1>> and tell him, "When it rains, the worm rises."
I should travel to the Shadowscale Enclave, west of Stormhold, and inform a <<1>> of Stormhold's concerns.
I've found some notes that were dropped by some suspicious Argonians. They all seem to be written in the same strange code. I should take them to the Listener and see if he can decipher them.
I've decided that <<1>>'s lies can't be allowed to continue. I should spread the word through the crowd that the signs were a lie.
<<1>>, the closest thing the village has to a leader, might be able to tell me what this package is about. His dwelling is on the western end of the central bridge.
<<1>> believed the crocodile was "<<2>>", a Daedroth. He appears to have more to say on the subject.
<<1>>, the closest thing the village has to a leader, might be able to tell me what this package is about. His dwelling is on the western end of the central bridge.
<<1>> believed the crocodile was "<<2>>", a Daedroth. He appears to have more to say on the subject.
It seems that Evan Chapelle's daughter has become involved with the Pellingare's crimes. I should find her and tell her of her father's imprisonment.
Chaupelle's daughter fears retribution from the bandit leader, Anelle Pellingare. I should kill her to prevent her coming after the Chaupelle family.
I was able to kill the bandit leader, Anelle Pellingare. I should let the Chaupelles know that they are safe from retribution.
I should return to <<1>> in front of the Town Hall, east of the Ward, to let her know what the Shadowscale has told me. He also gave me a totem to give to her that would ensure she believed my words.
Telenger will be waiting for us on the southeast road leading out of Ancestor's Landing.

Once their concerns were alleviated, each captain promised to calm the rioting workers. Captain Pierjean suggested I take the suspicious note to Dock Master Bahir. He's waiting in the Dockhouse, near the entrance to the docks.

I should present the forged documents and fake seal to Captain Maujad, the suspicious note to Captain Pierjean, and the guard uniform to Captain Emadal. They promised to calm the riot once this proof was presented.
The decision has been made. Erramenya is dead, consumed by the hostile spirits. I should speak with Telenger to conclude this awful debacle.
The decision has been made. Cirundelie is dead, consumed by the hostile spirits. I should speak with Telenger to conclude this awful debacle.
I refused to abide by the restless spirits' demands, and they attacked me. Now the assault is over, I should speak with Telenger to conclude this awful debacle.
I promised the monkey that I'd talk to Unishi in Sentinel's tavern and ask her to change him back.
Unishi has agreed to change the monkey back into an Orc, but only after I do her a favor. I must deliver two more potions for her and then return.

Irwad claims Unishi sold him a broken trinket. He'll pay her, but only if I do a favor for him in turn. He's tasked me with recovering some missing silks. The shipment was supposed to arrive by the road northeast of Sentinel. He suspects bandits.
I've recovered Irwad's silks, and they seem to be undamaged. I should return them to him inside Sentinel's inn and collect Unishi's payment.
I've collected Unishi's payment from Irwad. I should take it to her at Sentinel's tavern so she'll lift the curse on Mordrog.
Unishi gave me a potion to reverse the spell and change the monkey back into an Orc. I should take this to the monkey.
King Fahara'jad asked me to help Guard Captain Zafira deal with riots on the docks. I'll find her on Sentinel's docks. They're on the northeast side of the city.
Telenger asked me to meet him at his base camp within the ruins of Salas En, southeast of Ancestor's Landing.
I should find Telenger the Artificer and present him with the scroll I found.
I should ask Telenger what the scroll says.
I should ask Telenger what the scroll says.
I should bring Vivendus' cargo and idol back to him so he can recover from the loss of his riverboat caravan.
I should collect Kilban's cargo that has been scattered across the swamps of Bogmother, and also find the idol the Archein thieves stole from him.
I should try to find someone named Salkat in the Rain Catcher Fields south of Sentinel.
I've found the Archein contact for the necromancers. I should speak to him to find out exactly what he's supplying to the necromancers.
I should search the camps and the necromancers themselves in Bogmother to find any notes they may have. From those I may be able to decipher the parchment I found.
The parchment told of an Archein contact for the necromancers, south of the Bogmother statue. Scar-Eye, as he's called, will be waiting for a passphrase - "Lorkus sees all."

I've freed the captives of the Archeins in Bogmother. They spoke of one of their number who went to find out what the Archeins and the necromancers were doing at the shrine itself. I should find her and see what she's discovered.
The Archeins have captured or killed many pilgrims around Bogmother. I should find and free the ones still alive, and destroy the soul gems of the victims.

I've freed the captives of the Archeins in Bogmother. They spoke of one of their number who went to find out what the Archeins and the necromancers were doing at the shrine itself. I should find her and see what she's discovered.
<<1>> suggested that I could kill the Naga <<2>>, who is in a cave northwest of his location. He didn't seem enthusiastic about my prospects.
The <<1>> has been eliminated. I should return to the Archein camp to inform <<2>>.
Telenger asked me to collect Yokudan artifacts from the ruins of Ancestor's Landing.
I have collected the artifacts as requested. I should take them to Telenger for my reward.
I should return to <<1>> on the main floor of the Town Hall, and tell him about the message.
I should speak to <<1>> if I'd like to help him with his deserters. <<2>> mentioned I can find him by the Foresters Guild on the north side of Stormhold, across the bridge.
Now that I've forced several deserters to return, I should speak to <<1>> back at the Foresters Guild, west of the Marshlight Inn.
<<1>> said I can talk to <<2>> at the Foresters Guild if I feel I need some reinforcements. nnThe Foresters Guild is on the far northern side of Stormhold.
<<1>> wants me to talk to <<2>> at the Foresters Guild, north of the Town Hall, for reinforcements.
I found the key on the corpse of a minion of the Withered Hand. Ishould use it to storm the warehouse and free Dock Master Bahir.
I agreed to rescue Dock Master Bahir. He's being held in the warehouse on the northeastern side of the docks. I should kill Withered Hand minions until I find one who has the key to the warehouse.
It's uncertain whether the mediator is alive or dead. If he's alive, I should speak to him. If he's dead, I should bring back the instructions from his superiors as proof of his death.
The mediator attacked me. I'll have to defend myself.
There must be some clue to what the treacherous "mediator" was doing here. I should search around the area where I fought him - he was staying in one of the nearby tents.

<<1>> and I have now read the full message from the mediator's shadowy superiors. It suggests the more extreme Archeins plan to use the Nagas to kill the more moderate members.nnI should speak to <<1>> again.
I should enter the ruins of Salas En and find a Redguard warrior named Rinlan.
I've collected some curious petrified seeds from Kilban, which he says he obtained from the pillars about Bogmother. Perhaps replacing the seeds will "awaken the swamp," as Neekta said.

I should speak to Kilban Vivendus at the edge of the swamps of Bogmother on behalf of Neekta.nnShe says he may know the whereabouts of the "seeds of Bogmother," which she believes is the key to purging the intruders from her swamps.
I've released some sort of creature by planting the seeds in the shrines. I should find Neekta and let her know what has happened.
I've killed the necromancer dealing with the Archeins in Bogmother. I should let Neekta know the negotiations are over.
<<1>> asked me to speak with the king. He's at his royal manse in Sentinel's Royal District. It's on the city's south side, accessed by stairs or either of two great bridges.
More of the rain catchers have been lit aflame and I have been asked to save them by <<1>>.
<<1>>, one of the water gatherers, asked me to extinguish the fires destroying her rain catchers.  She gave me a bucket and more can be found at the johads.
I put out the fire at the Rain Catcher fields and should return to <<1>> to let her know the threat is dealt with.

A merchant described the thief to me as a young Redguard male in peasant clothes. He may still be somewhere nearby. If I find him and turn him in to the guards, I'll be doing Sentinel "a great service."
I should search for the owner of the dead goat and find out why it died.
I should bring the old hermit a sample of the poison Neyali gave me.
Zal at-Zazir told me to wrap the tongue of a lamia in cactus flowers, then sting it with the stinger of a scorpion. I should collect these reagents and present them to Neyali.
I have the reagents. I should give them to Neyali.
I have the reagents. I should give them to Neyali. Hopefully, I was not too late to save Marimah's life.
I have the reagents. I should give them to Neyali.

I found one page of a longer note containing the mediator's instructions from his superiors. I should look around to see if there are more pages.nnThey might be on the ground, like the first page was, or possibly in the possession of the Nagas.
I should return to <<1>> and give her the reed-parchment pages I've collected.
<<1>> asked me to arrange the parchment on the table near her, so we can both read them.
I should go talk to <<1>> to learn more about the Cult of the Fang. I can find him in the center of the Cult's encampment.
I've convinced several  merchants and prisoners to join the Cult. I should speak with <<1>> back at the Cult of the Fang's Camp.
I've found the provisions requested by <<1>>. I should bring them back to him at the Cult of the Fang encampment.
I've sparred with several Cult members. I should report to <<1>> on the progress of his troops.
I have defeated <<1>> and now lead the Cult of the Fang. I should speak with <<2>>.
I've deciphered the parchment I found. I should read it to discover its full contents.
I should return the cure to Neyali.
I should return the cure to Neyali.
I should return the cure to Neyali.
Uwafa murdered the other Throne Keepers and raised them as undead. Each risen Throne Keeper guards a corrupted shield. I must light the brazier inside each tower again to restore the shields.
I ignited the sacred braziers at the south, east, and north points of the temple. I should meet the Throne Keeper at the West Brazier.
I must throw the wrapped antidote bundles into the johad wells around Morwha's Bounty.
The johad wells have been cleansed of poison. I must tell Shaman  <<1>>. He'll be speaking with Marimah in his tent at Morwha's Bounty.
I should speak with the merchants north of camp as well as the prisoners held within to see if I can convince any of them to join the Cult.
The barrels of pitch should be washed up along the banks of the Oortrel River northeast of Ten-Maur-Wolk.
I've recovered enough pitch to ruin the Nagas' plans. I need to set ablaze the waters of the river fords east of Ten-Maur-Wolk. Pouring the contents of the barrels on a campfire should work.
I've disrupted the Naga attack along the river. I should return to <<1>> at her camp southwest of Ten-Maur-Wolk and tell her the good news.
I should visit the grave of <<1>>.
I should visit the grave of <<1>>.
I have killed the three ancient heroes that had been raised. I should return to Ramati and let him know the deed is done.
While I'm here, it would doubtless aid the defense of Alden Corimont if "helped" a few Nagas to die in the fire.
The goatherd thinks the Elder Throne Keeper at Tu'whacca's Throne may know about this seal. I should speak to the Throne Keeper. He's north of Morwha's Bounty.
I should use the scroll Ramati gave me and summon an Ash'abah healer.
Anzandi told me to ring the herder's bell near a goat to send it running in his direction.
I herded Anzandi's goats safely back into his care. I should speak to him.
I should collect various supplies to help outfit the Cult of the Fang.
I should return to Anzandi and see he makes it safely away from the lamia.
I should train members of the Cult of the Fang.  I can find them scattered around the Cult of the Fang's camp.
I should choose an Ash'abah healer or a warrior to assist me.
I should speak to the <<1>> here with me, and listen to what he has to say.
Three keys open the door to Tu'whacca's Sanctum. Owafa gave them to his followers after locking himself inside. I must kill Owafa's risen dead and recover all three keys.
I've collected three Throne Keeper keys, but I'm not sure how to use them. I should return them to the Elder Throne Keeper.
I must light the final brazier and then Throne Keeper Farvad will open the door into Tu'whacca's Sanctum where he believes I can find Uwafa.
I should wait for Throne Keeper Farvad to open the door into Tu'whacca's Sanctum where he believes I can find Uwafa.
I should enter Tu'whacca's Sanctum, kill Uwafa, and then recover the Ansei Wards.

I've slain Uwafa and recovered one of the Ansei Wards. The spirit of Ansei Radan appeared and thanked me, but reminded me that I need to find the other Wards. I should return to Throne Keeper Farvad outside Tu'whacca's Sanctum.
I should seek out the scholar Zohreh. She may have some ideas about how to find the other Ansei Wards.
There are recent tracks leading away from a corpse, heading to the east. I should follow the tracks to the ruins of Salas En.
I should go to the library in the Mages Guild to retrieve the ancient scroll for <<1>>. nnHe said I must use a portal at the back of the guild hall to reach the library.
Now that I have the ancient scroll, I should bring it to <<1>> on the main floor of the Mages Guild.
Artirinwe asked me to search for a Yoku sword on the beach west of her location. Then I could use the empty Soul Gem to extract spiritual energy from it.
I should return to Artirinwe with the filled Soul Gem.
Now that I've killed several cultists and destroyed the Cult of Sangiin's stolen cargo, I now need to find Dar'Virr, a smuggler captain.
I should kill cultists and destroy any stolen goods I find in Bloodgutter.
I should challenge <<1>> for leadership of the Cult of the Fang. I can find him near the center of the camp.
I should investigate the dying goatherd's claim. Morwha's Bounty is southeast of Sentinel.
I've dealt with the riled up traders. I have been asked to speak to the commander here at Velyn Harbor, <<1>>, who resides in the Military Quarter.
I've been asked to speak to <<1>> in the inn. I should be able to find her in the western part of the city.
I've cleaned up the mess at the bar. I should speak to the next guard, <<1>>, outside the Trade Quarter.
One of the patrons at the bar has been causing issues lately. <<1>> fears that if the Dominion disciplines him, it would put the citizens more on edge. I've been asked to take care of it instead.
I've dealt with the traders. I should return and speak to Captain Ahmuzi.
I've been asked to calm down the riled up merchants.nnI could try talking to them, but if that doesn't work, I should look around for some other means of quieting them down some.

I found a missive containing a request for the mercenaries to speak to <<1>> of Stillrise Village.nnIf I'm curious, I should locate the western mercenary camp. Once found, the missive says Stillrise lies just south of it.
I should find and talk to the mercenary leader. <<1>> said his camp is north of Stillrise.
<<1>> refused the truce. I should kill some of his men as <<2>> requested to seek revenge for the skeletons already fallen.
Now that I've killed many of the mercenaries, I should talk to <<1>> in Stillrise, south of the mercenary camp.
I should speak to <<1>> back at the huts in Stillrise and let him know that <<2>> is dead.
I should find <<1>> near the huts and ask him about his plan.
I should find the hive that <<1>> spoke of, above the waterfall to the north and hurl it into the mercenary camp. nnHe said I can use the path behind him to get there.
I should go into the swamp, east of Stillrise, and look for any remains I can find. <<1>> said I can find them lying around the swamp or kill the empty souls to obtain them.
I collected many remains and should find <<1>> in the Stillrise graveyard, south of the swamp and west of the main town, to give them to him.
I should look for the quatermaster at the Cult of the Fang to see if he is open to doing new business.
Telenger asked me to deliver a Soul Gem to each of his three assistants in Ancestor's Landing. He requested that I kill any hostile spirits I encounter along the way.
I should return to Telenger at the center of Ancestor's Landing.
Pilgrim Neekta believes Scar-Eye is here to meet the leader of the necromancers at Bogmother. I should confront him and his necromancer contact.
I must find Kalas at Morwha's Bounty, south of Rain Catcher Fields, and warn him that the Ansei Wards have been stolen. Uwafa and the Withered Hand may seek revenge against the Ash'abah.
Erramenya asked me to find a Yoku artifact along the rise west of her location. I can use an empty Soul Gem to extract spiritual energy from it.
I should return to Erramenya with the filled Soul Gem.
Cirundelie told me to search for a Yoku artifact among the rubble west of her location. I can use the empty Soul Gem to extract spiritual energy from objects I find.
I should return to Cirundelie with the filled Soul Gem.
I can use an empty Soul Gem to trap the Yoku spirit holding Telenger captive.
I have two Soul Gems left. I'll have to choose which of Telenger's assistants to free and which one I'll leave behind.
I've used the Soul Gems. All are free, save Artirinwe. We can escape the ruins by following the southeast road.
We've escaped Ancestor's Landing and the hostile spirits within it. I should speak to Telenger now.
Each assistant is held fast by a single ghostly captor. To free an assistant, I must use a Soul Gem on a spirit.
I've used the Soul Gems. All are free, save Erramenya. We can escape the ruins by following the southeast road.
We've escaped Ancestor's Landing and the hostile spirits within it. I should speak to Telenger now.
I've used the Soul Gems. All are free, save Cirundelie. We can escape the ruins by following the southeast road.
We've escaped Ancestor's Landing and the hostile spirits within it. I should speak to Telenger now.
The last captive told me his friend Minglos is near the Blood Cat leader's house. I should try to help him.
I should free any captives I find in Bloodgutter.

One of the farmers around Leafshadow Lake has asked me to retrieve a shipment of fish and fungus for the denizens of Malabal Tor.nnThe food can be found in sacks along the tree-paths, and on orcs that may have already started stealing it.
I've collected enough food for a shipment to be run to Silvenar and should take it to the Jaqspur runner to the southeast, along the lake's edge.
I have been asked to hunt down wood orcs in the trees above Leafshadow Lake as repayment for their murder of Bosmer at Leafshadow Lake.
I have slain a large number of wood orcs and should speak to <<1>> at the southeastern edge of Leafshadow Lake.
If I light the lamps, it should dissuade further orcs from attacking and assist the soldiers in seeing incoming enemies.
I've lit most of the lamps at the Leafshadow farms. One more should provide enough light for any defenders below to be able to see their opponents.
I have been asked to free the trapped farmers in the tree farms at Leafshadow Lake.
I have freed several Leafshadow farmers and was directed to a Dominion scout who was captured and may need aid.
I've been instructed to speak to the guard captain of Alten Corimont in order to enter the town and remain on the good side of the guards.
I've found the safehouse and was greeted by a gruff Nord. I should let him know Lei-Kai sent me.

The captain of the guards wanted to throw me into irons, but an Argonian named Lei-Kai intervened on my behalf.nnHe's put up a ruse that I am his slave. I should play along until I know what's going on.
Lei-Kai rescued me from an overzealous guard captain, and has asked that I meet him at a safehouse southeast of the guardhouse.
Now that I've killed Inerri, I should return to Minglos in the house next to the manor house and give him the news.
I should head to the manor house in Bloodgutter and kill Inerri. Minglos warned me that she is a tough combatant and I should be ready for her.
I've freed the slaves before the slavers had a chance to regroup. I also discovered Riane had freed herself. She asked me to tell Scale-Shorn she will not be returning because of his betrayal.
The porter Scale-Shorn has asked me to rescue the slaves from the wreckage of the slaver ships, as well as someone named Riane. The ships should be just outside Alten Corimont's harbor.
I've told Shade-Tail the news of her brother. She was understandably upset, and vowed revenge.nnI should let Keira know what has happened.
I should find the Archein gaoler Keira mentioned, and get information about Teeus' location and condition.
The gaoler informed me Teeus is being held near the eastern entrance of town. From the sound of it, they have already begun interrogating him. I should find him quickly.
I found Teeus, but his wounds were too great for him to move. I was ambushed by the interrogator, but managed to slay him. I should tell Shade-Tail of her brother's fate.
I should return J'Derr to Captain Dar'Virr onboard his ship.
I should look for J'Derr, Captain Dar'Virr's raven, onboard the ship at the other end of Bloodgutter.
I should look for Uurwen in the village of Gallowroot.
I agreed to kill some spiders. Kasal can't pay me much, but promised I could keep any dwemer gold I found.
I killed many spiders and freed <<1>> from Naluroen's lair; she agreed to return to <<2>>.nnI should return to him outside of the Kulati Mines, and let him know.
I should enter the ruins of Ancestor's Landing, southwest of Sentinel. Then I can speak to one of the High Elves there.
It was suggested I find some kind of treats for the raven to stop it from making a racket. Maybe check the galley of the cultists' ship?
Now that I have some treats, the raven shouldn't raise an alarm.
I must go to Murkvale and discover why the scouts have not returned.
Now that I've unleashed the hive, I can join the fight.nnI should find <<1>> down in the Mirewalk Camp and kill him.
I should speak to Ma'Zarman and see if I can get any more information.
I should head to the slums on the east side and look for anyone who seems suspicious in the area. Perhaps I can investigate and find out what's been going on with the missing people.

I've managed to find out that the villagers have been kidnapped in the night and dragged to the town to the east, Bloodgutter. I should let one of the Dominion soldiers know about this as soon as possible.
I must travel to Bloodgutter and find someone who knows about the local events.
I should find Foreman Shagora. She should still be inside Kulati Mines.
I should travel to the mines and speak to the owner, a man named Kasal.
Prince Azah and his soldiers are barricade in the eastern warehouse. Talia suggested that he might know more about what the Withered Hand is planning.
The necromancer Alesan is performing a ritual to destroy an ancient Ansei weapon, inside a warehouse by the docks of Tava's Blessing. I need to get inside and put an end to him.

By reforging the blade of the Ansei Ward, I restored Ansei Maja's power and he was able to defeat the dark spirit Alasan had become. I have given the restored Ansei Ward to Prince Azah for safekeeping. I should speak with the Prince once again.
I've found some biscuits that should make J'Derr more relaxed.
I've freed the slaves before the slavers had a chance to regroup. I also discovered Riane had freed herself. She asked me to tell Scale-Shorn she will not be returning because of his betrayal.
<<1>> is free and racing for the gate. I should speak to her outside Naluroen's nest.
Now I can enter Naluroen's nest. I should go inside and find <<1>>.
I've entered Naluroen's nest. I should find and speak to <<1>>.
I should see about collecting a few of these amulets the bandits have.
Now that I have some amulets, I should see if they have any effect on the villagers. Some may be too far gone to be helped.
I was able to rescue some villagers with the amulets I acquired from the bandits. I should return to Soradenor.
I've destroyed the bodies the Worm Cult necromancers were using in Alten Corimont. I should return to the safehouse and tell Shade-Tail of my success.
I should search for Shade-Tail at the sacred hall at the south end of Alten Corimont. Lei-Kai has asked me to be discreet, for the Worm Cult necromancers would not take kindly to snooping.

Shade-Tail has killed one of the main necromancers in the sacred hall, and discovered a veritable undead army of bodies. They are protected by some foul magic, however.nnI must figure out how to disrupt it so the bodies can be destroyed.
I've destroyed the ritual that protected the bodies of the necromancers. I should enter the sacred hall and destroy the bodies before the necromancers have a chance to enact their plan.
I've discovered that Hjarl was the one who betrayed Lei-Kai and his men. I should tell Shade-Tail the news.

The Shadowscale Shade-Tail returned to a ransacked house. It seems the Archeins discovered their safehouse and took the rest prisoner.nnLei-Kai is being held at the docks. I should speak to him to find out what happened.

Lei-Kai tells me he's heard of a meeting between the one who betrayed them and the Wharfmaster of Alten Corimont.nnI should lie in wait for them inside the manse and discover who betrayed the insurgents.
Alesan is defeated. I should recover the Seal of Tu'whacca now.
I shattered the Ward and disrupted Alasan's ritual. Ansei Maja has appeared. I should speak with her.
Kee-Scale's master has agreed to let him go free, despite asking me to do his task for him. I should let Kee-Scale know he is a free Argonian.

I should search the houses in Alten Corimont for any merchant manifests.nnKee-Scale's master is interested in their contents, and if I collect enough, it may win Kee-Scale's freedom. The merchants may not take kindly to this, though.
I've gathered the competing merchants' ledgers for Kee-Scale. I should present them to his master, and make sure he does not go back on his word.
I've mixed the venom in the amphora and tasted its contents. A strange vision spoke to me, a vision of a coiled snake rising from the fumes. Perhaps I can... speak back to it.
If I wish to attend elder Brinereed's funeral, I should gather the dreameater asp venom as Mire-Chant requested.nnThey wander the grounds of Alten Corimont, and are held sacred to the Argonians here.
I've managed to steal some bottles of medicine.nnHopefully this should be enough to cure the Altmer's sick son. I should return to her back in the slums district.
I'll need to find a way to get my hands on the medicine.nnI can either talk to the captain of the guard or ignore my honor and attempt to steal from the supplies in the military quarter.

The commander informed me that I might be able to speak to the Khajiit in the inn to see about what type of healing elixirs he carries upon him.nnOf course, I still have the option of stealing from the supply myself.
I did a favor for the Khajiit in the inn and was able to get my hands on some healing medicines from his land.nnI need to return to the slums and see if this works on the Altmer woman's son.
I found Telenval and Fodoril slain in the village, rescued Cerelas, and was forced to kill Glorwen. I should return to Venosir and tell him what happened.
I need to track down Venosir's missing family members. The father is named Telenval, the brother is Fodoril, the wife is Cerelas, and the mother is Glorwen.
I should escort <<1>> to Soradenor's home and find his cousin.
The hostage is safely back at Soradenor's home. I should talk with the worried villager.
I should talk to the hostage I set free.
I should untie the bosmer hostage.
Kasal mentioned if I found Foreman Shagora I should tell her to report to Kasal.
I must travel to the Ayleid ruins east of Murkvale and find the source of the stone amulets the bandits were using.
I agreed to kill some spiders. Kasal can't pay me much, but promised I could keep any dwemer gold I found.
I should find Dronoril, the trapper at Gallowroot.
<<1>> has fled the building on the eastern side of town where I first met Hadima. I should look the spirit there.
<<1>> is on the move, fleeing towards the blacksmith's forge.
<<1>> continues to elude us, hiding in yet another building in the southwest corner of town. <<2>> has a plan to trap him this time.
I should speak with the Ansei spirit.
To free <<1>>, I must gain access to Naluroen's nest. I may be forced to make a bargain with the Daedra.
I decided to feed a blind elder spider so I could gain entrance into the nest. <<1>> told me to enter the pool at the far end of the mine, touch the spider, and let it "feed."
I decided to escort one of the miners to <<1>> so I can gain entrance into her nest. She said they fascinate her, and she wants to speak with one.
I've agreed to work with <<1>> to forge a new Redguard blade. He will temper the steel while I operate his furnace.nnI must tell him when I'm ready to begin.

I've agreed to operate Nabeenam's furnace while he tempers the steel. It is cooled by three vents: left, center, and right, marked by where <<1>> is standing.nnI must use each vent as <<1>> calls them out to keep the furnace at an ideal temperature.
I have worked Nabeenam's furnace and help him forge a new blade. I should speak to him to find out how the blade turned out.
Agreeing with my choice, Tiela has asked me to speak with Casnar and make her choice known.
<<1>> has managed to trap <<2>>. I must now make the thing speak to us and reveal the necromancer's plans.
I should look around town and see who would be willing to have a drink with Larland.
I've managed to find the rock after some ruffians decided to try and ambush me. I should return to the inn and see how the drinks are going.
I've investigated the shipments to realize they were already stolen. I should return to the inn and see how the drinks are going.
I've managed to find the cat after some ruffians decided to try and ambush me. I should return to the inn and see how the drinks are going.
I need to travel to Lainlyn and search for the necromancer Shiri there. I will probably have to ask people around town to learn of her whereabouts.
I should seek out Priestess Sermenh once I reach HoonDing's Watch.
Now that we've stopped the werewolves, I should let Seligorn know that we've held our ground.
I should speak to one of the scouts and offer to help defend the townsfolk.
Help the scout ward off the werewolves.
The survivor's friends will be undead monsters now, wandering somewhere within Tava's Blessing. I need to find them, put them down, then take their favorite possession from them.
I should return to the survivor now and hand over the items he asked for.
Now that I've saved them, I should talk to the worried peasant.
I should find the trapped peasants in Gallowroot.
I should blow the horn when it's clear for the villagers to jump down and then escort them out of Gallowroot.
I'll need to collect mudcrab meat from the beach to the west of us in order to start this dish that Andri wishes to make.
I'll need to listen to Andri's orders as she calls them out in order to make this "Mud Crab Delight" just right.
I've been given some deliveries to get out to the soldiers. I have a small amount of time but I'll need to make stops at the port, the slums, and the military quarter before the food gets cold!

Outfitter Wickton wants me to prove that I can skin woodland wolves and then cure their hides to make a piece of cured thin leather. I need to first go outside of the gates and hunt woodland wolves.
The pirates also stole special oil from the lighthouse. It's needed for the signal fire. I'll check the pirate ship to see if they've hidden it there.
I should check the cave for other strange crystals and destroy them.

Farmer Vanne said that in his enchanted dreams, the spirit of his father visited him. He thinks his father's spirit is nearby, and he says his father can help me rescue Rozenn.

I must travel to Alcaire Castle and warn Duke Nathaniel.
I should go to the Koeglin lighthouse to find the lighthouse keeper. Once I find him, I can see if he'll send word back to the village to clear <<1>>'s name.

King Aphren repaired the sword. He wants me to give it to Princess Mira to make amends. Her crypt is down the corridor from his. Of course, the mage, Blaise Pamarc, also expects me to bring the sword to him. Apparently, the choice is mine.
I need to gather all the cursed skulls I can find.

To defuse the situation at the castle gates, I'll need to speak with Sir Hughes, the head of the Knights of the Flame.

I need to collect the various remains of Gathan's body from the mine cavern where he died.

I should find <<1>> at her home, south of the Smiths' Hall.
I should speak with Belene or <<1>> to see if they can give me any information on the whereabouts of <<2>>. nn<<3>> said their house is just across from hers, on the east side of Koeglin Village.

I found and freed <<1>>, but before he left, he warned me of the slaver's plans to attack Koeglin Village. I need to steal the plans from the lieutenant's tent. That will delay the attack and prove to the villagers that the slaver threat is real.
