Bloodthorn Lord Velian has attacked the Red Rook safe house and is protected by a powerful shield, fueled by the ward that originally protected the house.nnI should disrupt the ward so that I can stop Lord Velian.

Shaman <<1>> gave me several antidote bundles. They must be wrapped in zehtgrass, which can be found by the scorpion dens near Morwha's Bounty. I must throw these wrapped bundles into each johad well.
General Llethise has ordered me to go into Cyrodiil or the Battle Grounds and kill thirty members of the Aldmeri Dominion.
I have slain thirty members of the Aldmeri Dominion. I should speak to General Llethise at Colovian Gates.
I decided to spare the Duke. Gloria has taken him prisoner. I should speak with her about my decision.

I should find the hut north of the Wyrd Tree and destroy the corruption totem inside of it. While I'm destroying the totem I should kill bloodthorn cultists and search for the <<1>> that <<2>> told me about.
General Llethise has ordered me to go into Cyrodiil or the Battle grounds and kill fifty Daggerfall Covenant guards.
I have slain fifty Daggerfall Covenant guards. I should inform General Llethise at Nibenay Gate.
General Llethise ordered me to enter Cyrodiil or a Battleground and kill fifty enemy guards.
I have slain fifty enemy guards. I should speak to General Llethise at Nibenay Gate.
General Llethise ordered me to enter Cyrodiil or a Battle ground and kill fifty Aldmeri guards.
I have slain fifty Aldmeri guards. I should speak to General Llethise at Nibenay Gate.
Now that I know she's behind the disappearances, I should confront <<1>> in the back room of the dungeon beneath her house.

I've discovered a number of dead bodies in a dungeon below Captain Munada's home. They must be the people who disappeared from Bergama. Munada murdered them all. I should continue exploring the dungeon for signs of Captain Munada.
I need to escort the Camlorn Volunteer to the three towers. Each time we reach a tower, I need to protect the volunteer while she lights the signal fire.
The signal fires are lit and the gates are open. Now I need to confront Faolchu and finally destroy him. He has taken over a holding in the northern part of the city.
Faolchu is dead. I should tell General Gautier that Camlorn's nightmare is over.
I should speak with Gabrielle Benele and see what she has to say.
I must find the Midnight Talisman, which Gabrielle believes might be in or around the town of Crosswych. The talisman is necessary to get to Angof.
<<1>>, the Moth Priestess from <<2>>, is inside the <<3>> Inn. I should find out what's brought her here.
I was unable to collect the reagents in time. I should still return to Zal at-Zazir in Marimah's tent.
I have the reagents required to make the poison antidote. I must return to Shaman <<1>> at Morwha's Bounty. He's tending to Marimah in the leader's tent.

Gabrielle Benele believes we must get our hands on a Daedric relic known as the Midnight Talisman. That should help us get to Angof. She believes it was taken to Crosswych. I must acquire the talisman before returning to the Lion Guard redoubt.
I've acquired the Midnight Talisman. I must return to Gabrielle Benele in the redoubt and show it to her.
Gabrielle Benele has asked me to meet her at a tower at the base of the western cliffs, below Merovec's Folly.
Gabrielle wants to use the ancient Wyrd site on the beach near here to perform the ritual of recharging. I'll meet her there.

The talisman has been recharged, but it isn't safe to use. It's been corrupted by some sort of Daedric entity. I need to take the talisman to the Wyrd circle, where I can purge the Daedric corruption.
Gabrielle followed me to the Wyrd circle. Now that the talisman has been purged, I should speak with her.
I should speak with Gabrielle Benele back at the Lion Guard redoubt.
A spriggan spirit appeared where the lurcher died. Its spirit was released when it entered the ritual circle.
I've discovered a hidden cave beneath the <<1>> Inn. The sounds and smells I noticed outside the trapdoor are much stronger down here. I should continue exploring the cave and see what I can find.
I have fought my way through a secret lair of the Worm Cult. In the darkest depths of this bastion of evil I've encountered a powerful demi-lich, a terrible creature which must be destroyed.
I've entered the queen's chambers, acting against the recommendation of <<1>>. However, the peasant who first told me of the captain's corruption insisted the queen would want to know.

The queen's handmaiden asked me to conduct discreet inquiries to assess the city's defenses. I agreed to speak with the former guard captain, examine the defenses at the east gate and to find out why a Redguard refugee was put in the stocks.
The guard captain was not receptive to my questions. He ordered one of his thugs to attack me. Perhaps a sound beating will convince Gharzu I mean business.
The discharged guards agree: the guard captain is corrupt. I learned he frequents an inn. I should look for him there and hear what he has to say.

The regent's response to <<1>> seemed less than sincere. He didn't wish to bring the matter to the queen's attention. Perhaps there is more to this issue than I first thought. I should find the queen in the castle and inform her myself.

I've defeated one of the guard captain's thugs. Perhaps now he will take me seriously. I should confront the knight regent about <<1>> and see that he answers for his crimes. The regent is in Evermore's castle.
I've brought Gharzu to the knight regent, <<1>>, so he can answer accusations of extorting Evermore's people.
I've entered the queen's chambers, acting against the recommendation of <<1>>. However, the peasant who first told me of the captain's corruption insisted the queen would want to know.
A Beldama initiate asked me to find <<1>> and help her search for the elemental guardians.
Something must have gone wrong with the ritual. I should speak with Gabrielle.
<<1>> needs to understand the danger she's in.
The queen asked me to find Glarikha and Sir Jarnot and then to ferret out the Imperial spies in the city without causing a panic.

It seems the crows in the city are representatives of Uela, the leader of the invading Reachmen army. Uela wants to stop the Imperials as badly as I do, so we struck a bargain. I will find and mark the Imperial spies. Her crows will attack them.
With the help of Uela's crows, the Imperial spies have been dealt with. I should now investigate the weapons stash in the south alley that I heard Captain Hjurrun talking about.
<<1>> attacked me while I was in the South Ward. By his exclamations and the note on his body, it seems <<2>> is behind the rumors against <<3>>. I should return to the castle and confront him.
With the help of Uela's crows, the Imperial spies have been dealt with. I must deal with Captain Hjurrun and then I should meet the queen back in the castle to help her confont Duke Renchant.
The Mages Guild Researcher agrees with me that the sword may open a doorway into the past. He can help me follow whatever ripples it creates to the portal itself.
I've managed to lose my researcher. I should head back to the camp and speak to Husayn to see if someone else will join me.
With <<1>> dead, <<2>> will be able to plan for Evermore's future.

I believe <<1>> may be acting against the interests of <<2>>, but I need proof. The queen gave me the key to where he's staying, so I can find such proof. I should go to his room on the castle's lowest floor to discover if my suspicions are correct.
Now that I have access to <<G:1>> quarters, I should search for evidence of his involvement with the Imperials in Evermore.
I've found some suspicious items in <<G:1>> quarters. I should bring them to <<2>> and see what she makes of them.
I've confronted <<1>> at the inn, and he doesn't deny working against <<2>>. If I don't stop him, there's no telling what damage he would be able to do to <<2>> with the knowledge he's gained here.
<<1>> is staying in Evermore's Central Ward at the inn. <<2>> asked me to make him answer for his schemes against <<3>>. She wants to be rid of him once and for all.
<<1>> is dead, and his plans to ruin <<2>> from the inside have failed. I should return to <<3>> and let her know.

It appears the Direnni captured a messenger, but not before he passed on orders to one of the Alessian soldiers. I need to search the soldiers and their camp to find the orders so that the Direnni aren't surprised before they attack Faolchu.
I should head to the town square and speak with <<1>> about her missing groom, <<2>>.
I should go to <<1>> and speak with <<2>> about the werewolves in <<3>>.
I should collect zombie hearts and spirit essence, so I can take them to <<1>> at the dais in <<2>>.
I should take the zombie hearts and spirit essence to <<1>> on the dais within <<2>>.
<<1>> has asked me to start the ritual to infuse the Prince's body with the needed power. I should use the <<z:2>> near the body to do so.
Upon completion of the ritual, Prince Adrien's body became a bone collosus! I need to speak with <<1>> and make him explain himself.
I need to collect the essence of the restless spirits within <<1>>.
Now that I've collected the <<z:1>>, should infuse it with the <<2>>.
I can now use the <<1>> to summon three powerful spirits. I should look for the more elaborate graves in <<2>>. The <<1>> will capture the spirits' souls as they're defeated.
I protected <<1>> while he merged with his new body. I should speak with him.
I need to find Bernard Redain near Deleyn's Mill. He should be able to tell me more about what's going on there.
I have defeated the Withered Hand still in the vault, but it seems others escaped with the Ansei Wards. I should leave the vault and inform the king.
I've found Ishan's body. <<1>> transformed into a Reach mage right before me. He was not who <<2>> thought he was.nnI should return to <<3>> and let her know Ishan's body is safe.
I should discreetly question the mourners at Ishan's funeral to see if I can figure out what happened to his body in transit.
From speaking to the mourners at Ishan's funeral, it seems the best palce to look would be the graveyard itself.nnI should speak to the gravedigger and see if he knows the whereabouts of Ishan.
The gravedigger seems to think Ishan's body is at the gravesite. I should go there and check, just in case.
I found a strange signet ring in Ishan's empty coffin. Before I searched the coffin, I was attacked by some kind of undead creature in the graveyard.nnI should tell <<1>> about these events.
I've been allowed entrance into the sanctum of <<1>>, the mage who owns the signet ring found in the graveyard. I need to search the area for any evidence of Ishan's body  and possibly necromancy.
<<1>> told me the signet ring belongs to someone within the Mages Guild.nnI should go to the Mages Guild in Evermore and see if I can find the owner.
I've found Ishan's body in the sanctum of <<1>>. No doubt my presence here has been noticed by the mage. I should make sure he can't do any more harm to Ishan.
<<1>> transformed into a Reach mage right before me. He was not who <<2>> thought he was. I should search the area for signs of Ishan.
Casnar said I should purchase a ticket to the gray market. If I don't, the guards will attack me.
Now that I have a ticket, I'm free to enter the gray market.
Lady Laurent entered the tomb but has not returned. Her servant, Stibbons, has asked me to find her within.

Lady Laurent told me about the Jeweled Crown of Anton, a relic she wants to retrieve from the tomb. To get the crown, I need four keys that unlock the vault. She provided one key. I can find the others somewhere in the tomb.
I recovered the keys to the vault. I should place them in their correct sconces. Then the vault should open.
I may be able to ask Lady Laurent's hired help about the situation in the Tomb of Lost Kings.
I placed the keys. Something seems to be happening. I should watch and see what happens.
I can enter the vault now. Lady Laurent wants me to retrieve the Jeweled Crown of Anton, but the Seneschal wants me to take the cursed crown instead.
I entered the vault. I need to defeat the vault's guardian before I decide which crown to take.
I retrieved the Jeweled Crown of Anton. Now I need to find my way out of the Tomb of Lost Kings.
I escaped the Tomb of Lost Kings with the Jeweled Crown of Anton. I should give it to Lady Laurent at her camp.
Now that I've intimidated him, I should speak to <<1>> again. I suspect he'll be more willing to listen now.

A Bloodthorn cultist attacked me and chased Glutton away. The cultist seemed angry that I was near the strange vine. I should check with Swineherd Wickton and make sure that Glutton returned to his pen.
The <<1>> Audry gave me can also be used on myself. It will briefly cause bloodfiends to ignore me.
The Forgotten Seneschal is eternally bound to the Tomb of Lost Kings. He offered to help me if I agree to help him. In the meantime, I should speak with Lady Laurent, who's deeper inside the tomb.
<<1>> has asked me to collect three powerful souls. He said I should speak to <<2>> to learn how.
I need to find the construction details held by the shipwrights, blacksmiths, and dockmasters.
Heloise has led me to the Hinault Farmhouse. She wants me to knock on the door and see if the family is inside.

The Hinaults refuse to leave the safety of their farmhouse without any weapons to defend themselves with. Gennove Hinault gave me a list of specific weapons he wants me to gather. Heloise suggested I can find the weapons in the barn.
I collected all the weapons <<1>> asked for. I should return to the farmhouse so I can give them to him.
I returned to the Hinault farmhouse to find the door unlocked and ajar. Heloise was already inside, examining the corpse of <<1>>. The rest of the family is nowhere to be seen.
I confronted <<1>> with little success. <<2>> should be waiting for me in the queen's chambers by now. I should tell the queen of our suspicions.
The queen's handmaiden, <<1>>, has gone missing after leaving to investigate a shipment from Wayrest at the docks. I should speak to the harbormaster and see if I can find out what happened to her.
The harbormaster said <<1>> went to the <<2>> to see if the ship carried any supplies from Wayrest. I should look for her there. The ship is anchored at the end of the docks.
The <<1>> has crates full of Imperial gold as its cargo. I should go to the dock just outside of the <<1>> and tell <<2>> what I've found out.

Who the Imperial gold was intended for is still a mystery, but <<1>> has a lead. The thugs were supposed to meet someone behind the inn for their payment. I should go there and see if I can catch them in the act.

An Imperial emissary named <<1>> was the conspirator I saw at the meeting place behind the inn. I wasn't able to catch the conversation between him and the <<2>> sailor. I should confront him at the castle and see what he has to say about this.
I should look for the king in his palace.
I should consecrate the four vaulted tombs around <<1>> by scattering <<z:2>> within them.
I should speak with <<1>> and let him that I've consecrated the bodies in each tomb. Perhaps he can explain what I saw.
I should search some of the coffins in the cemetery. Perhaps I can find things to help the some of the followers of Kynareth to move on.
I have found several items inside some of the coffins in the cemetery. I should speak with some of the spirits and see if it helps them move on. I just have to figure out which item belongs to who.
I should speak with the High Priest, <<1>>. If he moves on, the rest of the followers are likely to do so as well.
I should discreetly question the mourners at Ishan's funeral to see if I can figure out what happened to his body in transit.
I've spoken to a debtor of Ishan's who mentioned paying for Ishan's coffin. The debtor sent Ishan to be measured for it. I should discreetly question the other mourners at Ishan's funeral.
I've spoken to Ishan's friend, who mentioned Ishan wianted to be buried in his family's plot in <<1>> instead of <<2>>. I should discreetly question the other mourners at Ishan's funeral.
I've spoken to Ishan's father, who mentioned his son wanted to be buried in his regiment's armor. I should discreetly question the other mourners at Ishan's funeral.

I've spoken to a debtor of Ishan's who mentioned he was paying for Ishan funeral. Ishan's father also said his son wanted to be buried in his armor. I should discreetly question the other mourner at Ishan's funeral.

I've spoken to a debtor of Ishan's, who mentioned he was paying for his funeral. Ishan's friend also said he wished to be buried in his family plot, in Evermore. I should discreetly question the other mourner here.

I've spoken to both Ishan's father and friend. They mentioned he wanted to be buried in his regiment's armor in his family's plot in Evermore. I should discreetly question the last mourner at Ishan's funeral.
I need to choose whether to continue raising <<1>> as a revenant or accept <<2>>'s offer.
I need to bind <<1>> to her necklace.
I should continue the ritual to bind <<1>>'s soul to his new body.
I should use <<1>> to summon the spirit of <<2>>
Heloise asked me to accompany her to check on the Hinault family. She wants me to wait for her outside while she finishes tending to the wounded soldiers.
Now that I have the <<1>>, I should bring it to <<2>>. She's at an altar within a ruined building near the center of <<3>>.
According to <<1>>, my help is needed to break the curse. She asked me to get the <<2>> from the north tower.
By channelling the sacrifice of <<1>>, the curse of <<2>> will eventually fade away.
Sinia gave me the <<1>> to show to <<G:2>> spirit. Caius can explain how to use it to break the curse. If Caius isn't following me, I should seek him beside his gravestone.
I must use the <<1>> to recover lost artifacts. They will show me visions of the past. They're part of the ritual to dispel the curse.
I have found the inner sanctum. Now I must free Padesh from his madness. According to the mage, guilt drove Padesh's spirit insane. I'll have to defeat him to clear his mind.
The madness afflicting <<1>> has passed. He said he needed to pray. Padesh may be at the altar where I spoke with Sinia earlier. I should talk to him.
By channelling the sacrifice of <<1>>, the curse of <<2>> will eventually fade away.
Sinia offered to sacrifice herself to remove the curse at Arlimahera's Grip. I need to destroy the <<1>> to complete the ritual.
I shattered the Ward and disrupted Alasan's ritual. I am not sure what happened to Alasan, but I worry about the consequences of shattering the Ward. I should gather the pieces.
The ghost asked me to grant a few moments of peace to the other Ra Gada sergeants. Each time I kill one, that allows the ghost a brief respite from the pain of existence.
I should find <<1>> at the chapel. I'll let him know I've given the Ra Gada sergeants a few moments of peace.
I have defeated Mannimarco's minions within the secret Worm Cult lair. I should escape this foul place now.
I left the hidden cave before exploring it fully. I should return there and resume my mission.

The Hinault family is barricaded inside their farmhouse. They refuse to open the door until I bring them weapons they can use to defend themselves. Heloise seems to have an idea. I should talk to her.
I should see if I can find <<1>> and deliver the letter to him.
I should search the mountains and rescue the harpy captives.
Now that the captive citizens are on their way back to Daggerfall, I should find <<1>>. She'll want to know of my success.
I should speak to <<1>> in Sentinel, north of the Rain Catcher Fields.
I spoke to the four legendary spirits of HoonDing's Watch. I should return to Farvad atop the monument.
I must speak to the four legendary spirits of HoonDing's Watch and answer their questions.
<<1>> said that either Sinia or Padesh must make a selfless sacrifice to break the curse. I must choose which one to proceed with the ritual.

I should find and deactivate the shrines near Sep's Spine. <<1>> told me that will stop the Withered Hand from creating more magical amulets and reduce their power over the undead. I must also obtain an intact amulet from a minion of the Hand.
There's a side gate in the western wall. That's my way into the city.

Bloodthorn cultists have commandeered the Wyrd portal stones. I need to reclaim the portal caves and open portals under the four huts around the Wyrd Tree. Then the Wyrd Sisters can travel through the portals and arrive without being seen.
I opened the portals for the Wyrd Sisters. They're performing their purification rituals around the Wyrd Tree. Now I need to open a portal for <<1>> at the tree's entrance.
I opened a portal for Wyress Gwen. I should ask her what else she needs me to do to help save the Wyrd Tree.

Darien wants to move the hidden civilians to a more defensible position: the Camlorn Inn. But the inn is locked tight. I need to find the dead innkeeper somewhere near the cathedral and recover his key.
I have the necessary ingredients for the lycanthropy cure. Now I just need to find Alinon the Alchemist.
Now that we're in the inn, I should talk to Alinon and see how the cure is coming along.
I should escort the Ash'abah warrior to the deep tombs of Tu'whacca's Throne.

Before I can consecrate the vaulted tombs, I need to gather <<z:1>> to spread within them.
Heloise asked me to tell <<1>> that she's running away. She's going to a place where she can't hurt anyone before her unnatural hunger drives her mad.
I've obtained the snake intestines. Now I must collect the fetish from a Baandari trader northeast of Lainlyn.
<<1>> asked me to meet him in the inner sanctum.
<<1>> asked me to speak to <<2>>. I need to find the whereabouts of a contact of hers named <<3>>.
The wanderer asked me to once again use a chime to attract goats. I should lead those goats to the serpents of the oasis  again.
Several of the serpents in the oasis fed after I brough goats to them. I should return the chimes to <<1>> and tell him what I've done.

The talks between the Saltwalker Company and the Withered Hand ended with the death of the necromancers' envoy, <<1>>. He was slain by a furious <<2>> for his treachery.  nnI should report the end of negotiations to <<3>> in Lainlyn.
I should ask <<1>> what's happened to <<2>>.
A peasant said one of the Wyrd "witches" is still in Evermore. She's near the Mages Guild. I should talk to her and see if the rumors of the princess' survival are true.
I should speak to <<1>> at the Fighters Guild in Lainlyn.
I should find <<1>> in the <<2>> and ask her if <<3>> of Evermore is still alive. I can request <<4>> to summon me a guide.
<<1>> and I killed the necromancer <<2>>. The chief of the Saltwalkers is furious, and has ordered her soldiers to kill us on sight. nnI should report the end of negotiations to <<3>> in Lainlyn.
<<1>> appeared when I took the amulet from her coffin. I should speak with her and find out why she's here.
Tasan wants me to find a disguise and infiltrate the Shining Scarabs' organization in order to find evidence of a traitor.
I've brought all of Queen Therese's retainers safely back to the temple. I should speak to the queen.
<<1>> has somehow been raised without my help. I must destroy him.
I have the souls <<1>> asked me to capture. I should meet him inside the Royal Crypt.
I need to defend <<1>> while he's attemping to merge with the revenant body.
Heloise is ready to go check on the Hinault family. I should talk to her and let her know we're good to go.
The undead attack at the docks was the work of the Withered Hand, a group of dangerous necromancers. It seems the Hand has also kidnapped Prince Azah. I should search for witnesses.

After placing the heart on Hircine's altar, I was confronted by a ghostly figure. It summoned one of Hircine's huntsmen to attack me before disappearing with the heart. I should see if there are any signs left on Hircine's altar.

The <<1>> told me the grotto's bear guardians are under a spell, making them attack the Wyrd on sight. If I kill a <<z:2>>, its spirit may appear. Once free from its body, it should be able to speak to me and tell me what's happening.

I should enter the <<1>> and search for the matriarch, the only one who may know what's happened. The matriarch is near the waterfall on the far side of the grotto. I can use the charm <<2>> gave me to disguise myself from the bear guardians.
I've found what seems to be the source of the corruption infecting the bear guardians. I should remove it from the waterfall before it causes any more harm.
The <<1>> told me I should take the heart to Hircine's shrine in the middle of the lake within the <<2>>. He might destroy the heart when I place it on the altar.
I've found a <<z:1>>. It seems to be enchanted. Despite being buried beneath a waterfall, it's warm to the touch. I should bring it to the <<2>> and see if she knows what I should do with it.
I promised <<1>> I would exact revenge on the Pellingare gang. I should kill any smugglers I encounter in the Wayrest sewers.
I've killed most of the Pellingare smuggling gang. I should return to the entrance of the sewers and speak with <<1>>.
I should get bandages from the barrels in the storage cavern.
I need to bind the wounds of  injured Shining Scarab recruits so that they can make their way to safety.
I should let Zakamud know that I was able to bind the wounds of several recruits, allowing them to return to the main camp.
The hold of the <<1>> is  locked. I should find a way to get the key from the captain or her crew.
I've found the key to the cabin of the <<1>>.
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I beat the storm to the last fire! I must now speak to Anjan.
I have spoken with both <<1>> and the necromancer <<2>>. <<3>> probably has some ideas for how we should proceed.
<<1>> asked me to put a stop to negotiations between the Withered Hand and the Saltwalker Company. I should meet the Fighters Guild envoy on the scene, <<2>>.
<<1>> is fed up with the whole situation. <<2>> may need some convincing to end the talks, and the necromancer <<3>> is determined sign the Saltwalker contract.
The talks between the Saltwalker Company and the Withered Hand must end. I am to distract <<1>> by standing on the red carpet in the corner of the tent. <<2>> can then surprise and kill him.

The talks between the Saltwalkers and the Withered Hand must end. I am to duel <<1>> to settle our dispute. This will satisfy the traditions of the Saltwalker Company.nnI must play the drum in the center of camp to begin the duel.
I could try to convince <<1>> to watch for treachery from <<2>>
I convinced <<1>> that <<2>> may try to do something to balance the duel in his favor. She said that she'll be watching for any treachery.
I defeated <<1>> in a duel, but not before he summoned the undead to his aid. He ran back into the commander's tent. I should follow him and speak to <<2>>.
I need to find a switch to unseal the portal chamber. Lady Laurent says she'll meet me inside.
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
I should speak to Lieutenant Glenan at her tent, just south of Sabine Lancarl.
I should lead Lieutenant Glenan on a patrol between the <<1>> and <<2>>. We need to scout the entire perimeter.
Lieutenant Glenan and I have completed our patrol. She'd like to speak with me before we continue.

We need to capture an Imperial picket for interrogation. Lieutenant Glenan gave me a <<z:1>> to incapacitate an enemy. My target must be weakened before I can use it, and we'll need to bind him before he regains his senses.

We've successfully captured an Imperial. I need to lead him and Lieutenant Glenan safely back to the mustering camp, where he'll be interrogated. It's unlikely the prisoner will go quietly. I should be prepared for him to make trouble.
I successfully returned an Imperial captive for questioning. I should speak to Lieutenant Glenan to find out what to do next.
I must reach the next fire, so I can beat the storm to the last fire!
The <<1>> asked me to finish consecrating <<2>> skeletons within the ruins of <<3>>. I should use the censer I took from his body to fulfill his request. The incense inside will purify the bones.
I've consecrated many <<1>> skeletons in the ruins of <<2>>. I should return to the Priest of Arkay's spirit near the entrance of the ruins and let him know I've completed his task.
When I took the censer, the spirit of the dead priest appeared and spoke to me. I should see what he wants.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.
Once I locate a tomb protected by wards, I can use the binding stone that Gabrielle provided. Then Gabrielle and the soldiers can teleport in and meet me.
Lieutenant Glenan has returned to her tent at the mustering camp. I can pick her up there and restart our patrol.

To prove his beliefs, Anjan threw bones onto the sand and prophesied I would win a race against a storm. I must run across the desert, following the trail of blue flames, so I can reach the end before the storm does.
Stibbons, Lady Laurent's servant, is concerned that her ladyship hasn't returned from the tomb yet. He asked me to look for her.
<<1>> is close to Lady Laurent. Perhaps he might have some additional information about the medallion she is looking to complete.
I have the souls <<1>> asked me to capture. I should meet him inside the Royal Crypt.
I retrieved the Cursed Crown of Anton. Now I need to find my way out of the Tomb of Lost Kings.
I escaped the Tomb of Lost Kings with the Cursed Crown of Anton. I should give it to Lady Laurent at her camp.
I need to enter the sewers beneath Wayrest to find <<1>>.
I must find and confront <<1>>, a corrupt investigator.
<<1>> is dead, but there's another investigator being held prisoner in the sewers. I should talk to <<2>> and offer my help.
<<1>> asked me to search the sewers for a hidden exit while she returns to Wayrest to summon reinforcements.
I've discovered the hidden route used by the Pellingare smugglers to exit the sewers. I should report my discovery to <<1>>, who will be waiting at the sewers' entrance.
I must find and confront <<1>>, a corrupt investigator.
Gabrielle and a Dragon Knight teleported safely into the crypts. I should speak to Gabrielle and determine our next step.
I should speak with <<1>>, the leader of the Evermore patrol. I need to make sure everyone made it safely to him.
Captive farmers are being interrogated by the Reachmen. Others are injured and need healing. I should find the farmers and help them.
I did not find the key. I should tell Rodric.
One of the Witchmen had a sketch of a priest. I should take it to Brother Themond who is by the windmill.
Brother Themond sent his son Vince to get Bonerender from the chapel in Evermore Farms. I should rush over there to help Vince.
I found Vince laying in the chapel injured surrounded by dead Reachmen.nnI should talk to him.
I found Vince laying injured in the chapel. He appears to be very badly wounded.nnI should talk to him.
I should eliminate the threat of the Reachmen's leader.
The Reachmen have taken Bonerender to someone named Lathidkel. I need to get it back from them.
I should return to Brother Themond with Bonerender.
She asked me to help the farmers defend themselves by getting them armor and weapons.
Now that I have the healing herbs, I should give them to the farmers.
I should let Marge Themond know taht I have equipped the farmers for battle.
The storm beat me to the last fire. I should return to Anjan.
Gabrielle and one knight managed to teleport into the safe area, but the rest of her team was lost in the process. I should look for the missing knights as I explore the crypts and search for Angof.
Lieutenant Glenan has returned to her tent at the mustering camp. If I pick her up there, we can try to capture an Imperial scout again.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.
I should let <<1>> know that I've delivered the rations. Then, I can get anther <<z:2>> to give <<3>>.
The monster should have walked to the waypoint you set, advanced the goal and despawned. If you kill him, the fail should trigger.

Interacting with the NPC should have completed that goal, choosing the conversation option should have completed the Talk To goal, and creating and "giving" the item to the NPC should have completed that goal.
I've found the two medallions Lady Laurent was looking for. I should bring them to either her or <<1>> back at the eastern outskirts of <<2>>.
<<1>> told me the correct order to reassmble the amulet. I should return to <<2>> and let her know: Secunda must be used before Masser.
I should be able to find a uniform in the storage rooms if I need one.
Before I can unlock the gargoyles' cages, I'll need to get a key from one of the researchers.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.
I found Darien and Sir Lanus, but there are still knights that are unaccounted for. I should continue to look for them.

After consulting a set of bones, Hadoon informed me that I am fated to die in the jaws of a terrible duneripper named Istraga. Istraga roams the desert south of Leki's Blade. Hadoon wants me to bring him one of its scales as proof.
I have slain Istraga and taken her scale. I must give the scale to Hadoon.

A clever goblin named <<1>> has asked that I help him escape by collecting three pieces of gear for a crude disguise. He also wants me to slay some of the warchiefs directing the remains of the Birdsnap tribe.
I've collected the disguise and slain the goblin warchiefs. I should bring the armor and robe to <<1>>. Then he can make his escape.
I should speak with the spirit of <<1>>.
I have freed the Knights of Farwatch from their reliquaries. I should return to <<1>>.
The spirit of <<1>> told me there are three reliquaries holding the spirits of his knightly brethren in <<2>>. I should search the tower and open the reliquaries.
Gabrielle and I have both arrived at the ancient Wyrd site. I should speak to Gabrielle when I'm ready to start the ritual.
I must travel northeast of HoonDing's Watch and meet Halelah at the town of Satakalam.
Brinarch is slain, and the grotto belongs to the Wyrd again. I should speak to <<1>> and see what she plans to do next.
I am to slay Reachmen near the ritual site and use their blood to destroy Brinarch's heart. Only then will he be vulnerable to attack, and able to be slain.
I must kill the Reachmen near Brinarch's ritual site. I'll use their blood to destroy his heart. Only then will he be vulnerable to attack.
Brinarch is slain, and the grotto is now the Wyrd's again. I should speak to <<1>> and see what she plans to do next.
Now that I've destroyed Brinarch's heart, I can finally slay him. If I can't slay him now, I'll have to eradicate every last vestige of his heart to make him vulnerable again.
target: Ora che ho distrutto il cuore di Brinarch, posso finalmente ucciderlo. Se non ci riuscissi, dovr rimuovere ogni rimanenza del suo cuore per renderlo nuovamente vulnerabile.

source: A Lion Guard soldier requested my help. He wants me to travel to the Lion Guard Redoubt and offer my services to Commander Marone Ales.
Hircine granted me a boon: the ability to defeat Brinarch and stop him from leading an army of Reachmen as an immortal "Briar Heart." I should tell <<1>> of my plans.
Hircine granted me a boon: the ability to defeat Brinarch and stop him from leading an army of Reachmen as an immortal "Briar Heart." I should discuss these plans with <<1>> before I proceed.
I should talk to other Shining Scarabs to learn more about them.
<<1>> met me after I left the <<2>>. He asked me to meet <<3>> at the <<4>> Mages Guild.
<<1>> cannot consecrate Veraya's remains because they're cursed. She asked me to take the bones to <<2>>. He's in the temple at <<3>>. She hopes <<2>> will know how to consecrate the bones.
Brother Cantrall has agreed to examine <<1>>. He hopes to uncover the specifics of the curse that prevented Zeli from consecrating them.
<<1>> has finished examining <<2>>. I should see if he learned anything from his attempt to unravel the curse.
When we consecrated <<1>>, we learned something disturbing: her son, <<2>>, is alive and well in <<3>>.nn<<4>> asked me to bring this news to <<5>>. I'll find him inside <<6>>, in the manse of <<7>>.
I must bring Veraya's remains to <<1>>, then help her complete the ritual to consecrate them. Once that's done, I must report to <<2>> in the manse of <<3>> in <<4>>.
To consecrate <<1>>, I must first speak to <<2>>. If she's not around, I should wait for her to return to the shrine outside <<3>>.

I must take <<1>> to the <<2>>. Only there, in the land of her birth, can we consecrate her bones. Brother Cantrall asked me to speak to <<3>> on the Wayrest Docks to book passage to <<2>>. Once I'm there, I should look for <<4>> and <<5>>.
I've landed safely in <<1>>. I must seek out <<2>>. <<3>> said he would send her word of my arrival.nnI must speak to her about consecrated the cursed bones of <<4>>.
Now that I've reached Warden Mine, I need to take notes on what I see.
I must first collect weapons from the Imperial troops that I defeat.
I have gathered a number of weapons for the resistance fighters. I should now find Istahn, inside the western mine entrance.

Istahn wishes me to create a distraction so he and his resistance fighters can escape the mines and kill the confused Imperials. I must gather a kindlepitch mixture from storage crates within the mine.
Fire salts and kindlepitch powder can create a dangerous fiery admixture. I should use it to set fire to the scaffolding repair crates both inside and outside of the mine. The fire will do the rest.
I have left Onsi's Breath and rescued the miners. I must find and speak to Istahn.
I must first collect weapons from the Imperial troops that I defeat.
I have gathered a number of weapons for the resistance fighters. I should now find Istahn, inside the western mine entrance.
I should rescue the villagers from the Reachmen and recover Kerbol's medallion. The Reachmen are encamped northeast of the village.
I've rescued the soldiers from the Reachmen. <<1>> mentioned that I should check in with his daughter, <<2>> after they were freed in case they were injured.
I healed Marthe using the medallion I retrieved from the Reachmen's camp. I should speak with Mayor Kerbol.
I need to collect wolf pelts to use to lure <<1>> out of hiding.
I need to offer Morick's heart to Hircine. In exchange, the Daedric Prince will bless Kerbol's medallion. Morick's altar is on the hill behind his cave.
<<1>> is performing her ritual at an altar overlooking the village. She's using werewolves she kidnapped from <<2>>. She must be stopped!
<<1>> is dead, and the villagers are free. I should speak with <<2>>.
I need to find Lieutenant Gidrielle, one of the soldiers who escaped the massacre. She followed the Reachmen to Fallen Grotto, far southwest of <<1>>.
<<1>> has asked me to help fight the Aldmeri incursion at <<2>> by killing their soldiers.
I've killed many of the Aldmeri soldiers beneath <<1>>. I should return to <<2>>.
I need to collect <<z:1>>, so I can lay a trap for one of Hircine's huntsmen.
I need to take the <<z:1>> to <<2>>. She's at the huntsman's camp at the southwest edge of the <<3>>.
After I defeated the huntsman, he agreed to parley with me. I should speak with him to learn the truth behind Brinarch and his Reachmen within the <<1>>.
I've gained entry to one of Hircine's hunting grounds, where I am to complete his challenge. I should speak to whomever I can find to learn more about Hircine's puzzle.
I've defeated the three challenges in Hircine's game, and from his comments, he seems pleased. I should go to his shrine within his hunting grounds to see if he will speak to me.
I must cast the <<z:1>> into the huntsman's fire to draw him near. Once he arrives, I must defeat him.
The fires are set. I must escape Onsi's Breath before the flames consume everything!
Josselin said she doesn't care how I acquire infromation from the prisoner. There may be more than one option. I should search the camp for items that might convince him to talk.
The prisoner has agreed to answer our questions of his own free will. I should speak with Josselin.
I've broken the prisoner's stubborn resistance. I should tell Josselin that he'll answer our questions now.
The prisoner will need to be convinced to reveal what he knows. Josselin might be able to tell me how I can convince him to talk.
Josselin shared her advice for interrogation with me. I can always ask her again.
The mad mage claims that uniting this <<1>> with its <<2>> will open some sort of portal.
The sorcerer told me to enter the portal I've opened. Through the portal should be a plaque with runic inscriptions. I need to read it for clues as to how to proceed.
The mad mage I've been working for can be heard through this final portal. I should speak into it and see if I can communicate with the sorcerer.
Sir Lanis has requested to speak with me before I leave. I should find him in by the commander's tent.
The three shard-keys are well-guarded. I need to defeat the guardians to acquire the shard-keys.
I gathered the shard-keys I need to unlock Angof's inner sanctum. Now I need to find the locked door.
I'm inside Angof's inner sanctum. It's time for Angof to die.
Angof is dead. I should use the portal and follow the others back to the redoubt. Wizard Gabrielle will want to know what happened.
I should find the captain of the Lion Guard and give him the journal I recovered. Then the Lion Guard can take proper action.
<<1>> suspected the journal I found was a ruse planted by the Imperials. I still need to help <<2>> guard the supply depot in the southeast corner of the camp.
Fire salts and kindlepitch stones can create a dangerous fiery admixture. I should use these two components to set fire to the scaffolding inside of the mine.
I found Vince laying injured in the chapel. He asked me to get Bonerender from a chest on the upper level of the chapel.
If I leave Hircine's hunting grounds for any reason, I should ask the huntsman near his camp site to send me there again.
I discovered the location of the ritual. I need to stop whatever they're doing and save Tahiri's life.
I told <<1>> I would rescue his daughter. I need to discover where the ritual is taking place. I can either examine the warehouse he mentioned or search for the location myself.
The message I found revealed the location of the ritual. I should look east of Sentinel Docks along the shore. Then I can find the Withered Hand and save Tahiri's life.
<<1>> mentioned an amulet that will protect me from the undead. If I could find one inside the warehouse, it may come in handy while I'm rescuing <<2>>.
Now that my lizard has won the race, I should return to <<1>>.
A pair of ancient heroes lie dead somewhere beneath Farwatch Tower.The runic plaque indicated that these dead heroes might open the way for the sorceror's portals.
I should purchase a racing lizard from <<1>>. I can find her near the race track outside of North Bergama.
I've placed my lizard at the race track outside Bergama. My lizard will run in the next race as soon as it starts.
Now that I've obtained a racing lizard, I should put it in its starting cage at the race track outside Bergama.
I activated the switch to unseal the portal chamber. Lady Laurent will meet me inside.
I should leave the central ruins so I can return to <<1>>.
I've activated the pillars so the back door into the lower ruins should be open. I should meet Lady Laurent inside.
I should return to <<1>> with Bonerender.
Letiza was injured trying to retrieve some gems from an abandoned  mine, encountering an angry ghost and some skeletons.  I agreed to look for the gems.
I should search the mine for signs of Samsi's partner.
I agreed to avenge Haidar's murder and give Samsi the cursed gemstones.
Haidar wants revenge for his murder. He's cursed the gemstones that he and Samsi found at the bottom of the mine. He wants me to give them to Samsi.
Haidar wanted me to avenge his death and give Samsi the cursed gemstones, but I refused. I'll give her the supply pack, as she requested.
Haidar's spirit was angry at me for not helping, but I decided not to give the cursed gemstones to Samsi. I am bringing back the supply pack, though, as she requested.
I found the remains of Samsi's partner, and his ghost appeared. I should speak to the ghost.
Krothag has asked me to destroy the Imperials' supplies so that they cannot follow the escapees into the desert.
I must find Krothag at the cave at the north side of the mines, above ground.
I have done all that Krothag has asked. I should find him outside of the mine compound.
The dead mage says that the ways and paths are now open into Farwatch Tower. I must return to the sanctuary, where I first found his stone, in order to exact his revenge.
I found a bone buried in the sand. The dog then ran off to what appears to be another mound of sand. I should follow the dog and unearth the next mound of sand.
I found another bone buried in the sand. The dog then ran off to what appears to be another mound of sand. I should follow the dog and unearth the next mound of sand.
I found another bone buried in the sand. The dog then ran off to what appears to be another mound of sand. I should follow the dog and unearth the next mound of sand.
I found another bone buried in the sand. The dog then ran off to what appears to be another mound of sand. I should follow the dog and unearth the next mound of sand.
I assembled the bones, and the skeleton has risen to stand before me. I should speak to it.
<<1>> asked me to examine <<2>>. I should assess her condition under the Sentinel's care.
I should search the troll dens within the <<1>> for any survivors.
After I rescued the peasants from troll dens, a Glenmoril wyress appeared. I should speak to her.
<<1>> asked me to meet her at Stenwick's hut. It's at the southern end of the <<2>>.
<<1>> asked for my help in placating the trolls in the <<2>>. He's given me a charm I'm to offer to an old troll behind Stenwick's hut.
<<1>> says I should speak with <<2>> behind the Crosswych Inn to talk about his plan.
Krothag has asked me to use the anchor stone at the southern command tent to call the two camp leaders, Falco and Larus, back from their wanderings. Once I have done so, I must kill them both.
I am caught in the magic of the Rite of Portals. I must endure the spell until it is complete.
The Commander has ordered me to capture the farm in Balfiera.
I have captured a Farm and should inform Commander.
I have helped in capturing a keep and should inform the Commander.
The Commander has ordered me to capture Fort Balfiera.
<<1>> was waiting for me on the docks of <<2>> when I arrived. I should speak to him about consecrating <<3>>.
The Commander has ordered me to capture the Lumbermill.
I have captured the Lumbermill and should inform the Commander.
The Commander has ordered me to capture the mine.
I have captured the mine resource and should inform the Commander.
The Commander has ordered me to go into  kill thirty members of the Ebonheart Pact or Daggerfall Covenant.
I have slain thirty enemies of the Dominion. I should speak to the Commander.
The Commander has ordered me to kill thirty members of the Ebonheart Pact.
I have slain thirty of the Ebonheart Pact. I should speak to the Commander.
The Commander has instructed me to kill thirty members of the Daggerfall Covenant.
I have slain thirty members of the Daggerfall Covenant. I should speak to the Commander.
The Scout has ordered me to recon the Farm.
I have scouted a farm resource and should inform Scout.
General Thoron has ordered me to scout the lumbermill.
I have scouted the Lumber Mill and should inform the Aldmeri Scout.
The Aldmeri Scout has ordered me to scout out the Mine.
I have scouted the mine and should inform the Aldmeri Scout.
The Skirmisher has instructed me to kill a member of the Daggerfall Covenant.
I have slain a member of the Daggerfall Covenant. I should speak to the Aldmeri Scout.
I stopped the ritual and rescued <<1>>. I should find <<2>> at the main dockhouse.
I should return to <<1>> and let her know what I've accomplished.
I should take these weapons to Brother Themond
Brother THemond said that folks are too hurt to fight so I should get some healing herbs.
Istahn requested I collect usable weapons and armor from the Imperials for the resistance fighters. I can find these on the Imperials and in arms caches near their tents and fortifications.
Istahn wanted me to find him near the eastern mine tunnel entrance.
Istahn wants me to enter the mines and recruit prisoners for an uprising against the Imperials.
The resistance is formed and ready. I should speak to Istahn in the nearby tunnel.
I need to find Krothag in the mines.
Istahn has asked me to rescue a mighty Orc named Krothag gro-Gorak from the rise, where he has been left to die.
Istahn asked me to rescue and recruit a mighty Orc named Krothag gro-Gorka. The Imperials have tied him up. They left him to die in the sun.
Krothag is extremely weak from thirst and the beatings he's received. In his current state, he can't break his chains. I need to find the key to unlock them.
I found the key that will release Krothag. I should return to him before it's too late.
The Aldmeri Commander has ordered me to scout Fort Balfiera.
I have scouted Fort Balfiera and should inform the Aldmeri Scout.
I have slain a member of the Daggerfall Covenant. I should speak to the Skirmisher.
The Skirmisher has instructed me to kill a member of the Ebonheart Pact.
The Skirmisher has instructed me to kill an enemy guard.
I have slain an enemy guard. It is time to inform the Skirmisher of my success.
The Skirmisher has instructed me to kill a Daggerfall Covenant guard.
I have slain a Daggerfall Pact guard. It is time to inform the Skirmisher of my success.
The Skirmisher has instructed me to kill an Ebonheart Pact guard.
I have slain an Ebonheart Pact guard. It is time to inform the Skirmisher of my success.
General Thoron has ordered me to  kill ten members of the Ebonheart Pact or Daggerfall Covenant.

Covenant soldiers plan to attack the fort from below. I must seal them down here by activating several floor plates. That will create a magical barrier. Strikes-from-Shadows asked me to activate three plates before meeting him in the last chamber.

I've found some dead troops inside the tower on the fort's eastern side. There was a fight between Pact and Covenant forces. Strikes-from-Shadows might have used the trapdoor in the room to escape. I should climb down and look for him.

An Argonian named <<1>> knows of a salve that will soothe the burns of injured Dunmer. He needs the proper ingredients to make it. The key ingredient is chitin from the lavawalker shalks infesting Senie.
I've recovered the chitin required for the cure. I should deliver it to an Argonian named <<1>>. He's in the temple on the north side of Senie.

<<1>> has ground the shalk chitin I collected into medicinal poultices. Injured Dunmer are suffering throughout Senie. I need to use the medicine on them. <<1>> also instructed me to speak with <<2>>.
I've used the Argonian poultice to heal a number of Dunmer injured by the eruption and the shalk invasion. I should seek out <<1>> and tell him of the aid the Argonians provided.

I told <<1>> of the aid the Argonians provided, but he's paranoid and suspicious. He fears an Argonian shaman named <<2>> has taken his daughter. If I can reassure him, he'll talk to the Argonian leaders in Senie.
<<1>> thought she saw <<2>> walking out of town before the volcano erupted. I should go west to the base of Ash Mountain to see if I can find her.
<<1>> appears shaken by the sigil <<2>> found burned into the earth. I should continue speaking with him.
Girvas and his daughter have been re-united. I should speak to him again.
I should head to the center of Davon's Watch and collect the <<1>> from the chest in the basement of the library.
I must meet <<1>> at the Daedric tower. We'll perform a ritual there and confront the spirit of <<2>>.
I'm to meet <<1>> at the Daedric ruins. We must perform a ritual and confront the spirit of <<2>>.
The Dark Elf scout Vartis asked me to acquire a copy of the orders the Orcs are following. I need to find out who they are, what they want, and who sent them to Deshaan.
I learned a great deal about the Oathbound Orcs and the reasons they were sent to Deshaan. I should report to Vartis Dareel.
I've been asked to check on Vartis Dareel, a tracker searching for missing Dark Elves near the western mountains.

To disrupt the siege of Davon's Watch, I've been instructed to destroy two Covenant ballistae on the western beach. Holgunn also wants me to start a fire at the construction site where they're building siege ladders.
<<1>> would like to find out what happened to his military brothers who were being held in the recently decimated Daggerfall Camp.
I should speak to Ix-Utha once again to bid her farewell.
Now that the enslaved dead are free to move on, I should seek out the spirit of Ix-Utha.
I discovered that <<1>> has joined the Worm Cult. These cultists have captured wounded Pact soldiers for their experiments. I should speak with Furon right away.
<<1>> asked me to infiltrate the mage's circle. I need to find something that could explain what they're doing.
I noticed a tome lying out in the circle's meeting place in a cave. I should grab it so Furon can understand what this cult is doing.
I should find <<1>> east of <<2>>. Then I can give her the journal we recovered from an Imperial spy, and the Lion Guard can take proper action.
I should get keys from Lord Montclair's jailers in the <<1>>.
I should get keys from Lord Montclair's jailers in the <<1>>.
I've found the Telvanni's group, but has misgivings about what's going on. I need to speak with these cagted Dunmer soldiers to find out what is going on.
I should find Duchess Elvaine in the basement of the castle and rescue her.
The mansion must hold something that will help the ghost of <<1>> regain her memory of what happened to her.
I found something that might help <<1>> remember her past. I should search the mansion for more clues to get her to remember.
I've scoured the mansion and found all of the items I could. Now I must see if any of them will help Leila remember.
I've activated the plates. I should report to Strikes-from-Shadows and tell him.
I must tell Captain Llaari of Ahknara's demise.

There is one last plate to activate. Strikes-from-Shadows asked me to slay Ahknara. He'll activate the last plate as he exits behind me. Ahknara is waiting outside the door behind Strikes-from-Shadows.
The cultists in the cave were abducting people wounded in the battle. Their captives are awaiting some kind of horrible experiment. I should free as many of them as I can.
I should meet Qismah at her home, so I can speak to her father, <<1>>.
I found the kwama nest. Now I need to obtain the <<z:1>>.
I need to bring the <<z:1>> back to <<2>>.
I should fight my way through Covenant forces to the manse north of Davon's Watch and save <<1>>.
I have the orders. I must return to Captain Hjolm. He'll be waiting at the gates of Fort Arand.
I should talk to Naryu Virian and help her decide how to handle her contract.
I've convinced Naryu to distract her brother, Llarevis Virian, while I poison his wine at his home.
I've informed Naryu that I will see if I can convince Llarevis to minimize both his sister's guilt and the possibility of a more brutal Tong approach by taking his own life.
I have told Naryu to let me handle her brother's killing in her stead.
Llarevis Virian is dead. I should return to Naryu and inform her of the outcome.
<<1>> discovered a mysterious note attached to the door of the Ancestor Moth house. I should read the nbte and see what clues it may provide.
Captain Noris has asked me to help free his men. They've been taken by the dreugh. I need to save the Pact soldiers by digging out dreugh mud mounds.
One of the rescued soldiers told me the Covenant is holding Lieutenant Galyn inside their ship. It's on the north side of Vivec's Antlers. I need to rescue her.

I've rescued Lieutenant Galyn. While she rallies her soldiers, she asked me to find her aide, Sings-With-Reed. She has a plan to turn the coral against the Covenant. Sings-With-Reed is probably watching over the Covenant camp.
Svanhildr wants me to burn down the Orc supply shacks. I need to collect kindlepitch from the Covenant in the area. The stuff is highly flammable.
I gathered kindlepitch as Svanhildr suggested. If I throw some of the material at a flame, I can set each supply shack on fire.
I set fire to the Orc supply shacks. I should find Svanhildr by the large gate and let her know.
I must collect some of these flasks and return to Eila.
Eila saw some of the assassins on the edges of the fort. I should smash the flasks around there and kill any assassins I find.
I found and slain many assassins. I must return to Eila and inform her.
I have the flasks and must return to Eila.
I must place the ritual items into the braziers.
I've found the attic room and used the key to get inside. I should search the room and see what Frodibert Fontbonne left behind.
I found a note written by Frodibert to his son. It seems he was not disappointed in his son after all. The key I found under the note should unlock the chest containing Donel's inheritance.
Inside the chest is Donel's inheritance money. I need to decide if I want to keep the money for myself or try to find Donel Fontbonne.
Tanval asked me to enter the tomb complex that begins across the square from the manse, and collect the <<1>>.
I've joined Holgunn at the manse in Davon's Watch. He's introduced me to Tanval Indoril. I should speak to him.
I've found <<1>>. I should use the signal near Morvani's location so <<2>> can find us.
I need to talk to Svanhildr and listen to her plan.
Drelden's kwama must be "persuaded" to return home. A sufficiently convincing beating should stun one and briefly make it friendlier. After that, I can use <<1>>  to order it home.
I've "convinced" several of Drelden's errant kwama to return to his mine. I should meet him there to claim my reward.
<<1>> appears shaken by the sigil <<2>> found burned into the earth. Perhaps this will inspire him to accept the aid of the Argonians.
I've found the missing <<1>>. Both her father Girvas and the Argonian shaman <<2>> arrived when I used the signal. I should speak to the Spellwright.

Gruznak the Impatient is dead and his Oathbound raiders are scattered and disorganized. I should find Svanhildr at the mouth of the pass and see if the reinforcements have arrived.
<<1>> asked me to seek out a mushroom at a kwama nest nearby. First, I must travel to a cave.
I've spoken with both Furon Rii and Reesa, and I've tried their methods. I should speak to <<1>>.
I need to collect Dark Elf skulls so I can disrupt the spell of domination over Idrasa's spirit. Skulls are boiling in cauldrons throughout Malak's Maw. I can collect them from these iron pots.
I gathered enough skulls for the altar on the far side of Malak's Maw. I must find a way to attract Khralek to the site and slay him.
The spire was consumed in a strange fire. Idrasa appeared. I should speak to her.
Placing the Dunmer skulls on the altar should disrupt the spell of domination and force Khralek to investigate.
I need to find Senar's sisters, Hlaren and Ravel.
Tanval asked me to enter the tomb complex that begins across the square from the manse. The door will allow me access to the tombs beneath Davon's Watch.
Idrasa asked me to go to the Orcs' terrible monument, the Spire of Broken Skulls. Once there, I will speak words of power in the name of the Tribunal and all of the slain Dunmer.
I've retrieved the <<1>>. I should return to <<2>> at the manse in Davon's Watch.
I should head to the west gate of Davon's Watch and speak with <<1>>.
Khralek is dead. I should speak with Idrasa and see if her spirit can rest now.
I need to go to the temple and retrieve the Sacred Thumb of Saint Aralor.
I've defeated the shaman who tried to destroy the Sacred Thumb. I should find Dolril and return the relic to him.
I must enter the tomb complex again. The door into the tomb is across the courtyard from the Davon's Watch headquarters.
<<1>> told me to deliver some of the <<2>> to her assistants, <<3>> and <<4>>.

Sergeant Eila asked me to report to Captain Hjolm. The sergeant found no evidence of a flanking attack to the west. She suspects they're coming from Hjolm's direction. Captain Hjolm is along the road to the east.
I should defend <<1>> from Covenant troops while he performs the ritual.
I gathered information about the disappearances, including evidence linked to the Llodos plague. I should return to the kinhouse and talk to Councilor Ralden about this.
A House Hlaalu guard informed me that if I want to offer my help, I need to speak to a councilor at the kinhouse.
Narsis villagers might have information, as well.

Text describing the decision of either sacrificing Dolril to recover the Tear of St. Veloth and saving the villagers, or rescuing Dolril and causing the relic to be stolen and causing the villagers to die.
Even if it means the Vereansu escape, I must rescue the village elder!
I must destroy the Vereansu supplies. If I grab a torch from the bonfire, I should be able to burn their supply crates.
Now that the Vereansu have been defeated, I should find Dolril Belvayn along the road to Narsis and give him the news.
Now that the Vereansu supplies are burning, I need to find <<1>>. He's on the road north of Muth Gnaar. I should tell him what happened.
I need to locate the witch Norgred claims he was escorting. He said they were camped east of where I met him.
The axe has been found. Evigna and Norgred are reunited  more or less.
I've found a group of plague husks in an abandoned homestead.  I'll look among them for the axe.
I found the <<1>>.  If I return it to Norgred, perhaps he can get <<2>> to forgive him.

The Argonian spirit has asked me to free the spirits of the dead from their undead masters. I'll need to destroy the Chimer spirits keeping them trapped on Nirn.
The recruiter in Wayrest should be able to help me locate Donel Frontbonne and pass along the note and his inheritance.
The large tent in the camp must belong to the Vereansu ashkhan. If I set fire to it, that should attract his attention!
Donel Fontbonne's note to his father indicated he was joining the army. I should speak with the recruitment officer in Wayrest's marketplace so I can locate the new soldier.
I collected the <<1>>. I must find Reesa and speak with her.
Captain Llaari thinks the Covenant assassins will be lurking near the walls of the fort. I should use the flasks of blinding light until I uncover the infiltrators. Then I must kill them.
I have the flasks and must return to Eila.
Captain Llaari's plan revolves around some alchemical weapons. I should get some flasks of blinding light from the second floor of the command post.
Strikes-from-Shadows mentioned a trap door in the command post. It leads to the bluff above Fort Arand. I should use that door to reach Ahknara and slay her.

Dethisam Berendas wants me to enter the quarantine to check on his sister, Aerona. I need a plague token to get in. He suggested a few people who might be willing to give up a token, or I could find one on a dead body.
I acquired a plague token. I should speak to the Maulborn gatekeeper and gain access into the quarantine.
The Maulborn Gatekeeper accepted my plague token. I can enter the quarantine now.
I entered Quarantine Serk. I should find Aerona Berendas. She should be in the crypts where the afflicted wait for the promised cure.
Aerona Berendas was waiting for me. I should speak with her.
Captain Llaari asked me to report to <<1>>, so I can let him know troops from Fort Arand are on the way.

I didn't find a witch, but I met Norgred's wife. <<1>> saw her husband run off toward some plague husks. They were near an abandoned house southeast of their camp by the river. I'll look for the <<2>> there.
Retrieve the Axe from Plague Husks
Onuja has told me Mavos is buried in the large tomb in the southern part of Othrenis. I should be able to speak to Mavos there.
After speaking with Eanen, I must tell Bala something.
I must travel to Ash Mountain and find <<1>>. I need to tell him what I've learned about the methods used to imprison the Brothers of Strife.
I agreed to help Onuja contact Mavos. I must chant at the shrines on the eastern and western rises of Othrenis.
The dead of Othrenis have awakened, and they thirst for my blood! If I'm to speak with Mavos, I must defeat them.
Mavos' ritual requires two items: a skull and a candle. These items are locked in chests to the east and west. I need to solve a puzzle at each chest to obtain them.
I closed the portals. Now I must speak to Magister Enuse. In Ash Mountain's past, he was studying to the north.
Magister Enuse wants me to summon ritual guardians at a pair of flame wells. These magical anchorheads are located southeast and southwest of Mavos's altar.
There was a large explosion before I was sent back to the present. This must be how Mavos died.nnI must talk to him.
I agreed to help Bala find Eanen's tomb. I should listen to what she needs to awaken him, so I can assist her.
Eanen's feelings for Bala were a lie. He and his wife found the story about her feelings to be quite amusing. I must tell Bala  something.
After speaking with Eanen, I'll have to tell Bala something.
After speaking with Eanen, I must tell Bala something.

I need to find the rod the Maulborn Commander used to stop the ritual. It should be locked in a tower within the Serk, far from the ritual circle. I'll need a key to get to it. One of the Maulborn might have a key.
House Redoran forces arrived while I was inside Quarantine Serk.nnI should speak to their leader, Bannus, Captain of the House Guard, and tell him what I discovered.

I found <<1>>'s witch. It's his wife, <<2>>. She said they had been arguing the night before. <<1>>was quite drunk and ran off in a rage, with the axe, to fight plague husks. I agreed to try and retrieve the axe.
Vara-Zeen is concerned for his mate, Leel-Vata, as she did not escape before the Khajiiti pirates attacked. I must find her in the village.
I need to speak to Vara-Zeen, the elder of Silent Mire.

Leel-Vata was injured while attempting to protect the village's sacred relics. She asked me to retrieve the sacred stones from the Khajiiti pirates and the Hist branch from the sorceress in the tent along the shore.
I recovered the sacred stones and the Hist branch. I should find Leel-Vata by the large rocks north of the village and return them to her.
Dedras and Mevis are somewhere in the sulfur pools. They could be in danger from the caustic environment and wild shalk.
I think I've found the right cave, but I heard the sounds of a struggle as I approached. I should seek out Saalu and Drathyra as soon as possible.

The commander of the Covenant soldiers wielded the poisoned blade that injured Saalu. The commander taunted Drathyra with an herbal antidote, then walked off with it. The invaders went south of Saalu's cave to burn the Othrys' barns.
I recovered the antidote. I must bring it back to the cave before Saalu's poison spreads too far.
I wasn't able to get back to Drathyra before the poison spread throughout Saalu's body. I should check on her back in the cave.
I've found everyone in the Othrys clan. I should return to the stead on the southern side of the <<1>>.

To learn the lessons of the past, I must speak to the spirits of Balreth and Sadal in the ruins to the south. I must also gather the <<1>>s Vunal requested.
I must gather what the Brothers have requested. Some of the Scamps in the area carry Heartstones, and the Brothers' bodies still burn on the altar in the middle of these Ruins.
I've spoken with the spirits and gathered Heartstones. I should return to <<1>> to see what comes next. He's usually studying at the base of the monument.

I've returned from my vision of the past. I should talk to <<1>> about what I've experienced.
I have the candle and the skull. I must return to Mavos to enter the vision.
<<1>> wants me to use some kind of magical device to prepare for the ritual. I should pick the snare out of the box by her side.

I must return to <<1>> to report on the success of the soul gem project.

<<1>> has asked me to collect <<2>> from <<3>> in the West part of the Ruins and <<4>>s from the <<5>> in the infirmary in the Southern ruins.

<<1>> of House Hlaalu hired me to investigate the truth behind the disappearances. I should search around town and speak to anyone who might know what's going on. Perhaps I can discover something the guards missed.
I should speak to the repair worker and offer to guard him while he makes repairs.

I should speak to the <<1>> and offer to guard him while he makes repairs.
Onuja has instructed me to chant once more at the central Othrenis brazier. This will rouse the dead, who will try to kill me for disturbing the rest of a highborn Dark Elf.
I spoke with the Othrys brothers. Neither of them are sure where their mother and sister have gone. One thought they might have taken refuge in a cave near the sulfur pools. I should head there next.
I've prepared the site for the ritual. Turoni instructed me to talk to <<1>> when I was done with my task. She should be at the altar in the center of the ruin.
I must bring <<1>> the items she asked me to collect and help her turn the brothers into powerful weapons. She waits for me on the altar in the middle of the ruins.
I must first place the <<1>> on <<2>> who lies on <<3>>.

Now, I must first place the <<1>> on <<2>> who lies on <<3>>.
<<1>>  has given me the honor of beginning the transformation ritual. I should pray at the <<2>> to begin.
I agree to kill wovles for him.
<<1>> shouted Virgil's name when he attacked. I should search the area to discover anything I can about Virgil's connection to the Imperials.
After killing the Imperials' leader, I found a note linking <<1>> to them. I should talk to Virgil and see if he can explain himself.
I should tell <<1>> about the deal between <<2>>  and the Imperials.
I should talk to <<1>> about his dealings with the Imperials.
Now that I have the key, I need to set the Argonian captives free.
The Khajiit pirate captain, Sa'dir, is on his vessel. I must fight my way on board and kill him.
Seeks-the-Night, the Argonian traitor, has revealed himself to me in the form of a shadowy projection. I should speak to him.
Seeks-the-Night is dead. I should speak to Vara-Zeen outside of the village and inform him of all that occurred.
The captured villagers are locked in chains. Leel-Vata suggested that I search the large tent for a key to unlock the prisoners.
Dami asked me to search supply crates inside the quarantine to find vials containing the Maulborn elixir.
I collected a few unmarked vials and should return to <<1>>.
Sa'dir likes to sleep in the rigging. I can probably shake him loose by spinning the ship's wheel and tipping the vessel.
I found Eanen. I must tell him of Bala's search.
I may have found <<1>>'s witch. It's his wife, <<2>>. Or at least she claims to be his wife. She said her husband was quite drunk and ran off in a rage, with the axe, to fight plague husks.
I found the <<1>>.  If I return it to Norgred, perhaps he can get <<2>> to forgive him.

Evigna and Norgred are reunited. More or less.
I've collected enough of the ritual components to enact the Rite of Recall. I should return to <<1>> at the paddock in the Horsemen's village.
When I came back outside, I found that Fafnyr and the other guards had been attacked. I don't see Gar anywhere. I should talk to Fafnyr and discover what's happened.
Now that I've saved <<1>>, killed the Goblin Warlord and the spider queen, I should return to <<2>> at the manor house and report the good news.

I need to use the Hist branch to mark the door to Seeks-the-Night's home in Silent Mire.

I freed the captured villagers and talked to Seeks-the-Night. Now I need to find Leel-Vata at the meditation mound and let her know what happened.
I should speak with <<1>> at his house in <<2>>.
I've honored the memory of Mavos at the two shrines in Othrenis. I must find and speak to Onuja the scholar, who waits for me at the center of the burial ground.
