<<1>> asked me to search for signs of <<2>> and <<3>>. He suggested that I look in spider cocoons east of the manor house.
I should search for trapped peasants inside of dreugh eggs. I can find the dreugh spawning grounds to the east of the house in <<1>>.
I need to find <<1>> and see if she'll accept a gift from Raston.
I distributed <<G:1>> gifts and spoke to the Mabrigash farseer. She wants me to prove my worthiness before they consider dealing with me or the Hlaalu merchant.
Before he died, the patient told me about the alchemy workshop on the upper floor. I should investigate it.
I found a note. The Maulborn certainly seem to be up to something. A nostrum entered the workshop. I should ask him what this is all about.
When I found <<1>>, he asked me to slay the <<2>>. It's inside a cave at the bottom of a waterfall east of <<3>>.
I should kill any dreugh I encounter around <<1>>.
Aerona Berendas said she heard about a ritual. I should check on her. If she's still alive, she may be able to help me stop the Maulborn.
The spirits of Othrenis have been satisfied. I should be able to find Mavos now. I should speak to Onuja and find Mavos' grave.
Mavos needs me to make contact with the altar to complete the ritual. He's confident the spell will work, but he isn't confident that we'll survive.
I must defend the hall from attacking Goblins.
I summoned the guardians, just as Magister Enuse instructed. Now I should speak with Mavos.
I need to find the Gulakhan and give him Raston's gift.
I need to find the Ashkhan and see if he'll accept a gift from Raston.
Guar have stampeded and scattered throughout the sulfur pools. They're peaceful creatures, but I'll still need to persuade them to return to their stables.
I've sent a number of guar back to the stables. I should check to make sure they've made it there safely.
An angry serpentbound ghost attacked Iru-Ahan while we were speaking.
I need to convince the farseer of the Mabrigash to meet with <<1>>.
<<1>> told me to find the shrine entrance to the base of the monument. It's just a little way north up the road.
Now that we've entered the fort, I should speak to <<1>>.
I should make my way to Kragenmoor and find someone that can direct me to the House Dres' grandmaster.
A perimeter guard instructed me to speak with <<1>> at the Pact's siege camp.
I should speak to <<1>> near the entrance to the ruins.
Garyn doesn't believe <<1>> has the soldiers he needs to hold <<2>>, yet the Covenant is still holding the fort. He's asked me to look for anything odd.
I should enter the ruins to meet <<1>>.
The Ghost Snake sent me back to the Mabrigash. It was neither for nor against opening the Vale to the Hlaalu merchant.
<<1>> suggested I collect small rats and lizards that live along the Coiled Path to use as an offering to Ghost Snake.
I must collect Graven Caps from around the tombs of Othrenis.
I must search the tombs in the northwest section of Othrenis.
I've collected enough Graven Caps. I must seek out Bala near Mavos' tomb in Othrenis.
Once I find Eanen's tomb, I must use the bit of dust she gave me to raise Eanen's spirit.
To get a guar to return to the stable, I'll need a harness to place on it. Guar harnesses are scattered around the sulfur pools.
I've collected all the harnesses I'll need to secure the guar.
I stopped the ritual accelerating the plague. It's time to leave Quarantine Serk.
I've reached the Fang Spires. I need to place my offering and see what happens.
I need to remove the bars keeping the gates closed. That should allow Tanval and Holgunn to lead the Dark Elves and Nords into the fort.

Each of the races in the PactNords, Dark Elves, and Argonianshave a reason to avoid working with the others. I must seek out a representative of each one, so I can figure out how to unite the factions.
<<1>>, the architect of the racial strife in Ebonheart, has been killed. <<2>> will want to know his town is now free of Covenant agents.
<<1>> might be able to provide me with more details on problems in <<2>>.
I've spoken to <<1>>  about Ebonheart's problems.
I must search the western tomb to find Eanen.
I should speak to <<1>> inside the ruins.
Now that <<1>> is dead, I should burn his tent and all his possessions.
I stepped between worlds. <<1>> has instructed me to enter the ruin corridors beneath the fort.
I'm in position. I should open the door for <<1>> and her troops by pulling a nearby lever.
I walked the Coiled Path to make an offering to the Ghost Snake.
The Orc orders implied some kind of agreement made between the Orcs and their instigators. I should search for this contract.
My final trial is to defeat Grandmother Ssurvac.
I defeated Grandmother Ssurvac. I'll seek the Ghost Snake's counsel on the issue of trade between the Mabrigash and House Hlaalu.
I should search for the missing necklace in the supply chamber <<1>> mentioned.
<<1>> said if I found the necklace, I should take it to his campsite across from the supply hall.
I need to continue to Vivec's Antlers. I must talk to <<1>> when I arrive.
I should speak to <<1>> once more.
The spellplague has been dispelled, and Keeper Vildras bade me fairwell. I should speak with <<1>> before I leave Heimlyn.
I've made my way to Kragenmoor. I should try to learn if anyone in the area has seen Tanval.

Mudcrabs are common around the shores of the Argonian quarter north of Ebonheart. Their meat is a convenient fertilizer. Ashreed grows in the shallow waters. It would work well as a wrapper for crab meat.
I've collected crab meat and ashreeds. I'm ready to fertilize the Hist sapling. It stands on an island near the center of the Argonian quarter north of Ebonheart.

<<1>> was half-crazed from imbibing Hist sap, but he clearly identified a Dunmer named Rhavil. He was the one who told him about the mind-altering qualities of tree sap. <<2>> appeared angry at this revelation.
I've collected the crab meat and the ashreeds. Now I need to combine the two into fertilizer.
I need to talk to <<1>> who is in the camp helping the injured.
Telvanni mages want to soothe those affected by the curse in Heimlyn. <<1>> asked me to collect <<zm:2>> from the <<zm:3>> and <<zm:4>> from the <<zm:5>>.
Field assistants are guarding a few residents of the keep huddled in living quarters. I should talk to them and let the totem's aura affect them. I must convince them to leave.
When the curse was unleashed, a Covenant captain fled to the top of the keep's tower. I should see if she's still there.
I've collected the ingredients needed by the Telvanni. I need to deliver them to <<1>> in the southern part of the keep.
<<1>> has come up with a more effective counter to the curse: a <<2>>. She wants me to create the totem using an artifact called a Daedric Urn.
<<1>> believes the way to cleanse the curse is by summoning and defeating its creators,  <<2>> and <<3>>. I need to open their soul cages to summon and disrupt them.
The Spirits had said I must subjugate three of the Angry Wraiths, whose power will be used to open the portal. Normally, they would cooperate, but the curse has made them angry.
I must destroy whatever creature or power is fueling the spellplague curse.
I need to disrupt the remaining ritual components to summon the power behind the spellplague.
I must find Ruvali and see if the creature has copied her.
Ra'shadda stayed in Sathram Plantation to see the Dro-m'Athra was stopped. I set him free for he was repentant.

I found J'kur's body. He was holding a note and a map. The note is intended to be delivered to someone named Vahara. The map points at an area to the north of the plantation.nnI must go there and look for Vahara.
I must deliver Hod's shield to his brother.
I've fertilized the Hist sapling as best I can. <<1>> asked me to meet her back at her lodge.
While I was gathering the fertilizer for the Hist sapling, the Argonians caught a Dunmer of House Dres trying to reach the tree. <<1>> agreed to let me speak to the mer and find out why he did this.
I've made my way into the cellar. Ulov said the creature, however it looks now, should be here.
I must find Ulov Stormwall to learn why he massacred his troops. Feldsii said he was just up the road from where I met her.
After slaying the soldier's double, a gruesome shape rose from the corpse and fled into the stables. I should chase after it before it finds a new body.
There's a woman standing in the entryway of the stables. I should speak to her. If she can't speak, I'll know the creature has found a new body.
The Khajiiti idol Ruvali used to frighten the creature is in the bedroom of her house. The only house is on the plantation is to the west. I need to fetch that totem.
I found the totem. I must return to Ruvali. I also found her husband's corpse.
Tiril's double is standing in the foyer of Ruvali's house. I must find and warn Ruvali.
I must prove to Ruvali that the creature before us is the monster, not her husband.
<<1>> believes the key to unraveling this magical corruption lies with Keeper Vildras, the guardian of the reliquary. I need to seek him out and find out if he will help us.
Azeenus wants me to burn boats and kill the pirate captain. Captain Sa'dir sleeps in the rigging of his ship, but he will come running if he hears the storm warning bell.
Silent Mire has been avenged. I should find Azeenus by the meditation mound in the village.
A simulacrum of Seeks-the-Night has appeared in front of me. I should speak to it and see what it has to say.
The Ghost Snake doesn't care what the Mabrigash decide, so long as they continue to honor and care for the Vale. I should return to the Farseer now.
I decided that the Mabrigash and the Hlaalu should trade with each other.

I need to use the snake totem to determine Raston's fate. If I give the totem to Raston, he'll be welcome in the Vale. If I burn the totem in the fire, he'll become a servant of the Ghost Snake. Or I can suggest a third option to Bodani.
I decided that the Mabrigash will remain isolated. The merchant will serve Ghost Snake.
Farseer Bodani crafted a totem. She thinks it will help in some way. I need to retrieve it from her tent.
This snake totem has some role in deciding the merchant's fate. I'll give it to the Farseer.
Slips-Through-Fingers dropped her pack and suggested there was something inside that would lead me to a secret meeting place.
Madras doesn't trust me yet, but I've decided to help him. I should speak to him again to find out what our next move is.
The chests in Aphren's hold are locked. Perhaps some of the spirits have the keys.
Slips-Through-Fingers claims to know where the missing villagers are. A note in her pack suggests that to find her, I need to follow the Star. I should keep my eyes open.
<<1>> is in the grips of strange magic. He is trapped in a dreamworld.
Keeper Vildras and the mages who created the curse are in position. I need to speak with <<1>>.
I can use the <<1>> to travel to the hidden vault.
A cat named Star is supposed to lead me to the secret meeting place. I need to follow the cat and see where she takes me.
I discovered a group of villagers meeting in secret on the lower level of a locked building. One of them is <<1>>. I should speak to her and find out what's going on.
I've been asked to help Slips-Through-Fingers and her friends. They want to rescue the abducted villagers, but they aren't soldiers. They have no idea what they're in for.
I've decided not to aid Madras. He's just going to get his people killed. I should tell one of the guards about this before Madras and his group do something foolish.
I found a guard right outside. I explained what was going on. She doesn't want to see anyone get hurt, so she's devised a plan to disrupt the meeting.
I need to catch rats to disrupt Madras's meeting. I should be able to find rats running around Narsis.
I need to bring these rats to the secret meeting and drop them at the door. Hopefully, that will slow Madras down.
The rats did their job. They disrupted the meeting and caused people to flee the building. I should speak to <<1>> again.
Guard Rila knows where the missing people are being held. She wants me to report back to the kinhouse and meet her there.
I must find the ingredients for an antidote to the gas in Deepcrag.
Edrasa Drelas asked me to take a batch of her antidote to her husband, Boril.
I need to find a few frightened scribs and herd them to a safe chamber at the end of the east passage.
I herded the scribs to the safe chamber. The kwama keeper seems very protective of his charges.
I need to seal the vials spewing fumes into the middle and lower chambers. I should also give the potion to any miners I find.
I told <<1>> that his wife was behind the sabotage in the mine.
I can bring any cuttle I collect back to Orona, but I made no promises.
I collected kwama cuttle. I should bring it to Orona.
The blacksmith named <<1>> is waiting for me. I should go speak to him.
I need to find the armory key upstairs, so I can open the weapon crates on the lower level.
I found out all I could. I should return to <<1>>.
I was unable to grab the weapons for the villagers in time. I need to report back to <<1>> and see what our next step is.
I've been given a whistle to blow in front of the kinhouse. That will signal the others to distract the guards.
I returned to the kinhouse, but Ralden isn't around. One of his advisors, Varon Davel, wants to speak to me.
Ralden asked me to speak to Giron Sadri, upstairs in the kinhouse. Ralden wants me to do whatever he asks.

Giron believes the Maulborn camped by the lake have something to do with the troubles in Narsis. He asked me to reduce their numbers while searching for anything that links them to the missing villagers or the Llodos Plague.
I found orders that suggest some vile substance was poured into the lake at the waterfall. I should go to the waterfall and look around.
The strange woman named Naryu has appeared again. She wants to speak to me. I should be ready for anything.
I've tried the plan proposed by the Rii brothers. An Argonian named <<1>> tried to get my attention as I finished talking to Furon. I should see what she has to say.
I've bound one of the dead soldiers. I need to lead the soldier's spirit to <<1>>.
<<1>> wants to force the spirits into the great beyond. She's asked me to use the <<2>> on one of the spirits of the battlefield.
I need to tell <<1>> that the <<2>> was able to release the spirit.
I returned to the kinhouse, but Ralden isn't around. One of his advisors, Varon Davel, wants to speak to me.
Naryu says Giron is connected to the Maulborn. Apparently, he's responsible for shipping the Llodos Plague into Narsis. She suggested I return to the kinhouse as soon as possible.
I learned about ruins to the west of Narsis where Giron and the missing villagers might be. I've got a key and just need to find the entrance.
I should tell Varon what I discovered.
I found the entrance to the ruins. Now I need to use the key and get inside.
I'm inside the ruins and the place is crawling with Maulborn. I need to find Giron and and put an end to this.
Councilor Ralden and the missing villagers should be here somewhere. I need to make sure they're all right.
Varon and the guards are waiting for me. I should speak to Varon.
Giron is dead. I found a key on his body, which means there's probably a locked door somewhere in the ruins.
The person I helped should be waiting outside. I need to find her so she can tell me where the villagers are being held.
I should help others around Narsis. Once they trust me, they might help me locate Giron.
I should investigate what happened here. I'll follow the path of debris that leads to the northeast, away from the main road.
<<1>> said they'd captured a raider wearing the insignia of House Dres. The lieutenant is concerned about Dark Elf house politics and asked me to speak to the captive.
Defender Maera saw a well-dressed Dark Elf head into the Mzithumz ruins with the Dwarven control rod. It has to be Ithis Omalor, scion of House Dres. She asked me to enter the ruins and find him.
I found Ithis Omalor. I should confront him about his complicity in the caravan attack.

I interrogated Ithis Omalor and learned that Magistrix Vox sent him to attack the Hlaalu caravan. I refused to grant him leniency for his crimes and sent him running to his death in the depths of Mzithumz.
I accompanied Ithis Omalor out of the Dwarven ruins of Mzithumz. I should speak with Defender Maera.
To prove the rest of the Pact can fight, <<1>>, the leader of the sawyers, expects me to defeat three of his men in single combat  while drunk on Nord mead.
The Nords won't accept my challenge unless I'm obviously drunk with mead. There's a keg of mead near <<1>>.
If I sober up before finishing all the fights, I can always drink more mead.
If I sober up before finishing all the fights, I can always drink more mead.
I pummeled several Nords. I should return to <<1>> to see if he's suitably impressed.

Caravan Master Girano is concerned about his employer's cargo. He wants me to recover the stolen cargo and its manifest from the raiders. The cargo is in crates and a Dres leader should have the manifest. I should find both to the north.
I recovered Girano's cargo and manifest. I should return both to him.
I need to alert the guards. I should unlock the door and return to the kinhouse.
<<1>> has a plan to bind the spirits in service. I need to use the <<z:2>> on a weakened spirit, so I can test the method out.

Aerona Berendas thinks that something strange is happening here. Something about a ritual. She asked me to enter the wards at the top of the hill and see if I can learn anything about the promised cure.
Inside the Maulborn Wards, I encountered a dying man named Grell. He seems to want to tell me something. I should speak to him and hear what he has to say.
I found unmarked vials full of glowing, yellow-green liquid inside the supply crates. I should collect a few of these to bring back to <<1>>.
I should kill any Goblins or spiders I encounter around <<1>>.
I've found a huge Dark Anchor swarming with bad things. I should break the anchor and send a message to Molag Bal.
Return and speak to the Fighters Guild Dude.
The Nords won't accept my challenge unless I'm obviously drunk on mead. Fortunately, I have a <<z:1>>.
After opening several cocoons, I finally located <<1>>. I should speak to him and ask about <<2>>.
I found the Maulborn Commander's rod. Now I need to stop the ritual.
I should gather snake eggs for Nerani, along with a Magicka-infused egg from the end of the path. She needs them for a ritual.
I also need to collect a special magicka-infused egg near the Fang Spires, so that the bonding ritual can be done properly.
I collected the snake eggs and a Magicka-infused egg for Nerani Telvar. With these, she can complete the training ritual.
<<1>> plans to kill the Goblin Warlord. I should find him deeper in the cave and offer my help.
The General claims Ragna Stormcrag is a Nord spy. There's something strange going on here, but I'll find Ragna and see what she has to say.
I should present myself to House General Gavryn Redoran. He should be in the main keep.
Ragna Stormcrag doesn't look like a spy to me. I should talk to her.
The General's bodyguard, Ragna Stormcrag, believes the General is behaving strangely. She wants me to go to the lower level of the keep and convince the guard to let me search the General's quarters.
I should tell Ragna about this new retainer and the meeting at the ruins by the river.

<<1>> needs someone to pray at three shrines surrounding Ebonheart, one for each leader of the Tribunal. He's hoping for a message from the gods, but expects only silence, and he's unwilling to face that himself.
I've told <<1>> about the messages the Tribunal gave me. He found that encouraging.
To gain the attention of the Tribunal, l need to light the braziers at their shrines. I must present offerings of a flower called "Roland's tears."
I've prayed at all three of the shrines.
If Ulov is correct, the monster killed the soldier whose body it copied. I should look in the cellar for the original body.
I need to purchase some Pine Charcoal from <<1>>, and then go to the crafting station to make the sword.
To prove that I have mastered the basics of Smithing, I need to create an Apprentice Sword and show it to <<1>>.
I have completed the apprentice sword. I now need to talk with <<1>>  to evaluate it and see if this is sufficent proof that I am ready to be an apprentice.
Smith <<1>> said I should ask questions if I don't understand. Perhaps I should ask him how to craft the sword.
I must craft an apprentice sword to prove my skills. Then <<1>> will  advance me to the rank of apprentice.
I need to purchase some pine charcoal  from <<1>>.
Talk to <<1>> more about how to research an item.
Once I have made an oxidizer copper ingot, I should talk to Smith <<1>>.
I need to learn the apprentice sword recipe and then talk to <<1>>.
I need to research the sword that Smith gave me. He tells me I must do this by taking it totally apart.
I need to get a damaged sword to research. They are on the table in the near <<1>>.
I have researched the damaged sword and learned some interesting techniques to apply when crafting my own sword.
I need to gather five oxidized copper ores and then refine them into a copper ingot. <<1>> said to talk to him if I needed more information.
I need to search the old mine south of the docks. I should be able to find oxidized copper ore there. nnOnce I have the ore I should then return to <<1>>.
I need to get a recipe from the table by <<1>>.
I should talk to Master Smith <<1>> to learn more about smithing.
I need to go to the old mine south of the docks.
I must travel to Fort Virak. I need to help Pact soldiers retake it.

As I was warned, all three shrines were troubled by ravenous alits. However, that had nothing to do with disapproval by the Tribunal. They were drawn by piles of offal left near each shrine. I should return to <<1>> with this news.
I'm giving this thing to Markiel!
I located the cave. Now I need to find the captured Hlaalu scouts.
I should seek out any reasons why the Maulborn are currently inside the Gorge before searching for the scouts. Perhaps one of them will carry something on their purse.

One document in the General's quarters indicates that he intends to execute Captain Valec Doronil. A second mentions that he has appointed an unnamed personal retainer to the mess tent. I should look into both of these leads.
The guard agreed to let me look around. I need to check the General's quarters for anything suspicious.
It seems <<1>> made a deal with the Thalmor, the military force of the Dominion in Shadowfen. <<2>> should hear about this immediately.
I should find out what the Dark Elf was doing in this dangerous town. Perhaps I could find out how he ended up in the stocks.
I need to get this "leader's" attention by roughing up some of her pirates. <<1>> said I could find them drinking in the town's bar, in the hold of a beached ship.
I won the right to speak to <<1>>, the leader of <<2>>. Her thugs said she would be in the captain's quarters of the beached ship, on the main deck.
I need to speak to the contact One-Eye found. I should see what he knows about the new Khajiit pirate in <<1>>. He should be waiting on the main deck of the beached ship.

I learned the name of this Khajiit pirate leader: it's <<1>>. <<2>> told me one of her pirates would be meeting with a Dominion contact in the warehouse very soon. I should hurry there and find a suitable hiding place.
<<1>> has made a deal with the Thalmor, the military force of the Dominion in Shadowfen. <<2>> should hear about this immediately.
The person I'm looking for is called "One-Eye." I won't be able to gain an audience with her without some violence.
The warehouse probably has some crates I could hide in while listening to the meeting.
I defeated my opponent and completed the Trial of the Fang. I should speak to <<1>>.
I awakened Hissmir's Zaht stones. I should inform <<1>> that Hissmir doesn't need to fear Dominion reprisals.
I recovered the stolen relics. I should return them to <<1>>.
I slew the killers of the missing pilgrims. I should tell <<1>> of their fate.
To complete the Trial of the Fang, I need to defeat a Hissmir warrior while under the influence of <<1>>.
To complete the Trial of the Mind, I must understand which elements of Argonian history match up. Three Argonian texts should provide clues.
I need to speak with <<1>> to discuss my performance in the Trial of the Heart. I can find him southeast of the pyramid.
I've completed the Trial of the Mind. I should speak with <<1>> about the next trial.

The Maulborn plan to ship crates of Llodos Plague into Mournhold and infect the whole city. Scout Mamyne suggested I kill Maulborn cultists in the camp to get forged manifests. That should slow them down.
I volunteered to locate the Hlaalu scouting party and find out what's going on in the gorge.
Baem, the soldier who accompanied Strikes-from-Shadows, ran after Ahknara. I must look for him. He might be injured or dead.
I must take the scribs to an area that is not affected by the gas.

I persuaded the races in Ebonheart to work together and defend the town. It seems each had some contact with a manipulative Dark Elf named <<1>>. <<2>> will certainly want to hear about his activities.

<<1>> asked me to investigate <<2>>. He has a house in town. He'd like me to wait outside and follow Rhavil when he leaves. Drathus cast a spell that will allow him to see what I see and communicate instructions to me.
Rhavil has left his house. I should follow him, but I must be careful not to get too close.
Rhavil entered a shack by the docks. Drathus asked me to wait until he leaves so we can investigate.
Rhavil has left. Drathus asked me to enter the shack and investigate.
There's not much in the shack. Most likely whatever Rhavil was doing in here, the evidence is on his desk.
Drathus wants me to return to Rhavil Urano's house look for more evidence. His house is in the southwest quarter of the city, near the Tribunal Temple. He probably won't come quietly.
The sword would like me to kill the goat.
Return to the sword to tell it of your great deeds.
I could also just buy the items from Donkey

Neposh is the only slave at the mine who managed to stay out of the Daedra's clutches. He has a plan to free people taken to Oblivion. He suggested I recovered firesap gel, an Argonian mixture confiscated by the Dark Elves.
Last-to-Water has escaped from Oblivion. I should speak again with Neposh.
The entrance to the ruins is down by the river, beyond the north gate of the fortress. I need to head there and enter the crypts.
Now that I'm inside the ruins, I should see if I can find Durel Gilveni, the General's retainer. The Maulborn have infiltrated this area, so I need to be careful.
The retainer turned out to be a Maulborn agent. He claims General Gavryn has been killed. I need to find proof of the General's death in the crypts below.
I informed Captain Valec about what I found in the ruins beneath Tal'Deic Fortress. I should see if he needs anything else from me.
Fevryn wants me to speak to Commander Taldyn over at the proving grounds.
Both sergeants are very angry with me. I should meet them in the proving ground to face their challenge.
I challenged members of the corrupt Redoran Sentinels and defeated them in combat. I should tell Commander Taldyn what happened.
Sergeant Aamrila was difficult to coerce. She seems to prefer an orderly and neat camp, so I might be able to provoke her by breaking things in her vicinity.
Sergeant Rendyn was difficult to provoke. He seems to value the well-being of the troops under his command. Perhaps I can get a rise out of him by bullying his troops.
With Sergeant Aamrila sufficiently angered, I now must do the same to Sergeant Rendyn.
I recovered the <<z:1>>. I should return it to <<2>>.
I gathered the shipping manifests. That should delay the shipment. I need to return to <<1>> to discuss our next move.
I recovered the firesap from a slaver's sack. Neposh hopes that pouring the firesap onto Oblivion's crystals should cause them to crack. That might return his people home.
I should check in with <<1>>. He's probably in the area where the Fighters and Mages Guilds are in Stormhold.
<<1>> asked me to speak to the families of the murder victims. I have to find out about Arilin Maralvel, Eroni Omobar, and Naldyn Indalor. If I need help, I should ask <<1>> for more information.

Now that I've spoken to the people on <<1>>'s list, I should enter the mortuary so I can examine the bodies. <<2>> gave me a key to get inside. He said I can find the mortuary on the outskirts of Stormhold.
After examining the bodies, I heard a woman say she has a message for me in the mortuary. I should find out what she wants.

<<1>> approached me in the mortuary. She asked me to meet <<2>> at his home. <<2>> swears he saw his wife, Eroni.nn<<1>> said I can find <<2>> on the east side of Stormhold, and she urged me to hurry. She believes Gethis may be in danger.
<<1>> told me the woman who attacked him may still be in his home. I should go inside and see what I can find.
I returned to <<1>>, but he wasn't there. I should speak to <<2>>. She seems eager to speak to me.

I discovered a dead Shadowscale scout inside <<1>>'s home. The scout had a journal claiming the Shadowscales aren't responsible for Eroni's death.nnI should bring the journal to <<2>>. He's probably still by the guildhall in Stormhold.

I'm in the ruined corridors beneath Fort Virak. I must avoid ghosts prowling the "otherworld" while making my way to the area exit. I should be able to leave the ghost-infested corridors through the far broken wall.
Scout Mamyne asked me to head to the cave and look for the rest of the scouting party. She plans to report to Captain Diiril. I should see what's going on in that cave.
The Trial of the Heart requires that I travel quickly to several points on my map. I must travel to the first waypoint.
The Trial of the Heart requires that I travel quickly to several points on my map. I must travel to the second waypoint.
The Trial of the Heart requires that I travel quickly to several points on my map. I must travel to the third waypoint.
<<1>> revealed they have a spy named <<2>> investigating recent crimes. She asked me to go to his home on the west side of Stormhold, so I can find out what sort of information he's gathered.
I entered Listens-to-Water's home and found him dead. I should search the room for any sign of the reports he was keeping for <<1>>.
I should go to the Ayleid entrance described in Listens-to-Water's report, so I can investigate. The report said the entrance is on the west side of the ruins in Stormhold.
Now that I've entered the ruins, I should investigate them to see what I can find.
While I was investigating the ruins, I heard the voice of <<1>> calling out to me. I should rescue him.
Now that I've released all the prisoners, I should find <<1>> outside the ruins.
After I rescued <<1>>, he asked me to continue through the ruins. He asked me to release people who have been kidnapped.
<<1>> said cultists raided the village last night, but guards tricked three of their lieutenants within their cellars. I agreed to convince the Worm Cultists to surrender.
He asked me to convince some of the mercenaries around Stormhold to leave. <<1>> said he didn't care how I did it.
Not as many mercenaries patrol Stormhold. I should return to <<1>> and deliver the news.
<<1>> wasn't at his stall, but there's a Nord standing nearby. Perhaps she knows where he went.
I need to kill crocodiles and harvest any organ that could resemble a stomach. I also need to gather spineweed. They grow in streams around Stormhold.
Now that I have all the ingredients I need, I should return to <<1>> in the Mages Guild.
I should speak to <<1>> about what she knows. She was last seen at Bogmother, a short distance from Stormhold.
I should investigate the village southwest of Stormhold.

I met an injured Pact soldier on the road from Vivec's Antlers. The Covenant has invaded the area, and the Pact is heavily outnumbered. The soldier asked me to speak to his superior, Captain Noris, in a camp by the north sea.
None of the Worm Cult lieutenants would surrender. I should inform <<1>>.

<<1>> said that an Argonian named <<2>> may know more about the Brother of Strife, the Coral Heart, and Alexandra Conele's plans to acquire it. She may also be able to tell me more about what's happening in Vivec's Antlers.
Elynisi says she needs an incense to return to her body. I should find it.
Now that she's awake, I should speak with her.
The ritual that must be performed requires specific ingredients. I can find them in the nearby houses.
I've found the ingredients, but it appears Elynisi's master has perished. I must head to the temple and speak with her at once.
I need to find <<1>> and tell her what I've learned.
I should talk to <<1>> about the Vanguard.
I should make my way to the Spire, and begin my climb to the top.
The grandmaster told me to talk to his seneschal, <<1>>, if I need anything.
Now that I'm inside the barracks, I need to look around for clues. I must learn where the grandmaster's son is being held.
Tanval's Vanguard is holding the Grandmaster's son in a Daedric tomb outside of the city. I should tell <<1>>.
I must search for <<1>> within the Daedric tombs and set him free.
I saw who was talking to Rhavil, and through me, so did the House Cousin. There's no reason to stay further.
Ral gave me the prod he uses when tending his herd. I need to use the prod on the guar as I find them around Kragenmoor. That should send them back to Ral.
<<1>> fears the cultists plan to enslave the living skeletons of <<2>>. She told me <<3>> has a way to stop the cultists' plan, but it requires my help. I should speak with him.
I should collect the <<1>> and the <<2>> to break the spell on the gate.
House Indoril is ready to dispel the ward holding the gate closed. I need to wait while Garyn and Tanval open the gates.
With the ward down, I'm free to enter the area around the keep.
This is it. I must slay <<1>>.

I should attune myself to the anima crystal to observe Vox's final memory. Once within the memory, I should speak to Aspera's projection.

I found J'kur's body. He was holding a note and a map. The note is intended to be delivered to someone named Vahara. The map points at an area to the north of the plantation.nnI must go there and look for Vahara.
I should tell <<1>> what I discovered during my investigation.
I need to let <<1>> know that <<2>> was one of the skin-stealers, and I've destroyed their ability to create more of them.
I should release <<1>> as I agreed.
I should travel to <<1>> and deliver the message.
I should investigate the locations <<1>> marked on my map for me to check.
I should enter the skin-stealers' lair through the portal atop the Daedric ruins on the hill at Ten-Maur-Wolk.
I need to explore the Daedric ruins and find a way to stop the skin-stealers.
<<1>> asked me to rescue his friends; in return, he can tell me how to stop the skin-stealers.
I can destroy the Hist vats by throwing in the enchanted fire salts <<1>> gave me.
After burning the Hist vats, <<1>> arrived. It appears he was a skin-stealer all along.
I need to find the three keys to <<1>>'s prison. The keys are on altars throughout the ruins.
I have the keys to unlock <<1>>'s prison. I should talk to her and determine the best course of action.
I should talk to <<1>> and confirm that I will not release her.

I should let Ulov know I've witnessed the creature he described.
Ulov is standing near the trapdoor in Ruvali's house. I should ask him if he's seen Ruvali.

I need to collect venom from the giant serpents within Zehtswater Cave. Then I need to combine the venom with the Antivenom Kit to create antidotes to the Lamia poison. With the antidote, I can rescue the mercenaries.
The mercenaries have been cured and they fled Zehtswater Cave. I should go outside and find <<1>>.

I need to collect venom from the giant serpents within Zehtswater Cave. Then I need to combine the venom with the Antivenom Kit to create antidotes to the Lamia poison. With the antidote, I can rescue the mercenaries.
An Ordinator informed me that Almalexia wants to see me at the Temple.
Daedra have invaded the Tribunal Temple. I need to destroy them and close the portals that spawn them.

Almalexia informed me invaders still hold the High Chapel. The combined powers of the Tribunal protect the area from mortal entry. To enter the High Chapel, I need to attain the blessings of Vivec and Sotha Sil at each of their altars.
I prayed at Almalexia's altar and now I should speak with her.
In order to receive Vivec's blessing, I need to pass his trial. I should speak with Almalexia to ask for advice.
To receive Sotha Sil's blessing, I need to pass his trial. I should speak with Almalexia to get advice before I begin.
I uncovered the spy. Now I have to defeat her. Then I should receive the blessing of Vivec.
I need to find a way to repair the Arbiter of Perfection, and then I need to destroy it. When I'm done, I should receive the blessing of Sotha Sil.
I received Vivec's blessing. Now I should go to Sotha Sil's cloister and pray at the altar to start his trial.
I received Sotha Sil's blessing. Now I should go to Vivec's cloister and pray at the altar to start his trial.
Sotha Sil has devised a trial that I need to pass in order to receive his blessing. Almalexia should be able to provide more information.
I need to find a way to repair the Arbiter of Trials. Then I need to destroy it. When I'm done, I should receive the blessing of Sotha Sil.
Vivec has devised a trial that I need to pass in order to receive his blessing. Almalexia should be able to provide more information.
I revealed the traitor. Now I have to defeat her. Then I should receive the blessing of Vivec.
I received the three blessings of the Tribunal. Now I should enter the High Chapel and hunt down the leader of this invasion force.
I found a Maulborn high priest in the High Chapel of the Tribunal Temple. He must pay for his crimes.
I defeated Vanus Sathram and saved the Tribunal Temple, but Vox escaped with the Judgment of Veloth. I should tell Almalexia what happened.
I need to return to the mortuary, so I can speak to <<1>>.
I need to enter the mortuary again to speak to <<1>>.
I should enter the Mages Guild and speak to <<1>>.
I should enter the Mages Guild, so I can speak to <<1>>.
Vox weakened Saint Veloth by shattering his reliquary. I need to recover the pieces, scattered around the shrine, and bring them to Master Aron.
The reliquary can now be reassembled and Saint Veloth's powers can be restored. I must go back to the top of the shrine and repair the reliquary.
The reliquary is whole again. I can see that Saint Veloth's spirit has also recovered. I should speak to him.
I restored the Shrine of Saint Veloth and received his blessing. It's time to face Magistrix Vox at Eidolon's Hollow.
I should kill Dremora and gather their hearts for Healer Dalen.

I met Acolyte Eldri at the Shrine of Saint Veloth. She collected Dremora hearts for Healer Dalen, who makes strong healing potions from them. I should find Healer Dalen at Eidolon's Hollow and give him the hearts.
I need to escort Elynisi to the inn in the northeast part of town.
I need to find Elynisi Arthalen on the road to Selfora.
I should speak to Elynisi in the Selfora Inn.
To purify the wellspring, I must gather the blood of the lamia that have infested <<1>>.
I gathered the <<1>> that I need to purify the wellspring. I must take it to the altar on the upper level of <<2>>.
Sep's power has purified the Lamia blood and created a potent curative. I need to pour it into the heart of the wellspring.
<<1>> is dead and the wellspring is purified. I should find <<2>> by the entrance.
I should enter Silyanorn ruins again.
The ritual preparation is complete. Talk to <<1>> and begin the final phase of the ritual.
I should use the ritual braziers to summon the guardians. Then I can open the portal into <<1>>.
<<1>> asked me to enter the mine and save some trapped miners, but she wasn't concerned about <<2>>.nnShe gave me food scraps to throw at and distract hungry Goblins I might find in the mine.
I've saved the other miners and now need to find <<1>>. Miner Iron-Kettle said he was in one of the Argonan houses in the mine.
<<1>> said I need to get the Goblin totem. Then I can stop the Goblins from attacking and help him free them from slavery. The Goblin war chief has the totem. He's in the camp above the mine.
Now that I have the totem, I should give it to <<1>> or <<2>>. They're both waiting in the Mud Tree Village mine.
I gave the <<1>> to <<2>>. He can use it to lead the Goblins to freedom. I should speak to his brothers in <<3>> and let them know what happened.
I collected several pieces of Saint Veloth's Reliquary. I should find Master Aron at the top of the shrine and give the pieces to him.
Before I can seal the wispmother, I must defeat her from within the cave.
I've defeated the wispmother, but if she reforms, I'll need to slay her again to seal her remains.
I need to collect small rats to use as an offering to Ghost Snake with the bag that I've been given. They can be found in the nearby bogs of Ghost Snake Vale.
My final trial is to defeat the Shadow Snake, a more sinister aspect of the Ghost Snake.
I have the offering. Now I need to place it in the offering bowl at the Fang Spires and see what happens.
I defeated the Shadow Snake. I'll seek the Ghost Snake's counsel on the issue of trade between the Mabrigash and House Hlaalu.
I walked the Coiled Path and made an offering to the Ghost Snake. It appeared before me. I should speak to it.
Now that the prisoners are free, I should talk to <<1>> in the next tunnel. I need to learn how to stop the skin-stealers.
I need to lower the wards at the entrance to the Tormented Spire.
With the wards down, I can enter the spire and begin the long climb to the top.
Walks-in-Ash managed to sneak onto the spire after Tanval. She and her troops were cut off when the wards went back up. I need to find her and learn what I can about Tanval's plan.

Walks-in-Ash told me about a series of ancient wards that still block our path up the mountainside. Each one is beneath a Daedric ruin, and each one must be lowered before the Pact soldiers can reach the top.
I've found the first ward on the approach to the spire. We'll need to lower it before we can continue.
The first ward is down. I must head back to the surface and see how the Pact troops are doing.
I must lower the next ward on the approach to the spire.
The northern pagoda leads to an underground room, which holds the crystal powering the second ward. I can use the House Dres key to enter the room and disable the ward.
I need to remove the crystal powering the second ward from the ruins beneath the northern pagoda.
The second ward is down. I should head back to the surface and see how the Pact troops are doing.
Holgunn and Walks-in-Ash have taken most of the Tormented Spire. I should find them near the volcano's caldera.
I've found Tanval. I should ask him why he's injured.
The caldera ruins contain the final ward preventing us from confronting the Brother of Strife.
One ward stands between the Pact and the second Brother of Strife.
The final ward is down. I must head back to the surface.
The final ward has been lowered. We should be able to enter the prison holding the second Brother of Strife.
The Dominion's forces have been routed. <<1>>'s ritual was a success. The Argonian spirits of the forsaken hamlet can now return to the restored Hist tree. They can be at peace.
With the Dominion's leader dead, perhaps <<1>> can find some peace.
I escorted Elynisi safely to the inn. She's speaking to someone named Meldras. I should wait until they finish their conversation.
The Argonian village of Scybalum is under attack. I need to talk to <<1>> to find out who is responsible.
Now that the Echo of Vox is defeated, I should speak to the Selforan Spirit.
I must make my way to the temple entrance.
A friendly spirit has appeared to me at the temple's entrance. It appears to want to speak with me.
The spirit told me that I need to find a vessel of holy water in the temple that has the power to quench the magical fires consuming Selfora.
I should test the holy water on the brazier of magic flame in the center of the temple's lower chamber.
Some manifestation of Lady Vox has appeared from the magic flame. I must defeat her.
Vox is dead. Almalexia recovered the hammer. I should speak to her.
The door ahead leads to Vox's Hollow. I should look for her there.
Vox draws upon the souls at the center of the Hollow. I should speak to her and provoke her into striking me with Veloth's hammer.
I've been transported to Vox's spirit realm, but the Blessing of Veloth protects me. My memories are still clear and my body is still whole. I should speak to the spirits here to learn more.
<<1>> says I'm blessed by the Night Mother to find the Shadowscale traitor who murdered their leader. I should speak with him further about what this means.
The Shadowscales were cryptic about their leader's problem, but said I could find him in the center of their enclave.
When I arrived to speak with the Shadowscale leader, I learned he was being prepared for burial! A Shadowscale named <<1>> challenged my presence. Perhaps she could tell me what happened.

The Shadowscales leader was murdered, and <<1>> says it was done by one of the Shadowscales. Before the the Shadowscales will trust me with the details of his murder, I must talk to the Speaker and the Listener.
The Listener and the Speaker gave me their blessing after undergoing painful trials, but I'm no closer to learning who killed the Shadowscale leader. Perhaps <<1>> can help me make sense of this.

<<1>> said the cryptic blessings from the Speaker and the Listener mean the secretive Shadowscales accept my presence. However, <<2>> does not. I must duel her if I'm to make sense of who killed their leader, and why.
I defeated <<1>> in a duel, meaning the Shadowscales accept my presence. I should speak to <<2>> about the death of the Shadowscale leader.
The key to lowering the final ward keeping us from Sadal lies in the grasp of a powerful Daedra. I must slay her and claim the key.
I've burnt the Dominion ships and retrieved the Relleis Lor keystone, I should return to <<1>> in Murkwater.
I can use the summoning bowl on the spire to summon Flamespinner.
Tanval said the first spirit is waiting for me on the platform in the center of the caldera.

The spirit of Arch-Mage <<1>> informed me that three Focus Stones are required to open Sadal's prison. The first Focus Stone is on the south side of the caldera. I must cross a pit of molten lava to reach it.
I have the first Focus Stone. I must return it to <<1>>.
<<1>> said another trial awaits me. I must speak to his colleague at the top of the stairs leading into the caldera.
Powerful spells are honed by trial and error. <<1>> wants me to prove my patience by retrieving a Focus Stone from the back of the cave. She said I must follow the spells they took to contain Sadal.
I have the second Focus Stone. I must return to <<1>>.
I must complete one final trial. I'll find the third spirit near a cave above the caldera.
Mavos has charged me with retrieving the final Focus Crystal. To do this, I must understand the ebb and flow of magic and be precise in my movements.
I have the final Focus Stone. I must return to <<1>>.
The spirit magi have agreed to help me. I need to place the three Focus Stones in the center of the caldera.
I've placed the Focus Stones as instructed. I'll finally be allowed access to Sadal's prison.
The spirits have opened a portal into Sadal's prison. At last, we can enter his realm and rebind him within the spire.
The Keeper has trapped several spirits within this realm. I should talk to the spirits and figure out how to set them free.
With the other spirits free, I need to convince Meram to join me. Perhaps by sharing the knowledge I learned with him, he'll regret his actions and join me.
The portal to the Reservoir of Souls stands open. I need to enter it and confront Vox.
I must fight through Vox's minions. Then I can confront Vox and end this.
The portal to the Reservoir of Souls stands open. I need to enter it and confront Vox.
I must fight through Vox's minions. Then I can confront Vox and end this.
Vox is dead. Almalexia recovered the hammer. I should speak to her.
Almalexia informed me that the Maulborn unleashed Daedra into the Tribunal Temple. I should enter the Temple and banish the Daedric invaders.
Advisor Varon suggested I seek the assistance of a group of villagers who decided to find the missing people on their own. Slips-Through-Fingers, an Argonian, is apparently connected to the group.
I defeated the Dominion spy who murdered the Shadowscale leader. <<1>> will be pleased to hear I've avenged their leader.
I've convinced <<c:1>> to help me find the murderer hidden amongst the Shadowscales.nnShe's asked me to follow her to her sanctum in the caverns below the Head of Sithis.
Now that we're at <<c:1>>'s shrine, I hope she'll advise me how to find the murderer.
<<1>> needs me to find the Shadowscale traitor who defies her. She commanded me to interrogate three prisoners who may have some knowledge of the traitor.
I defeated the soul of the Shadowscale traitor, who was actually a disguised Dominion spy. I should tell <<1>> I avenged their leader.
I've interrogated and dealt with the three prisoners. Now I must return to <<c:1>> and let her know.

<<1>> pulled me into the domain of Sithis, a mirror of <<Ac:2>>. She commanded me to search for the traitor, whose deceit will glow similarly to what I saw with the prisoners earlier. When I find it, I must destroy the traitor's soul.
I collected everything I could. I should return to <<1>>.
I should speak with the Enigma of Sotha Sil to receive its blessing.
I should speak with the Enigma of Vivec to receive its blessing.
I need to find a way into <<1>>.

The Imperial translation journal implies that they seek to create and control Dwarven constructs designed by the ancient Dwarven master Razak. They cannot, however, find the three keys to open the door to his vault.
I've found all three keys to Razak's vault. I should open the vault.
Razak's Vault is open! I should investigate the unsealed chamber.
I've found the cog mold. The Dwemer Journal included a map of the Wheel that emphasized a room to the south. I should take the mold to that chamber.
The cog is formed, but now I must take it to Razak's anvil and etch the cog's teeth. It can't be too difficult, right?
I should locate Razak's Machine and install the cog to see what happens.
Razak's Machine has spit out a strange Dwarven spider construct. It appears to be waiting for something.
I have made it inside <<1>> and must now search for evidence as to why the Imperials are here.
Now that the Echo of Vox is defeated, I should speak to the Selforan Spirit.
The Spirit has summoned a vision of the past. I should listen to learn what happened to Selfora.
The Dwemer contraption formed a cog for me, destroying the mold in the process. I should retrieve the completed cog.
The Dominion spy using Saervild's form is dead. Now that I've collected the relics, I should take them back to <<1>>.
I should collect relics in the area. According to Saervild, the vicecanons believe they contain magic that could turn the tide of the war against the Dominion.
I should return to the Inn to see if the two Dunmer I rescued made it there safely.
Once these medical supplies get to the tower above the overrun camp, I can find out where the keystone is kept.
I need to speak with <<1>> and tell him about the Keystone.
I can review the phrases from each of the clues I found in Razak's Wheel if I need to.
I've buried the remains, which brought <<1>> to the tree. I should speak with her before she passes on.
<<1>> is in a dilapidated building within the prison grounds.
I've retrieved Najeepa's remains from <<1>>. I should bring them to her spirit, so she can finally rest.
I should search the burning homes in the southern part of Selfora by dousing their burning doors and entering them.
I should search the prison towers for any signs of Bezeer's mother. Her spirit has not yet left. I should be able to identify her remains.
I found the spirit of Bezeer's mother. She told me where her remains are. I should go to the tower within the prison and retrieve whatever is left of her remains.
It appears I'm in a vision of the past. I should speak to the Ebonheart Acolyte near me to find out what's happening here.
In the Ash Mountain of the past, Balreth summoned Daedric portals. The acolyte I spoke to gave me a pouch of silver stones. Throwing these into the portals will close them.
Before any of the prisoners can tell me where the keystone is, I need to retrieve medical supplies from an overrun camp on the north side of the prison.
<<1>> has requested that I find and kill the Imperial commander, <<2>>, and recover her lost orders from <<3>>.
<<1>> is dead and <<2>>'s orders retrieved. I should find and inform <<2>>.
I've freed <<1>> from her bonds. I should speak to her.
Now that I've summoned the guardians, I should wait for them to open the portal into Ash Mountain.
I should enter the prison dungeon and locate the keystone.
I need to find <<1>>, a prisoner who entered the dungeon while foraging for supplies.
<<1>> believes the keystone is located within the prison warden's office, which will be in the structure above the cells. We'll need to find our way up there.
I must make a choice: I can absorb the keystone or release the prisoners.
The power released from the keystone has riled up the cannibals. I need to kill them and survive.
I chose to absorb the keystone instead of using it to free the prisoners. <<1>> was driven mad. I must escape the prison and let <<2>> know.
<<1>> fled from the prison after I killed <<2>>. I should meet him outside the prison walls.
<<1>> must still be somewhere within the prison grounds. I need to locate him and tell him what happened to the keystone.
Destroying <<C:1>> has calmed the dreugh. I should return to <<2>> and tell him what I've found  and what I haven't. His mother is still missing.
I should dig into the <<Amz:1>> to find Linnea, or any of the dreughs' other victims.
Acolyte Hlen saw the daedroth carry Saint Veloth's Skull into the nearby crypt. I must enter the crypt to recover the holy relic.
Selfora is safe now. I should return to the inn and tell Elynisi about her father.
Elynisi asked me to search the Selfora town hall to find her father, Tidyn. She gave me a key to unlock the building.
I'm in the town hall. Now I should search for Tidyn Arthalen.
The Forlorn One appeared over the body of Tidyn Arthalen. I should speak to the spirit and find out what happened here.

The Forlorn One is actually the spirit of Tidyn Arthalen. He was slain by Magistrix Vox and chained to Selfora by her echo. He wants me to go to the crater in the middle of Selfora, where he'll summon Vox's echo.
The spirit of Tidyn Arthalen summoned the Echo of Vox to the crater at the center of Selfora. I need to subdue the Echo of Vox and capture it by using the decanter.
I defeated and captured the Echo of Vox. It's trapped in the decanter and the curse on Selfora has lifted. Now that this is finished, I should speak to Tidyn.
I found one survivor: <<1>>. He ran away, asking me to meet him at the ruins.
<<1>> wants to speak with me before I do anything with the keystone.
I can ask my fellow Dark Brotherhood members for advice on my current contract.
<<1>> said <<C:2>> was supposedly created to placate the Argonians. Instead, it lured the dreugh to the ruins. I need to destroy it.
The dungeon's entrance is in a cave east of <<1>>'s tower. I need to enter it and find the keystone.
Vox is dead. Almalexia recovered the hammer. I should speak to her.
Vox is dead. Almalexia recovered the hammer. I should speak to her.
Teroni's lost cat is hiding somewhere in the town of <<1>>.
I was able to catch Teroni's cat. I should return him to her as soon as possible - I don't think he likes travelling in my bags.
I caught Teroni's cat. I should return him as soon as possible. I don't think he likes traveling in my bag.
Since her cat doesn't know me, Teroni gave me some of his favorite food. When I place the food on the ground near him, he should come to me.
<<1>> assured me her cat would be somewhere in Ebonheart. I should return to look for him.
I defeated the Maulborn Priest Sathram and saved the Tribunal Temple, but Magistrix Vox escaped with the Judgment of Veloth. I should leave the High Chapel and tell Almalexia what happened.
I should find Healer Dalen at Eidolon's Hollow and give him the Dremora hearts that Acolyte Eldri collected.
Now that I saved Dithis, I should return to the other mages and give them the good news.
I need to use the <<1>>. The Ashlanders should pass them without attacking.
I should use the <<1>>. The Ashlanders should pass them without attacking.
Now that I've destroyed the "offering," I should talk to <<MONSTER:22053>> again.

The tree-minder's missing items may be my first clue to solving the mystery. I need to find the broken staff, pages from her book, and the lost key.nnI'll head through the tunnel to search for the items in what lies beyond it.
Garyn asked me to journey to Othrenis and find <<1>>. He may need help.
The tree-minder's ghost appeared, hovering over the last object I recovered. I need to talk to this spirit.
I should report what I've discovered to Sees-All-Colors.
Now that the skin-stealer impersonating Saervild is dead, I should speak with Linnea back at the Steel-Wind family's camp.
<<1>> believes we can use the spirits of the Argonians to revive the Hist tree. I need to use her staff's headpiece to capture some. I'll subdue some spirits and meet her at the tree.

Now that I've subdued some of the hamlet's tormented spirits, I need to take the headpiece to <<1>> at the Hist tree. I'll talk to her once I get there. Perhaps I may come closer to solving this mystery and ending the spirits' torment.
I should find <<1>> in the Fighters Guild. I need to give him the Ayleid tome and the Prismatic Core recovered within the <<2>> ruins.
I should speak to <<1>> in the Fighters Guild in Wayrest.
I should enter the portal at the Wayrest Fighters Guild. It will take me to the Dwarven ruins of <<1>>, so I can join <<2>>.
I should explore the ancient ruins of <<1>> with <<2>>. I need to look for clues that explain what Doshia was looking for.

Valasha's diary spoke of her self sacrifice. She created a black soul gem that could empower a dangerous weapon. These items were to be hidden in the depths of <<1>>.nnWe should continue exploring to see if we can retrieve them.
Now that I've recovered both the black soul gem and the Ayleid tome, I should speak to <<1>>.

<<1>> asked me to return to <<2>> at the Fighters Guild in Wayrest. She wants me to deliver the Ayleid tome and the black soul gem to him for further study until she returns.nnShe has created another portal I can use to return to Wayrest.
I found the three keys. Now I need to find the three chests somewhere in the camp.
To imprison Balreth, I must gain control of the guardians at Ash Mountain. To summon the guardians, Garyn wants me to harvest the hearts of lesser Daedra.
After summoning the guardians, I should use the <<1>> to weaken them.
I agreed to look for this box. Tenel said the box sits in a crate beneath a green tent, outside Davon's Watch.
I agreed to look for this box. Tenel said the box sits in a crate beneath a green tent, outside Davon's Watch.nnHe asked me not to try and open the chest.
I found the box and should return it to Telen Andren.
I found the box and should return it to Telen Andren.
The portal stands open. The spirit of <<1>> has appeared once more at the portal entrance. I should speak to him to see if he has any advice for defeating Balreth.
<<1>> believes we can use the spirits of the Argonians to revive the Hist tree. I need to use her staff's headpiece to capture them. The headpiece came from the tree.

Having returned the broken headpiece to the tree-minder, I need to wait and see if she is able to restore the Hist tree  or at least put her fellow spirits to rest. I'll talk to her when she's finished.
The Dominion is boiling the stolen Hist sap, tormenting the spirits. I need to burn the Dominion's containers of Hist sap to ruin the contents.
I should head towards Mudshallow Cave and see if Linnea is there.
I've retrieved the <<1>> from Hectur. I should bring it to <<2>>.
If I'm to procure a bottle of <<1>>, I'll need to swap the real bottle with the fake bottle given to me by Heleran.
I should search inside Mudshallow Cave for any traces of Linnea.

The Hist sap is free of the Dominion's refinement containers, so the Argonian spirits should be calm again, but the Dominion's soldiers know where I came from. I must return to the Hist tree and confer with <<1>>.
I've freed the prisoners by destroying the keystone. I should speak with <<1>>.

The tree-minder believes that with the Hist sap freed, she may be able to perform a ritual that will either restore the tree or create a new sapling in its place. She needs me to make certain the Dominion doesn't stop her.
While fighting <<1>>, I can use <<2>> to stun him. <<3>>'s aura will restore me if I'm exhausted.
It's clear that someone's taken Saervild's identity. I must kill the man or mer impersonating him.
I tried to open the metal box, but was unable to budge the lid. In my attempt, I cut myself on one of the boxes sharp edges.
I should speak to <<1>> if I'm interested in joining the Dark Brotherhood.
I'm supposed to meet with Merric and Aelif, top lieutenants in the Fighters Guild. They're investigating a Coldharbour anchor near the city.
I've destroyed the Coldharbour anchor that nearly killed Merric. I should speak to him again to see what we should do next.
Aelif is taking me to the place where she and Merric were assaulted. She asked me to investigate the body for any clues.
The spirit of Merric mentioned someone named Melina. Aelif might be able to provide more information about this person.
Daedric anchors have touched down around Melina's island. I must defeat them before their influence spreads.

I need to protect the hamlet's spirits from Dominion forces. If they destroy the spirits, <<1>>'s ritual will lose its power, and the Hist tree won't be restored. If I fail, the hamlet will remain haunted forever.
He suggested I find the mine foreman, <<1>>. I need more information.
I've retrieved the <<1>> from Fedrasa at the Ebony Flask. I should return it to <<2>>.
If I'm to procure a bottle of <<1>>, I'll need to swap the real bottle with the fake bottle Heleran gave me.
My spider collected the parts Kireth needs to repair the emitter. I should find Kireth and give the parts to her.
Kireth entered the ruins without her brother, who was injured trying to follow her. He invented a control rod to deal with the constructs inside. I need to take it to his sister.
Kireth wants me to create a diversion so she can sneak through the next chamber. She suggested I use her brother's control rod to capture a Dwarven spider. She thinks it might take a few attempts.

Kireth needs spare parts to repair the Dwarven device. Since Dwarven constructs scavenge parts from broken automata, I need to break a few spiders. Then I can use the control rod to direct my follower to gather the parts.
The guardians have appeared. Now I must force them to do their duty and imprison Balreth.
I cleared the way out of the mine. I need to get proof from <<1>> before I allow him to leave.
<<1>> has arrived. He helped me imprison Balreth, a Brother of Strife, forever. I should speak to him and see if anything else remains to be done.
An Ashlander named <<1>> seeks the death of fearsome creatures in Stonefalls. I've slain the nix hound, <<2>>. The netch, <<3>>, and the clannfear, <<4>>, are still out there.

Sheogorath wants me to tour another part of his Chateau, a maze. He thinks the ambiance in there is too dark, and wants me to light some braziers as I go. He also said something about "Bumps in the Night"?

I spoke with the Retreat's librarian, a man named Bragur. He told me that Vaermina's nightmare creatures stole the books to preserve her secrets. He wants me to return them to the library.
